    '{"id":"01KBNAE3DD33N04XDFJM0EM29X","title":"Weekly Marketing Meeting (Shockoe <> New North)","summary":{"notes":"## **Campaign Performance and Lead Generation**\n\nCampaigns for **Foxwoods** and **St. Andrews** are live across the website, email, and Hay Reach, generating initial leads and solid engagement (02:17).\n\n- The **Vibe coding LinkedIn ads** have produced **2 leads** over two weeks, with one lead each last week and this week, indicating early traction (03:42).\n    - Despite the leads, Edwin flagged one contact as suspicious due to minimal interaction, prompting a follow-up to ensure lead quality.\n    - Colin highlighted the need to monitor lead authenticity to maximize return on ad spend.\n    - The campaign’s spend is just under **$200**, with an average cost per click below **$9** and a total of **23 clicks**, showing efficient audience penetration (07:01).\n    - On the ABM front, there are **8 highly engaged contacts**, with connection acceptance rates exceeding industry averages, signaling strong prospect interest.\n    - Colin recommended leveraging LinkedIn engagement data to retarget these contacts, boosting conversion chances.\n\n- Edwin is consolidating leads from multiple campaigns, including **Meta campaigns** which are delivering **8–10 leads** but at a higher cost per acquisition of **$55–$65**, compared to LinkedIn’s sub-$9 CPC, indicating LinkedIn’s current cost efficiency advantage (11:31).\n    - This insight will guide resource allocation towards the most cost-effective channels moving forward.\n\n## **Website and User Engagement Optimization**\n\nWebsite traffic is growing steadily, with a total user increase of **11%** and organic users up to **44**, but bounce rates remain a concern, signaling relevance and content issues (08:58).\n\n- Colin explained that bounce rates stem from misaligned keywords and lack of immediate page engagement, emphasizing the need for keyword-driven content and faster user decision cues (09:21).\n    - Recommended page improvements include adding snippets, featured images, and interactive elements to prompt users within their first five seconds.\n    - Edwin confirmed this approach aligns with analyzing traffic sources and keywords to refine content targeting (10:01).\n\n- The team plans ongoing research and content tweaks to align user intent with page messaging, aiming to reduce bounce and deepen engagement.\n\n## **Product and Website Development Strategy**\n\nThe **Zenda page** development is nearing completion with feedback incorporated, including navigation simplification and padding adjustments to improve user experience (04:35).\n\n- Colin and the team will swap the navigation to feature a Zenda theme and Shaka logo, and update placeholder videos once final assets are ready, ensuring brand consistency (05:23).\n    - Misty’s question about templating revealed no current template, but there is a plan to create a **custom post type** to allow reuse of this design for other products, supporting scalability (05:49).\n    - This template development is underway to streamline future product page builds.\n\n- Edwin identified that the homepage client logo carousel is not a global component, leading to manual updates on each page; the team will explore converting it into a **global component** for centralized management and easier updates site-wide (06:14).\n    - Colin will check developer feasibility to implement this change, which would improve operational efficiency and content consistency.\n\n## **LinkedIn Audience Building and Campaign Extension**\n\nTo maximize LinkedIn campaign impact, Colin proposed creating a targeted audience from contacts who accepted connection requests via Hay Reach and LinkedIn, enabling precise retargeting (10:16).\n\n- The audience requires a minimum of **300 matched profiles** on LinkedIn, which may require combining multiple contact sources, including Edwin’s existing networks and Meta leads, to reach this threshold (10:33).\n    - LinkedIn’s matching process is the longest step, but once complete, it allows focused ads with higher conversion potential.\n    - Colin will investigate integrating Edwin’s Meta leads into LinkedIn audiences to broaden targeting scope (11:15).\n\n- This strategic retargeting approach aims to increase campaign efficiency during the remaining weeks of the engagement.\n\n## **Operational Coordination and Next Steps**\n\nColin committed to checking on the possibility of **transferring email domains** used in campaigns, noting standard practice is to keep domains within their account but exploring exceptions as requested by Edwin (03:16).\n\n- The team will also prepare offboarding materials next week, with Colin promising to send Edwin an overview of **wording topics** prior to the meeting, ensuring preparedness and identifying any content gaps early (13:07).\n- Misty will be updated on the Zenda page templating feasibility and timeline, supporting product team scalability.\n- Edwin will follow up on the global carousel component feasibility with developers, aiming to reduce manual page updates.\n- The campaign team will continue lead tracking and follow-ups via HubSpot, improving lead management and responsiveness (08:37).","outline":null,"keywords":["campaigns","LinkedIn advertising","website development","domain transfer","lead tracking","audience targeting"],"overview":"- **Campaign Leads:** Foxwoods and St. Andrews campaigns are generating leads; LinkedIn ads yield 2 leads with low cost-per-click under $9.  \n- **Lead Quality Concerns:** One lead flagged as suspicious; emphasize verifying authenticity to enhance ad spend returns and overall effectiveness.  \n- **Website Traffic & Engagement:** Website traffic up by 11%, but bounce rates indicate content relevance issues, necessitating keyword-driven content improvements.  \n- **Zenda Page Development:** Zenda page nearing completion, with adjustments for better navigation and brand consistency; custom templates will support future scalability.  \n- **LinkedIn Audience Strategy:** Targeted audience creation suggested for LinkedIn to improve campaign efficiency; requires combining contact sources for adequate volume.  \n- **Next Steps:** Team to prepare offboarding materials, check email domain transfer options, and follow up on carousel component feasibility for efficiency.","action_items":"\n**Colin Costigan**\nCheck with the team about transferring email domains and coordinating with Mailforge support (02:59)\nReview possibility of converting the Zenda campaign page into a custom post type/template for reuse (05:49)\nConsult developers on making the homepage carousel a global component to synchronize changes across pages (06:14)\nPull LinkedIn connection acceptance data from Hay Reach, prepare segmented audience for LinkedIn ad targeting, and build audience list with minimum size criteria (10:14)\nSend Edwin and team the agenda and list of topics for next week’s meeting to aid preparation (13:25)\n\n**Edwin Huertas**\nMonitor and investigate suspicious LinkedIn lead responses and validate quality of leads generated (03:41)\nCoordinate collection of final videos to replace placeholders on Zenda page and confirm readiness for update (05:23)\nInvestigate making carousel updates easier by collaborating on global component changes with Colin (06:14)\nContinue consolidating lead tracking across LinkedIn and Meta campaigns within HubSpot for better follow-up (08:37)\nFollow up on LinkedIn lead conversations, especially on those that received additional materials like PDFs (07:43)\n\n**Misty Smith**\nMonitor ongoing Zenda page updates and coordinate feedback implementation with dev team (05:20)\n"},"duration":13.800000190734863,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Colin Costigan"},{"id":1,"name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"id":2,"name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"id":3,"name":"Kylee Anger"},{"id":4,"name":"Colin Costigan"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Hey, kai.","index":0,"end_time":17.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":16.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hey.","index":1,"end_time":17.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":17.36,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"How''s it going?","index":2,"end_time":18.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":17.76,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Good.","index":3,"end_time":19.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":18.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How are you?","index":4,"end_time":19.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":19.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Good, thanks.","index":5,"end_time":20.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":19.76,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Getting geared up for the holiday season.","index":6,"end_time":26.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":25.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Indeed.","index":7,"end_time":28.81,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":28.17,"speaker_name":"Kylee Anger"},{"text":"Indeed.","index":8,"end_time":29.77,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":29.21,"speaker_name":"Kylee Anger"},{"text":"Between all the different family events, it''s like starting every weekend.","index":9,"end_time":34.33,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":29.93,"speaker_name":"Kylee Anger"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":10,"end_time":35.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":34.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":11,"end_time":36.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":35.85,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"You as well?","index":12,"end_time":38.41,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":37.61,"speaker_name":"Kylee Anger"},{"text":"Yep.","index":13,"end_time":39.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":38.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":14,"end_time":40.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":39.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We.","index":15,"end_time":40.33,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":40.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"For like a family thing, we decided.","index":16,"end_time":42.37,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":40.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"To do a secret Santa.","index":17,"end_time":43.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":42.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, crap.","index":18,"end_time":44.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":44.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We got like two weeks to figure all this out.","index":19,"end_time":46.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":44.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yep, yep, yep.","index":20,"end_time":49.13,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":47.77,"speaker_name":"Kylee Anger"},{"text":"We were just talking about that.","index":21,"end_time":50.17,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":49.13,"speaker_name":"Kylee Anger"},{"text":"We used to do that and then we switched to doing more like a white elephant type type.","index":22,"end_time":55.65,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":50.17,"speaker_name":"Kylee Anger"},{"text":"So less pressure to get what suits that one person and then more fun on the day of.","index":23,"end_time":60.69,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":55.81,"speaker_name":"Kylee Anger"},{"text":"Yeah, definitely.","index":24,"end_time":61.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":60.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hello.","index":25,"end_time":64.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":64.37,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Hey, Edwin.","index":26,"end_time":66.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":65.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How are you doing?","index":27,"end_time":67.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":66.61,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Well, how about yourself?","index":28,"end_time":68.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":67.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"A little bit sick, but that''s good.","index":29,"end_time":72.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":70.37,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Life''s good.","index":30,"end_time":73.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":73.09,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"That''s not fun to hear, but definitely.","index":31,"end_time":76.21,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":74.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Common during this time of year.","index":32,"end_time":77.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":76.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yes, yes.","index":33,"end_time":81.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":79.97,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"I mean, a 70 degrees weather and I''m sick and.","index":34,"end_time":87.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":83.27,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Yeah, like, listen, snow and everything.","index":35,"end_time":90.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":87.23,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":36,"end_time":92.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":91.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Are you in Ecuador?","index":37,"end_time":93.51,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":92.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m still here.","index":38,"end_time":94.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":93.91,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":39,"end_time":95.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":94.79,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"I''ll be back next week.","index":40,"end_time":96.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":95.11,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":41,"end_time":97.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":96.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hope everything is going well with your mom.","index":42,"end_time":98.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":97.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yes.","index":43,"end_time":100.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":99.91,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"There''S been.","index":44,"end_time":102.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":102.07,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"There''s a.","index":45,"end_time":103.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":102.79,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Another slight complication.","index":46,"end_time":105.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":103.83,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Then they want to check on Monday, so I''m gonna spend hopefully half of day on Monday, but so far, so good.","index":47,"end_time":113.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":105.91,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"I don''t know what they want to check.","index":48,"end_time":114.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":113.26,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"That''s kind of my concern.","index":49,"end_time":115.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":114.9,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"But, yeah, crossing fingers.","index":50,"end_time":118.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":116.1,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":51,"end_time":119.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":118.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Cross our fingers with you.","index":52,"end_time":121.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":120.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, of course.","index":53,"end_time":123.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":122.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Is Misty joining today or should we dive in?","index":54,"end_time":127.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":124.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We can get started.","index":55,"end_time":128.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":127.38,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"I know she''s joining.","index":56,"end_time":129.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":128.34,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"She might.","index":57,"end_time":129.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":129.38,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"She might join in two minutes.","index":58,"end_time":131.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":129.82,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Okay.","index":59,"end_time":132.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":131.54,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"We were slacking, so I know she''s doing something.","index":60,"end_time":135.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":132.06,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":61,"end_time":136.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":135.55,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"All right.","index":62,"end_time":137.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":137.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Not a whole lot to go through today as we''re winding down on all the, you know, campaigns and projects.","index":63,"end_time":144.03,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":138.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Foxwoods and St. Andrews are live on the site, and those campaigns are live.","index":64,"end_time":151.07,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":145.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"On email and Hay Reach as well.","index":65,"end_time":152.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":151.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Were you reading something else, Edwin, or.","index":66,"end_time":159.31,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":157.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, No, I wanted to know, understand what those.","index":67,"end_time":163.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":160.65,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Those were being launched for a while.","index":68,"end_time":165.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":163.13,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"So these were the specific pages for this campaign.","index":69,"end_time":169.61,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":166.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Got it.","index":70,"end_time":170.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":170.33,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"For the campaign.","index":71,"end_time":171.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":170.81,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":72,"end_time":172.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":171.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And we sent over the list of.","index":73,"end_time":175.45,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":174.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Domains that we were using for emails as well.","index":74,"end_time":177.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":175.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Is there anything else you needed there?","index":75,"end_time":178.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":177.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No.","index":76,"end_time":179.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":179.61,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"That''s good.","index":77,"end_time":180.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":179.89,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"I was planning on doing.","index":78,"end_time":181.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":180.25,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"I put a service in place that it requires an email domain.","index":79,"end_time":187.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":183.05,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"I didn''t want to use the email.","index":80,"end_time":188.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":187.37,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"The shackle.com.","index":81,"end_time":190.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":189.08,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"are we transferring those at some point in the next couple of weeks?","index":82,"end_time":194.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":191.24,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"What''s the plan for that?","index":83,"end_time":195.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":194.2,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"I have to check.","index":84,"end_time":196.92,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":196.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Typically we do not transfer domains because.","index":85,"end_time":199.4,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":196.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We purchase them in our account.","index":86,"end_time":200.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":199.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But I''ll check with the team and see if there''s anything that we can do.","index":87,"end_time":204.2,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":200.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I Think we''ll have to work through.","index":88,"end_time":205.88,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":204.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Support at Mailforge to get those.","index":89,"end_time":210.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":207.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":90,"end_time":211.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":211.24,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"If it''s not all of them, maybe I like to see if it''s possible.","index":91,"end_time":217.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":213.16,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"At least a couple of those.","index":92,"end_time":218.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":217.67,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Yeah, I''ll see what we can do there.","index":93,"end_time":220.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":218.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":94,"end_time":221.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":221.03,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"And so far, the Vibe coding ads on LinkedIn have driven two leads.","index":95,"end_time":226.51,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":222.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"One last week, one this week.","index":96,"end_time":227.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":226.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, the last.","index":97,"end_time":229.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":228.47,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"The week last.","index":98,"end_time":230.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":229.27,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"The last week I followed, and I.","index":99,"end_time":232.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":230.23,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Think it''s a bot or something.","index":100,"end_time":236.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":234.31,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"It changed his profile to open to words, and he''s just replying with one word.","index":101,"end_time":242.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":236.87,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Interesting.","index":102,"end_time":244,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":243.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Or at least every other day or like.","index":103,"end_time":246.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":244.4,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"So I''m not sure if it''s like somebody just.","index":104,"end_time":249.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":246.4,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"I don''t know.","index":105,"end_time":252.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":251.52,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"But let me check because I want to make sure that''s not.","index":106,"end_time":255.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":252.88,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Because I''ve been getting up from the hate reach.","index":107,"end_time":257.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":255.52,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"I''ve been getting a bunch of those kind of.","index":108,"end_time":259.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":257.32,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"I follow the ones that I think are potential, but others are just like, no, I''m not in that company anymore.","index":109,"end_time":265.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":260.4,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"And this one particularly is just one word, like.","index":110,"end_time":268.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":265.88,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"And I can go and look into it.","index":111,"end_time":270.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":269.05,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"But yes, I see that''s working.","index":112,"end_time":272.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":270.29,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"So, yeah, we just keep it going.","index":113,"end_time":275.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":273.13,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":114,"end_time":276.49,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":275.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":115,"end_time":278.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":278.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hi, Misty.","index":116,"end_time":279.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":278.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":117,"end_time":284.25,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":283.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then we also developed the Zenda page, and I saw that Daniela left some feedback.","index":118,"end_time":290.33,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":284.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think that we''re all set here.","index":119,"end_time":292.17,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":290.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like, once.","index":120,"end_time":292.77,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":292.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Once.","index":121,"end_time":293.13,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":292.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''re working on the feedback now, so we''re going to swap out the navigation up top with just Zenda theme and like a Shaka logo.","index":122,"end_time":299.37,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":293.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Um, and then update just some padding on some things.","index":123,"end_time":303.06,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":300.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then.","index":124,"end_time":303.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":303.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I know she said she couldn''t see in this comment.","index":125,"end_time":306.3,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":303.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"She said based on my Slack, she wanted to check the tab.","index":126,"end_time":309.34,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":306.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"She just has to hit the browse button to be able to click on these tabs here.","index":127,"end_time":314.14,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":309.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So right now they''re all using the same placeholder video.","index":128,"end_time":318.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":316.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"She said you guys are working on the others.","index":129,"end_time":320.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":318.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yes.","index":130,"end_time":321.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":320.78,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":131,"end_ti