speaker_id":0,"start_time":348.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Did you by chance build, like, a template out of this?","index":146,"end_time":353.02,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":349.25,"speaker_name":"Kylee Anger"},{"text":"We did not.","index":147,"end_time":355.02,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":354.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Would you like the Zenda to be.","index":148,"end_time":358.14,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":356.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Would you like us to Make a.","index":149,"end_time":359.46,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":358.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Custom post type for this.","index":150,"end_time":360.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":359.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yes.","index":151,"end_time":361.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":361.5,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"We would want to use something similar for potentially other products.","index":152,"end_time":366.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":362.94,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Okay.","index":153,"end_time":367.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":367.34,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Yep.","index":154,"end_time":369.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":368.94,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":155,"end_time":369.98,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":369.42,"speaker_name":"Kylee Anger"},{"text":"All right, I''ll see what we can do there.","index":156,"end_time":371.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":370.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"While we''re in this website thing, I was going through some of the pages.","index":157,"end_time":378.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":374.62,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"We have the carousel on the homepage that shows the clients that we work with with the logos.","index":158,"end_time":385.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":379.56,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"If it''s a component, I would thought I would be thinking that if I change it in that one, it will change in the other pages what we.","index":159,"end_time":395.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":386.68,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Use in the same carousel.","index":160,"end_time":396.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":395.2,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"But it doesn''t seem like it was done that way.","index":161,"end_time":399.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":396.92,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Yeah, it wasn''t done globally because we also had some other pages that.","index":162,"end_time":403.72,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":399.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Where we wanted to show like specifically.","index":163,"end_time":405.48,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":403.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Golf oriented logos and things like that.","index":164,"end_time":407.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":405.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":165,"end_time":408.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":408.33,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"So there''s like multiple of this.","index":166,"end_time":411.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":409.93,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Like if I want to reuse the same for all the pages, I just need to.","index":167,"end_time":415.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":411.97,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Because I added one logo and it shows in the homepage.","index":168,"end_time":418.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":415.69,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"It''s good, but it doesn''t show.","index":169,"end_time":420.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":418.45,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"There is.","index":170,"end_time":420.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":420.25,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Like I said, I don''t want to go to individually.","index":171,"end_time":422.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":420.65,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"So that was for today''s question.","index":172,"end_time":424.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":423.13,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"If we can have a.","index":173,"end_time":426.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":424.89,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Or if there''s a way to have a component that I can just change in one place and whatever we use.","index":174,"end_time":431.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":426.05,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"In that component also changes.","index":175,"end_time":434.74,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":431.77,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":176,"end_time":435.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":434.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''ll check with the developers if we can make that a global component.","index":177,"end_time":438.42,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":435.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":178,"end_time":439.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":439.14,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":179,"end_time":443.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":443.06,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"All right.","index":180,"end_time":446.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":445.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then we''ll be following up with offboarding materials next week.","index":181,"end_time":449.78,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":446.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think we already answered these questions on Danielle''s feedback.","index":182,"end_time":457.06,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":454.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We just want to make sure we understood the goal of the new page.","index":183,"end_time":459.94,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":457.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So it''s just a different look and feel for this product.","index":184,"end_time":461.98,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":460.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that''s, that''s all good.","index":185,"end_time":463.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":461.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We just wanted to make sure.","index":186,"end_time":464.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":463.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then taking a look at some metrics.","index":187,"end_time":467.33,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":465.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So so far on LinkedIn vibe coding campaign, we spent just under $200 with a average cost per click coming in very low, just below $9 as well, generating 23 clicks.","index":188,"end_time":481.01,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":468.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''re getting good penetration into the audience.","index":189,"end_time":483.01,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":481.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And we have one conversion so far that this week and one that came in last week.","index":190,"end_time":487.41,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":483.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"On the ABM side, we''ve seen eight highly engaged contacts and the your connection request acceptance rate is far and above.","index":191,"end_time":499.5,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":489.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What we consider industry average.","index":192,"end_time":501.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":499.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean over half of the people.","index":193,"end_time":503.06,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":501.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Are accepting your requests.","index":194,"end_time":504.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":503.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I was checking out one of the conversations specifically where someone asked if you have any suggestions.","index":195,"end_time":510.38,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":505.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You sent over a PDF.","index":196,"end_time":512.06,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":510.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I didn''t know maybe if this was a good one to follow up on.","index":197,"end_time":514.9,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":512.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And see if they have reviewed it.","index":198,"end_time":516.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":514.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m adding because I''m keep.","index":199,"end_time":519.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":517.52,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"I''m not able to keep track Of I have this, I have the other campaign that running on meta which are also producing some leads.","index":200,"end_time":527.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":520,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"I''m now I''m putting everything HubSpot so I start following up that way because.","index":201,"end_time":531.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":527.4,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"I start losing track of which ones I''m replaying which one.","index":202,"end_time":534.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":531.04,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Yeah, I gotcha.","index":203,"end_time":535.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":534.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But yeah, this is a good one to continue.","index":204,"end_time":537.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":536.32,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Follow.","index":205,"end_time":538.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":537.92,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Great.","index":206,"end_time":539.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":538.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"For website traffic.","index":207,"end_time":541.84,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":540.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Website traffic is actually up 11% on total users and organic is slightly up to 44 users.","index":208,"end_time":549.24,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":541.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The bounce rate is the only issue.","index":209,"end_time":550.84,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":549.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So while traffic is increasing, we are still getting it.","index":210,"end_time":555.16,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":551.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It seems like people who land and don''t think it''s for them or they are just irrelevant in the audience.","index":211,"end_time":560.12,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":555.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Correct.","index":212,"end_time":561.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":561.08,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"That''s content related.","index":213,"end_time":565.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":564.44,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Right.","index":214,"end_time":566.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":565.72,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"So I guess how do you normally.","index":215,"end_time":568.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":566.08,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Tackle that kind of stuff for a bounce rate?","index":216,"end_time":572.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":569.16,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Yes.","index":217,"end_time":573.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":572.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":218,"end_time":573.44,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":573.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Typically it would be having a very keyword driven approach so that you''re getting relevant traffic to the PA and then also from the psychology perspective of it, someone needs to make their decision within five seconds that this is a page where they actually want to read more.","index":219,"end_time":587.46,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":573.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So having, you know, a lot of the pages we have like a snippet up top and then a featured image.","index":220,"end_time":591.9,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":587.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If we had maybe something more to interact with or something more that prompts them to do something, that''s where you.","index":221,"end_time":598.62,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":591.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"See more increased engagement.","index":222,"end_time":600.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":598.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Good.","index":223,"end_time":602.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":601.62,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"All right.","index":224,"end_time":603.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":602.58,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"I''m guessing that would be research by.","index":225,"end_time":607.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":604.9,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Based on where they''re coming from, keyword.","index":226,"end_time":609.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":607.46,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"They use or website that they came from, Correct?","index":227,"end_time":612.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":609.65,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Yes.","index":228,"end_time":613.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":612.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Good.","index":229,"end_time":614.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":614.17,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":230,"end_time":616.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":616.57,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"And then we just had some ideas for, for leveraging the engagement.","index":231,"end_time":620.61,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":616.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So with the amount of people that have been accepting a request, we could build and I know we only have a few weeks left with our engagement, we could build an audience in LinkedIn.","index":232,"end_time":628.65,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":620.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Of those people and target them, you know, really hard.","index":233,"end_time":631.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":628.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How long do you think you will need to get that in place before the time.","index":234,"end_time":636.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":633.05,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"So actually the, the longest part of this is LinkedIn''s matching.","index":235,"end_time":641.31,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":638.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we would just need to pull.","index":236,"end_time":643.51,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":641.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"From, hey, reach all the people that.","index":237,"end_time":644.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":643.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Have accepted your request, put them into a spreadsheet and upload them to LinkedIn.","index":238,"end_time":648.91,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":644.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then LinkedIn goes through a Can.","index":239,"end_time":650.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":648.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We match this profile?","index":240,"end_time":651.79,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":650.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then the audience needs to be at least 300 people.","index":241,"end_time":655.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":652.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''ll have to put in some other parameters there because it won''t be.","index":242,"end_time":661.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":657.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I don''t think we have 300 people that have accepted requests.","index":243,"end_time":663.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":661.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So it would be only that team request came from Haybridge, but not whatever amount of people I have in my network.","index":244,"end_time":675.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":666.43,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"We could expand it.","index":245,"end_time":676.83,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":675.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean we can.","index":246,"end_time":677.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":676.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I would have to see how we can Tap into your existing connections besides just running boosted ads on your profile.","index":247,"end_time":684.99,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":679.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The other thing is you mentioned that you have meta leads as well, that.","index":248,"end_time":688.87,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":686.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We could try and turn that into a LinkedIn audience.","index":249,"end_time":691.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":688.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s it for the send up product.","index":250,"end_time":693.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":691.46,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"That''s for that.","index":251,"end_time":694.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":693.18,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"That''s why you''re working on the page.","index":252,"end_time":696.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":694.54,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"And these are is another is the meta need follow up whatever they have.","index":253,"end_time":702.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":696.66,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"It''s kind of similar to LinkedIn.","index":254,"end_time":704.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":702.14,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"They have the same messaging portion.","index":255,"end_time":708.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":705.539,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"You change.","index":256,"end_time":708.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":708.34,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"It''s a CRM basically.","index":257,"end_time":710.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":709.14,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"But this is specifically for resorts and golf courses.","index":258,"end_time":714.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":711.7,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"You.","index":259,"end_time":715.155,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":714.9,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"And that''s also producing right now 9 or 8, 9 or 10 leads.","index":260,"end_time":719.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":715.155,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"But the cost per acquisition is higher.","index":261,"end_time":722.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":719.75,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Than LinkedIn, which is interesting.","index":262,"end_time":724.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":722.11,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"That is typically the opposite of what you would see.","index":263,"end_time":728.11,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":725.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s what I was like.","index":264,"end_time":729.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":728.91,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"That''s lower.","index":265,"end_time":731.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":729.79,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"I think the cost average right now is 55 or 65 in meta.","index":266,"end_time":736.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":731.19,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":267,"end_time":737.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":736.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, well then we''re looking pretty good at under $9 on LinkedIn.","index":268,"end_time":740.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":737.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh yeah.","index":269,"end_time":740.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":740.27,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":270,"end_time":742.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":741.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":271,"end_time":742.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":742.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But we''ll explore how many people have accepted the connection request on LinkedIn or on LinkedIn from Heyreach and try and.","index":272,"end_time":749.47,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":742.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Build a really tight knit audience and then you can have that stored in LinkedIn for any campaigns you want to run.","index":273,"end_time":753.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":749.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And that is actually everything that we had as we''re wrapping up.","index":274,"end_time":760.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":757.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we got the campaign live.","index":275,"end_time":761.59,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":760.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''ve seen some leads trickling in from LinkedIn.","index":276,"end_time":763.83,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":761.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''ll build out that audience.","index":277,"end_time":765.99,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":764.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''ll check on domain transfers.","index":278,"end_time":769.43,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":767.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And Misty to your question.","index":279,"end_time":771.51,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":769.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''ll check with the developers to see.","index":280,"end_time":773.75,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":771.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If we can turn the Zenda page into an easy to use template so that you guys can create more of those in the future.","index":281,"end_time":780.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":774.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And Edwin will also check into turning.","index":282,"end_time":783.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":781.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That carousel into a global component.","index":283,"end_time":784.99,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":783.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So if you change it in one spot, it changes across the site.","index":284,"end_time":787.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":784.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That would be great.","index":285,"end_time":788.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":787.59,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":286,"end_time":788.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":788.39,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Yeah, I know we have a wording topics for next week.","index":287,"end_time":793.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":788.95,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Can I have a overview or a list before we go into the meeting?","index":288,"end_time":798.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":794.15,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"That way I''m prepared to say we''re missing this.","index":289,"end_time":800.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":798.71,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"We''re missing this.","index":290,"end_time":801.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":800.63,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"And how are we going to make.","index":291,"end_time":802.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":801.23,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"This transitions or things?","index":292,"end_time":805.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":802.27,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Yeah, of course.","index":293,"end_time":805.91,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":805.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''ll be sending that message to you guys on Monday.","index":294,"end_time":807.95,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":805.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Great.","index":295,"end_time":809.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":808.83,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":296,"end_time":809.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":809.15,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":297,"end_time":810.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":809.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":298,"end_time":810.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":810.51,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"That''s all.","index":299,"end_time":811.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":810.95,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Anything else?","index":300,"end_time":812.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":811.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No.","index":301,"end_time":813.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":813.47,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"All right.","index":302,"end_time":815.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":814.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, I don''t think so.","index":303,"end_time":816.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":815.19,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"All right, great.","index":304,"end_time":818.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":817.15,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Well, thank you all very much.","index":305,"end_time":819.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":818.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Bye.","index":306,"end_time":820.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":820.19,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"All right, bye guys.","index":307,"end_time":821.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":821.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Bye now.","index":308,"end_time":822.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":821.91,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Bye.","index":309,"end_time":822.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":822.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"}],"dateString":"2025-12-10T18:00:00.000Z","host_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/88965765122?pwd=mPL1aFvxXYMYFRYawSa6f5Ez7s5Uv6.1","participants":["kylee.anger@shockoe.com,colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com,edwin@shockoe.com,misty.smith@shockoe.com,nina.belina@marketersindemand.com","kylee.anger@shockoe.com","edwin@shockoe.com","misty.smith@shockoe.com","nina.belina@marketersindemand.com"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01KBNAE3DD33N04XDFJM0EM29X","organizer_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"positive","confidence":0.9,"bullets":["Launched Foxwoods and St. Andrews campaigns across website, email, and Hayreach channels.","Generated two leads from Vibe coding LinkedIn ads; average CPC under $9 with 23 clicks.","Confirmed Zenda page feedback is being addressed; video updates pending from Edwin’s team.","Edwin requested global carousel component; Colin to consult devs for scalable implementation.","Next steps include building LinkedIn audience from Hayreach leads and checking domain transfers."],"highlights":[{"quote":"So we''re getting good penetration into the audience.","speaker":"Colin Costigan"},{"quote":"It''s looking good. Thank you.","speaker":"Edwin Huertas"},{"quote":"I''ll check with the developers to see if we can turn the Zenda page into an easy to use template.","speaker":"Colin Costigan"}],"topics":["launch","delivery","lead-gen","website","ads"],"model":"openai/gpt-4-1106-preview","version":1,"generated_at":"2025-12-10T00:00:00Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **Campaign Performance and Lead Generation**\n\nCampaigns for **Foxwoods** and **St. Andrews** are live across the website, email, and Hay Reach, generating initial leads and solid engagement (02:17).\n\n- The **Vibe coding LinkedIn ads** have produced **2 leads** over two weeks, with one lead each last week and this week, indicating early traction (03:42).\n    - Despite the leads, Edwin flagged one contact as suspicious due to minimal interaction, prompting a follow-up to ensure lead quality.\n    - Colin highlighted the need to monitor lead authenticity to maximize return on ad spend.\n    - The campaign’s spend is just under **$200**, with an average cost per click below **$9** and a total of **23 clicks**, showing efficient audience penetration (07:01).\n    - On the ABM front, there are **8 highly engaged contacts**, with connection acceptance rates exceeding industry averages, signaling strong prospect interest.\n    - Colin recommended leveraging LinkedIn engagement data to retarget these contacts, boosting conversion chances.\n\n- Edwin is consolidating leads from multiple campaigns, including **Meta campaigns** which are delivering **8–10 leads** but at a higher cost per acquisition of **$55–$65**, compared to LinkedIn’s sub-$9 CPC, indicating LinkedIn’s current cost efficiency advantage (11:31).\n    - This insight will guide resource allocation towards the most cost-effective channels moving forward.\n\n## **Website and User Engagement Optimization**\n\nWebsite traffic is growing steadily, with a total user increase of **11%** and organic users up to **44**, but bounce rates remain a concern, signaling relevance and content issues (08:58).\n\n- Colin explained that bounce rates stem from misaligned keywords and lack of immediate page engagement, emphasizing the need for keyword-driven content and faster user decision cues (09:21).\n    - Recommended page improvements include adding snippets, featured images, and interactive elements to prompt users within their first five seconds.\n    - Edwin confirmed this approach aligns with analyzing traffic sources and keywords to refine content targeting (10:01).\n\n- The team plans ongoing research and content tweaks to align user intent with page messaging, aiming to reduce bounce and deepen engagement.\n\n## **Product and Website Development Strategy**\n\nThe **Zenda page** development is nearing completion with feedback incorporated, including navigation simplification and padding adjustments to improve user experience (04:35).\n\n- Colin and the team will swap the navigation to feature a Zenda theme and Shaka logo, and update placeholder videos once final assets are ready, ensuring brand consistency (05:23).\n    - Misty’s question about templating revealed no current template, but there is a plan to create a **custom post type** to allow reuse of this design for other products, supporting scalability (05:49).\n    - This template development is underway to streamline future product page builds.\n\n- Edwin identified that the homepage client logo carousel is not a global component, leading to manual updates on each page; the team will explore converting it into a **global component** for centralized management and easier updates site-wide (06:14).\n    - Colin will check developer feasibility to implement this change, which would improve operational efficiency and content consistency.\n\n## **LinkedIn Audience Building and Campaign Extension**\n\nTo maximize LinkedIn campaign impact, Colin proposed creating a targeted audience from contacts who accepted connection requests via Hay Reach and LinkedIn, enabling precise retargeting (10:16).\n\n- The audience requires a minimum of **300 matched profiles** on LinkedIn, which may require combining multiple contact sources, including Edwin’s existing networks and Meta leads, to reach this threshold (10:33).\n    - LinkedIn’s matching process is the longest step, but once complete, it allows focused ads with higher conversion potential.\n    - Colin will investigate integrating Edwin’s Meta leads into LinkedIn audiences to broaden targeting scope (11:15).\n\n- This strategic retargeting approach aims to increase campaign efficiency during the remaining weeks of the engagement.\n\n## **Operational Coordination and Next Steps**\n\nColin committed to checking on the possibility of **transferring email domains** used in campaigns, noting standard practice is to keep domains within their account but exploring exceptions as requested by Edwin (03:16).\n\n- The team will also prepare offboarding materials next week, with Colin promising to send Edwin an overview of **wording topics** prior to the meeting, ensuring preparedness and identifying any content gaps early (13:07).\n- Misty will be updated on the Zenda page templating feasibility and timeline, supporting product team scalability.\n- Edwin will follow up on the global carousel component feasibility with developers, aiming to reduce manual page updates.\n- The campaign team will continue lead tracking and follow-ups via HubSpot, improving lead management and responsiveness (08:37).","outline":null,"keywords":["campaigns","LinkedIn advertising","website development","domain transfer","lead tracking","audience targeting"],"overview":"- **Campaign Leads:** Foxwoods and St. Andrews campaigns are generating leads; LinkedIn ads yield 2 leads with low cost-per-click under $9.  \n- **Lead Quality Concerns:** One lead flagged as suspicious; emphasize verifying authenticity to enhance ad spend returns and overall effectiveness.  \n- **Website Traffic & Engagement:** Website traffic up by 11%, but bounce rates indicate content relevance issues, necessitating keyword-driven content improvements.  \n- **Zenda Page Development:** Zenda page nearing completion, with adjustments for better navigation and brand consistency; custom templates will support future scalability.  \n- **LinkedIn Audience Strategy:** Targeted audience creation suggested for LinkedIn to improve campaign efficiency; requires combining contact sources for adequate volume.  \n- **Next Steps:** Team to prepare offboarding materials, check email domain transfer options, and follow up on carousel component feasibility for efficiency.","action_items":"\n**Colin Costigan**\nCheck with the team about transferring email domains and coordinating with Mailforge support (02:59)\nReview possibility of converting the Zenda campaign page into a custom post type/template for reuse (05:49)\nConsult developers on making the homepage carousel a global component to synchronize changes across pages (06:14)\nPull LinkedIn connection acceptance data from Hay Reach, prepare segmented audience for LinkedIn ad targeting, and build audience list with minimum size criteria (10:14)\nSend Edwin and team the agenda and list of topics for next week’s meeting to aid preparation (13:25)\n\n**Edwin Huertas**\nMonitor and investigate suspicious LinkedIn lead responses and validate quality of leads generated (03:41)\nCoordinate collection of final videos to replace placeholders on Zenda page and confirm readiness for update (05:23)\nInvestigate making carousel updates easier by collaborating on global component changes with Colin (06:14)\nContinue consolidating lead tracking across LinkedIn and Meta campaigns within HubSpot for better follow-up (08:37)\nFollow up on LinkedIn lead conversations, especially on those that received additional materials like PDFs (07:43)\n\n**Misty Smith**\nMonitor ongoing Zenda page updates and coordinate feedback implementation with dev team (05:20)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"c3707c23-65a0-4b9d-8506-d5c6f0e4e390","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
