INSERT INTO compass_notes (contract_id, meeting_id, note_type, title, content_raw, note_date, status, action_items, is_auto_generated)
SELECT
  new_meeting.contract_id,
  new_meeting.meeting_id,
  'meeting',
  'Meeting Notes: Weekly Marketing Meeting (Shockoe <> New North)',
  '## **Campaign Performance and Lead Generation**

Campaigns for **Foxwoods** and **St. Andrews** are live across the website, email, and Hay Reach, generating initial leads and solid engagement (02:17).

- The **Vibe coding LinkedIn ads** have produced **2 leads** over two weeks, with one lead each last week and this week, indicating early traction (03:42).
    - Despite the leads, Edwin flagged one contact as suspicious due to minimal interaction, prompting a follow-up to ensure lead quality.
    - Colin highlighted the need to monitor lead authenticity to maximize return on ad spend.
    - The campaign’s spend is just under **$200**, with an average cost per click below **$9** and a total of **23 clicks**, showing efficient audience penetration (07:01).
    - On the ABM front, there are **8 highly engaged contacts**, with connection acceptance rates exceeding industry averages, signaling strong prospect interest.
    - Colin recommended leveraging LinkedIn engagement data to retarget these contacts, boosting conversion chances.

- Edwin is consolidating leads from multiple campaigns, including **Meta campaigns** which are delivering **8–10 leads** but at a higher cost per acquisition of **$55–$65**, compared to LinkedIn’s sub-$9 CPC, indicating LinkedIn’s current cost efficiency advantage (11:31).
    - This insight will guide resource allocation towards the most cost-effective channels moving forward.

## **Website and User Engagement Optimization**

Website traffic is growing steadily, with a total user increase of **11%** and organic users up to **44**, but bounce rates remain a concern, signaling relevance and content issues (08:58).

- Colin explained that bounce rates stem from misaligned keywords and lack of immediate page engagement, emphasizing the need for keyword-driven content and faster user decision cues (09:21).
    - Recommended page improvements include adding snippets, featured images, and interactive elements to prompt users within their first five seconds.
    - Edwin confirmed this approach aligns with analyzing traffic sources and keywords to refine content targeting (10:01).

- The team plans ongoing research and content tweaks to align user intent with page messaging, aiming to reduce bounce and deepen engagement.

## **Product and Website Development Strategy**

The **Zenda page** development is nearing completion with feedback incorporated, including navigation simplification and padding adjustments to improve user experience (04:35).

- Colin and the team will swap the navigation to feature a Zenda theme and Shaka logo, and update placeholder videos once final assets are ready, ensuring brand consistency (05:23).
    - Misty’s question about templating revealed no current template, but there is a plan to create a **custom post type** to allow reuse of this design for other products, supporting scalability (05:49).
    - This template development is underway to streamline future product page builds.

- Edwin identified that the homepage client logo carousel is not a global component, leading to manual updates on each page; the team will explore converting it into a **global component** for centralized management and easier updates site-wide (06:14).
    - Colin will check developer feasibility to implement this change, which would improve operational efficiency and content consistency.

## **LinkedIn Audience Building and Campaign Extension**

To maximize LinkedIn campaign impact, Colin proposed creating a targeted audience from contacts who accepted connection requests via Hay Reach and LinkedIn, enabling precise retargeting (10:16).

- The audience requires a minimum of **300 matched profiles** on LinkedIn, which may require combining multiple contact sources, including Edwin’s existing networks and Meta leads, to reach this threshold (10:33).
    - LinkedIn’s matching process is the longest step, but once complete, it allows focused ads with higher conversion potential.
    - Colin will investigate integrating Edwin’s Meta leads into LinkedIn audiences to broaden targeting scope (11:15).

- This strategic retargeting approach aims to increase campaign efficiency during the remaining weeks of the engagement.

## **Operational Coordination and Next Steps**

Colin committed to checking on the possibility of **transferring email domains** used in campaigns, noting standard practice is to keep domains within their account but exploring exceptions as requested by Edwin (03:16).

- The team will also prepare offboarding materials next week, with Colin promising to send Edwin an overview of **wording topics** prior to the meeting, ensuring preparedness and identifying any content gaps early (13:07).
- Misty will be updated on the Zenda page templating feasibility and timeline, supporting product team scalability.
- Edwin will follow up on the global carousel component feasibility with developers, aiming to reduce manual page updates.
- The campaign team will continue lead tracking and follow-ups via HubSpot, improving lead management and responsiveness (08:37).',
  '2025-12-10 18:00:00+00',
  'published',
  '[{"text":"Check with the team about transferring email domains and coordinating with Mailforge support (02:59)","completed":false},{"text":"Review possibility of converting the Zenda campaign page into a custom post type/template for reuse (05:49)","completed":false},{"text":"Consult developers on making the homepage carousel a global component to synchronize changes across pages (06:14)","completed":false},{"text":"Pull LinkedIn connection acceptance data from Hay Reach, prepare segmented audience for LinkedIn ad targeting, and build audience list with minimum size criteria (10:14)","completed":false},{"text":"Send Edwin and team the agenda and list of topics for next week’s meeting to aid preparation (13:25)","completed":false},{"text":"Monitor and investigate suspicious LinkedIn lead responses and validate quality of leads generated (03:41)","completed":false},{"text":"Coordinate collection of final videos to replace placeholders on Zenda page and confirm readiness for update (05:23)","completed":false},{"text":"Investigate making carousel updates easier by collaborating on global component changes with Colin (06:14)","completed":false},{"text":"Continue consolidating lead tracking across LinkedIn and Meta campaigns within HubSpot for better follow-up (08:37)","completed":false},{"text":"Follow up on LinkedIn lead conversations, especially on those that received additional materials like PDFs (07:43)","completed":false},{"text":"Monitor ongoing Zenda page updates and coordinate feedback implementation with dev team (05:20)","completed":false}]'::jsonb,
