WITH new_meeting AS (
  INSERT INTO compass_meetings (contract_id, meeting_date, source, external_id, title, participants, duration_seconds, recording_url, transcript, sentiment, raw_metadata, created_at, updated_at)
  VALUES (
    '75b32155-1255-4d17-b437-152e300521a0',
    '2025-12-10 14:30:00+00',
    'fireflies',
    '01KBJMGZH3CM88KBTJ0RDRQB1F',
    'New North <> ThreatMark: Weekly Marketing Meeting',
    '{"Kate ThreatMark","Colin Costigan","Greg Smith","Colin Costigan","Nina Belina"}'::text[],
    1374,
    'https://us02web.zoom.us/j/84564648866?pwd=JR6eWxlxKbgogzCqTNUawSLUUhQoEa.1',
    '{"id":"01KBJMGZH3CM88KBTJ0RDRQB1F","title":"New North <> ThreatMark: Weekly Marketing Meeting","summary":{"notes":"## **Advertising Performance and Optimization**\n\nThe team improved Google Ads significantly by updating all site links, headlines, descriptions, and extensions, boosting ad strength to \"good\" while maintaining selective recommendation acceptance for better quality (02:45).  \n- This update included switching the landing page from Contact Us to the homepage, aiming to boost conversions with the upcoming carousel feature.  \n- Retargeting campaigns on AdRoll were redirected to the Q2 landing page, targeting US-based audiences, especially Michigan, ensuring alignment with customer geography (03:30).  \n- Colin reported a **25% cost decrease** and a very high click-through rate on Google Ads, mainly from brand search terms, with peak engagement from males aged **35 to 44** during weekday mornings and afternoons (16:27).  \n- LinkedIn campaigns saw a slight dip but included a new Q2-targeted PDF lead gen form ad launched earlier that week, expected to generate quality leads (16:27).  \n- AdRoll clicks increased by **200%** after targeting adjustments to the Q2 audience, signaling improved engagement (16:27).  \n\n## **Content Syndication and Podcast Metrics**\n\nThe podcast downloads are now visible in Databox through Buzzsprout integration, which syndicates episodes to Spotify and Apple and tracks downloads by episode (04:16).  \n- Greg confirmed that ThreatMark accounts exist on Spotify and Apple, allowing direct access to those platforms’ metrics if needed (04:41).  \n- This data integration supports better tracking of owned media performance and informs content strategy decisions.  \n\n## **Competitive Intelligence and Market Positioning**\n\nThe team analyzed competitor activity on LinkedIn, focusing on Feedzai and BioCatch, identifying their ad styles and messaging tactics (06:00).  \n- Feedzai uses multi-language, GIF-based, and event ads, while BioCatch relies heavily on scare tactics, focusing on emotional stories about fraud losses to influence audiences (06:00).  \n- Colin noted that exact regional targeting details are unavailable, but shared that their LinkedIn targeting likely overlaps with these competitors, implying direct market competition (07:29).  \n- This insight helps inform ThreatMark’s positioning strategy and ad messaging to differentiate and compete effectively.  \n\n## **Product and Website Updates**\n\nThe newsroom was updated to display post dates directly on the posts, improving content transparency and user experience (07:44).  \n- The new podcast episode with Kelly Paxton went live on the website, YouTube, Spotify, and Apple after Mike''s approval, featuring embedded players and enhanced content like summary, insights, and quote cards (07:44).  \n- The team is finalizing the form embedding on the site and troubleshooting a navigation jump issue reported by Kate, capturing video evidence to assist developers (08:50).  \n- Color consistency, mobile navigation dots, and auto-scroll features were refined on the homepage slider for better UX based on Kate’s feedback (11:17).  \n- Production of the end-of-year compilation video is underway, focusing on thematic snippets from past episodes to engage audiences (12:13).  \n- Kelly Paxton’s official title is still pending, delaying final production details (11:58).  \n\n## **ABM Strategy and Targeting**\n\nThe PSD3 campaign budget and strategy remain tentative, with Kate highlighting the need to better connect why prospects should engage about PSD3 issues (12:44).  \n- Greg emphasized that this campaign is relevant primarily for the EU and suggested prioritizing a blog post launch for quicker outreach while the asset is refined (13:46).  \n- Yuli will lead the ABM efforts targeting PSD3 within the broader EU activation plan (13:46).  \n- Nina and Greg are developing precise target account lists for 2024, focusing on nuanced eligibility and serviceability in the US market, particularly Michigan banks (14:57).  \n- This list-building will be an ongoing process owned internally, using HubSpot’s Target Account feature to sharpen focus and improve marketing efficiency (15:48).  \n\n## **Process Improvements and Meeting Cadence**\n\nGreg proposed moving weekly meetings to Monday mornings at **10:00 AM Eastern** starting next week to better align with internal planning and create a consistent weekly kickoff rhythm (18:07).  \n- Colin confirmed availability and updated calendars, emphasizing flexibility for larger projects that may span multiple weeks (19:37).  \n- This cadence change aims to synchronize marketing execution with internal team goals and improve weekly planning clarity.  \n- Colin committed to sharing final creative assets for LinkedIn PDFs with Kate to ensure smooth campaign launches (21:18).  \n- Greg requested updates on the homepage carousel feature, identifying it as the next major focus area for site improvements (22:26).","outline":null,"keywords":["Google Ads","Podcast Metrics","LinkedIn Campaign","ABM Strategy","Target Account Lists","Website Navigation Issue"],"overview":"- **Google Ads Optimization:** Ad strength boosted to \"good,\" 25% cost decrease, high engagement from males 35-44 during mornings.  \n- **Retargeting Campaigns:** Focused on Q2 landing page, targeting US audiences, especially in Michigan, improving conversion rates.  \n- **Podcast Integration:** Downloads now tracked via Buzzsprout on Spotify and Apple, enhancing content performance monitoring.  \n- **Competitor Analysis:** Reviewed LinkedIn strategies of Feedzai and BioCatch to inform ThreatMark''s ad messaging and market positioning.  \n- **ABM Strategy Development:** Tentative PSD3 budget discussed, with focus on EU outreach and precise target account lists for 2024.  \n- **Meeting Reschedule:** Weekly meetings moved to Monday at 10:00 AM Eastern for better planning alignment and execution.","action_items":"\n**Colin Costigan**\nSend podcast download Databox link to Greg for easier access (04:30)\nLocate and resend final LinkedIn PDF creative assets to Kate (21:25)\nCheck availability and confirm start for weekly meetings moved to Mondays at 10am Eastern beginning next week (19:40)\nProvide video and replication details of website navigation jump issue to development team for resolution (09:10)\nUpload updated fraud lifecycle diagram text changes received from Greg and forward to Michal for review (11:20)\n\n**Greg Smith**\nFollow up with Kate post-meeting to send finalized text changes for fraud lifecycle diagram (10:15)\nKeep Colin and Nina updated on planning progress for 2025 target account lists with nuanced segmentation (15:10)\n\n**Kate ThreatMark**\nConfirm Kelly Paxton’s official job title for final podcast production (11:15)\nContinue refining PSD3 asset and strategy, possibly shifting initial outreach to blog format; keep marketing informed (13:05)\n\n**Nina Belina**\nCoordinate with Colin and Greg regarding Monday 10am Eastern weekly meeting schedule and adjust calendar accordingly (20:15)\nSupport data integration for LinkedIn Q2 campaign and ABM efforts as needed (14:50)\n"},"duration":22.899999618530273,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"id":1,"name":"Colin Costigan"},{"id":2,"name":"Greg Smith"},{"id":3,"name":"Colin Costigan"},{"id":4,"name":"Nina Belina"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Hello.","index":0,"end_time":43.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":42.89,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"How''s it going?","index":1,"end_time":44.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":43.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Good.","index":2,"end_time":45.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":45.13,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"How you doing?","index":3,"end_time":46.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":45.45,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Doing all.","index":4,"end_time":47.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":46.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Feels like December.","index":5,"end_time":53.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":52.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":6,"end_time":55.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":54.82,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":7,"end_time":57.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":56.82,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"We''ve got storms here at the moment.","index":8,"end_time":58.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":57.18,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Not really.","index":9,"end_time":59.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":59.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You get a lot of rain though, I imagine.","index":10,"end_time":63.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":61.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think I actually live.","index":11,"end_time":65.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":63.94,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"In the rainiest part of the uk.","index":12,"end_time":69.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":67.7,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Like officially.","index":13,"end_time":73.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":72.34,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":14,"end_time":74.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":73.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hi, everyone.","index":15,"end_time":77.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":76.67,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Hi.","index":16,"end_time":78.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":78.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How''s it going?","index":17,"end_time":79.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":78.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Good.","index":18,"end_time":81.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":80.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Thanks.","index":19,"end_time":83.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":82.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Greg is joining us as well.","index":20,"end_time":103.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":101.79,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"He just came off another call.","index":21,"end_time":105.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":103.97,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Sounds good.","index":22,"end_time":111.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":110.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Give him a minute.","index":23,"end_time":113.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":112.37,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":24,"end_time":114.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":114.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Any plans for the.","index":25,"end_time":117.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":116.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, go ahead.","index":26,"end_time":118.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":117.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, no, go ahead.","index":27,"end_time":119.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":118.69,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Any plans for the weekend?","index":28,"end_time":121.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":120.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No.","index":29,"end_time":124.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":124.37,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Those are the best plans, Kate.","index":30,"end_time":127.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":125.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"True.","index":31,"end_time":127.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":127.25,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"How about you?","index":32,"end_time":131.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":130.54,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"I''m sure there''s something going on this weekend that I just can''t remember.","index":33,"end_time":137.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":134.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"There it is.","index":34,"end_time":140.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":139.82,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"I. I can manage ClickUp, but my wife manages our.","index":35,"end_time":147.86,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":144.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Our daily calendar for life.","index":36,"end_time":149.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":147.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hey, greg.","index":37,"end_time":155.83,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":155.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hello.","index":38,"end_time":156.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":156.47,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"How''s it going?","index":39,"end_time":158.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":157.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Not too bad.","index":40,"end_time":159.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":158.95,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Right, let''s jump on in.","index":41,"end_time":167.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":165.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":42,"end_time":173.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":172.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So after meeting last week, we went through all Google Ads and updated the site.","index":43,"end_time":179.63,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":174.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Links, headlines, descriptions, extensions, everything.","index":44,"end_time":182.31,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":179.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Got ad strength up to good.","index":45,"end_time":184.57,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":182.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Google will call it great if you just accept all of the recommendations blindly.","index":46,"end_time":189.65,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":185.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Which we tend to avoid accepting everything blindly.","index":47,"end_time":192.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":189.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So.","index":48,"end_time":193.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":192.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Interested to see how those go.","index":49,"end_time":195.05,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":193.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Also, change the landing page from the Contact Us page to the homepage.","index":50,"end_time":200.89,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":196.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And once we get the new carousel.","index":51,"end_time":203.33,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":201.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Live, I think that''ll be a stronger conversion point as well.","index":52,"end_time":206.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":203.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yep.","index":53,"end_time":208.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":208.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Updated.","index":54,"end_time":210.34,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":209.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Also the ad roll retargeting campaign to land on the Q2 landing page.","index":55,"end_time":215.38,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":210.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And we have some good metrics on.","index":56,"end_time":217.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":215.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The last slide for already seeing some improved stats there.","index":57,"end_time":220.18,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":217.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Before we keep going on that, do we have.","index":58,"end_time":224.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":222.26,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"I need to think about this.","index":59,"end_time":226.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":225.54,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Anyone that''s not in the US.","index":60,"end_time":231.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":229.3,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Is not a Q2 customer.","index":61,"end_time":235.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":234.1,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"So the Q2 landing page, because I think we added a few outside of the U.S. is that right?","index":62,"end_time":240.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":235.86,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"I think the L, the last one that was added was Michigan.","index":63,"end_time":247.71,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":243.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that should be fine.","index":64,"end_time":250.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":249.87,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah, I think we should be fine.","index":65,"end_time":252.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":251.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"With the audience that''s in there.","index":66,"end_time":254.03,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":252.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yes, we are.","index":67,"end_time":255.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":254.43,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Okay.","index":68,"end_time":255.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":255.23,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":69,"end_time":255.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":255.55,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":70,"end_time":256.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":255.75,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Okay.","index":71,"end_time":256.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":256.11,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yep.","index":72,"end_time":256.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":256.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m overlapping on something else.","index":73,"end_time":258.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":256.95,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Okay, I gotcha.","index":74,"end_time":259.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":258.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Threw me off for a second too.","index":75,"end_time":261.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":260.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So glad.","index":76,"end_time":262.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":261.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Glad we talked through that.","index":77,"end_time":263.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":262.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Kate, you had asked if we can get podcast downloads to show in databox, and so we''ve added those through on the Owned Experiences slide.","index":78,"end_time":272.36,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":264.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So it''ll show here and it''ll show breakdown by episode.","index":79,"end_time":274.96,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":272.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Also, how many episodes or how many downloads they''ve gotten.","index":80,"end_time":277.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":274.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sweet.","index":81,"end_time":278.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":278.36,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Where do you pull that from?","index":82,"end_time":281.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":279.64,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"This is coming from Buzzsprout, which is the tool we use to syndicate to Spotify and Apple.","index":83,"end_time":287,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":281.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, so.","index":84,"end_time":289.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":288.36,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"If I was to.","index":85,"end_time":292.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":291.48,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Is there like a threat mark account with both Spotify and Apple?","index":86,"end_time":300.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":296.72,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yes, yes.","index":87,"end_time":302.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":301.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":88,"end_time":303.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":302.6,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"And so if I was to log into the Spotify Threatmark account, I could probably get those metrics, right?","index":89,"end_time":311.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":303.08,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yes.","index":90,"end_time":312.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":311.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":91,"end_time":312.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":312.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":92,"end_time":313.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":312.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":93,"end_time":313.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":313.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But buzzsprout is just the intermediary that you''re using.","index":94,"end_time":317.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":314.24,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah, it.","index":95,"end_time":318.64,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":318,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It allows us to just upload in one spot.","index":96,"end_time":320.48,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":318.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It syndicates to all of those accounts and keeps metrics.","index":97,"end_time":324.24,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":320.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":98,"end_time":325.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":324.71,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":99,"end_time":325.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":325.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Got it.","index":100,"end_time":326.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":325.79,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Sweet.","index":101,"end_time":326.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":326.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":102,"end_time":328.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":328.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":103,"end_time":328.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":328.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Kate, feel free to take a look.","index":104,"end_time":330.23,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":328.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"At this and if you have any questions, let us know.","index":105,"end_time":331.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":330.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, do you mind dropping a link in the Slack channel so that.","index":106,"end_time":340.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":334.23,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Just so that I don''t think I. I have it, but it''s buried somewhere.","index":107,"end_time":344.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":340.15,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah, no problem.","index":108,"end_time":346.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":344.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":109,"end_time":361.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":360.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":110,"end_time":362.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":361.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, of course, we also KE you had asked, you know, what are our competitors doing?","index":111,"end_time":367.72,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":362.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so we tapped into a few different tools here with our main channel being LinkedIn.","index":112,"end_time":371.88,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":367.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s where a lot of our focus was.","index":113,"end_time":373.2,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":371.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But also pulled some spy food metrics, so.","index":114,"end_time":375.2,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":373.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We focused on Feedzai and BioCatch.","index":115,"end_time":379.21,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":376.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so we have links here that''ll show, like, different display ads that they''ve been running, for example, on LinkedIn.","index":116,"end_time":384.89,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":379.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we can see they even run some in a few different languages.","index":117,"end_time":390.29,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":388.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Some are more like GIF oriented, some event ads, things like that.","index":118,"end_time":395.29,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":390.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then we also have their spyfu LinkedIn here to show different keywords that they''re bidding on from a PPC perspective.","index":119,"end_time":405.62,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":397.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"In this document, we dive into, you know, what are they doing, how are they positioning themselves, what they''re talking about, things like that.","index":120,"end_time":416.1,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":408.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And we do the same thing for BioCatch.","index":121,"end_time":419.002,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":417.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"BioCatch is interesting.","index":122,"end_time":420.5,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":419.158,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They have a lot of scare tactic ads.","index":123,"end_time":423.62,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":421.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"A lot of their ads are centered around.","index":124,"end_time":427.38,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":425.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know, look at the story of this mother who was hacked and.","index":125,"end_time":433.55,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":428.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Lost her life savings and make sure that you avoid something like that.","index":126,"end_time":437.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":433.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Can we see what.","index":127,"end_time":444.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":443.35,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"I know you said mentioned about the different languages, but can we see what different regions they''re targeting?","index":128,"end_time":448.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":444.71,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"We can''t really see anything about targeting.","index":129,"end_time":451.51,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":449.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":130,"end_time":452.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":451.75,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"All we.","index":131,"end_time":454.96,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":454.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The insight that we have is that we''re obviously in competition with them on LinkedIn, so our targeting must be pretty close.","index":132,"end_time":461.04,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":454.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m sure it is.","index":133,"end_time":464.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":464.16,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":134,"end_time":465.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":464.96,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":135,"end_time":465.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":465.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":136,"end_time":467.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":467.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We also updated the newsroom.","index":137,"end_time":474.88,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":472.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Let''s test.","index":138,"end_time":476.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":476.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We also updated the newsroom to have dates on the post themselves.","index":139,"end_time":481.61,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":477.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So not just here, but they''ll show here.","index":140,"end_time":483.93,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":481.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":141,"end_time":485.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":484.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":142,"end_time":487.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":487.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then the episode is live.","index":143,"end_time":490.25,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":487.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Saw that Mike came through with approval today.","index":144,"end_time":493.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":490.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So live on the website, live on YouTube, and Buzzsprout is publishing to Spotify and Apple.","index":145,"end_time":500.65,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":495.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sweet.","index":146,"end_time":505.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":502.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we have the player automatically appear.","index":147,"end_time":507.78,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":506.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Summary, embed YouTube video, shout out to Peter and then key insights and a quote card.","index":148,"end_time":514.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":508.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Any questions on any of that?","index":149,"end_time":525.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":523.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All good.","index":150,"end_time":528.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":527.7,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"All right, so we''re still working on getting the form embedded, but we did.","index":151,"end_time":536.51,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":530.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Look, kid, at the issue that you.","index":152,"end_time":538.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":537.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Were having with the jump, it looks.","index":153,"end_time":540.91,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":538.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like it just happened to me.","index":154,"end_time":541.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":540.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s so interesting.","index":155,"end_time":542.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":541.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We weren''t able to replicate it, and now that we''re on the call, we can.","index":156,"end_time":546.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":542.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I hate when that happens.","index":157,"end_time":548.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":547.15,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Okay, so now we have some video to send over to the developers.","index":158,"end_time":560.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":556.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s actually a different jump.","index":159,"end_time":562.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":560.68,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"That was a different thing than what I was getting.","index":160,"end_time":564.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":562.2,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Oh, interesting.","index":161,"end_time":566.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":565.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It was cutting off at just above Win the War there, that text, and it was dropping down on the page.","index":162,"end_time":575.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":568.28,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Interesting.","index":163,"end_time":577.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":577.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, well, we''ll check and see.","index":164,"end_time":589.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":587.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If we can replicate that again.","index":165,"end_time":590.25,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":589.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The other part that we''re working on is getting the formatted here as well.","index":166,"end_time":593.17,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":590.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so once that''s done, we''ll send that over to you guys to take a look and then we can get.","index":167,"end_time":598.49,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":595.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That onto the live site.","index":168,"end_time":600.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":598.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We might need to.","index":169,"end_time":603.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":602.37,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Pull out the disrupt disruption.","index":170,"end_time":608.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":605.97,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"My favorite one.","index":171,"end_time":609.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":608.7,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":172,"end_time":610.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":609.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I wanted to ask if we have any updates there.","index":173,"end_time":611.74,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":610.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I know Mikhail''s been reviewing that, which may take some time.","index":174,"end_time":615.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":611.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Do you have an update on that, Greg?","index":175,"end_time":620.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":618.94,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Because I don''t.","index":176,"end_time":621.54,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":620.78,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah, what I was going to do is I was going to pass back to you the changes that we made to the fraud lifecycle diagram.","index":177,"end_time":631.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":621.54,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Just text changes, so nothing crazy.","index":178,"end_time":639.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":637.19,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"So, Kate, just nudge me on that after this call.","index":179,"end_time":645.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":640.55,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"I''ll send it over to you.","index":180,"end_time":646.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":645.19,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Trying to find it now.","index":181,"end_time":652.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":651.03,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"But.","index":182,"end_time":652.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":652.15,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"So I think that is what we wanted to update in there.","index":183,"end_time":664.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":660.4,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"And then we would.","index":184,"end_time":666.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":664.96,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Resend it over to Michal for feedback.","index":185,"end_time":670.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":667.76,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":186,"end_time":674.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":673.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":187,"end_time":677.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":677.36,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Yeah, we can drop that in.","index":188,"end_time":678.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":677.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Other than that, the changes that were made on that slider were the color consistency, the mobile dots, and the auto.","index":189,"end_time":685.64,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":680.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Scroll Kate, that you had mentioned.","index":190,"end_time":687.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":685.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Also.","index":191,"end_time":687.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":687.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Wanted to ask on the new episode with Kelly Paxton, if we can just confirm what her title is, because.","index":192,"end_time":697.36,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":691.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''Ve seen a few different ones.","index":193,"end_time":698.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":697.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":194,"end_time":700.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":699.72,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Did I freeze?","index":195,"end_time":704.199,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":703.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Nope.","index":196,"end_time":705.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":705.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":197,"end_time":706.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":706.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It was just Kate.","index":198,"end_time":708.52,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":707.56,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Very unfortunate position.","index":199,"end_time":710.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":709.16,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":200,"end_time":711.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":710.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"She was about to drop some gold.","index":201,"end_time":713.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":711.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":202,"end_time":714.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":713.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I can still hear you.","index":203,"end_time":719.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":718.52,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Oh, we can hear you now.","index":204,"end_time":722.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":720.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You''re back.","index":205,"end_time":722.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":722.2,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Okay, sorry.","index":206,"end_time":726.44,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":725.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So Kelly Paxton''s title, tbc.","index":207,"end_time":730.84,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":726.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Waiting for it to come out.","index":208,"end_time":732.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":731.24,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":209,"end_time":733.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":733,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":210,"end_time":734.2,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":733.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Then we''ll just have to.","index":211,"end_time":736.96,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":735.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Delay production just a little bit until we have that.","index":212,"end_time":739.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":736.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yep.","index":213,"end_time":740.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":739.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Then we''re also putting a script together for the end of the year compilation.","index":214,"end_time":744.8,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":741.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Video that we talked about last week.","index":215,"end_time":746.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":744.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The angle that we''re going to take with that, we''re going to go through and just establish a few themes and.","index":216,"end_time":754.72,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":749.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Then pull out different snippets that we can use from different episodes.","index":217,"end_time":757.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":754.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":218,"end_time":760.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":760.04,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Okay.","index":219,"end_time":764.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":764.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we just saw the navigation jump.","index":220,"end_time":765.92,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":764.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''re good there.","index":221,"end_time":766.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":765.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then, Kate, you mentioned budget allocation TBC for the PSD3 campaign as well.","index":222,"end_time":772.26,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":767.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, we.","index":223,"end_time":775.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":774.18,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"We.","index":224,"end_time":778.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":778.5,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"I think it''s going to be part of.","index":225,"end_time":780.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":779.14,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Our ABM strategy or.","index":226,"end_time":784.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":782.02,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Or some part of it.","index":227,"end_time":786.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":785.14,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"So it''s kind of TBC how we go about it right now.","index":228,"end_time":789.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":786.58,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"So I think we just table that conversation.","index":229,"end_time":791.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":789.62,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"But we''ve got the asset in a form.","index":230,"end_time":794.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":791.46,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Not a great form, but is a form.","index":231,"end_time":797.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":795.14,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"So maybe it was just a bit premature for me to share it with you.","index":232,"end_time":801.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":799.1,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"What do you mean by a not a great form?","index":233,"end_time":804.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":802.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It needs a little bit more connection of why prospects need to talk to us about it to solve their PSD three issues, I think.","index":234,"end_time":816.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":805.98,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":235,"end_time":817.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":816.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":236,"end_time":817.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":817.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":237,"end_time":820.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":819.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so I imagine this is the.","index":238,"end_time":821.14,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":820.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"ABM effort that Yuli will be spearheading among them.","index":239,"end_time":826.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":821.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":240,"end_time":826.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":826.34,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"You know, it''s relevant for the eu.","index":241,"end_time":830.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":827.26,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"So as we''re thinking about, you know, EU activation, this would be the one for there.","index":242,"end_time":835.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":830.3,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"I do think.","index":243,"end_time":837.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":836.54,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Kate, as we''re thinking about that, I know that we were talking about like a blog versus an asset.","index":244,"end_time":845.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":839.259,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"You know, maybe we get out with a blog faster just because we already got beat to the punch.","index":245,"end_time":851.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":846.3,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"And.","index":246,"end_time":854.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":854.23,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"And then the.","index":247,"end_time":855.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":854.59,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"The asset takes a little longer to make those connection points.","index":248,"end_time":859.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":855.27,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":249,"end_time":863.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":863.51,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Well, keep us posted on anything that we can create.","index":250,"end_time":866.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":864.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Right.","index":251,"end_time":867.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":866.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Provide that will help out.","index":252,"end_time":869.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":867.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":253,"end_time":875.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":874.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We also did go through an update on LinkedIn the Q2 audience to start receiving the PDF lead gen form ads.","index":254,"end_time":882.48,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":875.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That was done earlier this week.","index":255,"end_time":884.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":882.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So interested to see how that performs.","index":256,"end_time":886.88,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":885.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''ll keep our eye on that.","index":257,"end_time":888.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":886.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then Nina, do you wanted to speak to this last point here around the ABM segments?","index":258,"end_time":894.56,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":888.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we were discussing about creating lists for Michigan banks.","index":259,"end_time":903.28,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":897.68,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"So we were wondering if you want to use any kind of specific target lists or anything that would be more geographical rather than the list that we''re using now.","index":260,"end_time":913.83,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":903.99,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Yeah, we''re working on pulling together our target account lists for next year.","index":261,"end_time":919.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":914.55,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"So we will have the ultimate account lists fairly soon.","index":262,"end_time":927.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":921.43,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"So that''s not something I don''t think that we need help with.","index":263,"end_time":932.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":928.31,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"There''s a lot of nuance within who we can actually serve in the.","index":264,"end_time":938.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":932.76,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Especially in the US and so all of that nuance is getting pulled into what we''re building from a target account list perspective.","index":265,"end_time":945.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":938.28,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":266,"end_time":947.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":947.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So it''s going to take us a little while to like this will be an evolution, not a.","index":267,"end_time":952.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":948.36,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Not A revolution type thing, but we will, we''re going to be owning the list, building for that and making that a core competency.","index":268,"end_time":962.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":952.44,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":269,"end_time":963.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":963.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And are you planning to utilize HubSpot''s Target Account feature?","index":270,"end_time":966.54,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":963.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yes.","index":271,"end_time":967.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":966.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Fantastic.","index":272,"end_time":969.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":968.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s the idea.","index":273,"end_time":971.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":969.9,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"And speaking of that, I can''t remember when you were meeting with HubSpot.","index":274,"end_time":977.98,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":973.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That already happened.","index":275,"end_time":979.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":978.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, there today.","index":276,"end_time":981.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":980.3,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":277,"end_time":982.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":981.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''ll keep us posted on anything we can assist with further there.","index":278,"end_time":985.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":982.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yep, definitely.","index":279,"end_time":986.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":985.54,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"All right.","index":280,"end_time":988.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":987.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Taking a look at some of the metrics.","index":281,"end_time":990.42,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":988.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So on Google Ad side we''re seeing an incredibly high click through rate, but it is brand search terms obviously.","index":282,"end_time":997.22,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":990.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So if people are searching for threat marker threat market related terms, more likely to engage.","index":283,"end_time":1001.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":997.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And we saw the cost decrease actually.","index":284,"end_time":1006.02,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1002.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"By over 25%.","index":285,"end_time":1007.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1006.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Mainly targeting middle aged males 35 to 44 and peak impressions around morning to noon and then in.","index":286,"end_time":1017.72,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1009.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The afternoon on weekdays.","index":287,"end_time":1019.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1017.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"For the LinkedIn and AdRoll side.","index":288,"end_time":1023.64,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1022.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So on LinkedIn we did see a little bit of a decrease, but we also just launched that new campaign this week with Q2 targeting for the PDF downloads.","index":289,"end_time":1032.96,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1023.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And on the ad roll side we saw six clicks come through, which is a 200% increase after changing.","index":290,"end_time":1041.21,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1033.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The targeting and ads that were going to the Q2 audience there to send them to.","index":291,"end_time":1047.57,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1043.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That Q2 landing page.","index":292,"end_time":1048.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1047.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yep.","index":293,"end_time":1049.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1048.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Any questions or anything here?","index":294,"end_time":1053.53,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1052.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sounds good.","index":295,"end_time":1055.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1055.05,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":296,"end_time":1057.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1056.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":297,"end_time":1057.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1057.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then that brings us to our last slide, which is we would just.","index":298,"end_time":1060.97,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1057.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We kind of touched on it in our last meeting, but we''re getting a session on the books for 2026 planning.","index":299,"end_time":1066.94,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1061.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, definitely would like to do that.","index":300,"end_time":1071.74,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1068.54,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Ooh, this year''s almost done.","index":301,"end_time":1076.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1074.62,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Greg.","index":302,"end_time":1079.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1078.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s.","index":303,"end_time":1079.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1079.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You''re telling me.","index":304,"end_time":1080.54,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1079.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I, my daughter''s been my gauge for that.","index":305,"end_time":1083.66,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1080.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"She''s about to turn one next month and I''m like, where did the year go?","index":306,"end_time":1087.02,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1083.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh.","index":307,"end_time":1087.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1087.52,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"That''S a big birthday.","index":308,"end_time":1090.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1089.6,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"I''m wondering if this ends up being something that we have to do in early January.","index":309,"end_time":1097.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1093.84,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Could be just for context, we''re, we''re huddling up next week to.","index":310,"end_time":1105.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1098.88,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Kind of solidify our plan for next year and I think it''d be good for us to do that before we have that conversation.","index":311,"end_time":1114.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1106.72,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"So.","index":312,"end_time":1115.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1115.07,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"And the week after next is, is bingo.","index":313,"end_time":1119.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1116.43,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"We''re, we''re done.","index":314,"end_time":1119.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1119.03,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Everybody''s vacationing in various ways.","index":315,"end_time":1124.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1122.51,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"So yeah, so I would, I would say let''s try to get that booked for early January.","index":316,"end_time":1131.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1124.79,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"One of the things that.","index":317,"end_time":1135.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1134.11,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Kate and I were talking about just in terms of like process cadence and things like that that I think would be useful is, and this is obviously dependent on, on availability on Your side, Colin and Nina, but pushing our weekly meeting to Mondays, so that way we can have kind of more of a.","index":318,"end_time":1159.54,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1137.39,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"All right, this is what we want to do this week.","index":319,"end_time":1161.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1159.94,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Go.","index":320,"end_time":1163.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1162.9,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"And.","index":321,"end_time":1164.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1163.86,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"And it''s kind of more consistent with the week.","index":322,"end_time":1166.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1164.83,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"We have our team call on Mondays, so what we could do is have our team call first and then have, you know, our call with you guys.","index":323,"end_time":1174.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1166.75,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Would.","index":324,"end_time":1174.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1174.51,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Would there be any possibility for that?","index":325,"end_time":1176.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1174.91,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah, let me just check our availability.","index":326,"end_time":1179.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1177.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You want to start that as soon.","index":327,"end_time":1181.67,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1180.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"As, like, next week, if possible?","index":328,"end_time":1184.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1181.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":329,"end_time":1185.31,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1184.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Next Monday, the 15th.","index":330,"end_time":1188.83,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1186.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I.","index":331,"end_time":1189.31,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1188.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I have availability and make sure.","index":332,"end_time":1194.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1192.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Pulling Nina up as well, 9am Eastern.","index":333,"end_time":1198.84,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1194.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we could do that after your team call.","index":334,"end_time":1205.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1202.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Does 10:00am Eastern work?","index":335,"end_time":1207.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1205.8,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Nina, I see that you have a call on.","index":336,"end_time":1211.56,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1209.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Is that able to move?","index":337,"end_time":1212.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1211.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You''re on mute.","index":338,"end_time":1216.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1215.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It can probably be moved.","index":339,"end_time":1220.44,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1218.84,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"I don''t have any.","index":340,"end_time":1221.32,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1220.44,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Okay.","index":341,"end_time":1222.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1221.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, so we could do 10am Eastern.","index":342,"end_time":1224.12,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1222.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Cool.","index":343,"end_time":1225.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1224.76,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Let''s.","index":344,"end_time":1225.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1225.2,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Let''s plan to do that.","index":345,"end_time":1226.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1225.56,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Let''s plan to do 10am Eastern on Mondays, and we can switch starting next week.","index":346,"end_time":1232.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1226.64,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"And then, like, whenever there''s Monday holidays, we''ll accommodate for that, of course, but I think that''ll be a slightly better cadence for us to be able to kind of set everything up for the week and, you know, kind of deliver in weak, weak sized chunks.","index":347,"end_time":1248.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1232.4,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Because that''s kind of how we''re thinking about things internally as well, so.","index":348,"end_time":1253.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1250.41,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah, okay.","index":349,"end_time":1255.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1253.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, that sounds good.","index":350,"end_time":1257.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1256.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I just updated that on the calendar.","index":351,"end_time":1258.89,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1257.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Obviously, we''ll do our best to make everything happen, you know, in weeks when we meet, but sometimes if there''s a.","index":352,"end_time":1264.61,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1259.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Bigger project, it may span into the next week.","index":353,"end_time":1266.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1264.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yep, of course.","index":354,"end_time":1267.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1266.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Cool.","index":355,"end_time":1269.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1269.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, Anything else from your side that you guys wanted to share?","index":356,"end_time":1273.65,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1271.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Anything that we didn''t address that you want to go through?","index":357,"end_time":1276.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1274.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I just wanted to ask about the Creative for the PDFs on LinkedIn.","index":358,"end_time":1284.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1278.29,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Can you check the link to the final assets again, please?","index":359,"end_time":1288.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1286.21,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Did I miss it?","index":360,"end_time":1290.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1289.25,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Yes, I can check.","index":361,"end_time":1293.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1292.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Might have to just find those and send those.","index":362,"end_time":1314.14,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1312.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I''ll have to find those and.","index":363,"end_time":1329.31,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1328.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Send those back over to you, Kate.","index":364,"end_time":1330.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1329.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":365,"end_time":1333.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1332.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, of course.","index":366,"end_time":1334.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1333.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Anything else?","index":367,"end_time":1342.95,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1342.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Think that''s good.","index":368,"end_time":1349.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1346.96,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Keep us posted on the homepage carousel.","index":369,"end_time":1353.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1350.72,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"And that''s probably the.","index":370,"end_time":1354.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1353.24,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"The next, like, big thing, if you will.","index":371,"end_time":1357.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1354.24,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"And.","index":372,"end_time":1359.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1359.28,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah, sounds good.","index":373,"end_time":1362.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1360.88,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":374,"end_time":1363.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1363.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, well, have a great rest of your day, guys.","index":375,"end_time":1365.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1363.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sweet.","index":376,"end_time":1366.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1365.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Thanks, Colin.","index":377,"end_time":1367,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1366.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":378,"end_time":1367.4,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1367,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Bye.","index":379,"end_time":1367.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1367.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":380,"end_time":1368.08,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1367.64,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Bye.","index":381,"end_time":1368.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1368.16,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Bye.","index":382,"end_time":1368.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1368.48,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"}],"dateString":"2025-12-10T14:30:00.000Z","host_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/84564648866?pwd=JR6eWxlxKbgogzCqTNUawSLUUhQoEa.1","participants":["colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com,kate.burwood@threatmark.com,gregory.smith@threatmark.com,nina.belina@marketersindemand.com,iulia.lungu@threatmark.com","kate.burwood@threatmark.com","gregory.smith@threatmark.com","nina.belina@marketersindemand.com","iulia.lungu@threatmark.com"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01KBJMGZH3CM88KBTJ0RDRQB1F","organizer_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"positive","confidence":0.92,"bullets":["Optimized Google Ads and retargeting yielded improved metrics and lowered costs by over 25%.","Shifted podcast metrics into Databox, now showing episode-level download data from Buzzsprout.","Reviewed competitor ad activity across LinkedIn and SpyFu to inform campaign and content strategy.","Agreed to move weekly sync to Mondays to better align with internal planning cadence.","Launched updated lead-gen forms for Q2 audience and began planning PSD3 campaign engagement."],"highlights":[{"quote":"We saw the cost decrease actually by over 25%.","speaker":"Colin Costigan"},{"quote":"Podcast downloads... will show breakdown by episode.","speaker":"Colin Costigan"},{"quote":"Let’s plan to do 10am Eastern on Mondays... for better cadence.","speaker":"Greg Smith"}],"topics":["delivery","metrics","campaign","process","ads"],"model":"openai/gpt-4-1106-preview","version":1,"generated_at":"2025-12-10T00:00:00Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **Advertising Performance and Optimization**\n\nThe team improved Google Ads significantly by updating all site links, headlines, descriptions, and extensions, boosting ad strength to \"good\" while maintaining selective recommendation acceptance for better quality (02:45).  \n- This update included switching the landing page from Contact Us to the homepage, aiming to boost conversions with the upcoming carousel feature.  \n- Retargeting campaigns on AdRoll were redirected to the Q2 landing page, targeting US-based audiences, especially Michigan, ensuring alignment with customer geography (03:30).  \n- Colin reported a **25% cost decrease** and a very high click-through rate on Google Ads, mainly from brand search terms, with peak engagement from males aged **35 to 44** during weekday mornings and afternoons (16:27).  \n- LinkedIn campaigns saw a slight dip but included a new Q2-targeted PDF lead gen form ad launched earlier that week, expected to generate quality leads (16:27).  \n- AdRoll clicks increased by **200%** after targeting adjustments to the Q2 audience, signaling improved engagement (16:27).  \n\n## **Content Syndication and Podcast Metrics**\n\nThe podcast downloads are now visible in Databox through Buzzsprout integration, which syndicates episodes to Spotify and Apple and tracks downloads by episode (04:16).  \n- Greg confirmed that ThreatMark accounts exist on Spotify and Apple, allowing direct access to those platforms’ metrics if needed (04:41).  \n- This data integration supports better tracking of owned media performance and informs content strategy decisions.  \n\n## **Competitive Intelligence and Market Positioning**\n\nThe team analyzed competitor activity on LinkedIn, focusing on Feedzai and BioCatch, identifying their ad styles and messaging tactics (06:00).  \n- Feedzai uses multi-language, GIF-based, and event ads, while BioCatch relies heavily on scare tactics, focusing on emotional stories about fraud losses to influence audiences (06:00).  \n- Colin noted that exact regional targeting details are unavailable, but shared that their LinkedIn targeting likely overlaps with these competitors, implying direct market competition (07:29).  \n- This insight helps inform ThreatMark’s positioning strategy and ad messaging to differentiate and compete effectively.  \n\n## **Product and Website Updates**\n\nThe newsroom was updated to display post dates directly on the posts, improving content transparency and user experience (07:44).  \n- The new podcast episode with Kelly Paxton went live on the website, YouTube, Spotify, and Apple after Mike''s approval, featuring embedded players and enhanced content like summary, insights, and quote cards (07:44).  \n- The team is finalizing the form embedding on the site and troubleshooting a navigation jump issue reported by Kate, capturing video evidence to assist developers (08:50).  \n- Color consistency, mobile navigation dots, and auto-scroll features were refined on the homepage slider for better UX based on Kate’s feedback (11:17).  \n- Production of the end-of-year compilation video is underway, focusing on thematic snippets from past episodes to engage audiences (12:13).  \n- Kelly Paxton’s official title is still pending, delaying final production details (11:58).  \n\n## **ABM Strategy and Targeting**\n\nThe PSD3 campaign budget and strategy remain tentative, with Kate highlighting the need to better connect why prospects should engage about PSD3 issues (12:44).  \n- Greg emphasized that this campaign is relevant primarily for the EU and suggested prioritizing a blog post launch for quicker outreach while the asset is refined (13:46).  \n- Yuli will lead the ABM efforts targeting PSD3 within the broader EU activation plan (13:46).  \n- Nina and Greg are developing precise target account lists for 2024, focusing on nuanced eligibility and serviceability in the US market, particularly Michigan banks (14:57).  \n- This list-building will be an ongoing process owned internally, using HubSpot’s Target Account feature to sharpen focus and improve marketing efficiency (15:48).  \n\n## **Process Improvements and Meeting Cadence**\n\nGreg proposed moving weekly meetings to Monday mornings at **10:00 AM Eastern** starting next week to better align with internal planning and create a consistent weekly kickoff rhythm (18:07).  \n- Colin confirmed availability and updated calendars, emphasizing flexibility for larger projects that may span multiple weeks (19:37).  \n- This cadence change aims to synchronize marketing execution with internal team goals and improve weekly planning clarity.  \n- Colin committed to sharing final creative assets for LinkedIn PDFs with Kate to ensure smooth campaign launches (21:18).  \n- Greg requested updates on the homepage carousel feature, identifying it as the next major focus area for site improvements (22:26).","outline":null,"keywords":["Google Ads","Podcast Metrics","LinkedIn Campaign","ABM Strategy","Target Account Lists","Website Navigation Issue"],"overview":"- **Google Ads Optimization:** Ad strength boosted to \"good,\" 25% cost decrease, high engagement from males 35-44 during mornings.  \n- **Retargeting Campaigns:** Focused on Q2 landing page, targeting US audiences, especially in Michigan, improving conversion rates.  \n- **Podcast Integration:** Downloads now tracked via Buzzsprout on Spotify and Apple, enhancing content performance monitoring.  \n- **Competitor Analysis:** Reviewed LinkedIn strategies of Feedzai and BioCatch to inform ThreatMark''s ad messaging and market positioning.  \n- **ABM Strategy Development:** Tentative PSD3 budget discussed, with focus on EU outreach and precise target account lists for 2024.  \n- **Meeting Reschedule:** Weekly meetings moved to Monday at 10:00 AM Eastern for better planning alignment and execution.","action_items":"\n**Colin Costigan**\nSend podcast download Databox link to Greg for easier access (04:30)\nLocate and resend final LinkedIn PDF creative assets to Kate (21:25)\nCheck availability and confirm start for weekly meetings moved to Mondays at 10am Eastern beginning next week (19:40)\nProvide video and replication details of website navigation jump issue to development team for resolution (09:10)\nUpload updated fraud lifecycle diagram text changes received from Greg and forward to Michal for review (11:20)\n\n**Greg Smith**\nFollow up with Kate post-meeting to send finalized text changes for fraud lifecycle diagram (10:15)\nKeep Colin and Nina updated on planning progress for 2025 target account lists with nuanced segmentation (15:10)\n\n**Kate ThreatMark**\nConfirm Kelly Paxton’s official job title for final podcast production (11:15)\nContinue refining PSD3 asset and strategy, possibly shifting initial outreach to blog format; keep marketing informed (13:05)\n\n**Nina Belina**\nCoordinate with Colin and Greg regarding Monday 10am Eastern weekly meeting schedule and adjust calendar accordingly (20:15)\nSupport data integration for LinkedIn Q2 campaign and ABM efforts as needed (14:50)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"9924ebba-fbf8-4d0d-90bc-497a07ed6bb7","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
