d_time":2480.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2478.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Romp and roll.","index":881,"end_time":2485.51,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2484.55,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I just clicked on this.","index":882,"end_time":2487.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2486.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This is where it took me.","index":883,"end_time":2488.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2487.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Here''s Bombshell.","index":884,"end_time":2491.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2490.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The boathouse.","index":885,"end_time":2494.27,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2493.51,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"That''s in Florida.","index":886,"end_time":2494.95,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2494.27,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"That''s a good place to eat.","index":887,"end_time":2495.99,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2494.95,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"This is Boathouse Virginia.","index":888,"end_time":2497.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2496.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, I don''t know that one.","index":889,"end_time":2499.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2498.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Now I''m getting hungry.","index":890,"end_time":2502.93,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2501.81,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"For a grouper sandwich.","index":891,"end_time":2506.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2504.93,"speaker_name":"Ryan Fisher"},{"text":"Yeah, I can go for a big grouper sandwich.","index":892,"end_time":2509.17,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2506.85,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Dude, you''re getting me hungry, man.","index":893,"end_time":2510.53,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2509.17,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"The romp and roll.","index":894,"end_time":2513.49,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2512.45,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"You just went by the romp and roll.","index":895,"end_time":2515.01,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2513.49,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Have fun, learn more, make friends.","index":896,"end_time":2518.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2517.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Some sort of swingers club.","index":897,"end_time":2523.89,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2522.45,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"So we will put.","index":898,"end_time":2526.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2525.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The price over campaign.","index":899,"end_time":2529.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2528.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And the pain point campaign together.","index":900,"end_time":2532.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2531.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then I''ll start putting together some framework for Bing ads.","index":901,"end_time":2536.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2532.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I''ll think through the promo pop up.","index":902,"end_time":2540.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2538.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That is one thing.","index":903,"end_time":2541.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2540.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So when I send you guys the page that we''ve designed for the msp, let''s take a hard look at the content because I didn''t talk too much about to you guys about like, what the actual offer is that they get.","index":904,"end_time":2551.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2541.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It took a lot of information from the partners page on the website, but I just want to verify that information.","index":905,"end_time":2556.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2551.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, I appreciate that you do that.","index":906,"end_time":2558.17,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2556.41,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"So thanks.","index":907,"end_time":2558.73,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2558.17,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"We''ll start with your rough outline and we''ll go from there.","index":908,"end_time":2560.81,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2558.73,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Of course.","index":909,"end_time":2561.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2560.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Anything else from your end?","index":910,"end_time":2564.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2563.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I got nothing else.","index":911,"end_time":2566.33,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2565.21,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Well, hopefully that Sam guy either calls back or picks up on the next call.","index":912,"end_time":2572.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2567.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean, it looks like trash, so I''m not necessarily worried about it.","index":913,"end_time":2579.61,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2575.53,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":914,"end_time":2580.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2580.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, well, let me know if.","index":915,"end_time":2582.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2581.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"My thing of it is, is I just don''t like being lied to.","index":916,"end_time":2585.46,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2583.46,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"So that was my issue.","index":917,"end_time":2586.18,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2585.46,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I thought I''d been lied to, but I didn''t.","index":918,"end_time":2587.78,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2586.18,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I gotcha.","index":919,"end_time":2588.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2588.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s good.","index":920,"end_time":2589.54,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2588.98,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Yep.","index":921,"end_time":2590.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2590.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And we have, like I mentioned, we got points for other pages, other campaigns, things like that.","index":922,"end_time":2596.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2590.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I. I guess we''re talking this week about how we own three CX top to bottom.","index":923,"end_time":2600.58,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2596.66,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"So that''s probably gonna push some stuff your way as to what we want.","index":924,"end_time":2602.98,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2600.58,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"But first thing we need to do is not get it to show in Our pmax campaigns.","index":925,"end_time":2605.86,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2602.98,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Yep.","index":926,"end_time":2606.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2606.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":927,"end_time":2607.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2607.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s step one.","index":928,"end_time":2608.49,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2607.73,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"And then maybe we do a whole nother pmax campaign around just three cx.","index":929,"end_time":2614.73,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2610.73,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":930,"end_time":2615.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2615.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Or a Bing ads campaign around it.","index":931,"end_time":2619.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2617.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Fine.","index":932,"end_time":2620.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2619.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Let''s do that, too.","index":933,"end_time":2620.81,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2620.01,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"All right.","index":934,"end_time":2622.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2622.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Or we could do both.","index":935,"end_time":2624.57,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2623.61,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":936,"end_time":2625.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2625.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Can I make a note about this?","index":937,"end_time":2627.69,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2626.33,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":938,"end_time":2628.41,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2628.09,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Let''s have them run side by side.","index":939,"end_time":2629.61,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2628.41,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Let''s see which one gets more traffic.","index":940,"end_time":2631.13,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2629.61,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Yeah, and the thing about Microsoft ads is they''re cheaper.","index":941,"end_time":2633.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2631.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s less competitive, less kids in the sandbox.","index":942,"end_time":2635.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2633.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean, this is kind of genius.","index":943,"end_time":2637.86,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2636.02,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I like the outside the box thinking, Colin.","index":944,"end_time":2641.14,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2639.06,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Yep.","index":945,"end_time":2641.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2641.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, well, if anything else pops up, please let me know.","index":946,"end_time":2647.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2644.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, sounds good.","index":947,"end_time":2648.9,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2647.78,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"And, Matt, I hope that your wife''s friends start doing better and actually helping out with.","index":948,"end_time":2654.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2649.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, she''s made some money this week.","index":949,"end_time":2656.26,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2654.82,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Got a few organizations coming out.","index":950,"end_time":2660.55,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2658.83,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"She''s got quite a few people signed up.","index":951,"end_time":2662.19,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2660.55,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"She''s got quite a few nonprofit meetings set up, so.","index":952,"end_time":2665.47,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2662.19,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Nice.","index":953,"end_time":2666.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2665.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Well, she should tell her to look at the Fix caller ID website and see if she can get any.","index":954,"end_time":2670.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2666.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I asked her, I''m like, shit, man.","index":955,"end_time":2672.55,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2670.51,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"You got shit going on.","index":956,"end_time":2673.55,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2672.55,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"You.","index":957,"end_time":2673.87,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2673.55,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"You should just take over Tech Mode.","index":958,"end_time":2675.39,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2673.87,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"She say, no, thank you.","index":959,"end_time":2678.67,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2677.55,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"She''s laughed at my face and said.","index":960,"end_time":2680.99,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2678.83,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Anytime anyone has a good idea, Matt''s goes right to you should be running the joint.","index":961,"end_time":2687.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2683.3,"speaker_name":"Christopher Quigley"},{"text":"Come on, dude.","index":962,"end_time":2688.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2687.14,"speaker_name":"Ryan Fisher"},{"text":"I love it.","index":963,"end_time":2689.22,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2688.7,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I want to sit back.","index":964,"end_time":2691.7,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2690.66,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"All right, well, have a good rest of your day, guys.","index":965,"end_time":2696.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2694.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Great talking to you.","index":966,"end_time":2696.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2696.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":967,"end_time":2697.62,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2697.14,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Take care.","index":968,"end_time":2698.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2697.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Bye.","index":969,"end_time":2698.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2698.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Bye.","index":970,"end_time":2701.23,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2698.34,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"}],"dateString":"2025-12-09T20:00:00.000Z","host_email":"lhall@techmode.com","meeting_link":"https://teams.microsoft.com/l/meetup-join/19:meeting_NjEzNzdiMDAtMzIyNi00NzgxLWIwOTYtODBjZWQ4NjljZGM3@thread.v2/0?context={\"Tid\":\"3801011d-e732-48ee-be2a-e499b1a29ba4\",\"Oid\":\"e804fbe9-a623-4d26-a887-992e62fb92d1\"}","participants":["cquigley@techmode.com,colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com,monica.chinsami@marketersindemand.com,nathalie.mintjens@marketersindemand.com,lhall@techmode.com,michael.lewis@techmode.com,mlook@techmode.com,rfisher@techmode.com","cquigley@techmode.com","colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com","monica.chinsami@marketersindemand.com","nathalie.mintjens@marketersindemand.com","michael.lewis@techmode.com","mlook@techmode.com","rfisher@techmode.com"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01KBXFGDCRND77MSSN564PM325","organizer_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"neutral","confidence":0.83,"bullets":["Reviewed design and timeline for MSP reseller and virtual phone system pages; delivery staggered across weeks.","Decided against Stir/Shaken and SMS approval campaigns due to industry ambiguity and early timing.","Identified issue with PMAX ads overriding 3CX-specific ads; team pursuing negative keyword solution via Google rep.","Agreed to explore Microsoft Ads campaign for 3CX due to lower CPC and executive search behavior.","Marketing follow-ups confirmed leads were contacted; missing logs attributed to phone number formatting timing issues."],"highlights":[{"quote":"There''s a lot going on behind the scenes... might be a little bit early on it.","speaker":"Ryan Fisher"},{"quote":"I want to be like usage 3CX. We''re a titanium partner.","speaker":"Matthew Look"},{"quote":"We have to work through a Google rep to allow a negative keyword being added to the PMAX campaign.","speaker":"Colin Costigan"}],"topics":["ads","campaigns","3cx","delivery","leads"],"model":"openai/gpt-4-1106-preview","version":1,"generated_at":"2025-12-09T00:00:00Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **Website and Marketing Campaign Development**\n\nThe team is progressing on key web pages and campaigns to boost MSP and phone system partner engagement.\n\n- **MSP reseller page wireframe and copy are completed and set for design this week**, with a virtual phone and IP phone system page scheduled for next week (06:00)  \n    - The MSP page will include embedded forms directly on the page to reduce friction in lead capture, approved by Lindsay and Matthew (20:02)  \n    - Colin will provide the page designs and copy for review, focusing on clear partner offers before development (42:02)  \n    - The team plans to test a promo pop-up on the MSP page to encourage immediate sign-ups, with suggestions like “earn 10x commission on your first deal” (37:26)  \n    - Lindsay will handle implementation once pages are ready, freeing Colin’s team to focus on content and design (19:38)\n\n- **Paid ad campaigns are being refined with new headlines and landing pages for MSP and virtual phone system segments** (19:13)  \n    - Campaigns will split into categories to target specific pain points and product features for better conversion (19:36)  \n    - Colin is creating frameworks for Bing ads as an alternative channel, leveraging less competition and lower cost (42:02, 43:51)  \n    - The team agreed to test Microsoft Ads alongside Google to compare traffic and cost-effectiveness (43:48)  \n\n- **Spam and suspicious form submissions remain a challenge, with efforts to reduce bad leads through Google Ads audience targeting and enhanced CAPTCHA** (16:00)  \n    - Colin outlined plans to exclude repeat suspicious form fillers by creating a conversion audience to avoid wasting ad spend (16:00)  \n    - The team acknowledged that some submissions appear authentic but use deceptive data, requiring layered anti-spam measures (16:00)  \n\n## **3CX Brand and Paid Search Strategy**\n\nOwning the 3CX search space is a priority to capture high-intent leads and avoid campaign cannibalization.\n\n- **Matthew emphasized the need for 3CX branded ads to show exclusively on 3CX searches, rather than generic cost savings ads, to better position Tech Mode as a titanium partner** (29:00)  \n    - Colin confirmed that Performance Max (PMAX) campaigns currently override 3CX search ads, diluting brand presence (29:30)  \n    - Two approaches are being explored: setting account-level negative keywords and exact match targeting in the 3CX campaign, or working with a Google rep to add negative keywords directly to PMAX (29:44)  \n    - Colin and Ryan will jointly engage Google reps to accelerate resolution, acknowledging the difficulty of getting direct support (31:20)  \n    - The team agreed to create a separate PMAX or Bing campaign focused solely on 3CX messaging once the current conflict is resolved (43:27)  \n\n- **Ryan shared frustrations with Google support, noting the challenge in increasing quotas and managing campaigns without direct rep access** (31:40)  \n    - Lindsay suggested applying pressure through budget discussions to motivate Google reps to respond faster (32:10)  \n    - The team recognized Microsoft Ads as a promising alternative due to less competition and cost, supporting parallel campaigns (43:48)  \n\n## **Caller ID Authentication and Market Positioning**\n\nThe complexity and uncertainty of caller ID authentication affect product messaging and competitive positioning.\n\n- **The team confirmed only two main methods exist to improve caller ID: carrier registration via websites and call attestation, with Tech Mode controlling the latter but still facing challenges** (22:30)  \n    - Matthew and Ryan agreed the industry is in flux, making it hard to create clear marketing messages around solutions like Stir Shaken and call attestation (21:42)  \n    - Ryan explained that carriers use proprietary algorithms to assess call legitimacy, limiting predictability and control (25:18)  \n    - The team expressed skepticism over competitors’ claims, noting pricing pages and guarantees often appear misleading or \"scammy\" (23:50)  \n    - Colin reported working on new headlines and landing pages focused on caller ID authentication and related pain points but agreed the timing may not be right for full campaign launches (19:10, 36:33)\n\n- **Testimonials from competitors were found to be outdated or fabricated, highlighting an opportunity for Tech Mode to build trust through authenticity** (26:00)  \n    - Matthew and Ryan noted competitor references, like the Kansas City Chiefs testimonial, are misleading or invalid, underlining Tech Mode’s advantage in credibility (26:17)  \n    - The team plans to carefully vet MSP partner offers and testimonials on new pages to maintain transparency and trust (42:02)  \n\n## **Lead Management and Follow-Up Process**\n\nImproving lead capture and follow-up workflows is key to converting interest into sales.\n\n- **Recent form submissions show some leads do not convert beyond initial contact, prompting process improvements to automate follow-ups** (10:47)  \n    - Christopher described a new automated email sent immediately after cost savings calculator submissions, outlining benefits and offering Calendly links for consultations (10:56)  \n    - Despite automation, sales reps like Christopher continue personalized follow-ups to nurture leads, blending automation with human touch (11:58)  \n    - Lead data quality issues persist, such as missing or misformatted phone numbers causing tracking gaps; Lindsay identified workflows updating phone formats post-call to improve accuracy (15:14)  \n    - The team monitors lead activity closely to catch potential “ghost” leads or unresponsive prospects for targeted re-engagement or disqualification (08:19)  \n\n- **Matthew expressed frustration with inconsistent lead data but acknowledged that follow-up diligence is critical to avoid missed opportunities** (09:36)  \n\n## **Operational and Process Improvements**\n\nAdjustments to budgeting and campaign management processes aim to optimize spending and responsiveness.\n\n- **Budget pacing for paid campaigns has been updated to run on a monthly budget rather than daily limits, allowing more flexible spend control** (36:00)  \n    - Lindsay will monitor pacing closely to avoid early budget depletion and discuss pausing campaigns if spend accelerates too quickly (36:24)  \n    - This change supports more consistent lead flow and better allocation of marketing resources across the month (36:33)  \n\n- **The team plans to continue refining campaign targeting and content based on ongoing marketing meetings and feedback loops** (06:35)  \n    - Colin is ready to implement new campaigns and pages as soon as marketing priorities are set, allowing agile response to market conditions (19:54)  \n    - Lindsay offered to gather quick keyword ideas for pain point campaigns focused on common customer frustrations to drive relevant traffic (28:06)  \n\n## **Competitive and Market Insights**\n\nThe discussion revealed important competitive intelligence and strategic positioning opportunities.\n\n- **Tech Mode holds a competitive edge through direct control of call attestation, but market confusion limits clear messaging around caller ID fixes** (23:32)  \n    - Competitor websites often use outdated or misleading information, which Tech Mode can counter with transparency and expert positioning (24:38)  \n    - The team recognized the fluid nature of telecom standards like Stir Shaken, requiring cautious marketing until adoption stabilizes (21:42)  \n\n- **Emerging ad platforms like Bing Ads and future ChatGPT ads present new channels for growth outside Google’s crowded ecosystem** (34:00)  \n    - Colin highlighted lower competition and cost on Microsoft Ads, with plans to test alongside Google for performance comparison (43:48)  \n    - The team expressed excitement and caution about ads on AI platforms, noting potential shifts in digital marketing dynamics (34:24)  \n\n- **Internal humor and cultural references around competitor websites and spam leads underscored the team’s focus on authenticity and quality over gimmicks** (02:00 - 18:50)  \n    - The Fix Caller ID website was both mocked for design but respected for legitimacy, showing the team’s balance of humor with serious analysis (02:00)  \n    - Stories about identifying spam leads with fake identities reinforced the need for robust lead validation processes (17:25)","outline":null,"keywords":["caller ID verification","MSP reseller campaign","Google PMAX ads","3cx marketing","lead management","caller ID attestation"],"overview":"- **Website Progress:** MSP reseller page wireframe completed; design phase begins this week; testing promo pop-up for sign-ups planned.  \n- **Ad Campaign Refinement:** New headlines and landing pages for MSP and virtual phone system ads; exploring Bing Ads as alternative channel.  \n- **Caller ID Challenges:** Two main methods for caller ID exist; competitors'' claims often misleading, highlighting need for clear messaging.  \n- **Lead Management Improvements:** New automated emails and follow-up processes initiated; concerns over lead data quality persist.  \n- **Budget Management Changes:** Monthly budget pacing for campaigns adopted; adjustments aim to optimize spending and resource allocation.  \n- **Market Insights:** Tech Mode can leverage transparency against competitors’ misleading info; exploring Bing Ads and AI platforms for growth.","action_items":"\n**Colin Costigan**\nSend segmented spreadsheet of landing pages and campaign categories to Lindsay Hall for content integration (19:34)\nProceed with embedding forms directly on new landing pages and write copy for MSP campaign and virtual phone system pages (19:58)\nExplore and test solutions with Google reps for applying negative keywords to PMAX campaigns to separate 3cx branded and generic ads (31:15)\nDevelop Bing ads campaign for 3cx alongside Google campaign and monitor comparative performance (43:48)\nImplement changes to ad scripts to run monthly budget instead of daily budget and monitor budget pacing (36:12)\nContinue working on designs for MSP reseller page (due this week) and virtual phone system page (due next week) (37:26)\nPrepare promo popup ideas for partner pages to incentivize sign-ups (37:50)\nFollow up on lead submissions and monitor any new activity, especially on form spam and suspicious entries (42:47)\n\n**Lindsay Hall**\nIntegrate landing page content and manage campaign pages as provided by Colin (19:44)\nProvide keyword ideas and search volume data for pain point campaigns targeting caller ID and phone system issues (28:06)\nMonitor ad campaign budgets and report on pacing; coordinate internal marketing meetings focused on campaign strategies (36:33)\nAccept and manage promo content and popup messaging on partner pages to enhance lead generation efforts (37:50)\n\n**Matthew Look**\nRedesign Techmode logo and create website visual templates inspired by competitor’s pricing page (02:38)\nDrive campaign strategy for owning 3cx branded search terms and ensure those ads show exclusively for 3cx searches (43:26)\nCollaborate with Colin and Lindsay to align marketing campaigns and creative around 3cx messaging (43:26)\n\n**Ryan Fisher**\nParticipate in calls with Google reps regarding Google Cloud quota issues and PMAX keyword management (31:38)\nContinue troubleshooting lead call logs and coordinate with Colin and Lindsay to verify and improve data accuracy for leads (14:21)\nSupport integration of marketing campaigns with call analytics and attestation understanding to improve caller ID fixes (25:57)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"44a369cd-c4b4-43f6-92c7-71a3e078a7ad","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
