    '{"id":"01KBXFHVGWMM65E0VD3B1MPH9Q","title":"KTC // MiD: Weekly Marketing Meeting","summary":{"notes":"## **Video Package and Branding**\n\nThe team finalized the **Executive Advantage series video package** and selected a cohesive brand look that balances existing and future company identities (02:15).\n\n- **Michael Kersten and Colin Costigan agreed** on cover art option **four** for the video series, establishing a unified visual identity early in the campaign.\n    - The package includes consistent branding elements like captions and quote cards to maintain visual coherence across all video assets.\n    - Colin emphasized the importance of a cohesive look to support engagement and brand recognition.\n    - This video package is positioned to enhance audience connection and content professionalism.\n\n- For color palettes, they chose a **hybrid palette** blending KTC’s blues with Richie May’s greens, avoiding a full transition to Richie May’s colors (05:02).\n    - Colin noted the green tones signal finance and security, while blue adds a friendly, lighter feel suited to KTC Search’s identity.\n    - Michael preferred this approach to ease future integration without a disruptive overhaul.\n    - Retaining the existing logo mark avoids costly redesign and preserves brand equity.\n    - This decision balances brand continuity with a strategic nod to upcoming corporate alignment.\n\n## **Website Sitemap and Content Strategy**\n\nA more structured, funnel-based sitemap will replace the current flat layout to improve site navigation and user experience (08:01).\n\n- Colin presented a sitemap focusing on clear visitor paths leading from the homepage to key areas like services, resources, and testimonials.\n    - The homepage will emphasize **PE-backed companies**, reflecting their current strongest market segment.\n    - Michael approved this directional change, recognizing it will guide visitors more effectively.\n    - The new sitemap supports better user engagement and lead generation by simplifying choices and highlighting priorities.\n    - This redesign aligns with the goal of positioning KTC as a specialized and trustworthy partner.\n\n- Content rewrites for existing pages will be developed and sent to Michael for approval over the next few weeks, aiming for a **4-5 week total rollout** including HubSpot development (09:00).\n    - The HubSpot build phase is estimated at around **two weeks**, due to the modest site size.\n    - This timeline balances quality content creation with efficient deployment.\n    - The rewrite process will improve messaging clarity and align with the new user journey.\n    - Deliverables and approvals are clearly assigned to maintain momentum.\n\n## **Website Technical Issues and Migration**\n\nThe current website experiences performance problems, including slow loading, broken API scripts, and navigation failures, which require immediate fixes before migration (06:39).\n\n- Colin highlighted broken API calls and non-functioning homepage navigation affecting user experience and site reliability.\n    - Michael committed to reaching out to the technical team responsible for navigation and API fixes.\n    - These technical issues risk damaging visitor trust and must be resolved before launching the redesigned site.\n    - Coordination between content migration and technical fixes is critical to avoid delays.\n    - Addressing these problems early supports a smooth transition to the new HubSpot platform.\n\n- Migration will occur in one consolidated effort, combining content updates, design changes, and color palette adjustments (07:44).\n    - This approach reduces downtime and maintains brand consistency.\n    - It ensures all new assets and functional improvements launch simultaneously.\n    - The plan reflects a strategic choice to minimize disruptions and maximize impact.\n    - Michael and Colin agree this is the most efficient path forward.\n\n## **Competitive Website Analysis and Differentiation Strategy**\n\nThe team analyzed competitor sites to extract learnings and avoid common pitfalls, aiming to differentiate KTC with clearer messaging and user-friendly design (10:00).\n\n- Colin noted many competitors rely on generic, boilerplate content that lacks depth and engagement, which KTC will avoid (10:30).\n    - KTC’s content will be more detailed upfront, helping prospects understand value without extra digging.\n    - Michael emphasized wanting KTC to \"look like a big boy\" despite being smaller, relying on the team’s research and expertise.\n    - This approach targets improving trust and credibility through transparency and clarity.\n    - The strategy prioritizes user education and differentiation over flashy but shallow designs.\n\n- Specific competitor sites showed overused design elements that either confuse or distract users, such as excessive interactivity or hard-to-read text (12:12).\n    - Colin proposed a clean layout with intuitive user journeys and clear calls to action.\n    - The goal is to combine familiarity with distinctiveness to stand out while meeting user expectations.\n    - This design philosophy supports better engagement and conversion.\n    - The team will continue researching to refine these insights and incorporate best practices.\n\n## **Next Steps and Strategic Alignment**\n\nThe team will finalize the ABM plan alongside website and content efforts to drive coordinated marketing execution (14:00).\n\n- Colin confirmed that once content and sitemap plans are approved, writing and design will proceed with migration to HubSpot.\n    - Michael expressed confidence and readiness to move forward.\n    - This integrated approach ensures messaging, branding, and lead generation activities align.\n    - Delivering these elements together strengthens the overall market positioning.\n    - Ongoing communication and feedback loops will keep the project on track.","outline":null,"keywords":["branding","color palette","website sitemap","video package","competitor analysis","ABM plan"],"overview":"- **Video Package Finalized:** Executive Advantage video series selected cover art for cohesive branding, enhancing audience engagement and professionalism.  \n- **Hybrid Color Palette Chosen:** Blending KTC blues and Richie May greens maintains brand identity while signaling finance and security.  \n- **New Sitemap Structure Approved:** Funnel-based layout will improve user navigation, emphasizing PE-backed companies to enhance engagement and lead generation.  \n- **Website Technical Issues Identified:** Performance problems require immediate resolution before migration to ensure a smooth transition to HubSpot platform.  \n- **Competitor Analysis Highlights Differentiation:** KTC will use detailed content and user-friendly design, avoiding generic messaging found in competitor sites.  \n- **Next Steps Confirmed:** Team to finalize ABM plan post-approval to align content, branding, and lead generation efforts effectively.","action_items":"\n**Colin Costigan**\nFinalize color palette choice with KTC Search and incorporate into branding materials (06:34)\nComplete rewriting the webpage copy and send drafts to Michael for approval (08:45)\nCreate and share design mockups of the website in HubSpot for approval (08:45)\nDevelop the new website in HubSpot post-approval and manage migration, aiming for a 4-5 week turnaround (08:45)\nContinue research and refinement of competitor analysis to inform design and content strategy (10:30)\nFinalize ABM plan development and integrate it with the overall marketing strategy (13:48)\n\n**Michael Kersten**\nInvestigate and coordinate fixing website technical issues including API errors and homepage navigation problems with IT or relevant web team (07:26)\nReview and approve website copy and designs within timeframes provided (08:45)\nProvide feedback on competitor insights and branding decisions as required (14:21)\n"},"duration":14.479999542236328,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Colin Costigan"},{"id":1,"name":"Michael Kersten"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Hey, Michael, can you hear us?","index":0,"end_time":50.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":48.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I can''t hear you for some reason.","index":1,"end_time":52.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":51.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, there you are.","index":2,"end_time":54.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":53.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"There.","index":3,"end_time":54.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":54.18,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Can you hear me?","index":4,"end_time":55.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":54.54,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Now you can.","index":5,"end_time":55.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":55.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How are you doing?","index":6,"end_time":57.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":56.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Good.","index":7,"end_time":59.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":59.54,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Good.","index":8,"end_time":60.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":60.02,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":9,"end_time":61.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":60.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Another busy week.","index":10,"end_time":62.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":61.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Busy week and fighting a cold, so it always adds to the complexity.","index":11,"end_time":66.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":62.98,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s for sure.","index":12,"end_time":68.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":66.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Well, we''ll try to make this a fun meeting.","index":13,"end_time":70.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":68.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Maybe it''ll get you feeling a little better.","index":14,"end_time":71.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":70.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":15,"end_time":72.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":72.1,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"All right, so I''m going to go through the slide deck that we''ve prepared.","index":16,"end_time":77.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":73.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I want to go through.","index":17,"end_time":79.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":77.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''ve created the video package for the series and so we''ll walk through some different branding options there.","index":18,"end_time":84.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":79.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then I also wanted to.","index":19,"end_time":87.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":85.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I was going to send over color palettes, but I actually prefer walking through those.","index":20,"end_time":91.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":87.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''ll walk through four different options that we have for the KTC Search brand and then afterwards we will dig into sitemaps for the website.","index":21,"end_time":101.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":91.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So the current and the new proposed plan for the website and I also have just some competitor websites to go through to see if there''s anything you''ve really liked across those that you want to replicate on KTC Search.","index":22,"end_time":114.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":102.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So getting started with the video package.","index":23,"end_time":118.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":116.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we landed on Executive Advantage series and so we mocked up four different.","index":24,"end_time":121.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":118.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"These are what are considered cover art.","index":25,"end_time":123.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":122.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So if you were pulling up your show at a listing, this is what would show.","index":26,"end_time":127.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":123.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I always come in with a personal preference, but I like to also see if you like any of these more than the other.","index":27,"end_time":134.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":128.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Which one was yours?","index":28,"end_time":136.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":135.13,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I actually like number four over here.","index":29,"end_time":138.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":136.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":30,"end_time":139.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":138.89,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I would.","index":31,"end_time":143.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":143.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I would agree with that one.","index":32,"end_time":145.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":143.61,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Either three or three or four.","index":33,"end_time":147.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":145.05,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So I would agree.","index":34,"end_time":147.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":147.25,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So.","index":35,"end_time":148.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":147.93,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yep.","index":36,"end_time":149.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":148.49,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":37,"end_time":149.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":149.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And with that, we''ve also.","index":38,"end_time":152.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":150.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Developed all of the package that goes with it.","index":39,"end_time":157.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":155.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So now when we''re showing a screen recording of someone talking, it''ll have captions and everything below it with these sort of colors and branding.","index":40,"end_time":165.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":157.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":41,"end_time":167.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":167.06,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"When we produce their quote cards, there''s a few different options there as well.","index":42,"end_time":173.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":169.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then diving into the video package itself, this is just kind of every different type of asset that we would produce from any recordings.","index":43,"end_time":189.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":182.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":44,"end_time":189.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":189.3,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Looks good.","index":45,"end_time":198.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":197.55,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":46,"end_time":203.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":202.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then just the episode thumbnails.","index":47,"end_time":206.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":204.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So this is what would show like as a cover image.","index":48,"end_time":209.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":207.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, it looks nice.","index":49,"end_time":211.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":210.35,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":50,"end_time":215.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":214.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, well, that kind of guides also what the next piece of this is, is diving into color palette.","index":51,"end_time":221.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":215.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So this first one, this is exactly the current branding that you have, very rooted in blue, just different shades of blue.","index":52,"end_time":229.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":221.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Which kind of pass on a feeling of safe, secure, but not necessarily geared towards anything financial aspect, which is going to be more of the green colors.","index":53,"end_time":240.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":230.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So this is obviously one option if we just want to keep the existing branding of, of KTC as we build the brand of KTC Search.","index":54,"end_time":249.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":240.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Then there is Richie May''s color palette.","index":55,"end_time":253.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":251.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so I know we talked last week about eventually KTC rolling up into Richie May.","index":56,"end_time":259.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":253.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so this would be a way if we just wanted to adopt their brand colors.","index":57,"end_time":263.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":260.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It could be a seamless transition, you know, as you get absorbed into that environment of their website and everything else.","index":58,"end_time":270.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":263.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":59,"end_time":271.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":270.68,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"This third one is sort of a blend of the two.","index":60,"end_time":276.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":271.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So showing still like the strong blues, even a light blue as a nice accent color.","index":61,"end_time":282.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":277.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The green from the Richie May palette, then just having white and black in there as sort of tertiary colors, and then the last one a little bit darker play on that combined brand.","index":62,"end_time":293.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":282.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Before I dive in with any more explanation, is there any of these that are jumping out to you that you''re a big fan of or want to avoid?","index":63,"end_time":301.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":295.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, not really.","index":64,"end_time":303.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":302.57,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I mean, I guess what I would question would be for you is I like, just so we don''t reinvent the wheel and it, you know, knowing that eventually they''ll scrape me into there is.","index":65,"end_time":313.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":303.25,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I don''t know if I want to go necessarily all their colors, maybe a combination of both that you think that, you know, if we transition my site in there, that it wouldn''t totally mess up their color palette where, you know, we''re not reinventing my whole site just to import.","index":66,"end_time":327.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":313.93,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So, you know, probably this, this, that, you know, this one right here maybe, or the other one, that kind of comb.","index":67,"end_time":333.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":327.69,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"But I''d love to get your guys feedback and see what you think.","index":68,"end_time":335.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":333.33,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yeah, so personally, I really like this one.","index":69,"end_time":338.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":336.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think that their color palette, it''s very green, almost like booger or puke green, which again, green is.","index":70,"end_time":346.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":338.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Is associated with finance and, and security and things like that.","index":71,"end_time":349.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":346.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But I think lightening the brand up a little bit, where we bring like the fun, playful element of blues and like lighter grays that you have into what they are, I think that actually shows to me a better mesh of the companies rather than you just being sucked up into it.","index":72,"end_time":363.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":349.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Nope.","index":73,"end_time":363.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":363.07,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":74,"end_time":363.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":363.51,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":75,"end_time":364.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":363.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yep.","index":76,"end_time":364.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":364.11,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And then with that said, would you change the mark?","index":77,"end_time":366.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":364.67,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I''m assuming change the marks up too?","index":78,"end_time":368.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":366.67,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Well, actually, all of the colors are still.","index":79,"end_time":371.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":369.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So the colors that are represented in the mark are still included here as well.","index":80,"end_time":373.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":371.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we wouldn''t even need to change the mark.","index":81,"end_time":375.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":373.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":82,"end_time":376.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":375.55,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yeah, so that saves a headache of logo redesign as well.","index":83,"end_time":380.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":376.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And honestly, I''m a big fan of the mark and you can see we even incorporated it into the logo that we made here.","index":84,"end_time":387.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":381.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So even playing on it here.","index":85,"end_time":390.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":388.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":86,"end_time":391.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":390.36,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":87,"end_time":391.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":391.24,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":88,"end_time":394.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":394.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, so then we''ll roll with color palette three.","index":89,"end_time":396.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":394.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":90,"end_time":397.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":397.16,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"All right.","index":91,"end_time":399.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":399,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"As we were going through, I did notice some issues happening with the website.","index":92,"end_time":404.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":400.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Not sure why this is taking so long to load.","index":93,"end_time":406.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":404.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I just wanted to ask you if work is being done.","index":94,"end_time":409,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":406.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I noticed just some like, down here, it''s asking for an API connection that just opens up a broken page.","index":95,"end_time":419.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":411.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I''m not sure.","index":96,"end_time":420.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":419.56,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Nope.","index":97,"end_time":421.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":421.16,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I mean, yeah, the ask thing.","index":98,"end_time":422.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":421.52,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"But I mean, the sooner we probably move that, the better.","index":99,"end_time":425.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":422.92,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I mean, like I said, I''m not quite sure, so.","index":100,"end_time":427.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":425.88,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, yeah, I gotcha.","index":101,"end_time":429.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":427.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And it looks like the navigation isn''t working on the homepage either.","index":102,"end_time":431.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":429.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":103,"end_time":432.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":432.12,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"As you can see when we go to the 404, we have all the options here, but nothing loading.","index":104,"end_time":436.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":432.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, so is that just right now you''re live on there?","index":105,"end_time":440.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":437.45,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":106,"end_time":440.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":440.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":107,"end_time":441.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":441.21,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And last night even this button was like hidden behind this fold.","index":108,"end_time":445.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":442.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":109,"end_time":446.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":445.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, I''ll reach out.","index":110,"end_time":447.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":446.81,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So the navigations.","index":111,"end_time":448.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":447.85,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Reach out to navigations, networking.","index":112,"end_time":453.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":448.97,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Bottom of the site.","index":113,"end_time":456.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":455.29,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yeah, there''s like an API script right above the FAQ.","index":114,"end_time":460.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":456.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That looks like it''s broken.","index":115,"end_time":462.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":461.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":116,"end_time":465.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":464.82,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":117,"end_time":467.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":466.98,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Get to get to him.","index":118,"end_time":470.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":467.94,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"When do you guys.","index":119,"end_time":471.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":470.66,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"What''s your guys''s plan of action to kind of migrate this or stuff and we change the colors and all that.","index":120,"end_time":477.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":472.9,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I mean, is there, you know, at that same time kind of changing some of the content and some of that stuff too?","index":121,"end_time":481.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":477.78,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, we''re going to do it in kind of one fell swoop.","index":122,"end_time":484.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":481.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So.","index":123,"end_time":484.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":484.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And that''s what I have here.","index":124,"end_time":486.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":485.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So this is, this is your current sitemap.","index":125,"end_time":488.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":486.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"As you can see, it''s very flat.","index":126,"end_time":490.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":488.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"There''s.","index":127,"end_time":491.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":490.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"There''s a lot of different things to go to, but not a lot of like things guiding you on where you need to go.","index":128,"end_time":495.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":491.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The approach that we wanted to take is much more of like a funnel.","index":129,"end_time":499.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":496.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":130,"end_time":500.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":499.55,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So, you know, once you land on the homepage, you can go to services about us, resources, testimonials, all the things that people like, really want to see with the first couple seconds they land on a site and then breaking out.","index":131,"end_time":511.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":500.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know, the, the other services that we talked about, obviously PE back companies will be mentioned a little bit more than the others on the homepage because that''s where we''re seeing the most successful.","index":132,"end_time":519.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":511.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But I think that this speaks to, you know, what we''re going for of KTC Search.","index":133,"end_time":524.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":520.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":134,"end_time":524.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":524.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, it works for me.","index":135,"end_time":525.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":524.63,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":136,"end_time":526.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":525.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So then with that said and this approved, we''re going to start Taking the current page copy, doing some rewrites, sending that over to you for approval, getting the designs created in HubSpot, and then we''ll just be able to populate and switch some records, you know, and get this thing live.","index":137,"end_time":540.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":526.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":138,"end_time":541.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":540.75,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":139,"end_time":541.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":541.19,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Sounds like a plan to me.","index":140,"end_time":542.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":541.59,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"When do you think you guys would have all that done?","index":141,"end_time":544.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":542.59,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I mean, over the next few weeks we''ll be just writing the page copy and send that over to you and doing mock ups of the designs.","index":142,"end_time":553.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":545.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And if all that''s approved, then actually developing in a HubSpot is about a two week process.","index":143,"end_time":558.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":553.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So especially since we don''t have like you know, 300 pages on this site.","index":144,"end_time":563.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":558.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Those are, those are the ones that take a lot longer.","index":145,"end_time":565.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":563.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But as we''re writing this and getting approved, that''ll take about two weeks.","index":146,"end_time":568.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":565.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''re looking at probably a four to five week turnaround on this.","index":147,"end_time":571.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":568.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, that''s one.","index":148,"end_time":572.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":571.79,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Cool.","index":149,"end_time":573.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":572.91,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And then I just also had some competitor websites pulled up and wanted to just go through these with you to see if there''s anything that you''ve liked or hated about these sites.","index":150,"end_time":585.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":575.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And that could be elements they have on the site, things for people to engage with or even just they use this phrase and I never want to say that phrase ever.","index":151,"end_time":593.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":586.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m sure you''ve spent a lot of time across these websites so if anything jumps out to you, just please let us know.","index":152,"end_time":600.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":595.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay?","index":153,"end_time":601.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":600.63,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean most of the stuff, I mean I.","index":154,"end_time":603.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":601.51,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"You guys are doing the research, you know, I mean I''ve tried to do some research so I''m going to rely on you guys to say hey, based on you guys see what the best of the best are doing.","index":155,"end_time":611.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":604.28,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"The big boy.","index":156,"end_time":612.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":611.36,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So what, what can we do to make me look like I''m like a big boy even though I''m not?","index":157,"end_time":616.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":612.16,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So I''m gonna, I''m gonna push back on you guys from everything you''ve given me.","index":158,"end_time":619.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":616.4,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Clearly shows that you guys do your research.","index":159,"end_time":621.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":619.88,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So that''s what I need.","index":160,"end_time":622.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":621.88,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So we do a lot of research.","index":161,"end_time":624.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":623.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"HENCE like the 60 page documents that you''ve received on some of these things.","index":162,"end_time":629.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":625.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":163,"end_time":630.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":630.2,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"What I will say from.","index":164,"end_time":631.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":630.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And we''re going to do more research and we kind of never stop.","index":165,"end_time":634.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":631.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But what is, I find a lot of these.","index":166,"end_time":637.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":634.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Enterprise level are just boilerplate information.","index":167,"end_time":642.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":638.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They''re really not diving too deep into things.","index":168,"end_time":645.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":642.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Correct.","index":169,"end_time":645.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":645.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I think that''s the difference that we can pull out for ktc.","index":170,"end_time":649.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":646.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think we can have some of the like, you know, some of the look and feel, but just a better journey, you know, even as we''re scrolling through in Korn Ferry, obviously a massive company, you know, kind of one cta.","index":171,"end_time":660.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":649.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Up top, a bunch of text that''s centered, which from a psychology perspective, this is actually much harder to read than if they left oriented it because it''s so much, you know, cool.","index":172,"end_time":671.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":660.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like there''s some boxes here.","index":173,"end_time":672.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":671.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I don''t even know what they''re telling me or what I need to learn from them.","index":174,"end_time":675.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":672.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So it''s almost like a designer is like, I just want this to be really clean and I don''t really care what it says.","index":175,"end_time":680.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":676.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''re going to take a little bit of a different approach where it''s a clean, you know, clean layout, clean design, easy user journey.","index":176,"end_time":686.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":681.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But the content is going to bridge the gap from.","index":177,"end_time":689.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":687.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We can handle anything that this enterprise level company can.","index":178,"end_time":693.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":689.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But here''s our twist.","index":179,"end_time":694.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":693.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":180,"end_time":697.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":696.56,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Like it, like, it''s just insane.","index":181,"end_time":705.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":699.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Can you hear us?","index":182,"end_time":708.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":707.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, No, I can''t.","index":183,"end_time":708.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":708.04,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"There you go.","index":184,"end_time":709.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":708.84,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Sorry.","index":185,"end_time":709.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":709.2,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yep.","index":186,"end_time":710.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":709.56,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"No, no issue.","index":187,"end_time":710.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":710.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":188,"end_time":711.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":711.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Then here''s Spencer Stewart.","index":189,"end_time":712.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":711.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This one is a little bit better.","index":190,"end_time":714.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":713.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Kind of like almost like a pick your journey here.","index":191,"end_time":717.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":714.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Up top, like, who are you?","index":192,"end_time":719.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":717.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think that we can accomplish this in a hero section as well.","index":193,"end_time":723.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":719.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Probably a little bit cleaner.","index":194,"end_time":725.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":723.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":195,"end_time":727.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":727.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then go through that and then we''ll show like, you know, steps of, of the process of how people work with you.","index":196,"end_time":732.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":727.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":197,"end_time":733.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":732.46,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"But as you can see, even like some of these elements are just almost identical across some of these sites.","index":198,"end_time":737.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":733.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Exactly.","index":199,"end_time":738.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":737.66,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And we want to be.","index":200,"end_time":739.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":738.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We want to be different but also like still provide some familiarity to people as their browsing competitors.","index":201,"end_time":744.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":739.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":202,"end_time":745.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":745.04,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"This one is a little too interactive where it''s distracting.","index":203,"end_time":750.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":746.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":204,"end_time":750.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":750.32,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"You know, as, as you scroll through, like, okay, now my.","index":205,"end_time":753.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":750.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Now the circle is moving.","index":206,"end_time":754.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":753.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m just going to follow this.","index":207,"end_time":755.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":754.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m not even going to watch or look at any of the words.","index":208,"end_time":757.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":755.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Right.","index":209,"end_time":757.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":757.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":210,"end_time":761.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":761.52,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"They got a lot of stuff on theirs.","index":211,"end_time":763.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":761.84,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":212,"end_time":763.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":763.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then last was Russell Reynolds.","index":213,"end_time":767.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":765.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So again, almost the same exact hero section as Spencer Stewart.","index":214,"end_time":774.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":768.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Spencer Stewart, yeah.","index":215,"end_time":775.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":774.53,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Then just kind of a bunch of text here that doesn''t change until you hover.","index":216,"end_time":781.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":778.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Just more boxes.","index":217,"end_time":784.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":782.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yep.","index":218,"end_time":785.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":784.45,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Statistics that are like supposed to jump out at you, but the way that it''s structured, it''s actually a lot harder to read than it should be.","index":219,"end_time":792.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":786.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":220,"end_time":793.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":792.69,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So, yeah, these are the things that we''re looking at as we''re examining competitor websites.","index":221,"end_time":799.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":796.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":222,"end_time":800.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":800.07,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"That works for me.","index":223,"end_time":801.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":800.79,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":224,"end_time":802.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":801.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So overall what we''re seeing is a lot of these things are boilerplate, kind of boring, if I''m being honest.","index":225,"end_time":808.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":802.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Really not giving much information unless they actually engage look being they as in the.","index":226,"end_time":814.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":808.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The prospect, which in today''s day and age, because you are not a Korn fairy household name, we need to tell a little bit more upfront about what someone can expect when they engage with ktc.","index":227,"end_time":825.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":814.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Exactly.","index":228,"end_time":825.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":825.27,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yep.","index":229,"end_time":826.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":825.95,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I agree with that.","index":230,"end_time":827.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":826.39,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yep.","index":231,"end_time":827.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":827.19,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":232,"end_time":828.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":828.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That is actually all that I had because I did not.","index":233,"end_time":832.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":829.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I thought you would have many more questions around color palettes and video packages, so.","index":234,"end_time":836.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":832.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m pretty easy.","index":235,"end_time":837.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":836.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m rolling with the flow.","index":236,"end_time":839.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":837.9,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":237,"end_time":840.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":839.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, cool.","index":238,"end_time":841.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":840.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So then, next steps.","index":239,"end_time":842.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":841.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''re also developing your ABM plan so that we can get that moving.","index":240,"end_time":846.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":843.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''ll finalize everything for the content plan, the website plan, and then we''ll basically just get into writing and designing pages and then migrating all of it to HubSpot.","index":241,"end_time":855.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":847.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sounds like a plan.","index":242,"end_time":856.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":856.01,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Look forward to it.","index":243,"end_time":857.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":856.69,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":244,"end_time":858.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":857.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, well, thank you, Michael.","index":245,"end_time":858.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":858.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If you have any questions, please feel free to reach out at any time.","index":246,"end_time":861.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":858.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You bet you.","index":247,"end_time":862.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":861.45,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Talk to you guys soon.","index":248,"end_time":862.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":862.09,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Thanks.","index":249,"end_time":862.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":862.69,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"See you.","index":250,"end_time":863.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":862.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Bye.","index":251,"end_time":863.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":863.45,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Bye.","index":252,"end_time":864.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":863.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"}],"dateString":"2025-12-09T18:00:00.000Z","host_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/83519004309?pwd=JvKSZR6BzSlyNxK5WTgZHYayMsLSKi.1&jst=2","participants":["colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com,guille.santana@marketersindemand.com,tristan.pelligrino@marketersindemand.com,michael@kerstentalentcapital.com","guille.santana@marketersindemand.com","tristan.pelligrino@marketersindemand.com","michael@kerstentalentcapital.com"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01KBXFHVGWMM65E0VD3B1MPH9Q","organizer_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"positive","confidence":0.92,"bullets":["Aligned on cover art and branding for Executive Advantage series; option four was selected.","Chose blended color palette to ease future integration with Richie May while retaining identity.","Identified website navigation and API issues; Michael to follow up with developer support.","Agreed on new sitemap with guided user journey and service focus; content rewrite underway.","Estimated web migration and content production timeline as 4–5 weeks including HubSpot build."],"highlights":[{"quote":"Clearly shows that you guys do your research.","speaker":"Michael Kersten"},{"quote":"We''re going to do it in kind of one fell swoop.","speaker":"Colin Costigan"},{"quote":"Sounds like a plan to me.","speaker":"Michael Kersten"}],"topics":["branding","website","integration","timeline"],"model":"openai/gpt-4-1106-preview","version":1,"generated_at":"2025-12-09T21:06:00Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **Video Package and Branding**\n\nThe team finalized the **Executive Advantage series video package** and selected a cohesive brand look that balances existing and future company identities (02:15).\n\n- **Michael Kersten and Colin Costigan agreed** on cover art option **four** for the video series, establishing a unified visual identity early in the campaign.\n    - The package includes consistent branding elements like captions and quote cards to maintain visual coherence across all video assets.\n    - Colin emphasized the importance of a cohesive look to support engagement and brand recognition.\n    - This video package is positioned to enhance audience connection and content professionalism.\n\n- For color palettes, they chose a **hybrid palette** blending KTC’s blues with Richie May’s greens, avoiding a full transition to Richie May’s colors (05:02).\n    - Colin noted the green tones signal finance and security, while blue adds a friendly, lighter feel suited to KTC Search’s identity.\n    - Michael preferred this approach to ease future integration without a disruptive overhaul.\n    - Retaining the existing logo mark avoids costly redesign and preserves brand equity.\n    - This decision balances brand continuity with a strategic nod to upcoming corporate alignment.\n\n## **Website Sitemap and Content Strategy**\n\nA more structured, funnel-based sitemap will replace the current flat layout to improve site navigation and user experience (08:01).\n\n- Colin presented a sitemap focusing on clear visitor paths leading from the homepage to key areas like services, resources, and testimonials.\n    - The homepage will emphasize **PE-backed companies**, reflecting their current strongest market segment.\n    - Michael approved this directional change, recognizing it will guide visitors more effectively.\n    - The new sitemap supports better user engagement and lead generation by simplifying choices and highlighting priorities.\n    - This redesign aligns with the goal of positioning KTC as a specialized and trustworthy partner.\n\n- Content rewrites for existing pages will be developed and sent to Michael for approval over the next few weeks, aiming for a **4-5 week total rollout** including HubSpot development (09:00).\n    - The HubSpot build phase is estimated at around **two weeks**, due to the modest site size.\n    - This timeline balances quality content creation with efficient deployment.\n    - The rewrite process will improve messaging clarity and align with the new user journey.\n    - Deliverables and approvals are clearly assigned to maintain momentum.\n\n## **Website Technical Issues and Migration**\n\nThe current website experiences performance problems, including slow loading, broken API scripts, and navigation failures, which require immediate fixes before migration (06:39).\n\n- Colin highlighted broken API calls and non-functioning homepage navigation affecting user experience and site reliability.\n    - Michael committed to reaching out to the technical team responsible for navigation and API fixes.\n    - These technical issues risk damaging visitor trust and must be resolved before launching the redesigned site.\n    - Coordination between content migration and technical fixes is critical to avoid delays.\n    - Addressing these problems early supports a smooth transition to the new HubSpot platform.\n\n- Migration will occur in one consolidated effort, combining content updates, design changes, and color palette adjustments (07:44).\n    - This approach reduces downtime and maintains brand consistency.\n    - It ensures all new assets and functional improvements launch simultaneously.\n    - The plan reflects a strategic choice to minimize disruptions and maximize impact.\n    - Michael and Colin agree this is the most efficient path forward.\n\n## **Competitive Website Analysis and Differentiation Strategy**\n\nThe team analyzed competitor sites to extract learnings and avoid common pitfalls, aiming to differentiate KTC with clearer messaging and user-friendly design (10:00).\n\n- Colin noted many competitors rely on generic, boilerplate content that lacks depth and engagement, which KTC will avoid (10:30).\n    - KTC’s content will be more detailed upfront, helping prospects understand value without extra digging.\n    - Michael emphasized wanting KTC to \"look like a big boy\" despite being smaller, relying on the team’s research and expertise.\n    - This approach targets improving trust and credibility through transparency and clarity.\n    - The strategy prioritizes user education and differentiation over flashy but shallow designs.\n\n- Specific competitor sites showed overused design elements that either confuse or distract users, such as excessive interactivity or hard-to-read text (12:12).\n    - Colin proposed a clean layout with intuitive user journeys and clear calls to action.\n    - The goal is to combine familiarity with distinctiveness to stand out while meeting user expectations.\n    - This design philosophy supports better engagement and conversion.\n    - The team will continue researching to refine these insights and incorporate best practices.\n\n## **Next Steps and Strategic Alignment**\n\nThe team will finalize the ABM plan alongside website and content efforts to drive coordinated marketing execution (14:00).\n\n- Colin confirmed that once content and sitemap plans are approved, writing and design will proceed with migration to HubSpot.\n    - Michael expressed confidence and readiness to move forward.\n    - This integrated approach ensures messaging, branding, and lead generation activities align.\n    - Delivering these elements together strengthens the overall market positioning.\n    - Ongoing communication and feedback loops will keep the project on track.","outline":null,"keywords":["branding","color palette","website sitemap","video package","competitor analysis","ABM plan"],"overview":"- **Video Package Finalized:** Executive Advantage video series selected cover art for cohesive branding, enhancing audience engagement and professionalism.  \n- **Hybrid Color Palette Chosen:** Blending KTC blues and Richie May greens maintains brand identity while signaling finance and security.  \n- **New Sitemap Structure Approved:** Funnel-based layout will improve user navigation, emphasizing PE-backed companies to enhance engagement and lead generation.  \n- **Website Technical Issues Identified:** Performance problems require immediate resolution before migration to ensure a smooth transition to HubSpot platform.  \n- **Competitor Analysis Highlights Differentiation:** KTC will use detailed content and user-friendly design, avoiding generic messaging found in competitor sites.  \n- **Next Steps Confirmed:** Team to finalize ABM plan post-approval to align content, branding, and lead generation efforts effectively.","action_items":"\n**Colin Costigan**\nFinalize color palette choice with KTC Search and incorporate into branding materials (06:34)\nComplete rewriting the webpage copy and send drafts to Michael for approval (08:45)\nCreate and share design mockups of the website in HubSpot for approval (08:45)\nDevelop the new website in HubSpot post-approval and manage migration, aiming for a 4-5 week turnaround (08:45)\nContinue research and refinement of competitor analysis to inform design and content strategy (10:30)\nFinalize ABM plan development and integrate it with the overall marketing strategy (13:48)\n\n**Michael Kersten**\nInvestigate and coordinate fixing website technical issues including API errors and homepage navigation problems with IT or relevant web team (07:26)\nReview and approve website copy and designs within timeframes provided (08:45)\nProvide feedback on competitor insights and branding decisions as required (14:21)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"eac3d607-1ac2-460d-8fc4-9119d32b12ef","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
