    '{"id":"01KBDE91Q2PHZZ3ET45QD4YHTR","title":"Ponce Bank & MiD: Weekly Sync","summary":{"notes":"## **Compliance and Risk Management**\n\nThe SOC 2 compliance rerating process is delayed until a key IT meeting this Thursday, pushing the original deadline past Christina’s expected closure date (04:06).\n\n- **Pending SOC 2 review scheduled for Thursday** by RT, head of IT, after all related documents were sent (04:06)  \n    - Victor noted difficulty securing direct answers before the meeting, indicating limited immediate progress  \n    - The delay pushes the compliance closure beyond Christina’s target date, now expected after her return  \n    - Information has been escalated to senior management, including Christina’s manager Betty, to maintain visibility  \n    - This delay risks impacting related project timelines dependent on compliance confirmation  \n\n- **Compliance feedback is awaited on marketing materials, especially the 207 postcard redesign** which will include extensive compliance copy on the back (08:11)  \n    - Colin shared that the postcard’s front will require redesign once compliance text is finalized  \n    - Victor will coordinate with Jane and compliance teams to expedite review and feedback (08:38)  \n    - Compliance review of product sheets and handouts is also in progress to ensure messaging alignment  \n    - Timely compliance approval is critical to keep marketing launch targets this month  \n\n## **Marketing Collateral and Communications**\n\nMarketing materials are being redesigned to clarify target audiences and meet compliance needs, aiming for approval and print readiness this week (05:35).\n\n- **New product sheet layout to clearly define key features, benefits, and target users, driven by Christina’s direction** aims to finalize content before design completion (05:35)  \n    - Colin will send draft designs to Victor for compliance and retail head review before print approval (06:30)  \n    - Victor will manage compliance and retail feedback loops to ensure content accuracy and policy adherence (07:04)  \n    - The goal is to complete content review and finalize collateral within the current week for a timely rollout (07:40)  \n    - This structured approach reduces risk of rework and aligns messaging with compliance and sales needs  \n\n- **Direct mail list targeting is being optimized to balance reach and budget constraints for the 207 postcard campaign** (08:41)  \n    - Original list size was **12,000** contacts within a half-mile radius; efforts reduced it to **4,000–5,000** to meet budget (08:41)  \n    - Colin explained that more granular geographic targeting via postal routes is possible but cost-prohibitive and lacks recipient data (09:32)  \n    - A phased postcard approach (part one and two) is considered to manage content volume and compliance requirements (08:41)  \n    - Final quote for mailing list is pending and will determine purchase timing and campaign launch  \n\n## **Digital and Social Media Integration**\n\nSocial media account access remains incomplete, delaying full HubSpot integration planned for this week (10:18).\n\n- **Current digital assets connected to HubSpot include Google My Business, HubSpot analytics, Canva analytics, and Tag Manager, but key social accounts remain disconnected** (10:18)  \n    - Facebook and LinkedIn access are still pending; Twitter is inactive and excluded from integration plans (10:39)  \n    - Victor will confirm and expedite social account access with Jane to meet the HubSpot connection timeline (10:46)  \n    - Full integration is essential to unify marketing data and streamline campaign tracking across platforms  \n    - The lack of Twitter activity reduces complexity but may represent a missed engagement opportunity noted by Victor (12:44)  \n\n## **CRM and Website Configuration**\n\nHubSpot and website configuration documentation is complete and under internal review before final approval to proceed (11:08).\n\n- **HubSpot configuration and website plan documents were shared and are awaiting approval from Betty or Jane before final sign-off** (11:17)  \n    - Colin’s team is working on mapping Salesforce fields to HubSpot properties now that spreadsheet access is granted (11:48)  \n    - Victor will coordinate with Jane to avoid overlap and ensure comprehensive review before approval (11:53)  \n    - Final approval will trigger the full rollout and integration, described as “guns blazing” by Colin (12:29)  \n    - This cautious review approach aims to prevent errors and aligns with compliance and operational readiness  \n\n## **Project Coordination and Timeline Management**\n\nMultiple dependencies require close coordination to meet Christina’s goal of completing key projects this month (07:40).\n\n- **Victor will align with Jane to confirm review status, compliance feedback, and social access to maintain project momentum** (07:57)  \n    - Clear communication channels are established for timely updates and resolution of outstanding items  \n    - This coordination includes marketing materials, compliance reviews, social media access, and CRM configuration  \n    - The team acknowledges limited work remains internally and will await external feedback to proceed (13:09)  \n    - Maintaining this schedule is critical given Christina’s departure and the need to finalize before her absence  \n\n- **The team is focused on minimizing delays despite the SOC 2 compliance hold and reliance on external approvals** (04:45)  \n    - Escalation to senior management ensures visibility but does not accelerate the IT review timeline  \n    - Contingency planning appears limited but the team is prepared to resume quickly once approvals arrive  \n    - The prioritization of rapid feedback on collateral and digital integrations reflects a push to maximize progress in parallel  \n    - This approach balances compliance risk with the desire to meet aggressive marketing deadlines this month","outline":null,"keywords":["SOC 2 compliance","HubSpot configuration","product sheet design","marketing materials","mailing list","social media access"],"overview":"- **SOC 2 Compliance Delay:** Compliance rerating process is postponed until key IT meeting, impacting project timelines and Christina’s target closure date.\n\n- **Marketing Materials Review:** Compliance feedback on marketing items, including the 207 postcard, is urgently needed for timely launch.\n\n- **Target Audience Redesign:** New product sheets aim to clarify features and benefits, with content finalized this week for printing.\n\n- **Social Media Integration Issues:** Social media accounts are still disconnected from HubSpot, delaying full data integration and campaign tracking.\n\n- **HubSpot Configuration Approval:** Documentation is awaiting final sign-off to move forward with rollout and integration efforts.\n\n- **Project Coordination Focus:** Team emphasizes communication and timely updates to meet deadlines amid compliance-related dependencies.","action_items":"\n**Victor Garcia**\nTake notes on meeting discussions and relay non-HubSpot questions (03:49)\nFollow up with Jane on the SOC 2 compliance review progress and Thursday meeting outcomes (04:06)\nReview the product sheet design document sent by Colin and share with compliance and head of retail teams for approval (07:04)\nCoordinate with Jane on compliance feedback, the 207 postcard text, social media account access (Meta and LinkedIn), and mailing list parameters (08:38)\nEnsure no crossover in HubSpot and website configuration reviews, then approve or delay as needed in coordination with Betty or Jane (11:53)\nEmail team updates and next steps after internal reviews (13:00)\n\n**Colin Costigan**\nSend product sheet layout document for team review, including key features, benefits, and intended audiences (05:27)\nShare updates and await approval on marketing materials, including the TIS handout and redesigned postcards (08:38)\nMonitor mailing list quote and collaborate with Victor on procurement once received (08:38)\nConfirm integration of social media accounts in HubSpot once access is granted (10:39)\nCollaborate on generating Salesforce-to-HubSpot field mapping document (11:17)\n\n**Jane Trachet**\nProvide compliance feedback and additional paragraphs of text for marketing materials (08:38)\nAssist in social media account access facilitation (10:18)\nReview and approve HubSpot and website configuration documentation (11:53)\n"},"duration":13.4399995803833,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"victor garcia"},{"id":1,"name":"Tristan"},{"id":2,"name":"Colin Costigan"},{"id":3,"name":"Colin Costigan"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Sa.","index":0,"end_time":0.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":0.24,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Welcome back.","index":1,"end_time":185.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":184.63,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Welcome back.","index":2,"end_time":185.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":185.15,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"How''s it going?","index":3,"end_time":187.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":186.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Good.","index":4,"end_time":187.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":187.51,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"How are you doing?","index":5,"end_time":189.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":187.87,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"All right.","index":6,"end_time":189.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":189.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Did you have a good weekend questions?","index":7,"end_time":194.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":190.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yes, I definitely did.","index":8,"end_time":195.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":194.03,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"Working on a passion project right now, so kind of like in the.","index":9,"end_time":200.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":196.39,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"In the end phase of it, but just trying to push towards it.","index":10,"end_time":204.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":200.11,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Nice.","index":11,"end_time":205.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":205.37,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"Do some clarity on some questions.","index":12,"end_time":210.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":208.33,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"Good morning.","index":13,"end_time":218.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":218.17,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"Good morning.","index":14,"end_time":219.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":219.13,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"Good morning.","index":15,"end_time":220.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":219.73,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Good morning.","index":16,"end_time":222.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":221.61,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"Victor, I know Christina is out.","index":17,"end_time":226.81,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":225.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Do you know if Jane is planning on joining?","index":18,"end_time":228.49,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":226.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"She might be a little late because she does have a doctor''s appointment, so we don''t have to hold up on that, but I''ll take notes.","index":19,"end_time":234.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":229.05,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"For anything outside of HubSpot.","index":20,"end_time":237.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":236.07,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Sounds good.","index":21,"end_time":238.47,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":237.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The thing that I wanted to get started with just so we have enough time to get through the conversation is around this SOC 2 compliance and our rerating.","index":22,"end_time":245.91,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":239.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I literally was just sending an email out to rt, the head of IT right now.","index":23,"end_time":252.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":246.47,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"So we pushed all of that information that you got that Tristan asked in the email to them, and now they have a meeting on Thursday, unfortunately, to review everything from you guys to HubSpot.","index":24,"end_time":268.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":253.27,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"So right now it''s just a waiting game.","index":25,"end_time":270.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":269.2,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"I try to get them on the phone to join this meeting so we can get those questions answered, but she''s tied up.","index":26,"end_time":277.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":270.96,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"It''s like pulling teeth.","index":27,"end_time":279.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":278.08,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":28,"end_time":280.88,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":280.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":29,"end_time":281.12,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":280.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Cause I know Christina''s deadline was to have this, I think, handled by tomorrow.","index":30,"end_time":285.28,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":281.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I know that that''s.","index":31,"end_time":287.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":285.84,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"She already knows that this is going to probably push out until when she comes back, but.","index":32,"end_time":291.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":287.36,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Or until this Thursday meeting, unfortunately.","index":33,"end_time":293.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":291.37,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"So, yeah, there''s nothing more that we can do.","index":34,"end_time":297.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":293.77,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Besides, we already pushed it to superiors.","index":35,"end_time":300.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":297.77,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"We already pushed it to our.","index":36,"end_time":302.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":300.21,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Christina''s manager, Betty.","index":37,"end_time":306.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":304.17,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"So, yeah, there''s not.","index":38,"end_time":307.489,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":306.57,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"There''s nothing else that we can do at this point.","index":39,"end_time":308.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":307.489,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Okay.","index":40,"end_time":310.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":309.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, I hear you there.","index":41,"end_time":311.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":310.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":42,"end_time":311.93,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":311.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Just shoot us an email with anything else or any answers or anything that we can provide.","index":43,"end_time":315.37,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":311.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No problem.","index":44,"end_time":316.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":315.69,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":45,"end_time":317.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":317.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, then I''ll share my screen.","index":46,"end_time":320.5,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":318.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"A very hefty two decks you guys sent over.","index":47,"end_time":326.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":323.62,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":48,"end_time":328.5,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":327.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We like to be pretty comprehensive with our documentation, so we always have something source of truth to go back to.","index":49,"end_time":334.02,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":328.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Love it.","index":50,"end_time":334.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":334.34,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"We were sent over this product sheet, and so we''re making a few designs based off of it.","index":51,"end_time":340.66,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":335.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Christina''s request was to, like, have it broken down, basically by who it''s for, which wasn''t clear across the board in.","index":52,"end_time":348.58,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":341.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Inside the document that we received.","index":53,"end_time":350.09,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":348.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I''m going to send you guys over a document of how we''re going to lay out the information, and I''ll do a sneak preview here as well.","index":54,"end_time":356.65,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":350.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But really just breaking it down into the key features, the benefits, and who this is best for.","index":55,"end_time":363.73,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":357.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And this is how we''ll plan out the.","index":56,"end_time":365.53,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":363.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Triple brochure and the back front laminated design for someone''s desk.","index":57,"end_time":374.81,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":367.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":58,"end_time":375.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":375.61,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"Oh, that''s great.","index":59,"end_time":377.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":375.85,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"I had that idea years ago, so I''m glad that you guys are pushing that.","index":60,"end_time":382.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":377.85,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, I think it''ll be good.","index":61,"end_time":384.01,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":382.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Just always want to make sure that we''re buttoned up on content before we, you know, fully fledge out the entire design.","index":62,"end_time":390.41,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":384.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":63,"end_time":392.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":390.97,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Unless she gave you more direction, I think that that''s perfect.","index":64,"end_time":395.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":392.81,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Okay.","index":65,"end_time":396.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":395.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, sounds good.","index":66,"end_time":397.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":396.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I assume, actually, I don''t know if we''re not selling it to customer directly, I don''t know if we''ll need to go through compliance for anything, but maybe checking with the product teams if there''s anything else they want listed or maybe some of the tellers as well to review the design before we actually go to print.","index":67,"end_time":411.65,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":397.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":68,"end_time":412.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":411.89,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"So what we''re going to do with that, then, once you give me.","index":69,"end_time":415.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":412.29,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Well, are you forwarding me anything outside of what you''re showing me right now?","index":70,"end_time":420.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":415.73,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"I''m going to send this over to you just to review and make sure it''s buttoned up.","index":71,"end_time":423.57,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":420.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''ll send that over to our compliance team as well as our head of retail so that they can look that over.","index":72,"end_time":431.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":424.69,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Once we get the green light from them, then I''ll give you guys the green light and we''ll go from there.","index":73,"end_time":436.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":431.71,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"All right, perfect.","index":74,"end_time":437.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":436.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So let me.","index":75,"end_time":438.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":438.11,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Let me make a note of that.","index":76,"end_time":439.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":438.83,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Give me one second.","index":77,"end_time":440.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":439.75,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"Yeah, no problem.","index":78,"end_time":441.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":440.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Product.","index":79,"end_time":444.11,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":443.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Product.","index":80,"end_time":446.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":446.19,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"To the net for review and compliance.","index":81,"end_time":453.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":448.19,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"When do you guys.","index":82,"end_time":454.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":453.95,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"When were you guys trying to have this finalized by.","index":83,"end_time":457.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":454.91,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Just so that I have.","index":84,"end_time":458.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":457.35,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"We can try to stick with timelines.","index":85,"end_time":460.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":458.42,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"I mean, we''re.","index":86,"end_time":461.22,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":460.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''re basically under the instruction to move as quickly as possible.","index":87,"end_time":463.86,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":461.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This was one of Christina''s projects she wants wrapped up this month, and I want to just have time for back and forth of content design feedback.","index":88,"end_time":471.14,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":464.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, I mean, this week would be great if we can get a response.","index":89,"end_time":477.06,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":474.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":90,"end_time":478.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":477.46,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"All right, so then that''s something that I''ll have a conversation with Jane about, because I''m not sure if she''s had those conversations with her yet.","index":91,"end_time":488.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":483.22,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"So I''ll.","index":92,"end_time":489.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":488.5,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"I''ll regroup with her and figure that part out.","index":93,"end_time":491.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":489.22,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":94,"end_time":491.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":491.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, sounds good.","index":95,"end_time":492.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":491.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then we''re still just awaiting any additional feedback or the paragraphs of text that Jane and Christina alluded to from compliance.","index":96,"end_time":502.8,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":494.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It seems like we''re going to have to do a pretty comprehensive update to the design because it Sounds like the back of the postcard is just going to be paragraphs of compliance copy.","index":97,"end_time":511.92,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":502.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''ll have to redesign the fro