-- Meeting: Verisk // New North Weekly Meeting (2025-12-05 17:30:00+00)
WITH new_meeting AS (
  INSERT INTO compass_meetings (contract_id, meeting_date, source, external_id, title, participants, duration_seconds, recording_url, transcript, sentiment, raw_metadata, created_at, updated_at)
  VALUES (
    'bf57e936-b322-4b36-bf32-174d44c65e09',
    '2025-12-05 17:30:00+00',
    'fireflies',
    '01KBD4A086GVYP1ETY1FEE33M6',
    'Verisk // New North Weekly Meeting',
    '{"Baylee Gunnell","Tim Finnigan","Gab","Christina Bila","Igor Zagradjanin"}'::text[],
    1223,
    'https://us02web.zoom.us/j/84384090979?pwd=CWYLaJlFxbjtxp2qyx0nk6skchlVVg.1',
    '{"id":"01KBD4A086GVYP1ETY1FEE33M6","title":"Verisk // New North Weekly Meeting","summary":{"notes":"## **Podcast Production and Quality Control**\n\nThe team agreed to improve podcast editing quality to avoid embarrassing mistakes and streamline approval.\n\n- **Tim Finnigan emphasized the need for thorough pre-approval edits to prevent obvious errors in podcasts** like chopped intros, suggesting the team handle full edits before sharing with Callie for a final review** (04:21)  \n    - This approach ensures Callie''s feedback acts as a rubber stamp, reducing rework and reputational risk  \n    - Baylee Gunnell confirmed a more thorough quality check will be implemented following a record week of submissions  \n    - The team plans to move forward with the current episode to meet the live date next Thursday despite imperfect edits  \n    - Igor Zagradjanin committed to uploading Spotify videos and YouTube clips for all episodes going forward to boost reach  \n\n- **Tim and Baylee aligned on repurposing 14 ebook-related podcast clips into a 20-minute episode with a new intro and outro to promote the ebook before the holidays** (07:32)  \n    - Tim will record all podcast intros and outros on Tuesday between 9am and 12pm to consolidate efforts  \n    - Baylee’s team will splice clips and have the episode ready for live release targeted for December 18th, allowing a week turnaround  \n    - Gab highlighted the social media promotion role, reinforcing a coordinated campaign around the ebook launch  \n    - The timeline was agreed to balance quality with holiday season scheduling constraints  \n\n## **TMR Ebook Campaign and Ad Execution**\n\nThe ebook campaign is nearing launch with creative assets ready and ad setup planned for next week to ensure timely promotion.\n\n- **Igor Zagradjanin reported guest creatives, LinkedIn carousels, and video compilations are completed, with approved copy and designs awaiting final feedback to start revisions Monday** (12:53)  \n    - Gab committed to providing feedback by end of day to avoid delays  \n    - Baylee proposed a setup meeting Monday or Thursday to finalize ad platforms and workflows, with flexibility based on team availability  \n    - Christina Bila agreed to lead the Thursday 10am Eastern session, with Gab recording the meeting for later reference due to a scheduling conflict  \n    - The team aims to have all ad platforms logged in by end of year to enable deeper 2026 analytics and optimizations  \n\n## **Marketing Team Collaboration and Planning**\n\nThe marketing team is preparing for an in-person meeting in Chicago next week to boost team cohesion and align priorities.\n\n- **Gab shared that the marketing team of seven, including OPS, product, design, and inbound leads, will meet in Chicago for a mix of work and social activities to strengthen collaboration** (00:34)  \n    - Activities include attending a Blackhawks game and team dinners to foster relationships after nearly two years apart  \n    - This event supports productive planning and team morale, laying groundwork for upcoming campaigns and projects  \n    - Baylee acknowledged the team''s high output despite its small size, reinforcing the value of tight coordination  \n\n## **Content Repurposing and Creative Strategy**\n\nPlans were discussed to create a year-end recap highlighting top blog posts, using creative formats to boost engagement with minimal effort.\n\n- **Gab proposed making a recap of the top-performing blog posts using LinkedIn carousels and potentially a conversational video with Tim to showcase insights** (16:39)  \n    - Baylee supported the idea, suggesting a carousel and a YouTube video where Gab and Tim discuss why these blogs succeeded  \n    - Timing is flexible, with Gab aiming to launch the carousel before the holidays and the video possibly debuting in early 2026 at a Vegas meeting  \n    - Tim agreed that a January launch is acceptable if needed to ensure quality and impact  \n    - Gab will submit a project brief through the client portal to formalize the request and scope  \n\n## **Operational Improvements and Platform Access**\n\nThe team is focused on streamlining platform access and operational workflows to support faster campaign launches.\n\n- **Gab is proactively working on obtaining Apple ID access for all platforms before year-end, following a smooth Spotify login process, to enable deeper 2026 insights** (11:24)  \n    - Igor acknowledged this progress will speed up setup and campaign execution  \n    - Baylee offered flexible meeting options to review ad setup processes with Christina and Gab, ensuring future self-sufficiency  \n    - Christina will lead a training session on Thursday at 10am Eastern to understand platform setup and management, with Gab recording the session due to travel  \n    - This operational focus reduces bottlenecks and increases team independence for ongoing marketing execution","outline":null,"keywords":["Podcast editing","TMR ebook","marketing team meeting","ad campaign","creative content recap","platform access"],"overview":"- **Podcast Quality Improvement:** Team agreed on thorough pre-approval edits to prevent errors and reduce reputational risk.  \n- **Ebook Promotion Strategy:** 14 podcast clips will be repurposed into a 20-minute episode, targeted for release on December 18th.  \n- **Ad Campaign Readiness:** Ebook campaign assets are ready, with final feedback scheduled for Monday and ad platforms targeted for end of year.  \n- **Chicago Team Meeting:** Marketing team will meet in Chicago for collaboration and planning activities, enhancing team morale and project alignment.  \n- **Content Recap Initiative:** Plans to create a year-end recap of top blog posts using LinkedIn carousels and a video discussion.  \n- **Operational Streamlining:** Proactive efforts to obtain platform access will enhance setup speed and independence in campaign execution.","action_items":"\n**Baylee Gunnell**\nTroubleshoot Igor’s paid media admin login after the meeting (02:35)\nConduct more thorough QC on future podcast episodes before sending to Kelly Chapman (05:45)\nReview length of TMR ebook clips for podcast, target 1 minute per clip (08:26)\nAssemble and splice podcast clips with Tim’s recorded intro/outro by December 18th, assuming receipt of recordings by Tuesday (11:03)\nParticipate in ad setup walkthrough meeting on Thursday, 10:00 AM Eastern (14:43)\nSupport Gab with creative concepting for top blog posts recap and review project brief once received (19:30)\n\n**Tim Finnigan**\nProvide intro/outro recording for TMR ebook mini-podcast by Tuesday morning (09:45)\nMove forward with edits on podcast episode based on own and Gab’s feedback without waiting on Kelly’s comments (05:55)\nTarget podcast episode launch December 18th, flexible up to December 22nd (10:10)\nFollow up with Baylee for additional questions after Gab leaves (20:00)\n\n**Gab**\nProvide feedback on ad campaign designs today to accelerate Monday revisions (12:52)\nWork on Apple ID platform login before end of year for easier access in 2026 (11:30)\nCoordinate social promotion efforts for new TMR ebook podcast episode (09:15)\nSubmit project brief for top performing blog posts recap project via portal (19:20)\n\n**Christina Bila**\nAttend ad campaign setup walkthrough on Thursday, 10:00 AM Eastern, represent Gab if absent (15:25)\n\n**Igor Zagradjanin**\nSend ad campaign designs over Slack after meeting (12:45)\nManage edits for podcast episode and continue client portal design progress (16:05)\n"},"duration":20.3799991607666,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"id":1,"name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"id":2,"name":"Gab"},{"id":3,"name":"Christina Bila"},{"id":4,"name":"Igor Zagradjanin"}],"sentences":[{"text":"How''s everyone''s week been going?","index":0,"end_time":1.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":0.16,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"The worst.","index":1,"end_time":4.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3.84,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"The worst.","index":2,"end_time":5.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":5.12,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Let me tell you about it.","index":3,"end_time":7.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":6.32,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"Is this going to be our therapy session?","index":4,"end_time":10.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":9.04,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"No, it''s been great.","index":5,"end_time":18.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":17.6,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"You sure nap?","index":6,"end_time":21.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":20.08,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"It is Friday.","index":7,"end_time":25.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":24.24,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Hopefully you all can get some.","index":8,"end_time":28.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":25.89,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Some rest this weekend.","index":9,"end_time":30.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":28.61,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"That would be great.","index":10,"end_time":32.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":31.49,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Yeah, we''re actually.","index":11,"end_time":33.97,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":32.69,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"We''re meeting in person next week in Chicago.","index":12,"end_time":37.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":34.61,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"No way.","index":13,"end_time":38.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":37.65,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yep.","index":14,"end_time":39.49,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":38.93,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"First time and I don''t even know, Tim, when''s the last time I saw you.","index":15,"end_time":44.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":39.49,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Exactly?","index":16,"end_time":49.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":48.61,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"I don''t know.","index":17,"end_time":52.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":51.33,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"I don''t know.","index":18,"end_time":53.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":52.88,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"Yeah, so this will be good.","index":19,"end_time":54.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":53.36,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"I thought they said two years ago or something.","index":20,"end_time":57.84,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":55.52,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"That''s sounds right.","index":21,"end_time":60.08,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":57.92,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":22,"end_time":61.12,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":60.72,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":23,"end_time":61.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":61.12,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"We''re gonna go to a Blackhawks game.","index":24,"end_time":63.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":61.52,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"We''re gonna get Lou Malnati''s, like, wow, I''m ready.","index":25,"end_time":69.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":63.6,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"What''s.","index":26,"end_time":70.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":70,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"What''s the event for?","index":27,"end_time":71.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":70.72,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Just like a company get together or something.","index":28,"end_time":74.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":71.76,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Marketing.","index":29,"end_time":75.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":75.04,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Get together.","index":30,"end_time":76.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":75.6,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Marketing.","index":31,"end_time":76.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":76.24,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":32,"end_time":80.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":79.8,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So it''ll be productive.","index":33,"end_time":81.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":80.36,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"It''ll be fun.","index":34,"end_time":82.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":81.56,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"And.","index":35,"end_time":83.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":83.24,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":36,"end_time":85.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":84.84,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Who else is on the marketing team?","index":37,"end_time":87.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":85.8,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So it''s these three.","index":38,"end_time":90.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":89.16,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Right.","index":39,"end_time":91.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":90.92,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"And then Sean, our OPS guy.","index":40,"end_time":93.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":91.4,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Jill, who does more product stuff.","index":41,"end_time":96.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":94.68,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Don, our designer.","index":42,"end_time":98.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":97.88,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"You know Don.","index":43,"end_time":99.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":98.92,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":44,"end_time":100.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":99.64,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And Shannon, who is our inbound lead gal.","index":45,"end_time":105.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":101.56,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Good team.","index":46,"end_time":107.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":107.09,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":47,"end_time":108.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":108.13,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Should.","index":48,"end_time":111.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":110.85,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Should be a good time.","index":49,"end_time":112.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":111.25,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"That''s awesome.","index":50,"end_time":113.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":112.29,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Small but mighty.","index":51,"end_time":114.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":113.65,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Yep.","index":52,"end_time":115.01,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":114.61,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"Yes.","index":53,"end_time":115.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":115.01,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"You guys, you do a lot between.","index":54,"end_time":118.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":115.65,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Between all of you, a lot.","index":55,"end_time":120.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":118.85,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Done.","index":56,"end_time":120.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":120.45,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We do.","index":57,"end_time":121.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":121.25,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":58,"end_time":122.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":121.97,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Well, I know we''ve got some great stuff going on on our end, so I''ll just kick it over to Igor to.","index":59,"end_time":130.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":125.09,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"To share the slides.","index":60,"end_time":132.119,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":131.079,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":61,"end_time":133.599,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":133.159,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Hi, guys.","index":62,"end_time":134.279,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":133.599,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"What''s up?","index":63,"end_time":134.879,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":134.359,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"How you are?","index":64,"end_time":135.639,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":134.879,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"Hi.","index":65,"end_time":136.279,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":135.799,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"How you doing?","index":66,"end_time":137.479,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":136.679,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Doing great.","index":67,"end_time":139.079,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":138.359,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"How about you?","index":68,"end_time":140.039,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":139.239,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Good, good, good.","index":69,"end_time":141.639,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":140.759,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"I was able to add you as a paid media admin to our page.","index":70,"end_time":146.359,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":142.439,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Just saying.","index":71,"end_time":147.158,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":146.519,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, yeah, I read that.","index":72,"end_time":149.119,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":147.479,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"I read that today.","index":73,"end_time":150.119,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":149.119,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":74,"end_time":150.639,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":150.199,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Is there anything that I should do?","index":75,"end_time":152.279,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":150.639,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Bailey.","index":76,"end_time":152.839,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":152.279,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"You''ll just need to log in.","index":77,"end_time":158.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":157.57,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay.","index":78,"end_time":159.69,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":159.25,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, we can troubleshoot after the call, see, make sure it all works.","index":79,"end_time":164.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":159.69,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Cool.","index":80,"end_time":165.73,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":165.25,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Okay, so.","index":81,"end_time":167.17,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":166.13,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Here''S the.","index":82,"end_time":169.89,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":169.01,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Can you see my screen?","index":83,"end_time":173.41,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":172.21,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Cool.","index":84,"end_time":175.33,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":174.85,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So podcast updates and then.","index":85,"end_time":183.92,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":181.57,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"TMR ebook.","index":86,"end_time":186.88,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":185.68,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Most of it is done, but they mentioned the basically repurposing some things and then the ad campaign and finally client portal.","index":87,"end_time":197.76,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":186.88,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":88,"end_time":200.4,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":199.92,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So for the podcast, as you know, Michelle Barbo episode is done.","index":89,"end_time":206.96,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":200.48,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"And then I also uploaded the video episode to Spotify and also short clips and.","index":90,"end_time":214.82,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":206.96,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Yeah, so two short clips and another like promo video to YouTube.","index":91,"end_time":221.62,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":215.22,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"I love that.","index":92,"end_time":222.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":222.1,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"That all happened behind the scenes.","index":93,"end_time":224.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":222.82,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"That''s a.","index":94,"end_time":225.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":225.46,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"That was a great ad.","index":95,"end_time":226.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":225.94,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":96,"end_time":227.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":227.38,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Glad we figured that out.","index":97,"end_time":228.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":227.78,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":98,"end_time":229.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":229.38,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Nice.","index":99,"end_time":230.82,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":230.34,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":100,"end_time":231.46,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":230.9,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"That''s the point.","index":101,"end_time":233.22,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":232.42,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":102,"end_time":234.98,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":234.42,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"And then.","index":103,"end_time":236.58,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":235.94,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":104,"end_time":237.7,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":237.22,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Kelly Chapman.","index":105,"end_time":238.82,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":237.7,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Any feedback from her?","index":106,"end_time":240.95,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":239.59,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"And how tight is the deadline for this because I feel like.","index":107,"end_time":244.87,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":241.43,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"You and the Gavin team left the feedback and then how many days do we have to wait for Kelly''s feedback or should we just move on with the edits based on your feedback?","index":108,"end_time":259.35,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":246.55,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"I would move forward with edits based on our feedback, but I will tell you guys this.","index":109,"end_time":265.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":261.19,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"You can give feedback whoever''s doing it.","index":110,"end_time":267.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":265.67,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"I''ve never had any issues with it, but I was sort of embarrassed sharing that with Callie because there was like glaring mistakes in the first three minutes.","index":111,"end_time":279.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":268.38,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"The beginning part of it was chopped up and not correctly edited.","index":112,"end_time":283.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":279.54,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"And then there was a whole thing where a whole intro of my question was just cut and then it went into her doing it.","index":113,"end_time":291.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":284.38,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"So I don''t know if it was speed or was just.","index":114,"end_time":295.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":291.5,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"This was just a one off.","index":115,"end_time":296.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":295.59,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"But please, like, we can''t be doing sharing that with Cali and expecting her to catch that stuff.","index":116,"end_time":303.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":296.83,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"Like, I don''t want her to say, hey, this is really jacked up.","index":117,"end_time":307.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":303.79,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"You need to make changes.","index":118,"end_time":308.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":307.59,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"So we.","index":119,"end_time":309.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":308.79,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"So either the process is we.","index":120,"end_time":311.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":309.43,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"It comes to us, we.","index":121,"end_time":313.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":311.75,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"We do edits, then we give it to Cali.","index":122,"end_time":316.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":313.11,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"Like, we shouldn''t be relying on C''s edits.","index":123,"end_time":318.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":316.07,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"It should be a rubber stamp.","index":124,"end_time":319.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":318.27,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"Yep, I like it.","index":125,"end_time":320.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":319.91,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"Agreed.","index":126,"end_time":322.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":322.24,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, we''ll do a more thorough QC next time.","index":127,"end_time":326.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":322.88,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, I agree that is embarrassing.","index":128,"end_time":329.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":327.04,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We had, I think when this episode happened, we had like a record week of episodes submitted.","index":129,"end_time":337.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":330.96,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So with that being said, we should definitely catch that.","index":130,"end_time":341.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":338.24,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"It was like just a really busy week with.","index":131,"end_time":343.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":341.28,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I think people are trying to get a lot of stuff through before the holidays.","index":132,"end_time":346.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":343.44,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"But yeah, we''ll.","index":133,"end_time":347.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":346.88,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We''ll definitely revise that and, and communicate that with our team.","index":134,"end_time":350.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":347.64,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I would just move forward with what''s in frame from Tim and I because that''s pretty thorough.","index":135,"end_time":356.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":352.86,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"And we did plan on going live with this next Thursday.","index":136,"end_time":362.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":358.62,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"So let''s move forward with it.","index":137,"end_time":364.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":363.02,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"We can send the cleaned up assets to Callie and just be like, we cleaned it up.","index":138,"end_time":369.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":364.46,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"It looks great.","index":139,"end_time":370.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":369.58,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"You look great.","index":140,"end_time":371.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":370.54,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"She''s been pretty easy to work with.","index":141,"end_time":374.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":373.02,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":142,"end_time":377.71,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":376.95,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Sounds good.","index":143,"end_time":378.31,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":377.71,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Sounds good.","index":144,"end_time":378.95,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":378.31,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Thank you for, for the feedback.","index":145,"end_time":380.87,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":379.11,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"And then moving forward for all episodes, including the episode for with Kelly Chapman, we will.","index":146,"end_time":390.31,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":382.39,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Upload Spotify videos and short clips to YouTube.","index":147,"end_time":397.35,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":391.91,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Do you have any upcoming episodes in mind?","index":148,"end_time":401.67,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":398.15,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"The.","index":149,"end_time":403.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":402.88,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"What I wanted daily about is, is for the ebook, there was all those clips and I thought that that would be a good promotion of the ebook.","index":150,"end_time":412.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":403.08,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"Plus that would be a good podcast to be right before the holidays.","index":151,"end_time":416.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":412.04,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"Because.","index":152,"end_time":418.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":417.76,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"If we put a new one there, I''m like talking to Gab like it might be some dead space in there.","index":153,"end_time":425.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":420.48,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"It might not get the value that we want.","index":154,"end_time":427.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":425.24,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"I''m recording two podcasts next week, but I think those are going to be for January.","index":155,"end_time":431.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":427.52,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"So, Bailey, if you could just jump in on what you think about repurposing those voice.","index":156,"end_time":437.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":432.72,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"I don''t know.","index":157,"end_time":438.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":437.68,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"They''re not really voiceovers, but, yeah, clips into more of a formal podcast.","index":158,"end_time":443.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":438.2,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"And I.","index":159,"end_time":444.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":443.84,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"And I could do the intro outro.","index":160,"end_time":446.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":444.28,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"Not for each one, but just like explaining what this is about.","index":161,"end_time":450.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":446.8,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"And, you know, I''m thinking.","index":162,"end_time":452.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":450.88,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"You read my mind.","index":163,"end_time":453.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":452.48,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, you read my mind.","index":164,"end_time":455.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":454.72,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I think we can use what we''ve already done for the clips.","index":165,"end_time":460.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":455.92,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And rather than having.","index":166,"end_time":462.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":460.82,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Because I feel like the clips are really.","index":167,"end_time":464.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":463.14,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I don''t know if choppy is the right word, but they''re like short.","index":168,"end_time":467.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":465.14,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So I think for the podcast episode, we would just organize it by this person, this person, this person.","index":169,"end_time":473.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":467.94,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So it wouldn''t jump back and forth so much.","index":170,"end_time":475.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":473.42,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"But if you could just do like a two to three minute intro, talk about, like, maybe your favorite insight from the year, introduce the ebook, things like that, and then have just a short outro thinking people to listen, then we can slice it all together.","index":171,"end_time":493.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":475.94,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So, Bailey, do you happen to know, like.","index":172,"end_time":499.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":496.4,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"So if we put all 14 those clips, is it just like 10 to 20 seconds for each one of those?","index":173,"end_time":506.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":499.76,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"I''ll have to go and look, but we can try a name for that length for each of them.","index":174,"end_time":513.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":508.4,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Just have like our favorite takeaway from each episode.","index":175,"end_time":516.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":513.7,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay.","index":176,"end_time":520.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":519.86,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"Is that that way you''re thinking, or did you have something different in mind?","index":177,"end_time":524.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":520.9,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"No, I would just think that maybe it''s like a minute for each one.","index":178,"end_time":529.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":524.18,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":179,"end_time":529.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":529.3,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":180,"end_time":530.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":530.02,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"A little longer.","index":181,"end_time":531.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":530.42,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":182,"end_time":532.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":531.86,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"Seconds to a minute.","index":183,"end_time":533.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":532.5,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":184,"end_time":534.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":533.94,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"So maybe it''s just.","index":185,"end_time":535.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":534.46,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"Instead of just them talking, it''s like me asking the question and then their full answer for whatever that clip came from, and we just do that.","index":186,"end_time":544.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":535.9,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"So there''s.","index":187,"end_time":545.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":544.44,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"There''s 14 minutes there, and if I can do a couple minutes on the front end.","index":188,"end_time":549.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":545.32,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"So now it''s like a 20 minute, and then we can really promote the ebook.","index":189,"end_time":553.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":549.28,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"And Gab can do her specialty of, you know, getting people to look at it through social and all that good stuff.","index":190,"end_time":561.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":553.24,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"Yeah, no, that''s a great idea.","index":191,"end_time":563.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":562.36,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Then.","index":192,"end_time":564.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":564.63,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, everything''s working together.","index":193,"end_time":566.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":564.79,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"All.","index":194,"end_time":566.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":566.47,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"All going towards the ebook.","index":195,"end_time":568.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":566.87,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":196,"end_time":569.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":568.71,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"So then, Tim, when can you aim to have your intro outro goodness recorded in Riverside?","index":197,"end_time":577.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":570.71,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"What I would like to do, since I''m.","index":198,"end_time":579.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":577.43,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"I''m doing two podcasts Tuesday morning in the office, I would like to do it all at the same time?","index":199,"end_time":585.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":579.03,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"Something like 9 to 10, 10 to 11, then 11 to 12 on Tuesday.","index":200,"end_time":589.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":585.95,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"I can do that and get it to you.","index":201,"end_time":593.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":591.6,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"Okay, so by Tuesday afternoon, mid will have your voiceover stuff.","index":202,"end_time":601.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":594.08,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Not even voiceover, your clips.","index":203,"end_time":605.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":602.24,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Yeah, speaking.","index":204,"end_time":606.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":605.28,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"And then when would you want the episode to go live?","index":205,"end_time":611.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":608.24,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"I. I''m all.","index":206,"end_time":612.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":612,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"Let me just look at the calendar.","index":207,"end_time":614.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":612.92,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"I would say.","index":208,"end_time":617.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":616.41,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"Like the 17th, 18th, 19th.","index":209,"end_time":622.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":619.37,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"That would probably make the most sense.","index":210,"end_time":626.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":625.05,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"I just want to make sure that Bailey''s team has time to splice everything together and get our feedback before we.","index":211,"end_time":633.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":626.73,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Could even do it to 22nd.","index":212,"end_time":635.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":633.97,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"Like, I''m okay to be off cycle with this one, as long as we can try to dump it in.","index":213,"end_time":640.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":635.93,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"I want this in December.","index":214,"end_time":641.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":640.17,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"Mm.","index":215,"end_time":642.86,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":642.46,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"Billy, what''s more realistic?","index":216,"end_time":645.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":643.9,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"I mean, 22nd is a Monday.","index":217,"end_time":647.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":645.94,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Ideally, I feel like the 18th would be best, but whatever.","index":218,"end_time":654.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":649.98,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"We can make the 18th work if we get the intro outro by next Tuesday.","index":219,"end_time":658.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":654.46,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, that.","index":220,"end_time":659.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":659.1,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"That should be pretty feasible.","index":221,"end_time":661.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":659.82,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I was gonna say, because then from Tuesday to Tuesday, that''s a week to.","index":222,"end_time":665.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":661.26,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"To turn around in terms of like a first cut and then we know it''s a quick turnaround.","index":223,"end_time":670.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":665.98,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Yeah, we don''t have anybody.","index":224,"end_time":673.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":671.49,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"It''s just Gavin I.","index":225,"end_time":674.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":673.01,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"Weighing in on approvals.","index":226,"end_time":675.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":674.05,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":227,"end_time":677.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":676.53,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":228,"end_time":678.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":677.97,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay.","index":229,"end_time":679.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":678.93,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"If that''s a feasible timeline, then that''s what we''ll go with.","index":230,"end_time":682.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":679.73,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":231,"end_time":683.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":683.09,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Cool.","index":232,"end_time":685.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":684.61,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"I was going to spend this afternoon looking into the Apple ID stuff just so that by the end of the year we have all of our platforms logged in and we can drill deeper in 2026.","index":233,"end_time":695.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":685.97,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"But yeah, it''s on.","index":234,"end_time":698.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":698.04,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"It''s on my radar.","index":235,"end_time":699.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":698.92,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":236,"end_time":702.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":701.72,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I hope it is fast.","index":237,"end_time":705.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":702.6,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I hope it isn''t super time consuming.","index":238,"end_time":708.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":705.4,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Spotify was easy enough.","index":239,"end_time":710.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":708.84,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"I hope Apple.","index":240,"end_time":710.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":710.12,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":241,"end_time":711.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":710.84,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Nice.","index":242,"end_time":714.84,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":714.36,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Nice.","index":243,"end_time":715.24,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":714.84,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Great.","index":244,"end_time":715.56,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":715.24,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Yeah, so, yeah, I was going to ask about that.","index":245,"end_time":718.84,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":715.56,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So good to know that that''s.","index":246,"end_time":721.24,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":719.32,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"That''s gonna speed things up.","index":247,"end_time":725.68,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":723.6,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"And then the TMR ebook, we basically.","index":248,"end_time":730.72,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":726.72,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So, yeah, delivered guest creatives compilation videos and LinkedIn carousels.","index":249,"end_time":735.36,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":731.44,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"And yeah, this was the question that you basically covered in the previous slide.","index":250,"end_time":742.4,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":736.64,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So the convert ebook clips to mini podcast.","index":251,"end_time":746.12,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":742.48,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So.","index":252,"end_time":746.48,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":746.12,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"And we have the designs ready for the campaign.","index":253,"end_time":754.01,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":750.33,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"And I''ll send it over on Slack after the meeting.","index":254,"end_time":757.13,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":754.09,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Adderall is connected.","index":255,"end_time":759.53,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":758.25,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Copy was approved before that.","index":256,"end_time":762.01,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":760.17,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"And yeah, we''re waiting for the.","index":257,"end_time":764.41,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":762.01,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"For.","index":258,"end_time":765.89,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":765.53,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"For the comments on.","index":259,"end_time":767.17,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":765.89,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"On the designs.","index":260,"end_time":768.33,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":767.17,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"And yeah, gotta.","index":261,"end_time":770.33,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":768.33,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Gotta move fast on this one.","index":262,"end_time":771.85,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":770.33,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":263,"end_time":773.33,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":773.05,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Make sure to get you feedback before the day ends today.","index":264,"end_time":776.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":773.33,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Nice.","index":265,"end_time":777.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":777.59,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Great.","index":266,"end_time":778.63,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":778.23,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Great.","index":267,"end_time":779.11,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":778.71,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So we can start with the revisions on Monday probably already.","index":268,"end_time":783.35,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":779.27,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":269,"end_time":785.35,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":784.87,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Nice.","index":270,"end_time":786.15,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":785.67,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Basic.","index":271,"end_time":788.63,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":787.99,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s it.","index":272,"end_time":789.71,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":788.95,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Bailey, do you have any.","index":273,"end_time":791.03,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":789.71,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Anything you Want to add about this one?","index":274,"end_time":794.55,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":792.15,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"No, I think we''re covered there.","index":275,"end_time":796.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":795.51,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I know we''re gonna chat on Monday about setting things up, so I would have loved to have, like, the ads totally finalized before that meeting, but we can just talk big picture how to set things up, or if you want to reschedule for when the ads are ready, then we can actually get it all set up.","index":276,"end_time":814.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":796.83,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"But just up to you.","index":277,"end_time":815.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":814.54,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"What do you think, Christina?","index":278,"end_time":819.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":817.98,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Let''s see.","index":279,"end_time":821.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":820.94,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"Give me a minute.","index":280,"end_time":823.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":822.14,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I think we should, because we''re in office Tuesday and Wednesday.","index":281,"end_time":829.66,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":823.34,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"Potentially could do Thursday, the day of launch, if that makes sense.","index":282,"end_time":835.22,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":831.66,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"Just have everything done at the same time instead of two separate meetings or launch.","index":283,"end_time":841.02,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":835.22,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"And so that would work.","index":284,"end_time":843.26,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":841.1,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"One other idea too, if you wanted, we could set everything up beforehand, and then we just hop on the call and, like, answer any questions, like, kind of show you how it would have happened.","index":285,"end_time":856.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":844.3,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Just to, like, take some of that time off of your plate.","index":286,"end_time":860.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":858.58,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"If you''re looking pretty busy, it''s up to you.","index":287,"end_time":863.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":860.66,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Like, if you want to walk step through step how it would all go, or we can talk through it after.","index":288,"end_time":868.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":863.66,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Once it''s all set up.","index":289,"end_time":869.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":868.14,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I think we''ll probably.","index":290,"end_time":872.98,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":871.94,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"Because I know Gab, we wanted to see how it''s set up, because at least on my part, I don''t have an idea on how that is.","index":291,"end_time":880.34,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":873.62,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"Just in case for future, like, you guys aren''t able to, and we have to.","index":292,"end_time":885.85,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":881.14,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"But if there''s a way we can see it, like, even after you guys set it up, then that works with me.","index":293,"end_time":893.53,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":886.25,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"Okay.","index":294,"end_time":895.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":894.65,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, really, Just whatever works best for you.","index":295,"end_time":898.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":895.29,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And what.","index":296,"e