s  \n    - Baylee proposed a setup meeting Monday or Thursday to finalize ad platforms and workflows, with flexibility based on team availability  \n    - Christina Bila agreed to lead the Thursday 10am Eastern session, with Gab recording the meeting for later reference due to a scheduling conflict  \n    - The team aims to have all ad platforms logged in by end of year to enable deeper 2026 analytics and optimizations  \n\n## **Marketing Team Collaboration and Planning**\n\nThe marketing team is preparing for an in-person meeting in Chicago next week to boost team cohesion and align priorities.\n\n- **Gab shared that the marketing team of seven, including OPS, product, design, and inbound leads, will meet in Chicago for a mix of work and social activities to strengthen collaboration** (00:34)  \n    - Activities include attending a Blackhawks game and team dinners to foster relationships after nearly two years apart  \n    - This event supports productive planning and team morale, laying groundwork for upcoming campaigns and projects  \n    - Baylee acknowledged the team''s high output despite its small size, reinforcing the value of tight coordination  \n\n## **Content Repurposing and Creative Strategy**\n\nPlans were discussed to create a year-end recap highlighting top blog posts, using creative formats to boost engagement with minimal effort.\n\n- **Gab proposed making a recap of the top-performing blog posts using LinkedIn carousels and potentially a conversational video with Tim to showcase insights** (16:39)  \n    - Baylee supported the idea, suggesting a carousel and a YouTube video where Gab and Tim discuss why these blogs succeeded  \n    - Timing is flexible, with Gab aiming to launch the carousel before the holidays and the video possibly debuting in early 2026 at a Vegas meeting  \n    - Tim agreed that a January launch is acceptable if needed to ensure quality and impact  \n    - Gab will submit a project brief through the client portal to formalize the request and scope  \n\n## **Operational Improvements and Platform Access**\n\nThe team is focused on streamlining platform access and operational workflows to support faster campaign launches.\n\n- **Gab is proactively working on obtaining Apple ID access for all platforms before year-end, following a smooth Spotify login process, to enable deeper 2026 insights** (11:24)  \n    - Igor acknowledged this progress will speed up setup and campaign execution  \n    - Baylee offered flexible meeting options to review ad setup processes with Christina and Gab, ensuring future self-sufficiency  \n    - Christina will lead a training session on Thursday at 10am Eastern to understand platform setup and management, with Gab recording the session due to travel  \n    - This operational focus reduces bottlenecks and increases team independence for ongoing marketing execution","outline":null,"keywords":["Podcast editing","TMR ebook","marketing team meeting","ad campaign","creative content recap","platform access"],"overview":"- **Podcast Quality Improvement:** Team agreed on thorough pre-approval edits to prevent errors and reduce reputational risk.  \n- **Ebook Promotion Strategy:** 14 podcast clips will be repurposed into a 20-minute episode, targeted for release on December 18th.  \n- **Ad Campaign Readiness:** Ebook campaign assets are ready, with final feedback scheduled for Monday and ad platforms targeted for end of year.  \n- **Chicago Team Meeting:** Marketing team will meet in Chicago for collaboration and planning activities, enhancing team morale and project alignment.  \n- **Content Recap Initiative:** Plans to create a year-end recap of top blog posts using LinkedIn carousels and a video discussion.  \n- **Operational Streamlining:** Proactive efforts to obtain platform access will enhance setup speed and independence in campaign execution.","action_items":"\n**Baylee Gunnell**\nTroubleshoot Igor’s paid media admin login after the meeting (02:35)\nConduct more thorough QC on future podcast episodes before sending to Kelly Chapman (05:45)\nReview length of TMR ebook clips for podcast, target 1 minute per clip (08:26)\nAssemble and splice podcast clips with Tim’s recorded intro/outro by December 18th, assuming receipt of recordings by Tuesday (11:03)\nParticipate in ad setup walkthrough meeting on Thursday, 10:00 AM Eastern (14:43)\nSupport Gab with creative concepting for top blog posts recap and review project brief once received (19:30)\n\n**Tim Finnigan**\nProvide intro/outro recording for TMR ebook mini-podcast by Tuesday morning (09:45)\nMove forward with edits on podcast episode based on own and Gab’s feedback without waiting on Kelly’s comments (05:55)\nTarget podcast episode launch December 18th, flexible up to December 22nd (10:10)\nFollow up with Baylee for additional questions after Gab leaves (20:00)\n\n**Gab**\nProvide feedback on ad campaign designs today to accelerate Monday revisions (12:52)\nWork on Apple ID platform login before end of year for easier access in 2026 (11:30)\nCoordinate social promotion efforts for new TMR ebook podcast episode (09:15)\nSubmit project brief for top performing blog posts recap project via portal (19:20)\n\n**Christina Bila**\nAttend ad campaign setup walkthrough on Thursday, 10:00 AM Eastern, represent Gab if absent (15:25)\n\n**Igor Zagradjanin**\nSend ad campaign designs over Slack after meeting (12:45)\nManage edits for podcast episode and continue client portal design progress (16:05)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"0128a3f3-d02e-4491-8e94-80933e71db6d","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
