INSERT INTO compass_notes (contract_id, meeting_id, note_type, title, content_raw, note_date, status, action_items, is_auto_generated)
SELECT
  new_meeting.contract_id,
  new_meeting.meeting_id,
  'meeting',
  'Meeting Notes: Verisk // New North Weekly Meeting',
  '## **Podcast Production and Quality Control**

The team agreed to improve podcast editing quality to avoid embarrassing mistakes and streamline approval.

- **Tim Finnigan emphasized the need for thorough pre-approval edits to prevent obvious errors in podcasts** like chopped intros, suggesting the team handle full edits before sharing with Callie for a final review** (04:21)  
    - This approach ensures Callie''s feedback acts as a rubber stamp, reducing rework and reputational risk  
    - Baylee Gunnell confirmed a more thorough quality check will be implemented following a record week of submissions  
    - The team plans to move forward with the current episode to meet the live date next Thursday despite imperfect edits  
    - Igor Zagradjanin committed to uploading Spotify videos and YouTube clips for all episodes going forward to boost reach  

- **Tim and Baylee aligned on repurposing 14 ebook-related podcast clips into a 20-minute episode with a new intro and outro to promote the ebook before the holidays** (07:32)  
    - Tim will record all podcast intros and outros on Tuesday between 9am and 12pm to consolidate efforts  
    - Baylee’s team will splice clips and have the episode ready for live release targeted for December 18th, allowing a week turnaround  
    - Gab highlighted the social media promotion role, reinforcing a coordinated campaign around the ebook launch  
    - The timeline was agreed to balance quality with holiday season scheduling constraints  

## **TMR Ebook Campaign and Ad Execution**

The ebook campaign is nearing launch with creative assets ready and ad setup planned for next week to ensure timely promotion.

- **Igor Zagradjanin reported guest creatives, LinkedIn carousels, and video compilations are completed, with approved copy and designs awaiting final feedback to start revisions Monday** (12:53)  
    - Gab committed to providing feedback by end of day to avoid delays  
    - Baylee proposed a setup meeting Monday or Thursday to finalize ad platforms and workflows, with flexibility based on team availability  
    - Christina Bila agreed to lead the Thursday 10am Eastern session, with Gab recording the meeting for later reference due to a scheduling conflict  
    - The team aims to have all ad platforms logged in by end of year to enable deeper 2026 analytics and optimizations  

## **Marketing Team Collaboration and Planning**

The marketing team is preparing for an in-person meeting in Chicago next week to boost team cohesion and align priorities.

- **Gab shared that the marketing team of seven, including OPS, product, design, and inbound leads, will meet in Chicago for a mix of work and social activities to strengthen collaboration** (00:34)  
    - Activities include attending a Blackhawks game and team dinners to foster relationships after nearly two years apart  
    - This event supports productive planning and team morale, laying groundwork for upcoming campaigns and projects  
    - Baylee acknowledged the team''s high output despite its small size, reinforcing the value of tight coordination  

## **Content Repurposing and Creative Strategy**

Plans were discussed to create a year-end recap highlighting top blog posts, using creative formats to boost engagement with minimal effort.

- **Gab proposed making a recap of the top-performing blog posts using LinkedIn carousels and potentially a conversational video with Tim to showcase insights** (16:39)  
    - Baylee supported the idea, suggesting a carousel and a YouTube video where Gab and Tim discuss why these blogs succeeded  
    - Timing is flexible, with Gab aiming to launch the carousel before the holidays and the video possibly debuting in early 2026 at a Vegas meeting  
    - Tim agreed that a January launch is acceptable if needed to ensure quality and impact  
    - Gab will submit a project brief through the client portal to formalize the request and scope  

## **Operational Improvements and Platform Access**

The team is focused on streamlining platform access and operational workflows to support faster campaign launches.

- **Gab is proactively working on obtaining Apple ID access for all platforms before year-end, following a smooth Spotify login process, to enable deeper 2026 insights** (11:24)  
    - Igor acknowledged this progress will speed up setup and campaign execution  
    - Baylee offered flexible meeting options to review ad setup processes with Christina and Gab, ensuring future self-sufficiency  
    - Christina will lead a training session on Thursday at 10am Eastern to understand platform setup and management, with Gab recording the session due to travel  
    - This operational focus reduces bottlenecks and increases team independence for ongoing marketing execution',
  '2025-12-05 17:30:00+00',
  'published',
  '[{"text":"Troubleshoot Igor’s paid media admin login after the meeting (02:35)","completed":false},{"text":"Conduct more thorough QC on future podcast episodes before sending to Kelly Chapman (05:45)","completed":false},{"text":"Review length of TMR ebook clips for podcast, target 1 minute per clip (08:26)","completed":false},{"text":"Assemble and splice podcast clips with Tim’s recorded intro/outro by December 18th, assuming receipt of recordings by Tuesday (11:03)","completed":false},{"text":"Participate in ad setup walkthrough meeting on Thursday, 10:00 AM Eastern (14:43)","completed":false},{"text":"Support Gab with creative concepting for top blog posts recap and review project brief once received (19:30)","completed":false},{"text":"Provide intro/outro recording for TMR ebook mini-podcast by Tuesday morning (09:45)","completed":false},{"text":"Move forward with edits on podcast episode based on own and Gab’s feedback without waiting on Kelly’s comments (05:55)","completed":false},{"text":"Target podcast episode launch December 18th, flexible up to December 22nd (10:10)","completed":false},{"text":"Follow up with Baylee for additional questions after Gab leaves (20:00)","completed":false},{"text":"Provide feedback on ad campaign designs today to accelerate Monday revisions (12:52)","completed":false},{"text":"Work on Apple ID platform login before end of year for easier access in 2026 (11:30)","completed":false},{"text":"Coordinate social promotion efforts for new TMR ebook podcast episode (09:15)","completed":false},{"text":"Submit project brief for top performing blog posts recap project via portal (19:20)","completed":false},{"text":"Attend ad campaign setup walkthrough on Thursday, 10:00 AM Eastern, represent Gab if absent (15:25)","completed":false},{"text":"Send ad campaign designs over Slack after meeting (12:45)","completed":false},{"text":"Manage edits for podcast episode and continue client portal design progress (16:05)","completed":false}]'::jsonb,
