-- Meeting: Baylee Gunnell and Steven Frydrych (2025-12-04 16:00:00+00)
WITH new_meeting AS (
  INSERT INTO compass_meetings (contract_id, meeting_date, source, external_id, title, participants, duration_seconds, recording_url, transcript, sentiment, raw_metadata, created_at, updated_at)
  VALUES (
    'a3899b64-d779-4aee-afbb-d43e2125ccf8',
    '2025-12-04 16:00:00+00',
    'fireflies',
    '01KB4THNRAV9HYE5KYEYZYJ85Y',
    'Baylee Gunnell and Steven Frydrych',
    '{"Steven Frydrych | VITAL","Abner - VITAL","Baylee Gunnell","May Castillo","Fernando Rendon","Igor Zagradjanin"}'::text[],
    1134,
    'https://us02web.zoom.us/j/81660496506?pwd=Yz3quZpdsJOTq7ZnDbQlAqaQzoJkc9.1',
    '{"id":"01KB4THNRAV9HYE5KYEYZYJ85Y","title":"Baylee Gunnell and Steven Frydrych","summary":{"notes":"## **Liveapalooza Landing Page Optimization**\n\nThe team agreed to simplify and improve the landing page to boost clarity and lead booking efficiency.\n\n- **Steven Frydrych** emphasized prioritizing his two scheduling links—one for a **15-minute clarity session** and another for a **45-minute game planning session**—while **Brandon** will have only one link to reduce confusion and clutter (04:22).\n    - The **15-minute session** targets quick, casual visitors, while the **45-minute session** aims at higher-quality leads ready to invest more time.\n    - Steven explained that the current page layout causes users to miss the game planning link, especially on mobile, due to excessive scrolling and clutter (05:08).\n    - The goal is a cleaner, story-driven layout that prioritizes Steven’s links and reduces white space and confusion.\n    - This redesign should improve user experience and increase the booking rate, addressing past issues where many visitors only saw the first link.\n\n- **Baylee Gunnell** recommended simplifying scheduling by potentially adding a short survey to route users to the right session, but Steven cautioned that more clicks might increase drop-off, preferring quick one-click scheduling (03:10).\n    - Baylee suggested placing a scheduling link prominently near the top or side of the page for immediate access.\n    - Abner agreed that fewer clicks reduce dropouts and noted a previous landing page with all links posted might be easier for users (07:38).\n    - The team plans to keep the messaging and copy similar to the successful Cedia event page, focusing updates on layout and design improvements to enhance appeal (08:52).\n\n- **Abner** will provide Baylee with all necessary logos and marketing assets from Liveapalooza’s recent materials to support timely page buildout and branding consistency (10:10).\n    - Steven stressed the importance of starting early to avoid the last-minute rush experienced before Cedia, aiming to finish the landing page well ahead of the event and holidays (09:31).\n    - This will allow coordinated email blasts and marketing activity with a polished, user-friendly page ready to capture leads effectively.\n\n## **Event Marketing and Lead Generation Strategy**\n\nThe team is focused on maximizing lead bookings before and during Liveapalooza through targeted outreach and onsite engagement.\n\n- **Steven Frydrych** will execute an email blast via HubSpot to the entire existing CRM, but expressed concern about repeatedly messaging the same contacts with similar content (12:55).\n    - He seeks additional strategies to reach new or less engaged prospects beyond email.\n    - Baylee confirmed that no official attendee list is provided by the event, limiting pre-event targeting options (13:08).\n\n- **Baylee Gunnell** proposed leveraging organic social posts and encouraging event attendees to update their LinkedIn profiles and email signatures with direct booking links to increase visibility (14:55).\n    - This includes adding clear calls to action like “book time with me at Liveapalooza” on profiles and signatures for easier user access.\n\n- **Igor Zagradjanin** suggested exploring paid ads on Meta and LinkedIn to broaden reach using smart targeting algorithms for likely attendees (15:37).\n    - Baylee added that geotargeting ads during the event around the venue is effective but less helpful before the event without a contact list (16:14).\n    - The team agreed paid ads could enhance awareness during and after the event, complementing pre-event efforts.\n\n- The team discussed coordinating with partners attending the event to cross-promote and share contacts, which could broaden the audience beyond their CRM (17:22).\n    - **May Castillo** and **Abner** will check partner attendance and contact lists to explore collaboration opportunities (18:01).\n    - Cross-pollination with partners could improve lead volume by tapping into different networks.\n\n- Onsite, **Matt’s presentations** will be filmed if a camera team is available, with footage repurposed for YouTube and social channels to extend event reach (11:42).\n    - May will confirm camera availability and share info with Baylee for content planning (11:59).\n    - If no camera team is available, Baylee offered to recommend simple recording equipment to capture key moments (12:08).\n\n## **Process Improvements for Lead Capture and Follow-up**\n\nThe team emphasized streamlining the process to reduce last-minute stress and improve lead handling efficiency.\n\n- Steven highlighted that last time’s rushed timeline delayed copy and landing page readiness, creating a disjointed marketing push (09:31).\n    - This time, the goal is to start early and finish the landing page and email copy before the holidays to enable a smooth rollout.\n    - Baylee agreed that having more lead time will improve design quality and allow multiple review rounds (09:56).\n\n- The landing page will reduce unnecessary scheduling links from prior events, focusing on Steven’s prioritized links to limit confusion and dropouts (04:22).\n    - Abner confirmed all links are ready to be integrated once the page design is completed (09:29).\n    - The team plans to avoid adding extra steps like surveys unless they clearly improve conversion without adding drop-off risk (03:10).\n\n- The group agreed to maintain consistent messaging from the previous successful Cedia campaign while enhancing the user experience to increase engagement and booking rates (08:48).\n    - Steven will send the updated copy for Liveapalooza immediately after the meeting to align efforts (08:36).\n    - This approach balances proven content with improved presentation and usability.\n\n## **Technology and Content Assets Coordination**\n\nEffective use of branding and marketing materials is critical for cohesive event presence.\n\n- **Abner** will share all Liveapalooza logos and marketing assets in the Slack channel promptly to support Baylee’s design and content work (10:31).\n    - May confirmed these assets arrived recently, ensuring up-to-date materials are available (10:24).\n    - This will help maintain brand consistency across the landing page, email blasts, and social posts.\n\n- The team will ensure content capture during Matt’s presentations, either through existing event camera teams or by deploying simple recording gear (11:42).\n    - This footage will be repurposed across YouTube and social channels to maintain post-event engagement and extend lead nurture opportunities.\n\n- Baylee’s team will support creation of social media posts modeled after previous events, adapting to Liveapalooza specifics and audience preferences (11:42).\n    - These posts aim to increase event awareness and encourage booth visit bookings.\n\n## **Timeline and Coordination for Marketing Deliverables**\n\nThe group prioritized early completion of key marketing materials to avoid previous timing issues.\n\n- Steven stressed the need to finalize the landing page and email campaign before the upcoming holidays to prevent last-minute delays and enable a coordinated launch (09:31).\n    - Baylee and Abner will collaborate closely to ensure all assets and links are ready ahead of time.\n    - This effort aligns with the goal to have the campaign running smoothly before the team’s return from holidays.\n\n- The next steps include Steven sending Liveapalooza copy immediately, Abner providing logos and links, and May confirming event marketing assets and partner attendance (08:36, 10:31, 18:01).\n    - The team agreed to schedule a follow-up meeting if needed to refine creative ideas and finalize plans (18:02).\n    - Early preparation is expected to improve lead capture effectiveness and reduce operational stress.","outline":null,"keywords":["Landing page","scheduling links","Liveapalooza","event marketing","lead generation","geotargeting"],"overview":"- **Landing Page Revamp:** Simplify layout to enhance clarity; prioritize Steven''s two scheduling links for better booking efficiency.\n\n- **User Experience Focus:** Aim for a cleaner design; reduce excessive scrolling and clutter, improving mobile navigation for users.\n\n- **Lead Generation Strategy:** Develop targeted outreach via email blasts; explore social media and paid ads to reach new audiences.\n\n- **Onsite Content Capture:** Film presentations for YouTube and social media; ensure effective post-event engagement with repurposed footage.\n\n- **Early Completion Goal:** Finalize marketing materials before holidays; coordinate collaboration to ensure smooth rollout and lead capture.","action_items":"\n**Steven Frydrych**\nSend updated email copy for Liveapalooza event to Baylee after meeting (18:02)\n\n**Baylee Gunnell**\nBegin redesign and simplification of Liveapalooza landing page with improved layout focused on user experience and prioritizing Steven’s scheduling links (05:25)\nIncorporate provided logos and marketing assets into landing page and collateral after receiving files (10:37)\nDevelop social media strategy including organic posts and recommendations for LinkedIn profile and email signature CTAs to support booking sessions (15:12)\nExplore and advise on the feasibility of paid ads and geotargeting strategies for event promotion in coordination with the team (15:37)\n\n**Abner**\nShare Liveapalooza marketing assets, logos, and related folders with Baylee via Slack (10:31)\nProvide scheduling links ready for use to Baylee (09:29)\n\n**May Castillo**\nShare presentation details and marketing asset information with Baylee for event promotion (11:31)\nInvestigate availability of camera team at Liveapalooza for capturing event footage and communicate back (11:59)\n\n**Fernando Rendon**\nConfirm and share Liveapalooza marketing materials receipt (10:22)\nAssist in confirming partner attendance information if possible (13:48)\n"},"duration":18.899999618530273,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"id":1,"name":"Abner - VITAL"},{"id":2,"name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"id":3,"name":"May Castillo"},{"id":4,"name":"Fernando Rendon"},{"id":5,"name":"Igor Zagradjanin"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Hey, Abner.","index":0,"end_time":0.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":0.24,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"Thanks, Steven.","index":1,"end_time":2.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1.92,"speaker_name":"Abner - VITAL"},{"text":"How are you?","index":2,"end_time":3.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2.68,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"Good.","index":3,"end_time":4.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3.76,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"How you doing?","index":4,"end_time":4.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":4.12,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"Good.","index":5,"end_time":6.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":5.76,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"Good.","index":6,"end_time":6.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":6.16,"speaker_name":"Abner - VITAL"},{"text":"Glad that you''re back.","index":7,"end_time":7.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":6.72,"speaker_name":"Abner - VITAL"},{"text":"Yep.","index":8,"end_time":8.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":8.48,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"Good to be back.","index":9,"end_time":9.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":8.96,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"Did you go on a trip or something?","index":10,"end_time":11.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":10.4,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"No, a little health scare.","index":11,"end_time":15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":13.2,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"Had to do a few days in the hospital, but trying to get back into work today a little bit.","index":12,"end_time":20.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":15,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"I don''t know.","index":13,"end_time":20.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":20.2,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Well, glad you''re back, too.","index":14,"end_time":24.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":23.12,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Me, too.","index":15,"end_time":26.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":25.93,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"Cool.","index":16,"end_time":29.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":29.21,"speaker_name":"Abner - VITAL"},{"text":"So, really, I had a few things, but I really wanted to see what your thoughts were on this page and kind of how we could make this a little better for Liveapalooza.","index":17,"end_time":39.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":30.33,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":18,"end_time":40.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":39.85,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Let''S go through it.","index":19,"end_time":44.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":43.21,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Super excited for this event.","index":20,"end_time":45.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":44.01,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Also excited to meet you, Abner.","index":21,"end_time":48.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":46.81,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We''ve never met on a call before, so I know we''ve been chatting on Slack.","index":22,"end_time":51.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":48.37,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So glad we can finally meet digitally.","index":23,"end_time":54.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":51.69,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Is Fernando joining us?","index":24,"end_time":97.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":96.4,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"Looks like May was on the meeting, too.","index":25,"end_time":111.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":109.21,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I think May was going to come if she was able to.","index":26,"end_time":118.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":115.53,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"I thought Fernando was going to.","index":27,"end_time":119.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":118.05,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"If not.","index":28,"end_time":120.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":119.85,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"Abner, I''m sure you can update him after.","index":29,"end_time":122.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":120.45,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"Yep, sure.","index":30,"end_time":124.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":123.61,"speaker_name":"Abner - VITAL"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":31,"end_time":126.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":124.81,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, we can get started then.","index":32,"end_time":128.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":126.57,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":33,"end_time":129.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":129.37,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"Yeah, we can get started then.","index":34,"end_time":133.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":131.53,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"You kind of tell me, Bailey, what you were thinking.","index":35,"end_time":135.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":133.21,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":36,"end_time":137.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":137.05,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We would love to just strategize some ideas for the Lida Palooza conference coming up.","index":37,"end_time":144.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":137.53,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"First, just get an idea of what you''re doing right now, what''s already going to happen.","index":38,"end_time":151.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":145.69,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And then, I mean, we help a lot of our clients with stuff like this, so we can definitely toss around ideas and see where else we can plug into what you already have happening.","index":39,"end_time":160.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":151.53,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay, perfect.","index":40,"end_time":162.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":162.02,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"Right now, what we''re doing is we''re going to be offering those clarity sessions, and we need to build out that landing page.","index":41,"end_time":169.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":163.54,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"But I feel like there''s some areas of opportunity for us to do it better than what we did for Cedia.","index":42,"end_time":175.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":169.94,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"So I wanted to see if you had any time to kind of think that through and see how we could create a better landing page.","index":43,"end_time":182.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":176.66,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"I had my notes on it, but I kind of want to see.","index":44,"end_time":186.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":184.18,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"You''re the expert, not me.","index":45,"end_time":187.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":186.78,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":46,"end_time":190.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":190.28,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I think my.","index":47,"end_time":192.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":191.56,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"My biggest suggestion would be to simplify it.","index":48,"end_time":196.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":192.92,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"There were a lot of scheduling links, so if we can bring some clarity around that.","index":49,"end_time":205.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":196.76,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I don''t know if in internally there''s like, a difference between, like, why someone would want to schedule with a specific person.","index":50,"end_time":213.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":205.64,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Maybe we could just add some clarity around that.","index":51,"end_time":216.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":214.44,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Or I don''t know, we could probably do some cool.","index":52,"end_time":219.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":216.6,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Maybe like automations, they could fill out a survey and we connect them with the right person.","index":53,"end_time":224.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":219.64,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Or.","index":54,"end_time":225.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":225,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"That.","index":55,"end_time":227.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":227.32,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"That would definitely be my biggest suggestion, is just simplifying it.","index":56,"end_time":230.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":227.68,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":57,"end_time":232.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":231.96,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"I agree.","index":58,"end_time":233.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":232.32,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"Simplicity is best.","index":59,"end_time":234.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":233.16,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"The difference with lidapalooza is it''s only going to be Brandon and myself going.","index":60,"end_time":239.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":234.84,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"So we won''t need so many scheduling links.","index":61,"end_time":242.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":239.98,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":62,"end_time":245.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":244.62,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"So that''ll be part of it.","index":63,"end_time":246.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":245.02,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"Now I''ll still have two separate scheduling links and here''s why you tell me the best way to do this.","index":64,"end_time":252.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":246.54,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"So we have the 15 minute clarity session, which is very quick for someone that doesn''t want to invest a lot of time.","index":65,"end_time":259.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":253.66,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"There''s a lot of things going on at these shows, a lot of education.","index":66,"end_time":262.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":259.98,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"Someone''s like, hey, I''m kind of interested.","index":67,"end_time":264.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":262.86,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"I want to meet these guys and I can only get 15 minutes of their time.","index":68,"end_time":268.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":264.54,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"Then the people that are a little more serious or that are willing to carve out more time, I have the game planning session link, which is 45 minutes with me, which I would consider a higher quality lead.","index":69,"end_time":280.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":269.13,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"So the 15 minutes gets them in the door.","index":70,"end_time":282.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":280.81,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"But if they''re really serious about doing something with their business, they tend to use the other link.","index":71,"end_time":288.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":282.97,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"So I''ll have two links, Brandon will only have one for simplicity and we want to prioritize my links over his.","index":72,"end_time":296.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":289.37,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"So I''m not sure what that would look like on the landing page.","index":73,"end_time":299.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":296.51,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"The other thing I noticed, and part of it was the scheduling part not is there was a lot of scrolling and most people missed map.","index":74,"end_time":308.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":299.87,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"They missed the game planning session link, especially on the mobile version.","index":75,"end_time":312.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":308.75,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"It was kind of a cluster.","index":76,"end_time":314.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":312.83,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"So maybe cleaning up the mobile and just laying it out in a way that kind of tells more of a story and makes sense instead of just a bunch of things on a page.","index":77,"end_time":323.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":314.67,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"Does that make sense?","index":78,"end_time":324.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":323.88,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, I agree with that.","index":79,"end_time":327.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":325.24,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, I''ll pull this up too, just so everyone can see what page we''re talking about.","index":80,"end_time":335.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":329.8,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, I agree there.","index":81,"end_time":338.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":337.72,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"There''s a lot of white space here.","index":82,"end_time":341.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":338.84,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"This logo is really big.","index":83,"end_time":344.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":342.76,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So I''d maybe put one of the scheduling links just here on the right so people can do it like first, first thing they see.","index":84,"end_time":352.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":344.6,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Or even we could have like a kind of like what I mentioned, a short survey here and then it goes to another page based on what they say to schedule with the right person or the right type of meeting.","index":85,"end_time":365.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":352.56,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":86,"end_time":367.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":366.4,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"I like that idea.","index":87,"end_time":368.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":367.2,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"Where it''s a challenge for me is to.","index":88,"end_time":372.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":368.72,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"Typically the more clicks it takes, the more drop off there is.","index":89,"end_time":375.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":372.4,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"But unless you see something different, I want it to go more simplistically like they click the link because they''re already going to be somewhere else, whether it''s LinkedIn and email.","index":90,"end_time":383.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":375.24,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"So they''re already clicking over the landing page.","index":91,"end_time":386.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":383.92,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"If we can make it even quicker where they can just find a time and schedule instead of having to fill things out.","index":92,"end_time":392.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":386.16,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"Yep.","index":93,"end_time":393.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":393.28,"speaker_name":"Abner - VITAL"},{"text":"Also a great point.","index":94,"end_time":395.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":394.24,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"When we did this for the CD Expo, how did those meetings or like, what feedback did you get from people?","index":95,"end_time":403.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":396.96,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Like, do you feel like they had good expectations coming in?","index":96,"end_time":407.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":404.08,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Were they pretty clear on what the meeting was going to be about?","index":97,"end_time":410.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":407.84,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yes and no mix like it usually is with us?","index":98,"end_time":415.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":412.16,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"Definitely.","index":99,"end_time":416.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":416.16,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"I had the only meetings that pretty much scheduled because no one scrolled down.","index":100,"end_time":422.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":417.44,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"But that''s what I wanted is I wanted my calendar to be prioritized because I''m technically the only one in sales.","index":101,"end_time":427.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":422.28,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"So everyone else is just their support to help me out and eventually hand it off to me anyways.","index":102,"end_time":432.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":428.07,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"So I wanted to prioritize my links, but it felt like that''s as far as they got on the page.","index":103,"end_time":438.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":432.95,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"And it was just a lot of space.","index":104,"end_time":440.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":438.99,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"Like I said that we could probably make it a little sexier and make it more appealing to schedule than just a bunch of words on a white and gray page.","index":105,"end_time":448.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":440.23,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"Yep.","index":106,"end_time":450.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":449.75,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"What about you, Abner?","index":107,"end_time":452.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":451.35,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"Did you have any notes or questions on this?","index":108,"end_time":455.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":452.31,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"Not really.","index":109,"end_time":458.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":458.14,"speaker_name":"Abner - VITAL"},{"text":"We.","index":110,"end_time":459.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":459.42,"speaker_name":"Abner - VITAL"},{"text":"We had a separate landing page where all your links way back in Senior are posted.","index":111,"end_time":467.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":460.06,"speaker_name":"Abner - VITAL"},{"text":"I think that would be easier or just like, what?","index":112,"end_time":472.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":468.06,"speaker_name":"Abner - VITAL"},{"text":"Stephen''s point is, the lesser clicks the better to avoid dropouts.","index":113,"end_time":479.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":472.06,"speaker_name":"Abner - VITAL"},{"text":"And Bailey, did I.","index":114,"end_time":485.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":484.11,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"Did I send you the copy that I was going to use in the email blast to get people to this page?","index":115,"end_time":492.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":485.07,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":116,"end_time":493.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":492.67,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay.","index":117,"end_time":493.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":493.31,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"So that way you have kind of the verbiage and kind of what we''re going for and maybe we can kind of tie it together.","index":118,"end_time":500.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":494.51,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":119,"end_time":502.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":501.71,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So you''re thinking of doing something pretty similar for the next one?","index":120,"end_time":505.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":502.23,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, I already have the copy for it.","index":121,"end_time":508.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":507.31,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"Did I not send that to you?","index":122,"end_time":509.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":508.79,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"Oh, sorry.","index":123,"end_time":510.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":509.71,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I meant I have the copy for the Cedia X, so I don''t think I''ve seen the one for the Lidapalooza.","index":124,"end_time":515.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":510.23,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s very similar.","index":125,"end_time":517.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":516.11,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"I''ll send that to you after this meeting.","index":126,"end_time":519.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":517.47,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"It''s very similar.","index":127,"end_time":520.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":519.15,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"We basically changed the bonuses out, but it was pretty successful.","index":128,"end_time":524.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":520.35,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"So I don''t like messing with success until I have to.","index":129,"end_time":527.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":524.51,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"Yep.","index":130,"end_time":528.59,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":528.03,"speaker_name":"May Castillo"},{"text":"If it''s working.","index":131,"end_time":529.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":528.75,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, keep.","index":132,"end_time":530.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":529.95,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Keep using it.","index":133,"end_time":531.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":530.63,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay.","index":134,"end_time":532.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":532.19,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"I''ll send that over to you after this meeting.","index":135,"end_time":534.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":532.99,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"Okay, great.","index":136,"end_time":537.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":536.19,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Well, we''ll definitely want to.","index":137,"end_time":540.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":538.35,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Want to refresh some things.","index":138,"end_time":541.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":540.47,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Are you wanting to keep some of the copy on the page?","index":139,"end_time":545.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":541.79,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Pretty similar.","index":140,"end_time":546.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":545.39,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And it sounds like we''re wanting mostly to do some nice design updates, make the user experience a Bit sleeker.","index":141,"end_time":554.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":547.47,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"But the main message should be the same.","index":142,"end_time":557.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":555.79,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, I''m good with the messaging and the copy.","index":143,"end_time":561,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":558.84,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"It''s just the layout and the functionality of it.","index":144,"end_time":565,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":562.04,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"And then, Abner, we have the links ready to go, correct?","index":145,"end_time":569,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":565.24,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"Yep.","index":146,"end_time":570.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":569.72,"speaker_name":"Abner - VITAL"},{"text":"Okay.","index":147,"end_time":571.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":571.08,"speaker_name":"Abner - VITAL"},{"text":"So we can provide you those also.","index":148,"end_time":574.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":571.88,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"And we''re ready just to move forward.","index":149,"end_time":577.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":575.32,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"I just don''t want to be in the position.","index":150,"end_time":579.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":577.8,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"And this is no fault of anyone''s.","index":151,"end_time":581.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":579.16,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"Last time, everything felt very rushed, even for me.","index":152,"end_time":584.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":581.64,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"I was behind on getting copy out and sending out the emails and waiting for the landing pages.","index":153,"end_time":589.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":584.24,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"So I''d rather be ahead of the game, especially going into the holidays.","index":154,"end_time":592.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":589.47,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"So when we come back, we''re not starting this process.","index":155,"end_time":595.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":592.71,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"We''re finishing it up.","index":156,"end_time":596.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":595.03,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, I agree.","index":157,"end_time":598.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":596.39,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We have more time to make sure everything looks the way you want it.","index":158,"end_time":603.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":599.19,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Where sometimes, like, we got to run with the first draft.","index":159,"end_time":606.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":603.23,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, we''re running behind, definitely.","index":160,"end_time":610.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":607.27,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Abner, can you get Bailey all the logos and stuff for Lighted Palooza there?","index":161,"end_time":616.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":610.71,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"You might have to get with May, but there should be a folder or a packet from lidapalooza for marketing stuff.","index":162,"end_time":623.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":616.08,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"It came like two days ago.","index":163,"end_time":626.16,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":624,"speaker_name":"Fernando Rendon"},{"text":"May.","index":164,"end_time":626.68,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":626.32,"speaker_name":"Fernando Rendon"},{"text":"Oh, okay, perfect.","index":165,"end_time":627.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":626.68,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"Fernando, I didn''t even see you jump in.","index":166,"end_time":628.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":627.4,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"I will share that in the Slack channel.","index":167,"end_time":633.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":631.68,"speaker_name":"Abner - VITAL"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":168,"end_time":637.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":637.12,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So I think we got some clarity then with the web page.","index":169,"end_time":640.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":637.68,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Do you guys want help with any other marketing things for the event?","index":170,"end_time":645.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":642.43,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"What else do you have going on for it?","index":171,"end_time":647.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":645.47,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"May, I''ll let you jump in here.","index":172,"end_time":651.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":649.63,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"What''s currently going on with Matt and promoing, all that stuff?","index":173,"end_time":657.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":652.59,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"Maybe we don''t have.","index":174,"end_time":665.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":664.67,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"May.","index":175,"end_time":665.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":665.55,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yes, hello.","index":176,"end_time":667.48,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":666.27,"speaker_name":"May Castillo"},{"text":"Sorry, I''m here.","index":177,"end_time":669.24,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":667.72,"speaker_name":"May Castillo"},{"text":"Yeah, sorry, what was the question?","index":178,"end_time":672.28,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":669.24,"speaker_name":"May Castillo"},{"text":"We were talking about the Light of Palooza scheduling landing page, but Bailey says she can help with strategy and anything else we need to help market this.","index":179,"end_time":684.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":674.12,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"So Matt''s holding some sessions and stuff.","index":180,"end_time":686.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":684.12,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"Have you and Matt discussed this at all?","index":181,"end_time":689.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":687.08,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"No, we haven''t.","index":182,"end_time":691.96,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":691,"speaker_name":"May Castillo"},{"text":"But sure.","index":183,"end_time":693,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":692.04,"speaker_name":"May Castillo"},{"text":"I''m going to share all the info with Bailey about the presentations and also we receive the marketing assets.","index":184,"end_time":698.22,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":693,"speaker_name":"May Castillo"},{"text":"So I''m going to share that with you vaguely.","index":185,"end_time":702.38,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":698.86,"speaker_name":"May Castillo"},{"text":"Okay, perfect.","index":186,"end_time":703.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":702.62,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, we''ll definitely want to do some social posts like we''ve done for the other events.","index":187,"end_time":707.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":703.9,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And then I think we had also talked about cameras being at those events when Matt''s speaking.","index":188,"end_time":715.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":708.46,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"It sounded like they''ll have a team there.","index":189,"end_time":717.74,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":715.66,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, but we haven''t.","index":190,"end_time":722.28,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":719.66,"speaker_name":"May Castillo"},{"text":"We haven''t dig into that option, but let me work on it.","index":191,"end_time":727.32,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":723.32,"speaker_name":"May Castillo"},{"text":"Okay?","index":192,"end_time":728.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":727.56,"speaker_name":"Abner - VITAL"},{"text":"Yeah, let us know if they have a camera team there.","index":193,"end_time":731,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":728.12,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"You''ll just want to clarify with them if they''ll give you the footage.","index":194,"end_time":734.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":731.72,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Afterwards, if they don''t have a camera team, we can talk about like some simple equipment you can use because we''ll still want to get that footage because we can repurpose that on your YouTube and all your social channels.","index":195,"end_time":748.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":734.68,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay, got it.","index":196,"end_time":750.92,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":750.12,"speaker_name":"May Castillo"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":197,"end_time":752.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":752.36,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"And Bailey, for me, any strategy or anything you can think of that would help get people to book time with us in the booth.","index":198,"end_time":761.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":752.72,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"That''s the main purpose while we''re there is to get leads and to sell things.","index":199,"end_time":766.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":762.12,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"So if there''s anything past the email blast that I''m going to be doing, totally open to any ideas and strategies you have around that.","index":200,"end_time":774.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":767.32,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"Yeah, I think when we had talked, you won''t get a list of who''s attending the event, but so you''re just using who''s already like in your CRM.","index":201,"end_time":786.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":775.47,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay.","index":202,"end_time":787.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":787.31,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":203,"end_time":789.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":788.91,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"So I can take care of the HubSpot email blast.","index":204,"end_time":792.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":789.39,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"It basically goes out to every single contact we have.","index":205,"end_time":795.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":792.67,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"But anything past that and we''ve done this so many times already.","index":206,"end_time":798.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":796.11,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"My concern is that we''re going to be hitting the same people with similar messaging over and over again.","index":207,"end_time":803.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":799.31,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"So if there''s another way to reach these people, that''s what I''d be interested in getting help with.","index":208,"end_time":808.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":803.95,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"Yeah, I always wish we could get a list that''s.","index":209,"end_time":815.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":811.39,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"That is the most sure fire way to do that.","index":210,"end_time":819.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":815.87,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Do you have any partners who will also be at the event?","index":211,"end_time":826.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":822.27,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I''m sure we do.","index":212,"end_time":830.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":828.91,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"I don''t.","index":213,"end_time":831.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":831.02,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"I haven''t looked at that list yet, but usually one vision is there.","index":214,"end_time":835.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":831.54,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"Fernando, you have that.","index":215,"end_time":836.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":835.5,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"You''re muted.","index":216,"end_time":840.78,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":839.74,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Yeah, I''m sorry.","index":217,"end_time":842.06,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":841.02,"speaker_name":"Fernando Rendon"},{"text":"Do we have partners?","index":218,"end_time":844.78,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":843.66,"speaker_name":"Fernando Rendon"},{"text":"Yes.","index":219,"end_time":845.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":845.18,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"Do we have lists?","index":220,"end_time":846.7,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":845.58,"speaker_name":"Fernando Rendon"},{"text":"We have lists for process.","index":221,"end_time":847.82,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":846.7,"speaker_name":"Fernando Rendon"},{"text":"Right.","index":222,"end_time":848.38,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":847.98,"speaker_name":"Fernando Rendon"},{"text":"The process partners.","index":223,"end_time":851.02,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":849.66,"speaker_name":"Fernando Rendon"},{"text":"I''m not entirely sure.","index":224,"end_time":853.26,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":851.18,"speaker_name":"Fernando Rendon"},{"text":"Yeah, we have rosters for the buying groups, so that doesn''t necessarily mean they''re going to.","index":225,"end_time":858.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":854.06,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"To Palooza.","index":226,"end_time":860.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":859.33,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"So that''s the challenge is we don''t know who''s going.","index":227,"end_time":862.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":860.13,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"So we''re marketing something to people that might not even be going.","index":228,"end_time":866.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":862.45,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"That''s where we always get stuck on these.","index":229,"end_time":868.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":866.37,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":230,"end_time":868.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":868.45,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"Can we add like a small banner in the.","index":231,"end_time":871.53,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":869.25,"speaker_name":"Fernando Rendon"},{"text":"At the bottom of the Tuesday coffees maybe?","index":232,"end_time":875.49,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":871.53,"speaker_name":"Fernando Rendon"},{"text":"Yeah, I think we did something like that last time too, but it was for the whole website.","index":233,"end_time":880.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":876.69,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"It was just.","index":234,"end_time":882.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":880.85,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, we have a pop up.","index":235,"end_time":883.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":882.01,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":236,"end_time":883.61,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":883.33,"speaker_name":"Fernando Rendon"},{"text":"Yeah, a pop up.","index":237,"end_time":884.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":883.61,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So we could do that again as well that goes to your page so that they can book time with you.","index":238,"end_time":889.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":884.53,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"That would definitely help.","index":239,"end_time":890.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":889.09,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay.","index":240,"end_time":891.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":891.07,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"What about LinkedIn or Facebook?","index":241,"end_time":893.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":891.55,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"Yeah, I think we''ll.","index":242,"end_time":896.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":895.07,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"You do a lot of organic social posts encouraging people to check it out.","index":243,"end_time":901.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":896.59,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I would also recommend that anyone attending the event can just update some things on your LinkedIn.","index":244,"end_time":909.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":901.99,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So.","index":245,"end_time":910.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":909.87,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"Like you know, you can add links at the top of your profile.","index":246,"end_time":916.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":912.11,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Like I''d say like book time with me at lidapalooza.","index":247,"end_time":920.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":917.15,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So put that on there.","index":248,"end_time":921.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":920.51,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So it''s really, really easy for people to make that next step.","index":249,"end_time":924.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":921.63,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And then I''d also update your email signature for a little bit with that like a similar cta.","index":250,"end_time":931.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":924.49,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Those just little things can always help.","index":251,"end_time":934.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":933.05,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay, sorry.","index":252,"end_time":936.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":935.77,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"Oh sorry.","index":253,"end_time":937.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":936.57,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"Sorry for interrupting.","index":254,"end_time":939.05,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":937.45,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Just came to me.","index":255,"end_time":941.85,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":939.77,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"If is like paid ads an option.","index":256,"end_time":945.69,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":942.01,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Maybe we can somehow target like people who will be like through meta and LinkedIn, maybe we can target people.","index":257,"end_time":955.94,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":947.94,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"I mean meta has a pretty smart algorithm so they like based on the creatives and the copy, it may be able to find the people who will be attending the event.","index":258,"end_time":967.62,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":956.02,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So maybe that''s one option to expand the reach.","index":259,"end_time":972.42,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":967.94,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Yeah, gotcha.","index":260,"end_time":975.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":974.67,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"What we''ve seen work for that is geotargeting during the event.","index":261,"end_time":979.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":975.95,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So we can like put a radius around the event center.","index":262,"end_time":984.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":980.67,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So it''s pretty tricky to do that before the event to figure out what who to target without a list.","index":263,"end_time":991.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":985.07,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"If we had a list we could do that.","index":264,"end_time":993.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":991.99,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"But we can geotarget during the event.","index":265,"end_time":996.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":994.43,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"The, the challenge with that is like I know you want to book people probably before the event actually happens.","index":266,"end_time":1004.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":997.39,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So it''s more a good way to get to them during the event and have maybe some awareness after as well.","index":267,"end_time":1010.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1004.55,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay, gotcha.","index":268,"end_time":1013.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1011.99,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":269,"end_time":1014.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1013.59,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"Once we go to the event, Matt''s doing presentations and stuff and we always use a capture form to get the information.","index":270,"end_time":1022.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1014.03,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"So post event we can do follow up and stuff but we still want to.","index":271,"end_time":1026.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1022.55,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"This is a selling event for us.","index":272,"end_time":1027.819,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1026.499,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"Unlike the buying group ones where it''s all relationship building and schedule things for when we get back home.","index":273,"end_time":1032.939,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1027.819,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"This one we want to sell in the booth.","index":274,"end_time":1034.899,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1032.939,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"So that''s why the pre booking the appointments is equally important.","index":275,"end_time":1038.419,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1035.219,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"So going back a little bit to partners.","index":276,"end_time":1045.459,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1042.819,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"If you can find out if you have any partners at the event, this can be a really good way just to share resources.","index":277,"end_time":1054.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1047.299,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So they probably have a contact list that''s a little different than yours.","index":278,"end_time":1059.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1055.23,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And yeah, you kind of just help each other out.","index":279,"end_time":1063.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1060.83,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"You''re like, we''ll encourage people to your landing page if you want to encourage people to ours.","index":280,"end_time":1068.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1063.47,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So just a bit of cross pollination can be beneficial there.","index":281,"end_time":1072.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1068.99,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay, got you.","index":282,"end_time":1074.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1073.47,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"Abner or May, can you check later and see who''s going to be there near us?","index":283,"end_time":1081.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1075.63,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":284,"end_time":1082.42,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1081.86,"speaker_name":"May Castillo"},{"text":"Okay.","index":285,"end_time":1083.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1082.74,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":286,"end_time":1088.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1087.94,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"Cool.","index":287,"end_time":1091.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1091.14,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"That''s all I had.","index":288,"end_time":1093.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1092.1,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"I''m excited to see what you guys come up with and I''ll send you the copy right now.","index":289,"end_time":1097.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1093.14,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"That way, if you come up with any other creative stuff, or we can book another meeting or just in our next marketing meeting, let me know and we''ll just kind of go from there.","index":290,"end_time":1106.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1097.46,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":291,"end_time":1107.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1107.39,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, that sounds great.","index":292,"end_time":1108.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1107.75,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Thanks for hopping on today, chatting through some ideas, and we''ll get started on that.","index":293,"end_time":1113.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1108.83,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":294,"end_time":1114.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1114.35,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"Thank you, Abner.","index":295,"end_time":1115.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1114.79,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"Fernando, May.","index":296,"end_time":1116.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1115.99,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"Anything else?","index":297,"end_time":1117.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1116.71,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"I''m good.","index":298,"end_time":1118.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1118.35,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"No, no, no.","index":299,"end_time":1121.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1120.11,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I think that''s it for me.","index":300,"end_time":1123.19,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1121.87,"speaker_name":"Fernando Rendon"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":301,"end_time":1123.55,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1123.19,"speaker_name":"Fernando Rendon"},{"text":"Okay.","index":302,"end_time":1124.59,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1124.11,"speaker_name":"May Castillo"},{"text":"All right, we''ll talk later.","index":303,"end_time":1125.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1124.59,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"All right.","index":304,"end_time":1126.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1125.95,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"Thanks, guys.","index":305,"end_time":1126.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1126.31,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"Have a good one.","index":306,"end_time":1127.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1126.87,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":307,"end_time":1127.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1127.43,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"}],"dateString":"2025-12-04T16:00:00.000Z","host_email":"baylee.gunnell@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/81660496506?pwd=Yz3quZpdsJOTq7ZnDbQlAqaQzoJkc9.1","participants":["concierge@growwithvital.com,steven@growwithvital.com,may@growwithvital.com,baylee.gunnell@marketersindemand.com,fernando@growwithvital.com,igor.zagradjanin@marketersindemand.com","concierge@growwithvital.com","steven@growwithvital.com","may@growwithvital.com","fernando@growwithvital.com","igor.zagradjanin@marketersindemand.com"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01KB4THNRAV9HYE5KYEYZYJ85Y","organizer_email":"baylee.gunnell@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"positive","confidence":0.93,"bullets":["Agreed to simplify and reformat the Lidapalooza landing page for stronger scheduling conversion.","Steven confirmed messaging will remain but page layout and mobile UX will be redesigned.","Abner and May tasked with gathering and sharing updated event logos and marketing assets.","Team discussed supplementing HubSpot emails with LinkedIn updates, popups, and email signatures.","Baylee suggested cross-promoting with event partners and geotargeting ads around the conference."],"highlights":[{"quote":"I''d rather be ahead of the game, especially going into the holidays.","speaker":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"quote":"We could do a pop up again as well that goes to your page.","speaker":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"quote":"Maybe we can somehow target like people who will be like through meta and LinkedIn.","speaker":"Igor Zagradjanin"}],"topics":["launch","strategy","delivery","UX","promotion"],"model":"openai/gpt-4-1106-preview","version":1,"generated_at":"2025-12-05T17:15:00Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **Liveapalooza Landing Page Optimization**\n\nThe team agreed to simplify and improve the landing page to boost clarity and lead booking efficiency.\n\n- **Steven Frydrych** emphasized prioritizing his two scheduling links—one for a **15-minute clarity session** and another for a **45-minute game planning session**—while **Brandon** will have only one link to reduce confusion and clutter (04:22).\n    - The **15-minute session** targets quick, casual visitors, while the **45-minute session** aims at higher-quality leads ready to invest more time.\n    - Steven explained that the current page layout causes users to miss the game planning link, especially on mobile, due to excessive scrolling and clutter (05:08).\n    - The goal is a cleaner, story-driven layout that prioritizes Steven’s links and reduces white space and confusion.\n    - This redesign should improve user experience and increase the booking rate, addressing past issues where many visitors only saw the first link.\n\n- **Baylee Gunnell** recommended simplifying scheduling by potentially adding a short survey to route users to the right session, but Steven cautioned that more clicks might increase drop-off, preferring quick one-click scheduling (03:10).\n    - Baylee suggested placing a scheduling link prominently near the top or side of the page for immediate access.\n    - Abner agreed that fewer clicks reduce dropouts and noted a previous landing page with all links posted might be easier for users (07:38).\n    - The team plans to keep the messaging and copy similar to the successful Cedia event page, focusing updates on layout and design improvements to enhance appeal (08:52).\n\n- **Abner** will provide Baylee with all necessary logos and marketing assets from Liveapalooza’s recent materials to support timely page buildout and branding consistency (10:10).\n    - Steven stressed the importance of starting early to avoid the last-minute rush experienced before Cedia, aiming to finish the landing page well ahead of the event and holidays (09:31).\n    - This will allow coordinated email blasts and marketing activity with a polished, user-friendly page ready to capture leads effectively.\n\n## **Event Marketing and Lead Generation Strategy**\n\nThe team is focused on maximizing lead bookings before and during Liveapalooza through targeted outreach and onsite engagement.\n\n- **Steven Frydrych** will execute an email blast via HubSpot to the entire existing CRM, but expressed concern about repeatedly messaging the same contacts with similar content (12:55).\n    - He seeks additional strategies to reach new or less engaged prospects beyond email.\n    - Baylee confirmed that no official attendee list is provided by the event, limiting pre-event targeting options (13:08).\n\n- **Baylee Gunnell** proposed leveraging organic social posts and encouraging event attendees to update their LinkedIn profiles and email signatures with direct booking links to increase visibility (14:55).\n    - This includes adding clear calls to action like “book time with me at Liveapalooza” on profiles and signatures for easier user access.\n\n- **Igor Zagradjanin** suggested exploring paid ads on Meta and LinkedIn to broaden reach using smart targeting algorithms for likely attendees (15:37).\n    - Baylee added that geotargeting ads during the event around the venue is effective but less helpful before the event without a contact list (16:14).\n    - The team agreed paid ads could enhance awareness during and after the event, complementing pre-event efforts.\n\n- The team discussed coordinating with partners attending the event to cross-promote and share contacts, which could broaden the audience beyond their CRM (17:22).\n    - **May Castillo** and **Abner** will check partner attendance and contact lists to explore collaboration opportunities (18:01).\n    - Cross-pollination with partners could improve lead volume by tapping into different networks.\n\n- Onsite, **Matt’s presentations** will be filmed if a camera team is available, with footage repurposed for YouTube and social channels to extend event reach (11:42).\n    - May will confirm camera availability and share info with Baylee for content planning (11:59).\n    - If no camera team is available, Baylee offered to recommend simple recording equipment to capture key moments (12:08).\n\n## **Process Improvements for Lead Capture and Follow-up**\n\nThe team emphasized streamlining the process to reduce last-minute stress and improve lead handling efficiency.\n\n- Steven highlighted that last time’s rushed timeline delayed copy and landing page readiness, creating a disjointed marketing push (09:31).\n    - This time, the goal is to start early and finish the landing page and email copy before the holidays to enable a smooth rollout.\n    - Baylee agreed that having more lead time will improve design quality and allow multiple review rounds (09:56).\n\n- The landing page will reduce unnecessary scheduling links from prior events, focusing on Steven’s prioritized links to limit confusion and dropouts (04:22).\n    - Abner confirmed all links are ready to be integrated once the page design is completed (09:29).\n    - The team plans to avoid adding extra steps like surveys unless they clearly improve conversion without adding drop-off risk (03:10).\n\n- The group agreed to maintain consistent messaging from the previous successful Cedia campaign while enhancing the user experience to increase engagement and booking rates (08:48).\n    - Steven will send the updated copy for Liveapalooza immediately after the meeting to align efforts (08:36).\n    - This approach balances proven content with improved presentation and usability.\n\n## **Technology and Content Assets Coordination**\n\nEffective use of branding and marketing materials is critical for cohesive event presence.\n\n- **Abner** will share all Liveapalooza logos and marketing assets in the Slack channel promptly to support Baylee’s design and content work (10:31).\n    - May confirmed these assets arrived recently, ensuring up-to-date materials are available (10:24).\n    - This will help maintain brand consistency across the landing page, email blasts, and social posts.\n\n- The team will ensure content capture during Matt’s presentations, either through existing event camera teams or by deploying simple recording gear (11:42).\n    - This footage will be repurposed across YouTube and social channels to maintain post-event engagement and extend lead nurture opportunities.\n\n- Baylee’s team will support creation of social media posts modeled after previous events, adapting to Liveapalooza specifics and audience preferences (11:42).\n    - These posts aim to increase event awareness and encourage booth visit bookings.\n\n## **Timeline and Coordination for Marketing Deliverables**\n\nThe group prioritized early completion of key marketing materials to avoid previous timing issues.\n\n- Steven stressed the need to finalize the landing page and email campaign before the upcoming holidays to prevent last-minute delays and enable a coordinated launch (09:31).\n    - Baylee and Abner will collaborate closely to ensure all assets and links are ready ahead of time.\n    - This effort aligns with the goal to have the campaign running smoothly before the team’s return from holidays.\n\n- The next steps include Steven sending Liveapalooza copy immediately, Abner providing logos and links, and May confirming event marketing assets and partner attendance (08:36, 10:31, 18:01).\n    - The team agreed to schedule a follow-up meeting if needed to refine creative ideas and finalize plans (18:02).\n    - Early preparation is expected to improve lead capture effectiveness and reduce operational stress.","outline":null,"keywords":["Landing page","scheduling links","Liveapalooza","event marketing","lead generation","geotargeting"],"overview":"- **Landing Page Revamp:** Simplify layout to enhance clarity; prioritize Steven''s two scheduling links for better booking efficiency.\n\n- **User Experience Focus:** Aim for a cleaner design; reduce excessive scrolling and clutter, improving mobile navigation for users.\n\n- **Lead Generation Strategy:** Develop targeted outreach via email blasts; explore social media and paid ads to reach new audiences.\n\n- **Onsite Content Capture:** Film presentations for YouTube and social media; ensure effective post-event engagement with repurposed footage.\n\n- **Early Completion Goal:** Finalize marketing materials before holidays; coordinate collaboration to ensure smooth rollout and lead capture.","action_items":"\n**Steven Frydrych**\nSend updated email copy for Liveapalooza event to Baylee after meeting (18:02)\n\n**Baylee Gunnell**\nBegin redesign and simplification of Liveapalooza landing page with improved layout focused on user experience and prioritizing Steven’s scheduling links (05:25)\nIncorporate provided logos and marketing assets into landing page and collateral after receiving files (10:37)\nDevelop social media strategy including organic posts and recommendations for LinkedIn profile and email signature CTAs to support booking sessions (15:12)\nExplore and advise on the feasibility of paid ads and geotargeting strategies for event promotion in coordination with the team (15:37)\n\n**Abner**\nShare Liveapalooza marketing assets, logos, and related folders with Baylee via Slack (10:31)\nProvide scheduling links ready for use to Baylee (09:29)\n\n**May Castillo**\nShare presentation details and marketing asset information with Baylee for event promotion (11:31)\nInvestigate availability of camera team at Liveapalooza for capturing event footage and communicate back (11:59)\n\n**Fernando Rendon**\nConfirm and share Liveapalooza marketing materials receipt (10:22)\nAssist in confirming partner attendance information if possible (13:48)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"046f1f37-6615-487a-9d92-5cc852fb0cc3","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
