    '{"id":"01KB4THNR84WDZYH9JGKPNZ4WJ","title":"NEACH // New North","summary":{"notes":"## **Podcast Production and Financial Management**\n\nThe team agreed to manage podcast episode production tightly to control costs and stay within budget.\n\n- **NEACH will receive an invoice for the outstanding balance related to Alyssa’s spin-off, which is a significant amount, and the billing will be settled promptly** as Baylee committed to coordinate with Justin immediately after the meeting (02:09).  \n    - Meg emphasized the importance of clearing this balance within the current fiscal year to avoid budget complications.  \n    - Baylee outlined a plan to limit production to **two episodes per month moving forward**, allowing some flexibility to produce three in a month if fewer were done previously.  \n    - This control is intended to prevent continual overages in points, which complicate budget tracking and forecasting.  \n    - Meg confirmed coordination with Joe to better manage point usage and avoid “willy nilly” spending.\n\n- **Podcast content volume is steady, with a backlog scheduled through February and consistent YouTube engagement, especially driven by shorts which account for most of the 791 views** (04:48).  \n    - Baylee highlighted that although 791 views is modest, it’s strong within this niche industry.  \n    - Meg indicated Joe would handle reintroducing Spotify video content, likely starting in January due to his upcoming vacation (05:37).  \n    - The team agreed to hold off on Spotify video production until after the holidays to align with resource availability.\n\n## **Creative Asset Management and Workflow Enhancements**\n\nThe team decided to improve access to creative assets to streamline in-house editing and reduce dependency on external support.\n\n- **NEACH will receive Adobe Illustrator templates for podcast quote cards and thumbnails to enable Joe and Carlos to make edits independently** (07:01).  \n    - Carlos, who has experience with Photoshop but not Illustrator or Figma, welcomed receiving Illustrator files to ease his editing workflow.  \n    - Meg explained Joe’s typical process involves last-minute edits to quote cards and thumbnails, which creates inefficiencies that this handoff aims to reduce.  \n    - Providing the original templates is expected to save time and improve turnaround for asset customization.  \n    - Baylee committed to delivering these assets promptly after the meeting to enable this transition.\n\n## **Meeting Scheduling and Team Coordination**\n\nMeeting times were adjusted to better accommodate international team members and improve participation.\n\n- **The group agreed to move recurring meetings three hours earlier to accommodate Igor’s European time zone, settling on Thursdays at 10am Eastern as the new standard** (09:32).  \n    - Meg clarified her availability, restricting only Thursdays 11am Eastern, which worked well with the proposed time.  \n    - Carlos confirmed the new timing fit within his schedule despite existing CFM calls.  \n    - Baylee planned to reschedule the next meeting accordingly and cancel the one on New Year’s Day, although the team expressed interest in keeping that session.  \n    - This adjustment aims to improve engagement and reduce fatigue for international team members.\n\n## **Podcast Longevity and Market Positioning**\n\nThe team acknowledged the podcast’s strong position in a challenging market, underlining consistency as a key success factor.\n\n- **With three seasons completed and entering season four, the podcast ranks among the top 1% for longevity, far exceeding typical podcast lifespan averages** as Baylee noted industry data showing many podcasts fail past episode three (11:12).  \n    - Meg and Carlos celebrated this milestone as a sign of steady progress despite internal challenges.  \n    - Igor shared updated industry insights confirming shorter average podcast lifespans than previously thought, reinforcing the achievement’s significance.  \n    - Baylee emphasized that consistent output is the hardest part and the main driver of this success.  \n    - This positioning supports ongoing engagement and strengthens the podcast’s market credibility.\n\n## **Content Delivery and Communication Improvements**\n\nThe team plans to improve communication around point usage and content delivery to enhance budget visibility and workflow predictability.\n\n- **Baylee committed to providing clearer notifications when point limits are exceeded to avoid surprises and enable better planning** (04:16).  \n    - This will help NEACH manage their monthly points more effectively and reduce confusion around overages.  \n    - Meg expressed appreciation for this proactive approach, noting it will help keep spending aligned with budget expectations.  \n    - The team agreed to monitor point usage closely and shift excess points forward if needed to maintain balance.  \n    - Improved transparency in usage reporting supports stronger financial control and trust between partners.","outline":null,"keywords":["Podcast production","invoicing","episode scheduling","asset templates","meeting time adjustment","budget reconciliation"],"overview":"- **Podcast Production Management:** Focus on two episodes per month; possible flexibility for a third when needed to control costs.\n\n- **Outstanding Invoice:** NEACH will receive the invoice related to Alyssa’s spin-off. Payment to be settled before fiscal year end.\n\n- **Content Performance:** Podcast backlog scheduled through February; YouTube shorts driving 791 views, strong for niche market.\n\n- **Creative Asset Accessibility:** NEACH to receive Illustrator templates for in-house editing, improving efficiency and turnaround time for assets.\n\n- **Meeting Time Changes:** Recurring meetings moved to Thursdays at 10am Eastern to better fit international team members'' schedules.\n\n- **Podcast Longevity Achievement:** Podcast ranks in top 1% for longevity; strong consistency is key to overcoming market challenges.","action_items":"\n**Baylee Gunnell**\nSend invoice to NEACH for outstanding podcast balance to allow year-end reconciliation (02:10)\nCoordinate with Justin to prepare and dispatch the invoice promptly (02:30)\nProvide Adobe Illustrator and Figma templates for podcast assets to Carlos for internal editing (07:35)\nFollow up with NEACH on points balance and episode scheduling, ensuring future adherence to two episode/month limit (03:50)\nReschedule future meetings to Thursday 10:00 AM Eastern to accommodate all time zones (09:55)\n\n**Carlos**\nReceive and begin using Adobe Illustrator templates for podcast asset editing as provided (07:00)\n\n**Meg Norlund**\nCoordinate internally with Joe regarding the Spotify video efforts resuming in January (05:30)\nTurn around edits on recent podcast videos and communicate any additional asset needs (06:30)\n\n**Igor Zagradjanin**\nApologize for initial email omission and send updated assets including Baylee in CC (03:00)\nRequest meeting time change to accommodate European time zone (09:15)\n"},"duration":12.489999771118164,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"id":1,"name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"id":2,"name":"Carlos"},{"id":3,"name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Good.","index":0,"end_time":0.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":0.16,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":1,"end_time":1.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":0.72,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Nice.","index":2,"end_time":1.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1.28,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Glad to hear that.","index":3,"end_time":3.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2.56,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"A nice day so far.","index":4,"end_time":5.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3.76,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Amazing.","index":5,"end_time":6.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":6.24,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Oh, we lost carlos.","index":6,"end_time":14.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":12.64,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Hey, guys.","index":7,"end_time":46.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":45.61,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Hey.","index":8,"end_time":47.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":46.89,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"What''s up?","index":9,"end_time":47.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":47.29,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Not much.","index":10,"end_time":49.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":48.97,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"My daily issue with Zoom.","index":11,"end_time":54.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":51.46,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"Come in and go out.","index":12,"end_time":57.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":56.02,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"Yep.","index":13,"end_time":58.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":57.94,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Because you''re usually on teams, right?","index":14,"end_time":60.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":58.82,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s what we primarily use, but occasionally I have this issue with the audio that I have to do that.","index":15,"end_time":66.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":61.46,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"But it''s fine.","index":16,"end_time":69.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":66.9,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"It works.","index":17,"end_time":69.7,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":69.1,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Thanks for making it work.","index":18,"end_time":73.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":71.7,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yes, of course.","index":19,"end_time":74.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":73.7,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"Love your background, Megan.","index":20,"end_time":76.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":75.46,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Oh, thank you.","index":21,"end_time":78.88,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":77.84,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"It''s for our member meeting this December.","index":22,"end_time":81.68,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":78.88,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Oh, nice.","index":23,"end_time":82.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":82,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"That''s so cute.","index":24,"end_time":83.68,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":82.8,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Does the logo read correctly on your screen?","index":25,"end_time":86.96,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":84.32,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":26,"end_time":88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":87.44,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":27,"end_time":88.4,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":88,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Oh, nice.","index":28,"end_time":89.04,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":88.4,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Perfect setup.","index":29,"end_time":90.64,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":89.28,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":30,"end_time":91.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":91.52,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Because it''ll go backwards sometimes, but it''s looking good.","index":31,"end_time":94.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":91.88,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":32,"end_time":95.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":94.72,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"Excellent.","index":33,"end_time":96.16,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":95.44,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"I saw so many podcasts come through today.","index":34,"end_time":102.88,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":98.64,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Like four, I think.","index":35,"end_time":104.88,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":103.52,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Oh, my.","index":36,"end_time":106.48,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":106.08,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"A lot.","index":37,"end_time":107.36,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":106.8,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"A lot of podcast episodes.","index":38,"end_time":111.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":109.12,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yes.","index":39,"end_time":113.28,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":112.8,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Bailey, I got your email about the potential spin off for Alyssa and the outstanding balance.","index":40,"end_time":121.36,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":114.24,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Explain to me how to pay the outstanding balance.","index":41,"end_time":125.92,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":122.16,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Do you invoice us?","index":42,"end_time":127.28,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":125.92,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Is there.","index":43,"end_time":127.92,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":127.28,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"What''s the process for that?","index":44,"end_time":129.36,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":128.08,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Yeah, we would just send you an invoice.","index":45,"end_time":131.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":129.36,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay.","index":46,"end_time":132.21,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":131.81,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"So we just want to get over soon for.","index":47,"end_time":136.21,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":132.61,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"We''re still trying to figure out what Joe feels about us spinning off for Alyssa, but we want to get caught up on those points, especially because that was, like, a pretty big number.","index":48,"end_time":146.89,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":137.09,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"So we want to make sure we get that in and cut for this this year.","index":49,"end_time":151.41,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":146.89,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":50,"end_time":152.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":151.97,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, I''ll talk to Justin right after this and we can get that sent over.","index":51,"end_time":156.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":152.41,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay.","index":52,"end_time":157.09,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":156.61,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Appreciate that.","index":53,"end_time":157.89,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":157.09,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":54,"end_time":159.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":158.77,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay, well, we''ll just jump into it.","index":55,"end_time":162.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":159.09,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":56,"end_time":164.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":164.05,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"Just before I just want to apologize, like, because I sent, like, 30 minutes ago.","index":57,"end_time":170.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":164.61,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"I sent.","index":58,"end_time":171.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":170.81,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So I introduced myself to Joe and Elisa because.","index":59,"end_time":175.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":172.21,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Yeah, I sent the podcast assets for the two episodes and then I just forgot to CC Bailey, and then I. Yeah, I sent another email with.","index":60,"end_time":187.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":176.21,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"With her in it.","index":61,"end_time":189.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":188.51,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So, yeah, just apologize.","index":62,"end_time":191.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":189.51,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"That''s totally fine.","index":63,"end_time":192.91,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":191.43,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Sorry for your inboxes.","index":64,"end_time":195.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":193.47,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"No, it makes me feel better.","index":65,"end_time":198.63,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":196.91,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"So now I only have two podcasts to.","index":66,"end_time":200.59,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":198.63,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"To work through instead of four.","index":67,"end_time":202.07,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":200.59,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s two.","index":68,"end_time":203.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":202.07,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"It''s two more manageable for sure.","index":69,"end_time":205.55,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":203.07,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":70,"end_time":208.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":208.03,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So I think we''re just working through the details on the next two, so we''ll send those over here soon.","index":71,"end_time":214.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":208.51,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Um, just quick note on this as we were, like, going over the balance, we''ll definitely need to only do two episodes a month moving forward.","index":72,"end_time":224.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":214.98,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I think you only did one last month, so, like, hopefully it all shakes out okay.","index":73,"end_time":230.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":224.82,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We''ll just need to keep an eye on it.","index":74,"end_time":231.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":230.5,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Like, it''s fine if maybe you.","index":75,"end_time":234.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":231.9,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"If you don''t do one a month, we could do Three the next month.","index":76,"end_time":236.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":234.06,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"But we''ll just need to make sure we don''t go over every single month.","index":77,"end_time":240.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":236.66,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, I talked to Joe about that too.","index":78,"end_time":243.09,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":241.53,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Just like being better about our points, us managing that instead of just like willy nilly throwing it out.","index":79,"end_time":248.73,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":243.09,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Do you want to hold?","index":80,"end_time":251.45,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":249.93,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Let''s just keep an eye on this moving forward.","index":81,"end_time":258.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":256.09,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I think we could do a better job of telling you too, when you''ve gone over.","index":82,"end_time":262.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":258.33,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So once we take care of that just excess points, it''s really hard to be like following it when there feels like.","index":83,"end_time":271.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":262.65,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"It feels like there''s so much excess that we can''t get over.","index":84,"end_time":275.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":271.7,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So once we get that all squared away, if.","index":85,"end_time":277.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":275.3,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"If it becomes an issue, we''ll let you know and say, hey, we''ll just move this towards to next month so that we can stay on track.","index":86,"end_time":285.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":277.82,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":87,"end_time":286.18,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":285.62,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"And then just for social, tons of content, we''ve got stuff scheduled out I think through February.","index":88,"end_time":294.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":288.9,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So looking really great here.","index":89,"end_time":296.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":294.66,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And then for your YouTube analytics, looks like you''ve had just like pretty steady views.","index":90,"end_time":305.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":300.66,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"That being said, 791 is not a small number.","index":91,"end_time":309.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":306.42,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Like that is.","index":92,"end_time":310.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":309.54,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Is pretty good, especially considering how niche you are in your industry.","index":93,"end_time":316.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":310.66,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"But a majority of that is coming from your YouTube shorts, right?","index":94,"end_time":321.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":317.06,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I was gonna say that must be almost all shorts.","index":95,"end_time":324.02,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":321.3,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, a lot of it.","index":96,"end_time":326.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":324.1,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And then I think we had talked about this two weeks ago, but do you want to do Spotify video.","index":97,"end_time":335.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":329.96,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Again?","index":98,"end_time":337.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":337.32,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I think I was just gonna share this over with Joe to do.","index":99,"end_time":341.52,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":337.72,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"He said he could handle it.","index":100,"end_time":343.08,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":341.52,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Okay.","index":101,"end_time":344.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":343.48,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I don''t know.","index":102,"end_time":345.48,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":344.6,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Give me like a hot second.","index":103,"end_time":346.88,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":345.64,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"He''s about to go on vacation for a couple weeks, I think so.","index":104,"end_time":350.38,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":346.88,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"So let me try to regroup with him and maybe this is something we just start in January.","index":105,"end_time":354.29,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":350.61,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Okay, we will not worry about it for now then.","index":106,"end_time":357.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":354.93,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay, then.","index":107,"end_time":360.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":359.57,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I think we kind of already talked about points and all that stuff.","index":108,"end_time":363.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":360.29,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So I''ll.","index":109,"end_time":364.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":363.49,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I''ll chat with Justin and I''ll follow up with you if not.","index":110,"end_time":368.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":364.53,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, today, tomorrow we can get some stuff probably figured out.","index":111,"end_time":374.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":369.25,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay.","index":112,"end_time":375.65,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":375.01,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Yeah, sooner the better.","index":113,"end_time":377.29,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":375.65,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Just so I can get it into this year''s budget instead of next year''s.","index":114,"end_time":380.57,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":377.29,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"That would be awesome.","index":115,"end_time":381.41,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":380.57,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Yes, of course.","index":116,"end_time":382.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":381.65,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":117,"end_time":384.21,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":383.81,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Well, anything else?","index":118,"end_time":385.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":384.21,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"No, I''ll try to turn around some edits on those videos, but appreciate you guys speeding through all of this, especially with the 70 points over.","index":119,"end_time":393.09,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":385.97,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"I''d be like, no, I''ll see you when you pay me.","index":120,"end_time":395.49,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":393.09,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"It''s great.","index":121,"end_time":397.49,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":396.93,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Thank you for moving.","index":122,"end_time":398.33,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":397.49,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Oh, sorry.","index":123,"end_time":398.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":398.33,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I do have one thing.","index":124,"end_time":399.73,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":398.89,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Where do we find the assets for like the.","index":125,"end_time":404.24,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":400.61,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"The podcast?","index":126,"end_time":406,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":404.88,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Joe Wanted to try to make himself, like an additional quote video compared to, like, what we get the two, I think with what we do with you guys.","index":127,"end_time":416.64,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":406.32,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"And he was going to try to pull another quote, but we don''t know where the assets for this stuff are.","index":128,"end_time":420.8,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":416.64,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Yeah, I don''t know if we''ve ever given them to you before.","index":129,"end_time":423.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":421.12,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So.","index":130,"end_time":424.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":423.76,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Do you have, like, a preferred platform, do you, that you use?","index":131,"end_time":428.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":425.68,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I think they''re all originally created.","index":132,"end_time":431.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":429.7,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"The templates we use Adobe Illustrator and figma.","index":133,"end_time":435.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":431.86,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So, Carlos, do those mean anything to you?","index":134,"end_time":438.66,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":436.58,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Illustrator, figma.","index":135,"end_time":441.74,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":439.46,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"I don''t know.","index":136,"end_time":442.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":441.74,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"Yeah, but I could, I could definitely.","index":137,"end_time":443.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":442.22,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"Yeah, I''ve always made edits myself on Photoshop.","index":138,"end_time":448.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":444.9,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"Like this.","index":139,"end_time":449.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":449.14,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"Blur it out.","index":140,"end_time":450.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":449.78,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"Yeah, but perfect.","index":141,"end_time":451.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":450.62,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"Illustrator is perfect.","index":142,"end_time":452.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":451.94,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"Okay.","index":143,"end_time":453.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":453.22,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay, we can get you the templates then for Adobe Illustrator.","index":144,"end_time":457.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":453.62,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"You should have asked us sooner.","index":145,"end_time":459.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":457.97,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Sorry, you''ve just gone in Photoshop.","index":146,"end_time":461.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":459.33,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I, I, well, you know, my brain, like, I just saw Joe would send me something.","index":147,"end_time":466.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":461.97,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"He''s like, oh, this isn''t the quote I want to use, whatever it is.","index":148,"end_time":469.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":466.41,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"And it''s probably happened five times in the last year.","index":149,"end_time":471.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":469.17,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"It''s not like, it''s like, not a big deal.","index":150,"end_time":474.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":471.89,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"And I, my, my brain just like, I know how to solve this problem.","index":151,"end_time":477.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":474.45,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"I know the font, I know it''s simple.","index":152,"end_time":479.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":477.45,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"Boom, Clint, whatever.","index":153,"end_time":480.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":479.25,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"But having that on Illustrator is, yeah, very helpful.","index":154,"end_time":484.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":480.93,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"He does it sometimes with thumbnail too.","index":155,"end_time":487.29,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":484.97,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Like, for some reason, he doesn''t see that frame that, like, when you send the frame link, you can literally just mark off and put whatever edit you want.","index":156,"end_time":496.41,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":487.61,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"And he''ll say he''ll finalize the episode and we''re all good.","index":157,"end_time":499.45,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":496.41,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Then he''s like, well, I changed the title.","index":158,"end_time":501.33,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":499.69,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"And you''re like, yeah, it''s always after.","index":159,"end_time":502.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":501.33,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"Yeah, Carlos, fix this.","index":160,"end_time":505.21,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":502.81,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"I don''t know.","index":161,"end_time":505.93,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":505.21,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Like, yeah, so that the thumbnail would be helpful, too, for when he does crazy stuff like that.","index":162,"end_time":511.61,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":506.01,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Right.","index":163,"end_time":512.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":512.08,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"The quote cards.","index":164,"end_time":512.96,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":512.24,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"And I think he wanted the last one, the Wasserman podcast that came through, he wanted, like, it was just so meaty.","index":165,"end_time":521.08,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":512.96,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"He wanted to see if he could do little cuts.","index":166,"end_time":523.04,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":521.08,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"We''ll see if it''s in the skill set or not, but if he has it to however you put those things together.","index":167,"end_time":528.56,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":523.12,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"I don''t really know the process, but if you could send that to Carlos.","index":168,"end_time":532.4,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":528.56,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"That would be great.","index":169,"end_time":533.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":532.4,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, we can.","index":170,"end_time":534.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":533.08,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Thank you, Bailey.","index":171,"end_time":535.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":534.24,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, I''ll just Jerry rigging everything over here.","index":172,"end_time":539.12,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":536.72,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Love, Joe.","index":173,"end_time":542.44,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":541.68,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"That''s awesome.","index":174,"end_time":543.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":542.44,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, we''ll get that sent over.","index":175,"end_time":547.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":545.5,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay.","index":176,"end_time":548.22,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":547.66,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Appreciate it.","index":177,"end_time":549.18,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":548.3,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Of course.","index":178,"end_time":550.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":550.14,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Well, great.","index":179,"end_time":551.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":551.02,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We''ll follow up here shortly then, with just the, the invoice stuff.","index":180,"end_time":555.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":552.22,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And.","index":181,"end_time":556.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":555.74,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And thanks for chatting, Bailey.","index":182,"end_time":558.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":556.38,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, just a second.","index":183,"end_time":559.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":558.78,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":184,"end_time":560.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":560.14,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Should we ask about the.","index":185,"end_time":562.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":560.9,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":186,"end_time":562.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":562.46,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So basically, yeah, we wanted to ask you if it''s possible to move the meeting to, like, earlier.","index":187,"end_time":570.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":562.86,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Because.","index":188,"end_time":572.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":572.7,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean, I based in Europe, so this is like, late hours for me.","index":189,"end_time":577.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":572.94,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So if it''s okay to, like, like three hours earlier than this.","index":190,"end_time":582.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":577.82,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"If that''s okay for you.","index":191,"end_time":583.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":582.3,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Thursdays.","index":192,"end_time":586.94,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":585.98,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"The only time that I cannot do it is Thursdays at 11am Eastern.","index":193,"end_time":594.38,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":588.14,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"So as long as it''s not 11 to 12 Eastern.","index":194,"end_time":597.26,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":594.62,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"I''m fully open Thursdays.","index":195,"end_time":599.1,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":597.74,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Could you do 10am I could.","index":196,"end_time":603.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":599.66,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Does that work for you, Carlos?","index":197,"end_time":604.46,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":603.06,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"On Thursdays?","index":198,"end_time":605.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":604.54,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":199,"end_time":605.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":605.3,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"Meg.","index":200,"end_time":606.58,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":606.22,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"We also have.","index":201,"end_time":607.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":606.58,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"We have two CFM calls.","index":202,"end_time":610.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":607.98,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"The.","index":203,"end_time":610.54,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":610.14,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"I think those are changing, though.","index":204,"end_time":612.3,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":610.94,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Okay.","index":205,"end_time":613.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":612.7,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"All right.","index":206,"end_time":613.58,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":613.14,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"Yeah, that works for me.","index":207,"end_time":614.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":613.74,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"Yeah, makes sense.","index":208,"end_time":616.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":615.26,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"What time is it where you''re at?","index":209,"end_time":618.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":616.86,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"9:30Pm oh, my God.","index":210,"end_time":624.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":621.02,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Yo, this should have been an email.","index":211,"end_time":626.87,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":625.43,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"We don''t need a video chat.","index":212,"end_time":628.31,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":626.87,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"No, no, it''s fine.","index":213,"end_time":629.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":628.47,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"It''s fine.","index":214,"end_time":629.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":629.47,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"It''s fine.","index":215,"end_time":630.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":629.99,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"I wanted to meet you guys, like, and.","index":216,"end_time":632.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":630.59,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":217,"end_time":632.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":632.39,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Get to know you better.","index":218,"end_time":633.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":632.71,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So.","index":219,"end_time":634.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":634.07,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":220,"end_time":634.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":634.31,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"And then now that we''ve got to know each other better.","index":221,"end_time":637.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":634.51,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s cool.","index":222,"end_time":638.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":637.59,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Just wanted to ask about that and thank you for your consideration.","index":223,"end_time":642.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":638.79,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Of course.","index":224,"end_time":643.79,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":643.27,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Of course.","index":225,"end_time":644.23,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":643.79,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Whatever works.","index":226,"end_time":645.59,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":644.71,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Minus those.","index":227,"end_time":646.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":645.59,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"That time, we''re good.","index":228,"end_time":647.67,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":646.23,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Okay.","index":229,"end_time":648.19,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":647.67,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"I just rescheduled, so in two weeks.","index":230,"end_time":651.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":648.19,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We''Ll have that.","index":231,"end_time":653.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":652.9,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And then I think the meeting after that will be on New Year''s Day, so I''ll just cancel that one.","index":232,"end_time":660.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":654.26,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"No, we want to have that one, too.","index":233,"end_time":663.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":661.86,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Pull out the champagne.","index":234,"end_time":666.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":665.78,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"We''ll have a party.","index":235,"end_time":669.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":668.74,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"That will mean.","index":236,"end_time":673.54,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":672.74,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"I think we''re going into season four of the podcast.","index":237,"end_time":676.82,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":673.54,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Wow, that''s pretty great.","index":238,"end_time":678.18,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":676.98,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"I heard that a lot of podcasts don''t even make it till three seasons, so.","index":239,"end_time":681.7,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":678.34,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Yeah, most don''t get past episode three.","index":240,"end_time":684.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":681.96,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Really?","index":241,"end_time":686.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":685.64,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":242,"end_time":686.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":686.44,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"That''s new.","index":243,"end_time":687.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":686.88,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"I thought it was like, a year or two years ago.","index":244,"end_time":690.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":687.4,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"It was past episode 10, I think.","index":245,"end_time":692.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":690.36,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":246,"end_time":692.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":692.44,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So now it''s past episode three, so it''s crazy.","index":247,"end_time":695.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":692.84,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Wow.","index":248,"end_time":696.2,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":695.64,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Really be.","index":249,"end_time":697.44,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":696.92,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"You''re, like, in the top 1%.","index":250,"end_time":699.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":697.44,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Like, there are very few podcasts that get past two seasons.","index":251,"end_time":705.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":699.64,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"It doesn''t seem like that because you''re probably seeing, like, these huge podcasts that just go on forever.","index":252,"end_time":711.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":706.28,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"But there are a lot of podcasts out there that get started and just never keep going.","index":253,"end_time":718.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":712.46,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"That is wild.","index":254,"end_time":720.06,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":719.02,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"That is insane.","index":255,"end_time":721.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":720.3,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"I mean, that is even more of a.","index":256,"end_time":723.66,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":721.9,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"An accomplishment.","index":257,"end_time":725.1,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":723.98,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":258,"end_time":725.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":725.1,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We might be scatty and difficult, but we have three seasons under our belt.","index":259,"end_time":729.74,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":725.58,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"You''re consistent.","index":260,"end_time":731.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":729.9,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"That''s the biggest.","index":261,"end_time":732.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":731.1,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"That''s the hardest part.","index":262,"end_time":733.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":732.1,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So.","index":263,"end_time":733.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":733.26,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":264,"end_time":736.38,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":735.74,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Well, this is super fun, and thank you guys for your help.","index":265,"end_time":738.98,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":736.62,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"We appreciate it.","index":266,"end_time":739.82,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":738.98,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Of course.","index":267,"end_time":740.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":740.39,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay, we''ll talk later.","index":268,"end_time":742.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":741.11,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Take care.","index":269,"end_time":743.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":743.35,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"Bye.","index":270,"end_time":744.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":743.91,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"}],"dateString":"2025-12-04T20:30:00.000Z","host_email":"baylee.gunnell@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/88046600611?pwd=5o555CNd3jppz39fBqq2aKtgUYF0MV.1","participants":["baylee.gunnell@marketersindemand.com,cortiz@neach.org,mnorlund@neach.org,igor.zagradjanin@marketersindemand.com","cortiz@neach.org","mnorlund@neach.org","igor.zagradjanin@marketersindemand.com"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01KB4THNR84WDZYH9JGKPNZ4WJ","organizer_email":"baylee.gunnell@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"positive","confidence":0.91,"bullets":["Confirmed payment process for outstanding balance; Baylee to send invoice after meeting.","Agreed to cap podcast production at two episodes per month to stay within point budget.","Delegated Spotify video uploads to Joe starting in January due to his planned vacation.","Secured agreement to shift meeting time earlier to accommodate Igor''s European schedule.","Carlos to receive Illustrator templates to streamline creation of custom quote and thumbnail assets."],"highlights":[{"quote":"Looking really great here... we''ve got stuff scheduled out I think through February.","speaker":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"quote":"We might be scatty and difficult, but we have three seasons under our belt.","speaker":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"quote":"We''ll follow up here shortly then, with just the, the invoice stuff.","speaker":"Baylee Gunnell"}],"topics":["budget","delivery","planning","content"],"model":"openai/gpt-4-1106-preview","version":1,"generated_at":"2025-12-05T17:43:00Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **Podcast Production and Financial Management**\n\nThe team agreed to manage podcast episode production tightly to control costs and stay within budget.\n\n- **NEACH will receive an invoice for the outstanding balance related to Alyssa’s spin-off, which is a significant amount, and the billing will be settled promptly** as Baylee committed to coordinate with Justin immediately after the meeting (02:09).  \n    - Meg emphasized the importance of clearing this balance within the current fiscal year to avoid budget complications.  \n    - Baylee outlined a plan to limit production to **two episodes per month moving forward**, allowing some flexibility to produce three in a month if fewer were done previously.  \n    - This control is intended to prevent continual overages in points, which complicate budget tracking and forecasting.  \n    - Meg confirmed coordination with Joe to better manage point usage and avoid “willy nilly” spending.\n\n- **Podcast content volume is steady, with a backlog scheduled through February and consistent YouTube engagement, especially driven by shorts which account for most of the 791 views** (04:48).  \n    - Baylee highlighted that although 791 views is modest, it’s strong within this niche industry.  \n    - Meg indicated Joe would handle reintroducing Spotify video content, likely starting in January due to his upcoming vacation (05:37).  \n    - The team agreed to hold off on Spotify video production until after the holidays to align with resource availability.\n\n## **Creative Asset Management and Workflow Enhancements**\n\nThe team decided to improve access to creative assets to streamline in-house editing and reduce dependency on external support.\n\n- **NEACH will receive Adobe Illustrator templates for podcast quote cards and thumbnails to enable Joe and Carlos to make edits independently** (07:01).  \n    - Carlos, who has experience with Photoshop but not Illustrator or Figma, welcomed receiving Illustrator files to ease his editing workflow.  \n    - Meg explained Joe’s typical process involves last-minute edits to quote cards and thumbnails, which creates inefficiencies that this handoff aims to reduce.  \n    - Providing the original templates is expected to save time and improve turnaround for asset customization.  \n    - Baylee committed to delivering these assets promptly after the meeting to enable this transition.\n\n## **Meeting Scheduling and Team Coordination**\n\nMeeting times were adjusted to better accommodate international team members and improve participation.\n\n- **The group agreed to move recurring meetings three hours earlier to accommodate Igor’s European time zone, settling on Thursdays at 10am Eastern as the new standard** (09:32).  \n    - Meg clarified her availability, restricting only Thursdays 11am Eastern, which worked well with the proposed time.  \n    - Carlos confirmed the new timing fit within his schedule despite existing CFM calls.  \n    - Baylee planned to reschedule the next meeting accordingly and cancel the one on New Year’s Day, although the team expressed interest in keeping that session.  \n    - This adjustment aims to improve engagement and reduce fatigue for international team members.\n\n## **Podcast Longevity and Market Positioning**\n\nThe team acknowledged the podcast’s strong position in a challenging market, underlining consistency as a key success factor.\n\n- **With three seasons completed and entering season four, the podcast ranks among the top 1% for longevity, far exceeding typical podcast lifespan averages** as Baylee noted industry data showing many podcasts fail past episode three (11:12).  \n    - Meg and Carlos celebrated this milestone as a sign of steady progress despite internal challenges.  \n    - Igor shared updated industry insights confirming shorter average podcast lifespans than previously thought, reinforcing the achievement’s significance.  \n    - Baylee emphasized that consistent output is the hardest part and the main driver of this success.  \n    - This positioning supports ongoing engagement and strengthens the podcast’s market credibility.\n\n## **Content Delivery and Communication Improvements**\n\nThe team plans to improve communication around point usage and content delivery to enhance budget visibility and workflow predictability.\n\n- **Baylee committed to providing clearer notifications when point limits are exceeded to avoid surprises and enable better planning** (04:16).  \n    - This will help NEACH manage their monthly points more effectively and reduce confusion around overages.  \n    - Meg expressed appreciation for this proactive approach, noting it will help keep spending aligned with budget expectations.  \n    - The team agreed to monitor point usage closely and shift excess points forward if needed to maintain balance.  \n    - Improved transparency in usage reporting supports stronger financial control and trust between partners.","outline":null,"keywords":["Podcast production","invoicing","episode scheduling","asset templates","meeting time adjustment","budget reconciliation"],"overview":"- **Podcast Production Management:** Focus on two episodes per month; possible flexibility for a third when needed to control costs.\n\n- **Outstanding Invoice:** NEACH will receive the invoice related to Alyssa’s spin-off. Payment to be settled before fiscal year end.\n\n- **Content Performance:** Podcast backlog scheduled through February; YouTube shorts driving 791 views, strong for niche market.\n\n- **Creative Asset Accessibility:** NEACH to receive Illustrator templates for in-house editing, improving efficiency and turnaround time for assets.\n\n- **Meeting Time Changes:** Recurring meetings moved to Thursdays at 10am Eastern to better fit international team members'' schedules.\n\n- **Podcast Longevity Achievement:** Podcast ranks in top 1% for longevity; strong consistency is key to overcoming market challenges.","action_items":"\n**Baylee Gunnell**\nSend invoice to NEACH for outstanding podcast balance to allow year-end reconciliation (02:10)\nCoordinate with Justin to prepare and dispatch the invoice promptly (02:30)\nProvide Adobe Illustrator and Figma templates for podcast assets to Carlos for internal editing (07:35)\nFollow up with NEACH on points balance and episode scheduling, ensuring future adherence to two episode/month limit (03:50)\nReschedule future meetings to Thursday 10:00 AM Eastern to accommodate all time zones (09:55)\n\n**Carlos**\nReceive and begin using Adobe Illustrator templates for podcast asset editing as provided (07:00)\n\n**Meg Norlund**\nCoordinate internally with Joe regarding the Spotify video efforts resuming in January (05:30)\nTurn around edits on recent podcast videos and communicate any additional asset needs (06:30)\n\n**Igor Zagradjanin**\nApologize for initial email omission and send updated assets including Baylee in CC (03:00)\nRequest meeting time change to accommodate European time zone (09:15)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"aa86d812-d3d0-42e5-807f-878f2c01debd","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
