WITH new_meeting AS (
  INSERT INTO compass_meetings (contract_id, meeting_date, source, external_id, title, participants, duration_seconds, recording_url, transcript, sentiment, raw_metadata, created_at, updated_at)
  VALUES (
    'ade9bb8a-fde3-4756-a63e-11ce7f227292',
    '2025-12-02 21:05:00+00',
    'fireflies',
    '01KBD7SB75HF7FV4J5G4BSW3YH',
    'Ricoh // New North: Weekly Meeting',
    '{"Nathalie Mintjens","Roz","Lou Bogani"}'::text[],
    1618,
    'https://us02web.zoom.us/j/85828735088?pwd=b9W3cDKwBeJQyK00Qs0iP3vvCmTxIZ.1',
    '{"id":"01KBD7SB75HF7FV4J5G4BSW3YH","title":"Ricoh // New North: Weekly Meeting","summary":{"notes":"## **Sales Guide Template Revamp**\n\nThe team decided to update the sales guide title pages to a cleaner, more consistent format while retaining core content and branding elements.\n\n- **Roz confirmed the preference for a clean title page layout with more breathing space around the logo on the bottom left corner, requiring at least an \"R\" length margin from the \"for internal use only\" box** (07:59)  \n    - Linnea reviewed and approved the new front page and table of contents layout with this spacing adjustment.  \n    - The revised title pages will remove the old GUI image and use the new Batch Builder refresh images to maintain consistency.  \n    - Roz asked for placeholders to be added if any images are missing so work can continue in her absence.  \n    - The team expects to complete the revamp and have updated sales guides ready for Roz’s return to ensure smooth progress.\n\n- **Roz plans to send the current Info Print Manager (IPM) sales guide for conversion into the new format, aiming to start this before her vacation** (26:21)  \n    - This IPM update is the next priority after Optimizer sales guide completion.  \n    - Roz emphasized moving quickly on the IPM guide to maintain momentum.  \n    - Natalie and Lou will be the primary owners to begin shifting IPM once the Optimizer guide is finalized.  \n    - The timeline aligns with Roz’s short absence, ensuring deliverables continue without delay.\n\n## **Video Animation and Branding Consistency**\n\nThe team agreed on key visual and audio standards for the Ricoh Total Flow Optimizer overview video to ensure brand consistency and clear messaging.\n\n- **Roz requested that \"Solution Overview\" appear together as the full title to avoid disconnecting the core message** (15:35)  \n    - The video will transition smoothly into the animated product overview after the title display.  \n    - Roz emphasized the importance of seeing the animation live to refine visual flow and pacing.  \n    - The team will combine “Solution Overview” into a single line for clarity on all title screens.  \n    - This sets the foundation for a polished marketing video that fits Ricoh’s brand tone.\n\n- **Roz highlighted that the sound in the logo bumper animation at the end of the video must remain unaltered and no other audio should overlap during this clip** (20:52)  \n    - The bumper is about five seconds with a distinctive “bing” sound essential for brand recognition.  \n    - Roz stressed this audio is standard across all Ricoh videos and should not be muted or replaced.  \n    - Other parts of the video can have audio overlays without restriction.  \n    - This ensures consistent brand audio branding across all platforms.\n\n- **Roz suggested replacing the current icons under key messages with icons from the existing company icon set for visual consistency** (24:00)  \n    - The icons represent \"streamline operations,\" \"automate batching,\" and \"reduce manual intervention.\"  \n    - She will review the icon set and email recommended icons to Natalie and Lou for incorporation.  \n    - Roz wants to avoid introducing new icon styles that conflict with established branding.  \n    - This small change aims to unify the look and feel across all collateral.\n\n## **Product Messaging and Terminology Refinement**\n\nClarifications were made to refine the product messaging for better accuracy and user understanding in the video and sales materials.\n\n- **Roz clarified that the phrase “reduce manual intervention” is more accurate than “reduce manual steps” to describe automation benefits in printing workflows** (17:30)  \n    - Intervention refers to less manual handling of print jobs, which better captures operational savings.  \n    - This subtle wording change helps align messaging with customer pain points and industry terminology.  \n    - The team agreed to update the copy accordingly in both video and sales guide content.  \n    - This precision supports clearer communication of product value.\n\n- **Roz expressed a preference for the balloon graphic style that includes a product hero image inside it, rather than a plain outline balloon** (20:00)  \n    - She felt the hero image balloon better ties the visual to the specific product showcased.  \n    - The team will standardize on this style across the video to maintain thematic consistency.  \n    - This choice supports stronger brand recognition and product association in marketing materials.  \n    - Minor tweaks will be made after seeing the animation in motion.\n\n## **Collaboration and Workflow Efficiency**\n\nThe meeting reinforced smooth collaboration practices and set realistic expectations for timelines and feedback.\n\n- **Roz praised having direct conversations with the team to speed up decision-making on design and content issues** (25:45)  \n    - She noted it reduces back-and-forth and helps clarify details quickly.  \n    - Roz apologized for potentially slowing video designers but prioritized brand alignment over speed.  \n    - Natalie and Lou committed to incorporating Roz’s icon and layout feedback promptly.  \n    - This collaborative rhythm aims to keep deliverables on track despite Roz’s upcoming vacation.\n\n- **Roz committed to sending any pending materials, like the IPM sales guide and additional feedback, before her departure tomorrow** (26:40)  \n    - This ensures the team has all resources needed to continue work without waiting.  \n    - Roz’s proactive approach minimizes bottlenecks during her absence.  \n    - The team agreed to start on IPM guide updates immediately after Optimizer completion.  \n    - Clear ownership and timelines were established to maintain steady progress.","outline":null,"keywords":["Sales Guide","Video Storyboard","Ricoh Total Flow Optimizer","Branding Consistency","Vacation Planning","Iconography"],"overview":"- **Sales Guide Update:** New title pages will have a cleaner layout with proper spacing and updated images for consistency.  \n- **IPM Sales Guide Conversion:** Current guide to be converted to new format before Roz''s vacation; priority after Optimizer guide completion.  \n- **Video Animation Standards:** \"Solution Overview\" will be one title; audio in logo bumper must remain unchanged for brand consistency.  \n- **Icon Consistency:** Existing company icons to be used in messaging for visual uniformity across materials.  \n- **Messaging Precision:** “Reduce manual intervention” replaces “reduce manual steps” for clarity in product automation benefits.  \n- **Collaboration Efficiency:** Direct discussions encouraged for quicker decisions; Roz to send pending materials before vacation to avoid delays.","action_items":"\n**Roz Regan**\nReview and email icon choices from Ricoh icon set for video use (25:34)\nPossibly send the current Info Print Manager (IPM) sales guide for template migration before leaving (13:53)\nProvide feedback and final approval on animation once first version is created (20:45)\n\n**Nathalie Mintjens**\nUpdate sales guide title pages with new template, remove old GUI images, and maintain refreshed product images; ensure logos have proper spacing (08:08)\nCoordinate with Lou to check availability of images and create placeholders for any missing assets (12:51)\nMake storyboard changes combining ''Solution Overview'' text and update video transitions per Roz’s instructions (14:41)\nPrepare first version of video animation and ensure compliance with no audio overlap on logo bumper (20:52)\n\n**Lou Bogani**\nAssist Nathalie in reviewing image assets for sales guide and updating title pages as per instructions (12:51)\n"},"duration":26.969999313354492,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"id":1,"name":"Roz"},{"id":2,"name":"Lou Bogani"}],"sentences":[{"text":"How''s it going, Roz?","index":0,"end_time":7.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":6.08,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Oh, not too bad.","index":1,"end_time":8.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":7.28,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Sorry, I just.","index":2,"end_time":9.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":8.32,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"I just washed my hands and now I have water underneath my watch.","index":3,"end_time":12.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":9.12,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"And I''m like.","index":4,"end_time":13.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":12.72,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Feels icky.","index":5,"end_time":16.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":14.96,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":6,"end_time":17.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":17.28,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":7,"end_time":19.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":18.8,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"So that was the sound, not you guys.","index":8,"end_time":21.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":19.24,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"My watch.","index":9,"end_time":22.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":22.16,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Are you coming back from vacation or you''re going on vacation?","index":10,"end_time":29.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":26,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I am going on.","index":11,"end_time":31.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":30.07,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"So I.","index":12,"end_time":32.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":31.51,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Yes.","index":13,"end_time":32.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":32.31,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Thank you so much for the quick movement and flexibility on the call.","index":14,"end_time":38.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":32.71,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"I appreciate it.","index":15,"end_time":39.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":38.35,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Yeah, I''m.","index":16,"end_time":40.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":40.39,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"I''m heading out to Mexico, actually, for a few days with the.","index":17,"end_time":47.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":40.99,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"The hubster.","index":18,"end_time":48.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":47.19,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"So.","index":19,"end_time":48.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":48.23,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":20,"end_time":49.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":49.27,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Nice.","index":21,"end_time":50.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":50.55,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Which part?","index":22,"end_time":51.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":50.99,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Mexico City.","index":23,"end_time":53.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":52.55,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"He.","index":24,"end_time":54.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":54.23,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"My husband, who is the luckier one of us, both, he.","index":25,"end_time":60,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":56,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"We went to one of his conferences for his work, and at this conference is.","index":26,"end_time":65.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":60.4,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"It''s like a global, international kind of situation.","index":27,"end_time":68.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":65.64,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"And they have these really great.","index":28,"end_time":69.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":68.48,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"They do, like, raffles to, you know, help bolster their.","index":29,"end_time":74.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":70.64,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Their budgets.","index":30,"end_time":75.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":75.04,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"And they usually have really great wrap.","index":31,"end_time":77.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":75.92,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Like, the prizes are usually really good.","index":32,"end_time":79.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":77.6,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"And one of them happened to be two nights at a really nice hotel in Mexico City with a trip out to Teotihuacan and spa time and meals included and stuff like that.","index":33,"end_time":94.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":79.08,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"So that''s why we''re going to Mexico City.","index":34,"end_time":95.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":94.25,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Wow, nice.","index":35,"end_time":97.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":96.41,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":36,"end_time":99.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":99.37,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"So.","index":37,"end_time":99.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":99.73,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"And we baked a few more days in there because we''re like, well, if we''re going all that way, we may as well sell, you know, stay some extra time as well.","index":38,"end_time":105.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":99.97,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"So I have strong armed him into taking me to the Museum of Anthropology out there.","index":39,"end_time":113.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":105.77,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"So.","index":40,"end_time":113.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":113.33,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"And he''s on a quest to find the best queso fundido he can find.","index":41,"end_time":118.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":115.41,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"I''m like, okay, priorities.","index":42,"end_time":120.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":118.73,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"It''s.","index":43,"end_time":123.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":123.01,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"That''s good.","index":44,"end_time":124.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":123.57,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"Funny you should see him.","index":45,"end_time":126.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":125.49,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"He''s got.","index":46,"end_time":127.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":126.97,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"I''m kidding you not.","index":47,"end_time":129.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":127.57,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"It''s like an 8 and a half by 11 sheet in, like 10 font of all of these different restaurants, both sides, by the way.","index":48,"end_time":139.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":129.25,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"So it''s like, you know, two pages of this stuff.","index":49,"end_time":141.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":139.02,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"And he spent an ungodly amount of time on Sunday afternoon researching all of them to see which ones he wanted to go to.","index":50,"end_time":148.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":141.54,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"I''m like, okay.","index":51,"end_time":149.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":148.98,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"I''m like.","index":52,"end_time":153.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":152.58,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"And then when I asked him what the point of it all was, he was like, queso fundido, man.","index":53,"end_time":157.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":153.3,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"I''m like, okay.","index":54,"end_time":158.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":157.5,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Sorry if that was not implied.","index":55,"end_time":162.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":160.55,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"I apologize.","index":56,"end_time":163.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":162.91,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Yeah, Queso fundido and guacamole.","index":57,"end_time":170.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":167.99,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"And he''s a happy man, apparently.","index":58,"end_time":171.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":170.07,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"So.","index":59,"end_time":171.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":171.71,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"I''m like, okay, that''s fine.","index":60,"end_time":173.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":171.91,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"So he''s never taken me to a bad restaurant yet, so I leave the restaurants up to him.","index":61,"end_time":178.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":174.39,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"So.","index":62,"end_time":179.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":178.87,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Because he does so much research, apparently.","index":63,"end_time":182.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":179.83,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Oh, yeah, yeah.","index":64,"end_time":183.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":182.31,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Well, he did the same thing.","index":65,"end_time":184.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":183.59,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Went to London.","index":66,"end_time":185.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":184.63,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"We were in London like earlier this year for three days, and he had again, a two page sheet of pubs that he had researched.","index":67,"end_time":195.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":185.23,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Yeah, exactly.","index":68,"end_time":197.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":196.25,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":69,"end_time":197.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":197.17,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"That look.","index":70,"end_time":198.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":197.69,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Yes, that look.","index":71,"end_time":199.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":198.21,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"And I''m like, you know, we''re only there for two days.","index":72,"end_time":201.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":199.41,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Like, how many of these do you think we''re going to hit?","index":73,"end_time":203.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":201.89,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Well, to his credit, he thought about it and we hit like five of them in one afternoon because they were all like in the same neighborhood, right?","index":74,"end_time":213.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":203.77,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"They were all like down from each other kind of thing.","index":75,"end_time":216.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":213.41,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"I''m like, oh my God, I''m gonna be so hungover by this time we''re done with all these pubs.","index":76,"end_time":221.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":216.69,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"But yeah, I''m like, dude, how many of these do you think we''re gonna hit?","index":77,"end_time":225.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":221.97,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"He must have had like, I don''t know, like 50 or 60.","index":78,"end_time":228.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":225.85,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"I mean, it''s London, there''s so many pubs, they''re everywhere.","index":79,"end_time":232.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":228.93,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"But yeah, yeah, he was on a mission.","index":80,"end_time":235.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":232.69,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Just like the case of fundido, apparently.","index":81,"end_time":238.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":235.89,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"So here I am.","index":82,"end_time":240.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":238.29,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"That''s a good travel partner to have though.","index":83,"end_time":244.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":242.06,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah, absolutely.","index":84,"end_time":245.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":244.7,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, he''s.","index":85,"end_time":247.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":245.78,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"I mean, he''s the concierge.","index":86,"end_time":248.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":247.22,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"So I leave like all this kind of stuff up to him, quite frankly, because he hears about it way before I do.","index":87,"end_time":254.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":249.18,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Like, way before I do, he will, you know, he''ll talk to like his buddies, and before I know it, we have like a whole, you know, everything''s planned, but, but he does, he does tend to overbook us and I always have to remind him not to do that.","index":88,"end_time":270.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":255.1,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Like, I''m like, dude, we have like 24 hours.","index":89,"end_time":276.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":272.57,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Where are you gonna sandwich that?","index":90,"end_time":277.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":276.21,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"You know, insert activity in.","index":91,"end_time":280.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":277.89,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"And I''m.","index":92,"end_time":280.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":280.05,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And you know, he did it again to me today.","index":93,"end_time":282.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":280.61,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"He was like, he''s like, well, you know, they have one of those hop on, hop off buses in Mexico City.","index":94,"end_time":287.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":282.33,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"And he''s like, they''ve got like three different routes.","index":95,"end_time":289.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":287.05,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"It looks like a lot of fun.","index":96,"end_time":290.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":289.77,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"And we always have good, like, luck with those buses.","index":97,"end_time":293.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":290.65,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"I have to admit, like, if you''re trying to get around someplace and you don''t want to have a car and you don''t want to have to deal with all of that, then the hop on, hop off buses are the bomb.","index":98,"end_time":302.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":293.33,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Ye, they, they are great.","index":99,"end_time":303.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":302.13,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"Yeah, they are.","index":100,"end_time":304.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":303.19,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"They, they''re super touristy.","index":101,"end_time":306.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":304.15,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"But man, they work right.","index":102,"end_time":307.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":306.03,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Like, they''re touristy for a reason.","index":103,"end_time":309.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":307.35,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"So we did that in Singapore, we''ve done it in, we did it in, in Spain.","index":104,"end_time":316.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":310.63,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"A few places in Spain, they work great.","index":105,"end_time":318.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":316.11,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"So he wants to do that in Mexico City.","index":106,"end_time":320.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":318.87,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"And I''m like, dude, that''s usually like, a day''s worth of our time.","index":107,"end_time":323.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":320.55,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"And I''m not saying no, but I''m just saying we''ve got this tour out to Teotihuacan.","index":108,"end_time":329.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":323.83,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"We''ve got, you know, this lunch place that he wants to go to in the middle of one day.","index":109,"end_time":335.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":330.15,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Then we''ve got, you know, the spa time booked at another day.","index":110,"end_time":340.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":335.4,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"And I''m like, which day do you want to do this?","index":111,"end_time":342.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":340.24,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"It''s like a.","index":112,"end_time":344.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":343.96,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"Feels like a marathon rather than vacation a bit.","index":113,"end_time":348.119,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":344.92,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"Sometimes.","index":114,"end_time":349.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":348.44,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Sometimes it can be.","index":115,"end_time":350.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":349.32,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":116,"end_time":351.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":350.68,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":117,"end_time":351.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":351.32,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"The only way I can get him to stay in one place for any length of time is if the hotel has a hot tub.","index":118,"end_time":357.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":351.96,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"I''m not.","index":119,"end_time":358.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":357.81,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"And I''m.","index":120,"end_time":358.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":358.29,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"And I''m not joking.","index":121,"end_time":359.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":358.89,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"I mean that sincerely.","index":122,"end_time":361.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":360.05,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"I can get him to go anywhere if there''s a hot tub involved.","index":123,"end_time":364.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":361.57,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":124,"end_time":366.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":366.05,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":125,"end_time":368.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":367.81,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Thank you, Natalie.","index":126,"end_time":369.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":368.33,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Oh, yeah.","index":127,"end_time":372.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":371.89,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"He''s crazy.","index":128,"end_time":373.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":372.53,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":129,"end_time":374.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":373.57,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Everything I hear about your husband, I''m.","index":130,"end_time":375.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":374.01,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Just, like, such a character, an interesting person.","index":131,"end_time":379.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":375.65,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"To be fair, though, it never wavers.","index":132,"end_time":381.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":379.33,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"He knows what he likes, and it''s.","index":133,"end_time":384.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":382.05,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"It does, for the most part, stay the same.","index":134,"end_time":386.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":384.29,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"And he is flexible.","index":135,"end_time":388.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":386.85,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"When there''s things I want to do, he will definitely go out of his way to do those things for me.","index":136,"end_time":392.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":388.29,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"So I have to hand it to him.","index":137,"end_time":395.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":393.41,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"You know, we do things that we like together, for sure.","index":138,"end_time":398.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":395.97,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"And, I mean, I dragged that man through way too many cathedrals in Spain because they''re everywhere, and they''re.","index":139,"end_time":405.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":398.69,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"But they''re beautiful, right?","index":140,"end_time":406.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":405.89,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Like, the architecture.","index":141,"end_time":407.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":406.97,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"For me, it''s the architecture and the history of the thing.","index":142,"end_time":410.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":407.97,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"And he''s just looking around, going, stone.","index":143,"end_time":414.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":410.45,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":144,"end_time":419.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":419.04,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"This is the man that walked into the British Museum and announced to me that he wanted to see the statues made out of stone of the men with beards.","index":145,"end_time":426.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":419.48,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"I remember this.","index":146,"end_time":429,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":428.24,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Okay.","index":147,"end_time":429.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":429,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":148,"end_time":430.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":429.84,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"I''m like, dude, you gotta.","index":149,"end_time":432.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":430.88,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"You gotta narrow it down a bit.","index":150,"end_time":434,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":432.24,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":151,"end_time":440.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":440.33,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"It turned out to be the.","index":152,"end_time":442.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":440.61,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"The men with beards, with bodies of horses and, like, winged bodies of horses.","index":153,"end_time":449.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":443.61,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"I''m like, lead with that the next time, because then I could have told you where they were, because I know exactly what you''re talking about.","index":154,"end_time":453.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":449.09,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"When do you leave?","index":155,"end_time":458.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":457.13,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Tomorrow.","index":156,"end_time":460.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":459.37,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Okay.","index":157,"end_time":461.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":460.57,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":158,"end_time":462.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":461.61,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":159,"end_time":462.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":462.09,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"And then we come.","index":160,"end_time":463.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":462.53,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"We''re back Tuesday, so it''s.","index":161,"end_time":464.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":463.13,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"It''s real quick.","index":162,"end_time":465.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":464.49,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"You know what I mean?","index":163,"end_time":465.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":465.09,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Like, we just had sort of, like, the two free days, and we didn''t have, like, a ton of vacation time left, so just a couple of days.","index":164,"end_time":473.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":465.77,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Okay.","index":165,"end_time":474.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":473.83,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":166,"end_time":475.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":474.87,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"And, Natalie, did I.","index":167,"end_time":477.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":476.15,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"On the.","index":168,"end_time":477.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":477.27,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"On marked up.","index":169,"end_time":479.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":477.99,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Did I go through the sales guide template?","index":170,"end_time":482.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":479.19,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Did I put notes on There or did I just think about it?","index":171,"end_time":487.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":483.03,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"The one that I sent over?","index":172,"end_time":490.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":488.95,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah, I think you said that you were going to review it with Linnea.","index":173,"end_time":493.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":490.79,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I don''t think.","index":174,"end_time":494.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":493.83,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And I did, and I thought about putting notes on it, and then maybe I said, no, let''s not do that, because I knew I was talking to you guys guys today.","index":175,"end_time":500.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":494.31,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"So I have some feedback on that.","index":176,"end_time":503.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":501.01,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"She loves the, like, the front page, the table of contents.","index":177,"end_time":509.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":504.93,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"It all looks good.","index":178,"end_time":509.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":509.09,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"The only thing she was requesting on the front page and again on the second page, is that the logo on the bottom left corner.","index":179,"end_time":517.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":509.97,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":180,"end_time":519.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":518.45,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"It needs more space around it between that thing that says for internal use only.","index":181,"end_time":525.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":519.01,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Okay.","index":182,"end_time":526.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":526.57,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Yeah, it needs like an.","index":183,"end_time":528.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":527.21,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"At least an R length around it.","index":184,"end_time":531.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":528.89,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"And she thought that was just maybe a bit tight.","index":185,"end_time":533.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":531.65,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"So if we could just give it a bit more space, it''s like, yeah, sure.","index":186,"end_time":538.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":534.57,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Easy, easy peasy, you know, nothing.","index":187,"end_time":540.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":538.61,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"I''m like, yeah, no worries.","index":188,"end_time":542.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":540.93,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"And then I would say the same for this one.","index":189,"end_time":543.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":542.01,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"If it can just go down into the corner a tiny bit more away from the box.","index":190,"end_time":547.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":543.85,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Same thing.","index":191,"end_time":549.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":548.49,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Like, just a little bit more breathing space around it and we''re good.","index":192,"end_time":552.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":549.13,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Okay.","index":193,"end_time":553.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":552.8,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"And then on these ones, she actually really liked the first one, which I don''t hate either.","index":194,"end_time":562.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":554.24,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"And I know we talked about it back and forth about adding the.","index":195,"end_time":565.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":562.24,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"The image of the, like, the actual product on, and she was like, well, you.","index":196,"end_time":570.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":567.04,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"You know, you see it throughout the document.","index":197,"end_time":572.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":570.8,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Anyway, does it matter?","index":198,"end_time":573.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":572.4,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"I''m like, no, not really, but I just didn''t want to go too far away from it.","index":199,"end_time":576.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":573.36,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"So I think we''ll go with this one right here.","index":200,"end_time":580.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":577.04,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Yeah, she just really likes really clean.","index":201,"end_time":583.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":581.95,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"You know, we can go longer with the box if we need to or whatever, you know, depending on the content.","index":202,"end_time":588.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":583.87,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"So I think this one looks great.","index":203,"end_time":590.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":588.83,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"If we could just be mindful though, of the gradient on the balloon, because it.","index":204,"end_time":597.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":592.27,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"The one on the title page looks darker somehow.","index":205,"end_time":602.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":597.91,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"So I don''t know if it''s different.","index":206,"end_time":604.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":602.27,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"It looks a little darker.","index":207,"end_time":605.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":604.19,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Okay.","index":208,"end_time":606.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":606.19,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":209,"end_time":608.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":607.31,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Just.","index":210,"end_time":608.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":608.59,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"If we could just review it.","index":211,"end_time":609.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":608.79,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Not the end of the world, because we were just talking about, like, placements and stuff.","index":212,"end_time":614.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":610.19,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"So I think we''re fine.","index":213,"end_time":615.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":614.03,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"And then if you could scroll down again, Natalie.","index":214,"end_time":620.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":617.07,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Okay.","index":215,"end_time":621.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":620.67,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah, so we said no to that one and.","index":216,"end_time":625.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":621.15,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Yeah, no to this one.","index":217,"end_time":626.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":625.03,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"And then she agreed with me.","index":218,"end_time":628.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":626.15,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"She was totally fine with keeping the content pages the way they are.","index":219,"end_time":631.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":628.51,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"So I think just to move this forward while I''m away, if we could just revamp all of the title pages.","index":220,"end_time":641.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":632.19,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Like the next one is Key capabilities.","index":221,"end_time":642.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":641.23,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"As an example, keep all the content, you know, pages the same.","index":222,"end_time":647.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":642.91,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Just each one of these title pages into the new format and then fire it back over to me.","index":223,"end_time":653.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":647.91,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"I think will be good.","index":224,"end_time":654.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":653.23,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"So.","index":225,"end_time":654.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":654.51,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Okay, great.","index":226,"end_time":655.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":654.91,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":227,"end_time":656.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":656.03,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"For these title pages.","index":228,"end_time":658.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":656.99,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Roz.","index":229,"end_time":659.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":658.55,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So we completely get rid of this GUI image here?","index":230,"end_time":663.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":659.03,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, we''re getting rid of it.","index":231,"end_time":665.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":664.12,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Yep.","index":232,"end_time":666,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":665.48,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Yeah, we''ll go with the new version.","index":233,"end_time":668.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":666,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"So this.","index":234,"end_time":669.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":668.6,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"The one, the first one.","index":235,"end_time":671.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":670.36,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Yeah, little.","index":236,"end_time":673.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":673,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Just.","index":237,"end_time":674.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":673.68,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Just.","index":238,"end_time":674.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":674.12,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Yeah, it just needs to look like that.","index":239,"end_time":675.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":674.48,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Like, most of these title pages have, like, obviously, like a title.","index":240,"end_time":679.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":675.88,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Like, so the next one would be key capabilities in place of why, you know, why Optimizer, blah, blah, blah.","index":241,"end_time":685.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":679.32,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"And then just keep the content and that goes in the white box and we''re done.","index":242,"end_time":690.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":685.88,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Okay.","index":243,"end_time":691.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":691.04,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Okay.","index":244,"end_time":692.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":691.76,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"And original image.","index":245,"end_time":694.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":692.8,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"If.","index":246,"end_time":695.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":695.12,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Yeah, if you woul