.","index":336,"end_time":924.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":923.72,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"So it does.","index":337,"end_time":925,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":924.28,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"I would like Solution Overview to be on the same line, or however we want to call it.","index":338,"end_time":932.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":925.159,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Okay.","index":339,"end_time":933.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":932.76,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Because that''s what it is.","index":340,"end_time":935.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":934.12,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Right.","index":341,"end_time":935.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":935.16,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"It''s the Ricoh Total Flow Optimizer Solution Overview.","index":342,"end_time":938.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":935.4,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"That''s the.","index":343,"end_time":938.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":938.48,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"The actual title of the thing.","index":344,"end_time":941.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":939.01,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"And yeah, it needs to be all together, if that makes sense, so that a person knows what they''re.","index":345,"end_time":951.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":944.53,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"You know, what they''re doing.","index":346,"end_time":953.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":952.13,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"I''m okay with these being Rico Total Flow Optimizer.","index":347,"end_time":957.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":953.21,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Stop.","index":348,"end_time":957.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":957.57,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"And then Solution Overview.","index":349,"end_time":960.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":958.05,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Stop is okay, but it''s.","index":350,"end_time":963.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":960.37,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"It''s literally the title of the entire shooting match.","index":351,"end_time":965.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":963.49,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"So I want to be sure that it''s.","index":352,"end_time":967.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":965.89,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Makes sense.","index":353,"end_time":968.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":967.76,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Okay.","index":354,"end_time":969.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":968.88,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Yeah, got it.","index":355,"end_time":971.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":969.84,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"So we''ll combine those, and then after that, it transitions into the animated video, which will play for just a couple of seconds.","index":356,"end_time":980.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":971.44,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And then we have these videos that you provided.","index":357,"end_time":984.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":982.16,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Right.","index":358,"end_time":985.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":985.2,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"All of that fun stuff.","index":359,"end_time":987.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":985.6,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Okay.","index":360,"end_time":987.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":987.12,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"All right.","index":361,"end_time":989.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":988.64,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And then here, streamline your operations Automate job action and reduce manual intervention.","index":362,"end_time":997.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":989.08,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Here we created new icons.","index":363,"end_time":1004.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1002.01,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":364,"end_time":1005.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1004.89,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"And I''m.","index":365,"end_time":1006.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1005.45,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"I''m on the fence about how this is going to look.","index":366,"end_time":1010.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1006.65,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"I can''t remember what we had there to begin with.","index":367,"end_time":1016.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1014.65,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"I think it was like, potentially, oh, I see your cat''s tail.","index":368,"end_time":1021.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1016.77,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"That''s so funny.","index":369,"end_time":1022.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1021.74,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"I thought I had like, some views maybe of the actual product, but I can''t.","index":370,"end_time":1031.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1023.86,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"I can''t be sure.","index":371,"end_time":1032.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1031.14,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"So let''s leave it for now.","index":372,"end_time":1035.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1032.26,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"I kind of want to see it.","index":373,"end_time":1036.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1035.66,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"I.","index":374,"end_time":1037.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1036.98,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Like I said, I feel like I''m coming to the point now where I''m like, I need to see what it looks like live.","index":375,"end_time":1041.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1037.54,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":376,"end_time":1042.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1042.02,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"But I will say streamline operations is fine.","index":377,"end_time":1047.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1043.7,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Automate batching is fine, but it really is reduced manual intervention and not steps.","index":378,"end_time":1055.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1048.26,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"I know it''s kind of tedious, but intervention in printing land means that there''s less manual touches of a print job.","index":379,"end_time":1068.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1057.7,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"So it won''t.","index":380,"end_time":1069.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1068.98,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"It isn''t always necessarily about the steps in a process, if that makes sense.","index":381,"end_time":1073.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1069.86,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Mm.","index":382,"end_time":1074.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1074.38,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":383,"end_time":1075.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1075.34,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"So if we could just make it intervention.","index":384,"end_time":1077.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1075.78,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"I think that''s fine.","index":385,"end_time":1078.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1077.38,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":386,"end_time":1080.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1079.66,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"And then we did some fancy schmancy things about how this will look.","index":387,"end_time":1085.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1080.1,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":388,"end_time":1087.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1086.7,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And then this computer screen.","index":389,"end_time":1089.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1087.14,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So this is just going to be a.","index":390,"end_time":1090.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1089.34,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Like a quick transition.","index":391,"end_time":1092.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1091.02,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":392,"end_time":1093.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1093.34,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"From this computer onto the GUI itself.","index":393,"end_time":1096.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1093.86,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Okay.","index":394,"end_time":1097.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1097.02,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"So we don''t have to worry about, like people not being able to see.","index":395,"end_time":1100.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1097.54,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"This is just perfect.","index":396,"end_time":1101.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1100.53,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"I figured that''s what was going on.","index":397,"end_time":1103.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1101.97,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"So thanks for.","index":398,"end_time":1104.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1103.61,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Thanks for explaining that.","index":399,"end_time":1106.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1104.69,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"That makes sense to me.","index":400,"end_time":1107.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1106.17,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Although I will say the three fingers on the computer look really creepy to me.","index":401,"end_time":1111.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1107.41,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"But it''s like the claw coming up from underneath.","index":402,"end_time":1117.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1112.93,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"So maybe.","index":403,"end_time":1119.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1118.37,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Let''s see how it looks.","index":404,"end_time":1120.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1119.65,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Of course, is still is different than moving, but if it looks very claw.","index":405,"end_time":1125.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1120.81,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Like perhaps we get rid of the fingers and it''s just a zoom in on the computer.","index":406,"end_time":1129.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1125.05,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"But I do like kind of that personal interaction.","index":407,"end_time":1132.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1130.17,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"So maybe it''s two hands on the computer doing something as opposed to just, you know, the claw coming in.","index":408,"end_time":1138.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1132.85,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":409,"end_time":1139.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1139.05,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Okay.","index":410,"end_time":1140.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1140.25,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":411,"end_time":1141.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1141.13,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"No claw.","index":412,"end_time":1148.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1148.09,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"I honestly thought that''s what you''re gonna put there.","index":413,"end_time":1153.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1151.45,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Ensure this isn''t a claw.","index":414,"end_time":1154.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1153.25,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"The claw.","index":415,"end_time":1159.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1159.35,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"And then we do a little bit about the.","index":416,"end_time":1162.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1160.71,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"This, the screens.","index":417,"end_time":1164.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1163.11,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"And then it blazes into Rico.","index":418,"end_time":1168.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1164.55,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Imagine change now with that line.","index":419,"end_time":1173.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1168.59,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"The third slot.","index":420,"end_time":1177.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1175.99,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"The third picture on low.","index":421,"end_time":1179.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1177.35,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":422,"end_time":1179.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1179.23,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"That.","index":423,"end_time":1179.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1179.63,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Do we feel that maybe it should match the.","index":424,"end_time":1184.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1180.39,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Like the inside of that balloon should be the same as what you did earlier on this.","index":425,"end_time":1191.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1185.21,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Like that one.","index":426,"end_time":1192.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1191.85,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":427,"end_time":1193.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1192.53,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Do we think it should be the same?","index":428,"end_time":1196.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1194.65,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Because I feel like we didn''t use the line, you know, the outline balloon anywhere else.","index":429,"end_time":1203.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1198.81,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"And we didn''t use this balloon anywhere else.","index":430,"end_time":1206.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1204.17,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"So I''m like, I feel like we should pick one.","index":431,"end_time":1209.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1206.61,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Maybe you have a preference?","index":432,"end_time":1212.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1210.74,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Well, I like the one with the Hero image in it personally.","index":433,"end_time":1215.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1213.14,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Okay.","index":434,"end_time":1216.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1215.86,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Because it''s specific to, you know, this product.","index":435,"end_time":1219.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1216.98,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Right.","index":436,"end_time":1220.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1219.86,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"So, yeah, yeah, so let''s try that.","index":437,"end_time":1223.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1220.42,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"And I think with those minor adjustments, I think you can go ahead and have them animate it.","index":438,"end_time":1230.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1223.42,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Okay.","index":439,"end_time":1230.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1230.26,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Yeah, I''m sure there''ll be a little bit of fine tuning no matter what.","index":440,"end_time":1235.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1231.3,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Like, but I think now I need to see it live because I''ve gotten to the point where I can only imagine so much in my head and I don''t want to over imagine it either.","index":441,"end_time":1245.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1235.78,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":442,"end_time":1245.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1245.36,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Okay, well, so, yeah, we''ll make these updates and then create the first version of the animation.","index":443,"end_time":1252.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1246.24,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"See what it can you.","index":444,"end_time":1254.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1252.88,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"I''m so sorry.","index":445,"end_time":1254.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1254.28,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Can you go down to the bottom again to the logo bumper?","index":446,"end_time":1257.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1254.88,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Okay.","index":447,"end_time":1260.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1259.6,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"So that audio there, that says with Ricoh Total Flow Optimizer, that can''t be over this animation.","index":448,"end_time":1268.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1260.56,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Okay.","index":449,"end_time":1269.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1269.31,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Because this animation has a.","index":450,"end_time":1271.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1269.91,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"It.","index":451,"end_time":1272.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1271.79,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"When you run it, it goes.","index":452,"end_time":1273.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1272.11,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"It has like a little sound clip that goes with it.","index":453,"end_time":1276.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1273.87,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"And that sound clip can''t go away.","index":454,"end_time":1278.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1276.59,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"So just so for clarity purposes, there can''t be any audio over this particular clip.","index":455,"end_time":1285.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1279.47,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Everything else is fair game.","index":456,"end_time":1286.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1285.71,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Okay.","index":457,"end_time":1288.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1288.11,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Yeah, just so we''re clear, because otherwise I''ll get my wrist slapped.","index":458,"end_time":1294.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1289.15,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"But yeah, if you run that little animation, it''s like five seconds, not even.","index":459,"end_time":1299.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1295.78,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"And it does like a bing, bing.","index":460,"end_time":1302.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1299.94,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"It bings.","index":461,"end_time":1303.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1302.46,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"It makes a little sound.","index":462,"end_time":1304.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1303.14,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"So.","index":463,"end_time":1305.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1304.82,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Okay.","index":464,"end_time":1307.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1306.82,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":465,"end_time":1308.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1307.86,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Yeah, I did hear that.","index":466,"end_time":1311.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1310.42,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, yeah.","index":467,"end_time":1314.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1312.34,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"So I can''t get rid of that.","index":468,"end_time":1315.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1314.14,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"I mean, well, I could get rid of it, but I. I shouldn''t get rid of it is basically how that goes.","index":469,"end_time":1319.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1315.14,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Because that''s like the.","index":470,"end_time":1320.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1319.6,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"The exit for every RICO video everywhere, apparently.","index":471,"end_time":1324.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1320.64,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"So.","index":472,"end_time":1324.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1324.32,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":473,"end_time":1325.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1325.36,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Okay.","index":474,"end_time":1327.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1326.64,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, that was it.","index":475,"end_time":1328.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1327.12,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Okay.","index":476,"end_time":1329.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1329.2,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"I did see.","index":477,"end_time":1330.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1329.56,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Yeah, I think it''s coming along.","index":478,"end_time":1331.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1330.16,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":479,"end_time":1332.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1332.08,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And then you said once this one is done, we''ll kind of use it as a basis for other overview videos.","index":480,"end_time":1338.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1333.84,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah, I have to review it with everyone first.","index":481,"end_time":1341.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1339.04,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"But I wouldn''t mind, like, I wouldn''t mind doing it for IPM and for rpd.","index":482,"end_time":1346.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1341.28,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"So the COD Vol Have a similar sort of look and feel.","index":483,"end_time":1349.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1346.07,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"I am going to keep my how to videos the same so that the.","index":484,"end_time":1353.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1350.27,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"And using that intro that you guys did for all of them, all the different Hero products, because those I need to be able to change on the fly really easily.","index":485,"end_time":1363.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1354.51,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Whereas I feel like the overview are more marketing and should have a bit slicker look because those are going to be on web pages and social media potentially and things like that.","index":486,"end_time":1376.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1363.79,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"So I just wanted them to have a cleaner, slicker kind of look.","index":487,"end_time":1382.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1376.23,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"I am tempted to say, like, on that slide above where it says, like, automated batching and all the rest of it, that instead of using those icons because they aren''t quite the same as our icon set, is to maybe use some of the style that Lou has pulled in with those tabs, you know, like the white tabs that go across the, you know, the, the pages to just to loop it in a tiny bit with what we''re doing with all the other collateral pieces.","index":488,"end_time":1417.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1383.67,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"But yeah, if you go to the very top.","index":489,"end_time":1422.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1420.14,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Yeah, that white.","index":490,"end_time":1422.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1422.1,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"The white.","index":491,"end_time":1423.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1423.1,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"I call it the tab.","index":492,"end_time":1425.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1424.3,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Yeah, that white box, like replace the icons.","index":493,"end_time":1429.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1425.34,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Well, and I think maybe the box comes from left to right, let''s say, and then streamline operations goes on top of it.","index":494,"end_time":1438.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1430.78,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Okay, maybe.","index":495,"end_time":1444.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1442.54,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Okay.","index":496,"end_time":1446.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1446.14,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":497,"end_time":1447.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1447.26,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Because I think that''s what''s driving me a bit crazy with those icons that are on.","index":498,"end_time":1452.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1447.74,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"On there, is that they''re not the same as our icon set because they don''t have the little white box in the bottom right corner.","index":499,"end_time":1459.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1452.51,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Would it be nice to just use the outline drawings and not have the backgrounds?","index":500,"end_time":1466.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1461.15,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Well, we still use the.","index":501,"end_time":1470.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1468.75,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Still use the box as the.","index":502,"end_time":1471.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1470.19,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"As the line drawing anyway.","index":503,"end_time":1473.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1471.75,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Right, Yeah, I think that''s what''s throwing me off about it, honestly.","index":504,"end_time":1478.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1473.63,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"So, I mean, you know, maybe we can think of another way to do it incorporating those.","index":505,"end_time":1485.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1479.39,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"I.","index":506,"end_time":1485.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1485.07,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"The.","index":507,"end_time":1485.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1485.39,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"The tab.","index":508,"end_time":1486.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1485.71,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Like if the tab came out and maybe the icon is, you know, shows up and then streamline operations underneath it.","index":509,"end_time":1496.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1486.31,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"I just, I just think that those icons need to look like they came from our icon set.","index":510,"end_time":1501.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1496.35,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"I just don''t want to do anything new.","index":511,"end_time":1505.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1501.51,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Okay.","index":512,"end_time":1507.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1506.82,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":513,"end_time":1508.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1507.62,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Because I know that we have like that one for automated batching.","index":514,"end_time":1512.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1508.42,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"We actually have an icon for batching in our icon set.","index":515,"end_time":1517.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1512.1,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"And I think if we''re going to talk about batching, we should use batching.","index":516,"end_time":1521.699,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1518.26,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"So why don''t I do this?","index":517,"end_time":1524.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1523.62,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Why don''t I just take a quick look at our icon set and I''ll send you an email, one for each of these icons and we can go from there.","index":518,"end_time":1532.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1524.7,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Okay.","index":519,"end_time":1533.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1533.15,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":520,"end_time":1534.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1534.19,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"So it''s streamline ops, it''s automate batching, and it''s reduce manual steps.","index":521,"end_time":1548.669,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1534.67,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Okay, let me look at the.","index":522,"end_time":1552.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1551.07,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Our icon set and I''ll choose like three for you.","index":523,"end_time":1555.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1552.43,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Okay.","index":524,"end_time":1556.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1555.71,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":525,"end_time":1557.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1556.75,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"I''m apologizing to the designers for video right now, but I just don''t want to introduce new icons if I don''t have to.","index":526,"end_time":1564.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1558.04,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":527,"end_time":1565.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1565.32,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Okay.","index":528,"end_time":1566.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1565.96,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":529,"end_time":1566.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1566.44,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Okay.","index":530,"end_time":1568.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1568.28,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"All right.","index":531,"end_time":1570.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1569.56,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Very good.","index":532,"end_time":1570.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1570.08,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Yes.","index":533,"end_time":1570.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1570.48,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"It''s always quicker when I have you guys to talk to you about those kinds of things, so thank you so much.","index":534,"end_time":1575.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1570.72,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Anything else pending before I run away to my next call?","index":535,"end_time":1578.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1575.8,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"No, that was everything from my side.","index":536,"end_time":1581.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1579.48,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":537,"end_time":1581.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1581.48,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"So we''ll move forward with the sales guide and this video.","index":538,"end_time":1585.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1581.84,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Okay, very good.","index":539,"end_time":1587.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1586.15,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"And yeah, like I said, if I have a quick moment this afternoon and I think I will, I will send through the current info, print manager, sales guide and you know, once optimizer is done, you can start right in with ipm.","index":540,"end_time":1600.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1587.15,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Okay.","index":541,"end_time":1601.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1601.27,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":542,"end_time":1602.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1601.79,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"Awesome, Rose.","index":543,"end_time":1603.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1602.47,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"Great.","index":544,"end_time":1603.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1603.27,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"That sounds good.","index":545,"end_time":1604.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1603.75,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Thank you so much.","index":546,"end_time":1605.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1604.59,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Appreciate it.","index":547,"end_time":1606.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1605.43,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Take care.","index":548,"end_time":1607.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1606.79,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":549,"end_time":1609.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1608.39,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":550,"end_time":1610.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1609.91,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"We''ll talk next week.","index":551,"end_time":1611.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1610.35,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Bye.","index":552,"end_time":1611.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1611.19,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Bye.","index":553,"end_time":1611.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1611.43,"speaker_name":"Roz"}],"dateString":"2025-12-02T21:05:00.000Z","host_email":"nathalie.mintjens@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/85828735088?pwd=b9W3cDKwBeJQyK00Qs0iP3vvCmTxIZ.1","participants":["nathalie.mintjens@marketersindemand.com,colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com,lou.bogani@marketersindemand.com,kiyan.klocker@marketersindemand.com,rosalynne.regan@ricoh.ca,linnea.wolken@ricoh-usa.com","colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com","lou.bogani@marketersindemand.com","kiyan.klocker@marketersindemand.com","rosalynne.regan@ricoh.ca","linnea.wolken@ricoh-usa.com"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01KBD7SB75HF7FV4J5G4BSW3YH","organizer_email":"nathalie.mintjens@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"positive","confidence":0.92,"bullets":["Confirmed new sales guide template direction; Roz approved content layout and banner image treatment.","Requested updates include logo spacing, banner consistency, and streamlined image use across materials.","Roz delegated sales guide title page revisions to Nathalie and Lou; changes to proceed during vacation.","Video storyboard finalized; Roz emphasized consistent branding and rejection of nonstandard icon styles.","Roz plans to upload InfoPrint Manager guide next; Nathalie to initiate when Optimizer version is complete."],"highlights":[{"quote":"She loves the, like, the front page, the table of contents. It all looks good.","speaker":"Roz"},{"quote":"We''ll rejig the rest of the sales guides with this new template.","speaker":"Roz"},{"quote":"I just don''t want to introduce new icons if I don''t have to.","speaker":"Roz"}],"topics":["delivery","branding","video","handoff"],"model":"openai/gpt-4-1106-preview","version":1,"generated_at":"2025-12-05T00:00:00Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **Sales Guide Template Revamp**\n\nThe team decided to update the sales guide title pages to a cleaner, more consistent format while retaining core content and branding elements.\n\n- **Roz confirmed the preference for a clean title page layout with more breathing space around the logo on the bottom left corner, requiring at least an \"R\" length margin from the \"for internal use only\" box** (07:59)  \n    - Linnea reviewed and approved the new front page and table of contents layout with this spacing adjustment.  \n    - The revised title pages will remove the old GUI image and use the new Batch Builder refresh images to maintain consistency.  \n    - Roz asked for placeholders to be added if any images are missing so work can continue in her absence.  \n    - The team expects to complete the revamp and have updated sales guides ready for Roz’s return to ensure smooth progress.\n\n- **Roz plans to send the current Info Print Manager (IPM) sales guide for conversion into the new format, aiming to start this before her vacation** (26:21)  \n    - This IPM update is the next priority after Optimizer sales guide completion.  \n    - Roz emphasized moving quickly on the IPM guide to maintain momentum.  \n    - Natalie and Lou will be the primary owners to begin shifting IPM once the Optimizer guide is finalized.  \n    - The timeline aligns with Roz’s short absence, ensuring deliverables continue without delay.\n\n## **Video Animation and Branding Consistency**\n\nThe team agreed on key visual and audio standards for the Ricoh Total Flow Optimizer overview video to ensure brand consistency and clear messaging.\n\n- **Roz requested that \"Solution Overview\" appear together as the full title to avoid disconnecting the core message** (15:35)  \n    - The video will transition smoothly into the animated product overview after the title display.  \n    - Roz emphasized the importance of seeing the animation live to refine visual flow and pacing.  \n    - The team will combine “Solution Overview” into a single line for clarity on all title screens.  \n    - This sets the foundation for a polished marketing video that fits Ricoh’s brand tone.\n\n- **Roz highlighted that the sound in the logo bumper animation at the end of the video must remain unaltered and no other audio should overlap during this clip** (20:52)  \n    - The bumper is about five seconds with a distinctive “bing” sound essential for brand recognition.  \n    - Roz stressed this audio is standard across all Ricoh videos and should not be muted or replaced.  \n    - Other parts of the video can have audio overlays without restriction.  \n    - This ensures consistent brand audio branding across all platforms.\n\n- **Roz suggested replacing the current icons under key messages with icons from the existing company icon set for visual consistency** (24:00)  \n    - The icons represent \"streamline operations,\" \"automate batching,\" and \"reduce manual intervention.\"  \n    - She will review the icon set and email recommended icons to Natalie and Lou for incorporation.  \n    - Roz wants to avoid introducing new icon styles that conflict with established branding.  \n    - This small change aims to unify the look and feel across all collateral.\n\n## **Product Messaging and Terminology Refinement**\n\nClarifications were made to refine the product messaging for better accuracy and user understanding in the video and sales materials.\n\n- **Roz clarified that the phrase “reduce manual intervention” is more accurate than “reduce manual steps” to describe automation benefits in printing workflows** (17:30)  \n    - Intervention refers to less manual handling of print jobs, which better captures operational savings.  \n    - This subtle wording change helps align messaging with customer pain points and industry terminology.  \n    - The team agreed to update the copy accordingly in both video and sales guide content.  \n    - This precision supports clearer communication of product value.\n\n- **Roz expressed a preference for the balloon graphic style that includes a product hero image inside it, rather than a plain outline balloon** (20:00)  \n    - She felt the hero image balloon better ties the visual to the specific product showcased.  \n    - The team will standardize on this style across the video to maintain thematic consistency.  \n    - This choice supports stronger brand recognition and product association in marketing materials.  \n    - Minor tweaks will be made after seeing the animation in motion.\n\n## **Collaboration and Workflow Efficiency**\n\nThe meeting reinforced smooth collaboration practices and set realistic expectations for timelines and feedback.\n\n- **Roz praised having direct conversations with the team to speed up decision-making on design and content issues** (25:45)  \n    - She noted it reduces back-and-forth and helps clarify details quickly.  \n    - Roz apologized for potentially slowing video designers but prioritized brand alignment over speed.  \n    - Natalie and Lou committed to incorporating Roz’s icon and layout feedback promptly.  \n    - This collaborative rhythm aims to keep deliverables on track despite Roz’s upcoming vacation.\n\n- **Roz committed to sending any pending materials, like the IPM sales guide and additional feedback, before her departure tomorrow** (26:40)  \n    - This ensures the team has all resources needed to continue work without waiting.  \n    - Roz’s proactive approach minimizes bottlenecks during her absence.  \n    - The team agreed to start on IPM guide updates immediately after Optimizer completion.  \n    - Clear ownership and timelines were established to maintain steady progress.","outline":null,"keywords":["Sales Guide","Video Storyboard","Ricoh Total Flow Optimizer","Branding Consistency","Vacation Planning","Iconography"],"overview":"- **Sales Guide Update:** New title pages will have a cleaner layout with proper spacing and updated images for consistency.  \n- **IPM Sales Guide Conversion:** Current guide to be converted to new format before Roz''s vacation; priority after Optimizer guide completion.  \n- **Video Animation Standards:** \"Solution Overview\" will be one title; audio in logo bumper must remain unchanged for brand consistency.  \n- **Icon Consistency:** Existing company icons to be used in messaging for visual uniformity across materials.  \n- **Messaging Precision:** “Reduce manual intervention” replaces “reduce manual steps” for clarity in product automation benefits.  \n- **Collaboration Efficiency:** Direct discussions encouraged for quicker decisions; Roz to send pending materials before vacation to avoid delays.","action_items":"\n**Roz Regan**\nReview and email icon choices from Ricoh icon set for video use (25:34)\nPossibly send the current Info Print Manager (IPM) sales guide for template migration before leaving (13:53)\nProvide feedback and final approval on animation once first version is created (20:45)\n\n**Nathalie Mintjens**\nUpdate sales guide title pages with new template, remove old GUI images, and maintain refreshed product images; ensure logos have proper spacing (08:08)\nCoordinate with Lou to check availability of images and create placeholders for any missing assets (12:51)\nMake storyboard changes combining ''Solution Overview'' text and update video transitions per Roz’s instructions (14:41)\nPrepare first version of video animation and ensure compliance with no audio overlap on logo bumper (20:52)\n\n**Lou Bogani**\nAssist Nathalie in reviewing image assets for sales guide and updating title pages as per instructions (12:51)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"f67fe990-bd26-4b95-b101-ea7bfd708ae6","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
