INSERT INTO compass_notes (contract_id, meeting_id, note_type, title, content_raw, note_date, status, action_items, is_auto_generated)
SELECT
  new_meeting.contract_id,
  new_meeting.meeting_id,
  'meeting',
  'Meeting Notes: Ricoh // New North: Weekly Meeting',
  '## **Sales Guide Template Revamp**

The team decided to update the sales guide title pages to a cleaner, more consistent format while retaining core content and branding elements.

- **Roz confirmed the preference for a clean title page layout with more breathing space around the logo on the bottom left corner, requiring at least an "R" length margin from the "for internal use only" box** (07:59)  
    - Linnea reviewed and approved the new front page and table of contents layout with this spacing adjustment.  
    - The revised title pages will remove the old GUI image and use the new Batch Builder refresh images to maintain consistency.  
    - Roz asked for placeholders to be added if any images are missing so work can continue in her absence.  
    - The team expects to complete the revamp and have updated sales guides ready for Roz’s return to ensure smooth progress.

- **Roz plans to send the current Info Print Manager (IPM) sales guide for conversion into the new format, aiming to start this before her vacation** (26:21)  
    - This IPM update is the next priority after Optimizer sales guide completion.  
    - Roz emphasized moving quickly on the IPM guide to maintain momentum.  
    - Natalie and Lou will be the primary owners to begin shifting IPM once the Optimizer guide is finalized.  
    - The timeline aligns with Roz’s short absence, ensuring deliverables continue without delay.

## **Video Animation and Branding Consistency**

The team agreed on key visual and audio standards for the Ricoh Total Flow Optimizer overview video to ensure brand consistency and clear messaging.

- **Roz requested that "Solution Overview" appear together as the full title to avoid disconnecting the core message** (15:35)  
    - The video will transition smoothly into the animated product overview after the title display.  
    - Roz emphasized the importance of seeing the animation live to refine visual flow and pacing.  
    - The team will combine “Solution Overview” into a single line for clarity on all title screens.  
    - This sets the foundation for a polished marketing video that fits Ricoh’s brand tone.

- **Roz highlighted that the sound in the logo bumper animation at the end of the video must remain unaltered and no other audio should overlap during this clip** (20:52)  
    - The bumper is about five seconds with a distinctive “bing” sound essential for brand recognition.  
    - Roz stressed this audio is standard across all Ricoh videos and should not be muted or replaced.  
    - Other parts of the video can have audio overlays without restriction.  
    - This ensures consistent brand audio branding across all platforms.

- **Roz suggested replacing the current icons under key messages with icons from the existing company icon set for visual consistency** (24:00)  
    - The icons represent "streamline operations," "automate batching," and "reduce manual intervention."  
    - She will review the icon set and email recommended icons to Natalie and Lou for incorporation.  
    - Roz wants to avoid introducing new icon styles that conflict with established branding.  
    - This small change aims to unify the look and feel across all collateral.

## **Product Messaging and Terminology Refinement**

Clarifications were made to refine the product messaging for better accuracy and user understanding in the video and sales materials.

- **Roz clarified that the phrase “reduce manual intervention” is more accurate than “reduce manual steps” to describe automation benefits in printing workflows** (17:30)  
    - Intervention refers to less manual handling of print jobs, which better captures operational savings.  
    - This subtle wording change helps align messaging with customer pain points and industry terminology.  
    - The team agreed to update the copy accordingly in both video and sales guide content.  
    - This precision supports clearer communication of product value.

- **Roz expressed a preference for the balloon graphic style that includes a product hero image inside it, rather than a plain outline balloon** (20:00)  
    - She felt the hero image balloon better ties the visual to the specific product showcased.  
    - The team will standardize on this style across the video to maintain thematic consistency.  
    - This choice supports stronger brand recognition and product association in marketing materials.  
    - Minor tweaks will be made after seeing the animation in motion.

## **Collaboration and Workflow Efficiency**

The meeting reinforced smooth collaboration practices and set realistic expectations for timelines and feedback.

- **Roz praised having direct conversations with the team to speed up decision-making on design and content issues** (25:45)  
    - She noted it reduces back-and-forth and helps clarify details quickly.  
    - Roz apologized for potentially slowing video designers but prioritized brand alignment over speed.  
    - Natalie and Lou committed to incorporating Roz’s icon and layout feedback promptly.  
    - This collaborative rhythm aims to keep deliverables on track despite Roz’s upcoming vacation.

- **Roz committed to sending any pending materials, like the IPM sales guide and additional feedback, before her departure tomorrow** (26:40)  
    - This ensures the team has all resources needed to continue work without waiting.  
    - Roz’s proactive approach minimizes bottlenecks during her absence.  
    - The team agreed to start on IPM guide updates immediately after Optimizer completion.  
    - Clear ownership and timelines were established to maintain steady progress.',
  '2025-12-02 21:05:00+00',
  'published',
  '[{"text":"Review and email icon choices from Ricoh icon set for video use (25:34)","completed":false},{"text":"Possibly send the current Info Print Manager (IPM) sales guide for template migration before leaving (13:53)","completed":false},{"text":"Provide feedback and final approval on animation once first version is created (20:45)","completed":false},{"text":"Update sales guide title pages with new template, remove old GUI images, and maintain refreshed product images; ensure logos have proper spacing (08:08)","completed":false},{"text":"Coordinate with Lou to check availability of images and create placeholders for any missing assets (12:51)","completed":false},{"text":"Make storyboard changes combining ''Solution Overview'' text and update video transitions per Roz’s instructions (14:41)","completed":false},{"text":"Prepare first version of video animation and ensure compliance with no audio overlap on logo bumper (20:52)","completed":false},{"text":"Assist Nathalie in reviewing image assets for sales guide and updating title pages as per instructions (12:51)","completed":false}]'::jsonb,
  true
FROM new_meeting;

