INSERT INTO compass_notes (contract_id, meeting_id, note_type, title, content_raw, note_date, status, action_items, is_auto_generated)
SELECT
  new_meeting.contract_id,
  new_meeting.meeting_id,
  'meeting',
  'Meeting Notes: Agrippon // New North Weekly Connect',
  '## **Marketing Strategy and Messaging Alignment**

The team agreed on the urgent need to refine and unify Agrippon’s messaging across all channels to drive demo requests and better engage target customers (00:13).  
- **Keenan** emphasized the importance of a clear, concise “hook” on the website and marketing materials that immediately captures executives’ attention, focusing on pain points and key benefits rather than long, wordy stories.  
- He plans to deliver a prioritized list of **top one-liners and features by Monday** to guide website and content revisions, aiming for a fluid message that aligns sales decks, demos, and marketing collateral.  
- The homepage will undergo a **facelift focusing on wording changes and selective imagery updates** rather than a full redesign, to incrementally improve visitor engagement and conversion rates (00:34).  
- **Natalie** will provide the current library of outbound emails, LinkedIn ads, and landing pages today to enable Keenan’s review and feedback, fostering a working partnership with iterative, small tweaks prioritized for quick impact.  
- The goal is to create targeted messaging sections addressing different audiences, such as executives seeking quick insights and billing staff focused on operational benefits, supporting differentiated calls to action like demo scheduling or needs consultations.

## **Lead Generation and CRM Platform Evaluation**

Current lead generation struggles center on converting high engagement into demo bookings, with only **one demo completed so far despite hundreds of clicks** (00:36).  
- Keenan questioned the role and value of **Salesforce versus Zoho CRM**, discovering Zoho is the current CRM but limited by a free plan restricting contact volumes and email capabilities (00:09).  
- The team agreed that the choice of CRM or marketing automation tool should depend on clearly defined goals, with readiness to invest if necessary for better outbound reach and lead nurturing (00:11).  
- Keenan found no active Salesforce usage, and Zoho’s limitations led to consideration of upgrading or switching platforms to support scalable email campaigns and marketing lists.  
- Access to detailed engagement data, such as website visitor tracking and email click reports, will be critical for targeting and follow-up; **Natalie’s team agreed to share this data**, including weekly reports identifying top engaged contacts worth outreach (00:43).  
- Shane confirmed that leads generated from demo scheduling currently trigger email notifications only to him, and Keenan requested to be added to these alerts for timely follow-up (00:48).

## **Website and Demo Scheduling Enhancements**

Improving the demo scheduling process was identified as a key conversion lever (00:20).  
- Two distinct **Calendly links were created**: one for a 30-minute needs consultation and another for a longer demo, catering to prospects with different time availability and intent (00:21).  
- These links will be strategically placed in different website sections to target varying visitor mindsets and encourage action, such as quick consultations for initial interest or full demos for serious buyers.  
- Keenan will send both Calendly links to Natalie immediately for website updates ensuring prospects reach the correct contact point without friction (00:25).  
- The team agreed to incrementally roll out website changes in pieces rather than a big relaunch, enabling faster deployment and continuous improvement based on real user response (00:28).

## **Outbound Campaigns and LinkedIn Social Media**

Current outbound efforts generate clicks but low demo conversions, indicating a messaging or engagement gap (00:35).  
- Natalie described ongoing **account-based marketing (ABM) campaigns** using email sequences, LinkedIn paid ads, and direct LinkedIn messages targeting dental industry contacts (00:41).  
- A recent **free trial email offer** is being tested for higher conversion, and detailed click data from these campaigns helps identify highly engaged prospects for personal outreach (00:42).  
- Keenan plans to review and refine LinkedIn posts, deleting overly wordy or ineffective ones and creating more focused content aligned with the new messaging framework (00:33).  
- Due to technical issues with Publer and social account connections, Keenan will take over LinkedIn posting directly, drafting monthly social posts for Natalie’s review and approval (00:57).  
- The team acknowledged a need to improve social media presence and coordination with other marketing channels to build consistent awareness and lead generation.

## **Sales and Marketing Collaboration and Workflow**

Clear coordination between Keenan and Natalie’s teams will enable rapid execution of messaging updates and marketing improvements (00:29).  
- Natalie’s team commits to a typical **one-week turnaround for new landing pages or email campaigns**, supporting an agile, incremental approach to changes (00:36).  
- Communication will primarily occur via email, supplemented by the Markup tool for easy inline feedback on documents and drafts, streamlining collaboration (00:38).  
- Shane confirmed minimal legal or compliance review is required on marketing content, allowing flexibility to quickly test and iterate messaging (00:40).  
- Keenan emphasized maintaining message consistency across sales decks, demos, and website content to avoid confusing prospects and maximize conversion efficiency.  
- Plans include reaching back out to previously engaged leads with updated messaging to renew interest and capture additional demos (00:46).

## **Timeline and Next Steps**

The team aims to complete the initial messaging refresh and website updates by **Christmas**, enabling a strong start to outreach efforts in January (00:52).  
- Natalie will send current marketing materials today for Keenan’s review, and he will deliver his prioritized list of messaging one-liners and feature highlights by Monday for website input (00:31).  
- Coordinated incremental deployment of changes will begin immediately upon content alignment, avoiding delays from a full overhaul (00:28).  
- Keenan will integrate with lead engagement data and CRM notifications to actively follow up on high-interest prospects, accelerating demo bookings and pipeline development (00:45).  
- The team will continue refining outbound campaigns and social media posts as part of ongoing optimization efforts.',
  '2025-12-04 14:49:11+00',
  'published',
  '[{"text":"Send list of prioritized one-liners and key features with specific direction for website updates by Monday (31:23)","completed":false},{"text":"Review marketing materials folder once received from Natalie and provide feedback (31:23)","completed":false},{"text":"Take ownership of LinkedIn post management including deleting old posts and creating new content drafts (19:14)","completed":false},{"text":"Follow up proactively with highly engaged contacts from email and website visitor data once given access (45:45)","completed":false},{"text":"Collaborate with Natalie to refine messaging and website content iteratively (26:42)","completed":false},{"text":"Send all current marketing materials including emails, ads, one-pagers, pitch decks, LinkedIn posts in an easily reviewable folder today (31:23)","completed":false},{"text":"Grant Keenan access to website visitor data and email engagement reports for deeper lead analysis (44:00)","completed":false},{"text":"Update website contact/demo scheduling links with Keenan’s Calendly links (48:00)","completed":false},{"text":"Use Markup tool for sharing marketing collateral drafts for easier feedback collection (39:08)","completed":false},{"text":"Continue supporting parallel marketing projects with emphasis on prioritizing website and messaging improvements (28:18)","completed":false},{"text":"Provide login credentials and information related to Facebook account for Natalie to manage (59:16)","completed":false},{"text":"Share current social media login and campaign information with Natalie and Keenan as needed (33:01)","completed":false},{"text":"Participate in podcast recordings and marketing collaborations as scheduled (51:31)","completed":false}]'::jsonb,
  true
FROM new_meeting;

-- Meeting: MiD//Noetic: Weekly Set Meeting  5/8 - Onwards (2025-12-03 19:00:00+00)
WITH new_meeting AS (
  INSERT INTO compass_meetings (contract_id, meeting_date, source, external_id, title, participants, duration_seconds, recording_url, transcript, sentiment, raw_metadata, created_at, updated_at)
  VALUES (
    '1f878142-1760-4df2-805b-1f114427475d',
    '2025-12-03 19:00:00+00',
    'fireflies',
    '01KBDNMTQY6TQSY8D9YHTTWHKR',
    'MiD//Noetic: Weekly Set Meeting  5/8 - Onwards',
    '{"Colin Costigan","nancieruder","Nathalie Mintjens","Julia Oher","Rachel Curtis"}'::text[],
    3359,
    'https://us02web.zoom.us/j/85039954260?pwd=7GrXTMosQASbwQapyiVncGn3aAbQCz.1',
    '{"id":"01KBDNMTQY6TQSY8D9YHTTWHKR","title":"MiD//Noetic: Weekly Set Meeting  5/8 - Onwards","summary":{"notes":"## **Podcast Compilation and Script Refinement**\n\nThe team is finalizing the podcast compilation video with a focus on a strong thematic hook centered on navigating marketing uncertainty in 2025.\n\n- **The compilation intro script will emphasize navigating the complex marketing landscape in 2025**, with Nancy slated to record the opening around December 22nd, aligned with upcoming marketing meetings (12:07)\n    - Nancy and Rachel will record the intro together for efficiency during the next episode session on December 22nd.\n    - Nancy suggested leading with Mike Linton’s insights on understanding marketing''s role in organizations to better hook senior marketers.\n    - Marissa Jarrett’s approval is being sought to retain certain clips that reference her early time at 7:11, ensuring no controversy.\n    - Colin will update references from “Kristen” to “Chris” for Chris O’Boyle’s episode, which is planned for a December 11th release.\n\n- **Script feedback focused on tightening segments and improving thematic clarity** (06:00)\n    - The team agreed to strengthen the hook around uncertainty and decision-making rather than outdated AI experimentation messages.\n    - Minor “nip and tuck” edits included cross-outs and tightening of individual snippets to improve flow.\n    - Rachel and Julia confirmed no further major script changes beyond the provided feedback.\n\n## **AI Campaign Creative and Landing Page Updates**\n\nThe AI campaign visuals and landing page require improvements to better reflect the campaign’s complexity and brand authenticity.\n\n- **Visuals for email sequences and ads were revised to show a messier, more complex “before” state and a clearer “workflow” after state**, matching AI’s inherently chaotic nature (17:26)\n    - The team preferred a scribble or poorly drawn map representing complexity over simplistic three-box diagrams.\n    - Color adjustments to “noetic orange” for before and green for learn more CTAs were requested for readability.\n    - The “Get a handle on the lions” metaphor was replaced due to poor translation of meaning.\n    - Background colors on graphics were adjusted to lighter gray for better contrast with colorful elements.\n\n- **Landing page design feedback stressed making visuals more human and less AI-generated, with clearer calls to action** (22:18)\n    - The current images were described as “dark and plastic,” prompting a move toward more realistic, relatable photos.\n    - Button text should be lowercase and consistent with other website elements for brand compliance.\n    - The call to action “See how it works” may mislead users; alternatives like “Learn more” or “Connect with us” are preferred to avoid bait-and-switch feelings.\n    - The four-phase approach text will use sentence case rather than all caps to improve readability and tone.\n    - The “trusted thought leader” language will be added above the AI content section to avoid implying direct AI work for listed brands, reducing legal risk.\n\n## **Paid Media Performance and Campaign Prioritization**\n\nPaid ad campaigns delivered modest engagement with a need to consolidate efforts for better focus and cost efficiency.\n\n- **November LinkedIn ads achieved a click-through rate of 0.47%, slightly above the industry benchmark of 0.44%, with three leads at a cost of $541 per lead** (33:43)\n    - The team identified five paid campaign components: full playbooks for first-year CMOs and healthcare, infographic versions of those playbooks, and the marketing leadership playbook.\n    - Traction was strongest on healthcare infographics and document downloads targeting healthcare job titles.\n    - Brand awareness campaigns targeting job titles showed high cost and diminishing returns due to saturated, highly targeted LinkedIn audiences.\n    - Colin recommended pausing the new CMO outreach and the marketing leadership campaign to prioritize the AI campaign and the infographic content, reducing overlap and spend.\n\n- **The AI campaign includes LinkedIn ads, email sequences, and outreach, requiring a clear focus to avoid diluted messaging across campaigns** (40:14)\n    - The team agreed to maintain the AI campaign alongside healthcare and first-time CMO infographics, totaling three main campaign focuses.\n    - Clarification was made regarding campaign terminology differences between LinkedIn ad sets and internal marketing language to ensure alignment on scope and spend.\n\n## **Sales Pipeline Metrics and Dashboard Improvements**\n\nEfforts to refine sales pipeline metrics and dashboard data have improved visibility into lead generation and opportunity progression.\n\n- **Year-to-date leads over the last 12 months stand at approximately 139, with goals targeting 16 new opportunities or $200,000 in new hunting opportunities** (43:46)\n    - Colin adjusted the Pipedrive dashboard to use a rolling 12-month date range, resolving previous API limitations.\n    - The dashboard currently combines leads from both New North and internal sources, but can be separated if needed for clearer attribution.\n    - The focus remains on moving leads from stage zero to stage one and beyond to track conversion effectively.\n    - Rachel confirmed that dashboard metrics now include click-through rates by campaign, supporting ongoing performance monitoring.\n\n- **Client engagement updates highlighted ongoing talks with Marriott and Waymo but no imminent deals** (46:49)\n    - Meetings with Marriott’s Tanya are planned for January, with openness to internal introductions.\n    - Waymo contacts have been challenging to communicate with; the team is pursuing follow-ups but acknowledges the client’s fast-moving environment.\n    - December is a difficult month for client engagement due to holiday schedules.\n\n## **Website and Podcast Analytics**\n\nWebsite visitor patterns and podcast engagement show mixed yet promising trends, signaling opportunities for further content promotion.\n\n- **Website visitors have slightly declined in the past 30 days, but average session duration increased by a similar margin, indicating deeper engagement from fewer visitors** (48:04)\n    - Podcast views on YouTube rose by **32%**, largely attributed to the release of the Mike Linton episode.\n    - Key pages like case studies and brand strategy saw notable traffic increases, with brand strategy up by **63%**.\n    - Playbook page views decreased but remain steady, reflecting the impact of newly published content.\n    - The team opted to direct paid ad traffic to LinkedIn lead forms to reduce barriers to conversion rather than sending users to the website.\n\n- **Newsletter subscriber count is growing steadily due to active subscriptions, but listener numbers remain the primary engagement metric** (51:08)\n    - Nancy has been actively subscribing contacts to the newsletter to increase visibility.\n    - The team recognizes that podcast listening habits often involve non-subscribers, emphasizing quality content over subscription volume.\n    - Rachel’s timely promotion of new podcast episodes supports audience growth despite personal challenges faced by guests.\n\n## **Next Steps and Timeline Commitments**\n\nThe team established clear timing and responsibilities to advance project completion and maintain campaign momentum.\n\n- **The podcast compilation video is targeted for mid to late December release following script tweaks and recording sessions scheduled for December 11th and 22nd** (54:33)\n    - Colin will send the updated Chris O’Boyle episode script with naming corrections within minutes to allow Nancy sufficient time for review.\n    - Rachel flagged her absence for the next meeting on December 10th; the team acknowledged and adjusted accordingly.\n\n- **AI campaign creative updates and landing page changes will proceed promptly to enhance visuals, accessibility, and user experience** (21:41)\n    - Design and copy edits including color changes, button text compliance, and clearer CTAs will be implemented.\n    - The trusted thought leader language positioning will be adjusted to mitigate legal risks tied to brand associations.\n\n- **Paid campaign consolidation will focus on AI and high-performing infographic assets to maximize ROI and reduce ad spend waste** (39:54)\n    - Full playbooks and less effective campaigns will be paused to prioritize resources on proven content formats.\n    - Ongoing tracking via dashboards and analytics tools will support data-driven decisions moving forward.","outline":null,"keywords":["AI Campaign","Podcast Episodes","Marketing Leadership","Landing Page","LinkedIn Ads","Dashboard Metrics"],"overview":"- **Podcast Compilation Focus:** Finalizing video with a theme on navigating marketing uncertainty in 2025; recordings planned for December 11th and 22nd.\n\n- **AI Campaign Visuals Improvement:** Revised campaign visuals to reflect complexity; replaced metaphor and adjusted colors for better clarity and contrast.\n\n- **Paid Media Insights:** November LinkedIn ads achieved 0.47% CTR; aim to pause low-performing campaigns to focus on AI and infographic content.\n\n- **Sales Metrics Tracking:** Year-to-date leads at 139; targeting 16 new opportunities or $200,000; dashboard updates for better lead tracking implemented.\n\n- **Website and Podcast Trends:** Slight website visitor decline, but increased session duration; YouTube podcast views rose 32% with the Mike Linton episode.\n\n- **Next Steps Defined:** Podcast video targeted for mid-late December release; campaign updates and paid media consolidation will optimize performance and resources.","action_items":"\n**Colin Costigan**\nSend updated welcome note and personal context documents to team (04:40)\nIncorporate Nancy’s script feedback and add stronger hook for navigation theme in compilation video (06:00)\nUpdate script references for Chris O’Boyle’s name from Kristen to Chris accordingly (14:30)\nFollow up with Riverside support on content migration options and inform team (15:15)\nApply color adjustments and typography improvements to AI ad visuals and CTAs based on feedback (18:50)\nModify landing page imagery to include more authentic, less AI-generated photos according to suggestions (22:00)\nRework brand partner language on landing page to “trusted thought leader” phrasing (29:45)\nFlip bullet order on landing page content to emphasize human skills and expertise (31:10)\nAdjust CTA wording on landing page to avoid “bait and switch,” testing “Learn More” or “Connect With” (32:50)\nPause less effective LinkedIn campaigns as advised, focusing spend on AI campaign and infographics (39:45)\nAdjust Pipedrive dashboard filters from calendar year to last 12 months to fix lead count errors (43:20)\nRevert dashboard lead count to show New North leads only for clarity (45:50)\nMonitor and report website visitor metrics, average session duration, and YouTube podcast view increases (48:30)\nFinalize and send Chris O’Boyle script to Nancy before her review slot tomorrow (55:15)\n\n**Nancy Ruderman**\nReview finalized script edits and provide feedback to Chris O’Boyle promptly (55:20)\nSchedule recording for compilation video intro aligned with December 22nd marketing meetings for efficiency (10:50)\nOversee shifts in campaign focus and budget allocation per Colin’s recommendation (39:50)\n\n**Rachel Curtis**\nCollaborate with Julia to process assets and quotes for upcoming podcast episodes (05:10)\nPrepare and deliver finalized landing page feedback focusing on accessibility, color scheme, and button text consistency (22:00)\nShare dashboard and campaign metrics deck with internal team for clarity on performance (44:10)\nPromote podcast episodes with timely social media or other channels, considering guest circumstances (52:30)\n\n**Julia Oher**\nWork with Rachel on podcast episode assets and script review to enhance content clarity (05:10)\nProvide input on landing page section content order and visual emphasis for stronger messaging (31:10)\nContribute to landing page imagery feedback and push for humanized visuals (22:30)\n\n**Nathalie Mintjens**\nConfirm and track guest interview scheduling, including follow-up frustrations with Mac McGee (13:30)\nAssist Colin in Riverside studio content transfer investigation and process options (15:10)\nSupport campaign metrics clarification and ad spend breakdown (34:00)\n"},"duration":55.9900016784668,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Colin Costigan"},{"id":1,"name":"nancieruder"},{"id":2,"name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"id":3,"name":"Julia Oher"},{"id":4,"name":"Rachel Curtis"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Hey.","index":0,"end_time":10.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":10,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hello.","index":1,"end_time":11.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":10.72,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"How''s it going?","index":2,"end_time":13.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":12.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Good.","index":3,"end_time":14.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":14.32,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"How are you doing all right.","index":4,"end_time":17.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":15.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Just back to back all day.","index":5,"end_time":19.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":17.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Catching up on a lot, I''m sure.","index":6,"end_time":22.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":20.32,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Trying.","index":7,"end_time":23.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":23.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"To.","index":8,"end_time":25.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":25.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hi.","index":9,"end_time":40.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":40.17,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Hey.","index":10,"end_time":42.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":42.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How''s it going?","index":11,"end_time":43.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":42.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Going well.","index":12,"end_time":44.53,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":43.93,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"How about you two?","index":13,"end_time":45.37,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":44.53,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Doing all right?","index":14,"end_time":46.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":45.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hi, Nancy.","index":15,"end_time":48.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":47.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How was your time off, Colin?","index":16,"end_time":50.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":48.65,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"It was.","index":17,"end_time":51.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":50.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":18,"end_time":53.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Distant memory now.","index":19,"end_time":55.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":54.28,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah, flew by.","index":20,"end_time":57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":55.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That was great.","index":21,"end_time":58.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":58.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean got to take my daughter down to Florida.","index":22,"end_time":61.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":58.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"She loved it.","index":23,"end_time":61.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":61.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s great.","index":24,"end_time":63.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":62.52,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":25,"end_time":63.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":63.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How about you guys?","index":26,"end_time":64.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":64.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How was Thanksgiving?","index":27,"end_time":65.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":64.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How was Thanksgiving, Julia?","index":28,"end_time":69.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":68.52,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Thanksgiving feels like a distant memory.","index":29,"end_time":72.36,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":70.2,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"But it was so nice.","index":30,"end_time":75.12,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":74.12,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"I had a like very quiet Thanksgiving holiday and my parents are now coming into town for this weekend.","index":31,"end_time":82.52,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":75.12,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"So.","index":32,"end_time":83,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":82.6,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"Looking forward.","index":33,"end_time":85.06,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":84.66,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"It was the calm before.","index":34,"end_time":86.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":85.86,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Totally.","index":35,"end_time":88.18,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":87.54,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"It was the common.","index":36,"end_time":89.22,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":88.26,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"We got a ton of snow.","index":37,"end_time":90.3,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":89.22,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"Natalie knows this, of course.","index":38,"end_time":91.62,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":90.3,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"We''re still getting snow.","index":39,"end_time":92.74,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":91.62,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":40,"end_time":93.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":92.74,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I keep meaning to ask you what''s the total accumulation in the city?","index":41,"end_time":98.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":94.66,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I love an exaggerated like weather update.","index":42,"end_time":103.3,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":98.9,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"So I''m going to say like maybe nine inches.","index":43,"end_time":106.26,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":103.38,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"Eight or nine inches.","index":44,"end_time":107.46,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":106.26,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"Natalie, do you want to keep me honest?","index":45,"end_time":110.02,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":108.18,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"I concur.","index":46,"end_time":111.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":111.19,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"It''s.","index":47,"end_time":112.31,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":111.87,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"It has not stopped since like last week.","index":48,"end_time":114.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":112.31,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s crazy.","index":49,"end_time":115.75,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":114.63,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"So you, you''ve gotten like several kind.","index":50,"end_time":118.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":115.83,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Of mini storms, one major and then several mini.","index":51,"end_time":122.39,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":118.11,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"Kind of continuing to keep it white and it has not melted whatsoever.","index":52,"end_time":128.47,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":123.59,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"And interestingly like I think this is my 15th like in Chicago winter and I don''t think we''ve gotten this kind of Snow in like 12, 13 years.","index":53,"end_time":141.91,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":129.59,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"So it feels really fun and different.","index":54,"end_time":144.42,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":142.15,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":55,"end_time":146.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":145.54,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And it''s really something too when you get like the snow on top of the Snow in the D.C. area and it''s like just like such a famous.","index":56,"end_time":156.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":146.5,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"They called it Snowmageddon in 2011 maybe had three storms, like one in December and I think two in February.","index":57,"end_time":166.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":156.18,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And the two in February were like back to back.","index":58,"end_time":168.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":166.74,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And it was the most snow like ever, like ever, ever.","index":59,"end_time":173.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":169.38,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And you know, we don''t really get snow in this area but it was like that final storm.","index":60,"end_time":181.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":174.27,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Were you here then, Colin?","index":61,"end_time":184.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":182.11,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Were you here back then?","index":62,"end_time":185.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":184.03,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I mean it was such a white out.","index":63,"end_time":188.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":185.63,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"You couldn''t see, like it was kind of spooky.","index":64,"end_time":191.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":189.31,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"You couldn''t see outside and you''re just like, okay, if we lose power, like we''re screwed.","index":65,"end_time":195.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":191.35,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":66,"end_time":197.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":196.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Several people in my town did lose power.","index":67,"end_time":199,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":197.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It was, it was rough.","index":68,"end_time":200.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":199.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":69,"end_time":201.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":201.24,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"It''s scary.","index":70,"end_time":202.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":201.72,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Like you were digging out your, your vents on the back of your house like because the snow was, you know, piling up against the house.","index":71,"end_time":210.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":202.36,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"It was probably up to my waist.","index":72,"end_time":212.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":210.28,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Oh my gosh.","index":73,"end_time":214.44,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":213.16,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"I love that.","index":74,"end_time":215.72,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":214.52,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"I.","index":75,"end_time":216.08,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":215.72,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"Because it was snow on Top of snow.","index":76,"end_time":217.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":216.08,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Right.","index":77,"end_time":217.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":217.6,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So maybe we put.","index":78,"end_time":218.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":217.8,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And then we got like another foot.","index":79,"end_time":220.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":218.88,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"It was insane.","index":80,"end_time":220.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":220.12,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I feel like if it''s going to be cold, give me beautiful snow.","index":81,"end_time":225.36,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":221.96,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"And if you''re going to give me snow, give me lots of it.","index":82,"end_time":228.03,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":225.36,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"Give me a lot.","index":83,"end_time":228.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":228.03,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Right?","index":84,"end_time":228.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":228.71,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":85,"end_time":229.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":228.99,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Don''t give me this piddly 2 inches business.","index":86,"end_time":231.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":229.31,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"This is like the first time I had to actually pull out my, you know, I. I choose to pull out my boots, but I had to wear.","index":87,"end_time":238.95,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":231.47,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"Boots in the house.","index":88,"end_time":240.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":238.95,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":89,"end_time":240.67,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":240.19,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":90,"end_time":241.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":240.75,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"No question.","index":91,"end_time":241.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":241.11,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Right.","index":92,"end_time":242.03,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":241.63,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Well, I know we have a lot to do, so.","index":93,"end_time":244.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":242.11,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Colin, take us away.","index":94,"end_time":246.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":244.83,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Let''s do it.","index":95,"end_time":247.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":246.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Rachel, I hope you had a great Thanksgiving.","index":96,"end_time":250.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":249.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If you have some time at the end, would love to catch up on it.","index":97,"end_time":252.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":250.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":98,"end_time":254.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":253.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I was in a meeting when you guys sent over that last email, so I''ve not had a chance to review that, but I will pull it up so that we can talk through it.","index":99,"end_time":260.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":254.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I know you had some items in there.","index":100,"end_time":262.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":260.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I just figured get the details to you.","index":101,"end_time":264.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":262.26,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I mean, it was in close succession to this meeting, so I did not necessarily anticipate that you were going to have ingested it.","index":102,"end_time":270.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":264.38,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"On the waiting on here.","index":103,"end_time":274.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":272.9,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I thought I had sent.","index":104,"end_time":277.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":275.78,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah, I found that that''s.","index":105,"end_time":278.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":277.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s my fault.","index":106,"end_time":279.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":278.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No worries.","index":107,"end_time":280.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":279.94,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I. Catching up on emails.","index":108,"end_time":281.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":280.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"A problem with my outlook.","index":109,"end_time":285.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":283.51,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So then I thought maybe it bounced.","index":110,"end_time":287.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":285.91,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":111,"end_time":289.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":289.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we actually.","index":112,"end_time":290.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":289.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And we''ll send this over, but got the welcome note added in here.","index":113,"end_time":293.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":290.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then I added also the additional personal context here.","index":114,"end_time":298.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":293.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":115,"end_time":298.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":298.47,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And have you sent this to me yet?","index":116,"end_time":300.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":298.91,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I have not.","index":117,"end_time":300.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":300.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''ve not.","index":118,"end_time":301.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":300.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We just added this in maybe like an hour ago.","index":119,"end_time":303.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":301.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, very good, Very good.","index":120,"end_time":306.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":303.99,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And I sent over right before this meeting, Pam and Patrick''s quotes and episode episode titles.","index":121,"end_time":316.38,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":308.22,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"And then this week I''m going to work through the assets and quotes in episodes for the other two with Julia.","index":122,"end_time":322.78,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":317.18,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"So those are coming your way.","index":123,"end_time":324.54,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":322.86,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Fantastic.","index":124,"end_time":325.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":325.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":125,"end_time":327.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":326.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I know you guys also provided feedback for the script.","index":126,"end_time":329.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":327.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":127,"end_time":330.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":330.22,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So on the script, like a lot.","index":128,"end_time":333.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":330.66,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I can even just pull up your email here.","index":129,"end_time":334.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":333.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":130,"end_time":335.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":334.86,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Like nip and tuck.","index":131,"end_time":336.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":335.22,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"But I. I think that the biggest thing is that I just think we need it to have a more powerful hook of like, what the theme is.","index":132,"end_time":345.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":336.06,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And I think.","index":133,"end_time":346.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":346.02,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So.","index":134,"end_time":349.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":348.98,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I''m not.","index":135,"end_time":349.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":349.38,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I''m not feeling like I got it, like, exactly right.","index":136,"end_time":353.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":349.98,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"But something.","index":137,"end_time":354.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":353.26,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Something having to do with like how to lead an uncertainty or.","index":138,"end_time":359.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":355.46,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Or something in like that.","index":139,"end_time":362.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":359.62,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"That''s kind of where we''re getting at with like, most all of it.","index":140,"end_time":365.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":362.58,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So I just think that that that intro.","index":141,"end_time":369.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":367.6,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Needs that focus.","index":142,"end_time":373.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":371.6,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So that you know, the senior marketers are like, oh, I''d better listen to this.","index":143,"end_time":377.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":373.6,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":144,"end_time":378.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":377.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I feel like a common theme and we can think of stronger words for it, but it''s really been like, navigating the marketing environment this year, like, across so many different industries and roles.","index":145,"end_time":386.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":378.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And, you know, you got people that are.","index":146,"end_time":388.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":386.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think it was Kate Warnock.","index":147,"end_time":390.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":389.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Right.","index":148,"end_time":390.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":390.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Who works at a company and then there''s a merger, and then seven months later they''re rolling out a whole new brand.","index":149,"end_time":394.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":390.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then, you know, there''s just so many different stories, but it''s all.","index":150,"end_time":397.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":394.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Navigating 2025 has been so different.","index":151,"end_time":400.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":397.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s what I''ve really learned from watching the episodes.","index":152,"end_time":402.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":400.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":153,"end_time":402.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":402.23,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":154,"end_time":403.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":402.79,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And I think, like, most of them have to do.","index":155,"end_time":406.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":403.19,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Most of the snippets tell stories that have to do with, like, somebody having to, like, make a call.","index":156,"end_time":413.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":407.11,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"In uncertainty.","index":157,"end_time":416.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":414.79,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I think, though, that what you''re saying is, like, it''s tangential, but it''s.","index":158,"end_time":424.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":418.95,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"But it''s slightly different.","index":159,"end_time":425.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":424.5,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"But one of my suggestions was I actually don''t think that the Michael clip is strong enough.","index":160,"end_time":431.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":425.26,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Because to me, that feels like AI 12 months ago.","index":161,"end_time":437.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":433.14,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Because it''s kind of encouraging people to experiment.","index":162,"end_time":440.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":438.66,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I think everybody knows that now.","index":163,"end_time":442.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":440.7,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"What I think would be a strong thing to lead with is that I know that Mike Linton talked about.","index":164,"end_time":449.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":443.86,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Understand what the role of marketing is in your organization.","index":165,"end_time":455.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":451.55,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And I think that that is.","index":166,"end_time":456.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":455.15,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I don''t know how easy it''s going to be to grab.","index":167,"end_time":460.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":457.31,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"You know, I don''t know how long he went on about it, but.","index":168,"end_time":463.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":460.91,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"But it''s such a.","index":169,"end_time":465.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":464.51,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"It''s such a pain point.","index":170,"end_time":467.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":465.95,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":171,"end_time":467.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":467.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like, people just get into these jobs and then they''re like, oh.","index":172,"end_time":471.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":468.03,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Marketing''S not regarded the way I thought.","index":173,"end_time":475.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":473.39,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And then sometimes it changes, like, once you''re in there too.","index":174,"end_time":478.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":475.51,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So.","index":175,"end_time":478.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":478.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I think, like, if it''s around navigating, like.","index":176,"end_time":482.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":478.95,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Like play around with what you think that is, but if it''s something around, like, navigating this ever changing marketing landscape, I think that a clip like that from Mike could be a good lead in.","index":177,"end_time":494.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":482.39,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I wouldn''t take out his other one.","index":178,"end_time":496.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":494.63,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Unless you think it''s problematic to have two.","index":179,"end_time":499.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":498.23,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Because I think that that one''s good.","index":180,"end_time":501.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":499.91,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"No, I wouldn''t.","index":181,"end_time":502.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":501.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I was.","index":182,"end_time":504.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":503.83,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I. I do need to check with one of my comments in here.","index":183,"end_time":508.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":504.55,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So I. I kind of talk about individual snippets.","index":184,"end_time":513.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":508.95,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":185,"end_time":515.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":514.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You want to check with Marissa?","index":186,"end_time":516.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":515.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"With Marissa Jarrett?","index":187,"end_time":517.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":516.27,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I. I think she''ll be okay, and I''d hate to lose it.","index":188,"end_time":522.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":519.51,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I. Julia, I appreciated your thought on that.","index":189,"end_time":525.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":522.87,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Like, Is this still okay to use?","index":190,"end_time":526.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":525.27,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I think it will be.","index":191,"end_time":528.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":527.51,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Because, you know, our plan is to air this like December, January, and she leaves end of December, so I think it''s okay.","index":192,"end_time":540.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":530.95,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"It also hearkens back to the beginning of her time at 7:11, which isn''t.","index":193,"end_time":548.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":542.01,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"It''s not controversial.","index":194,"end_time":550.329,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":549.13,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"You know what I mean?","index":195,"end_time":551.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":550.329,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"It was a while ago, so I''m hoping we''ll be able to keep it.","index":196,"end_time":554.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":551.37,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I''m gonna.","index":197,"end_time":555.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":554.65,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I''m gonna ask her in a way to make it easy for her to say yes.","index":198,"end_time":558.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":555.09,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Love it.","index":199,"end_time":559.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":558.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":200,"end_time":560.26,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":559.94,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"And then I think the rest of it was just kind of like nip and tucks.","index":201,"end_time":563.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":560.42,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Like, we, we took a lot of.","index":202,"end_time":565.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":563.42,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"We.","index":203,"end_time":570.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":569.86,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"We did some cross outs or gray outs, just in bits to make them a little bit tighter.","index":204,"end_time":575.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":570.26,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":205,"end_time":580.74,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":580.26,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"So.","index":206,"end_time":581.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":580.9,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And then that''s all just, you know, how are compilations best done?","index":207,"end_time":586.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":581.18,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And as I said, my note, I think you cared for most of this, but I just thought it was worth sharing.","index":208,"end_time":590.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":586.5,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, always good.","index":209,"end_time":592.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":591.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Anything else on that, Rachel or Julia?","index":210,"end_time":596.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":593.98,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I know you had done notes within.","index":211,"end_time":599.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":597.42,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I don''t think so.","index":212,"end_time":601.46,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":600.54,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"I think that covered our collective feedback.","index":213,"end_time":604.98,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":601.46,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Unless I''m missing anything, Julia.","index":214,"end_time":606.62,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":604.98,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"No, I just wanted to clarify, Nancy, will you be the one reading that opening.","index":215,"end_time":611.34,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":606.939,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"Great question.","index":216,"end_time":614.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":613.74,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I think so.","index":217,"end_time":615.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":614.46,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Okay.","index":218,"end_time":616.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":615.58,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Once the reason I ask is, I think then it''s okay.","index":219,"end_time":620.12,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":616.64,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"But there wasn''t a ton of.","index":220,"end_time":622.32,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":620.12,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"You within the, like.","index":221,"end_time":625.92,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":623.92,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"Snippets.","index":222,"end_time":628.64,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":627.92,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"And so I think if you''re opening it, it''ll be fine.","index":223,"end_time":633.04,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":630.24,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"Your voice will be present and part of.","index":224,"end_time":635.36,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":633.04,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"Part of this overall compilation.","index":225,"end_time":638,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":635.44,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"But if not, that might be something we need to keep in mind.","index":226,"end_time":641.12,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":638.32,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":227,"end_time":641.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":641.28,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And to your point, like, I should be saying something insightful.","index":228,"end_time":646.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":641.68,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Right.","index":229,"end_time":648.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":648.38,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Because I do think that a lot of people might like, click on and only give it, you know, five to.","index":230,"end_time":654.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":648.7,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"30 seconds at the start.","index":231,"end_time":656.3,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":654.7,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"So we would need to schedule.","index":232,"end_time":659.139,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":657.02,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Nancy, when it works for you, just to record that quickly.","index":233,"end_time":662.62,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":659.139,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"I think for efficiency.","index":234,"end_time":666.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":663.98,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Rachel, you and I could do it when we''re doing that other episode.","index":235,"end_time":672.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":667.5,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"When is the next one?","index":236,"end_time":675.12,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":673.6,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"No, not the crisp oil.","index":237,"end_time":678.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":676.56,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"A boil one, but.","index":238,"end_time":679.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":678.16,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Oh, it''s.","index":239,"end_time":681.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":680.64,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"It''s not till the 22nd.","index":240,"end_time":682.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":681.6,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"It''s not for a while.","index":241,"end_time":684.44,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":683.52,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"And then we were supposed to launch this in around that time.","index":242,"end_time":688.4,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":684.44,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"So.","index":243,"end_time":689.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":689.2,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":244,"end_time":689.84,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":689.48,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Tie it to one of our marketing meetings.","index":245,"end_time":693.52,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":691.52,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Yes, we could.","index":246,"end_time":699.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":698.71,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Or we could do it off the back of Chris o'' Boyle if you had it.","index":247,"end_time":705.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":699.47,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Thursday enough time.","index":248,"end_time":708.95,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":707.35,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"If we do it next Thursday to add it in.","index":249,"end_time":711.11,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":708.95,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Yeah, I think that can.","index":250,"end_time":713.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":712.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think that can work out fine because it would basically just be adding an addition to the beginning and then we Just need to make sure, like, the backup music and things like that match up.","index":251,"end_time":721.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":713.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":252,"end_time":722.32,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":721.84,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"If that works for you guys, then that works for us.","index":253,"end_time":724.88,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":722.4,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"All right, Then I''m going to just put in our calendar.","index":254,"end_time":730.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":727.36,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"At the back end.","index":255,"end_time":736.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":735.52,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"To record the compilation intro.","index":256,"end_time":744,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":741.68,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I think that''s also a great opportunity to lean into, like, the navigating the complex landscape of marketing in 2025.","index":257,"end_time":751.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":746.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":258,"end_time":752.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":752.46,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"To kind of lay out the theme.","index":259,"end_time":754.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":752.86,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, agreed.","index":260,"end_time":756.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":754.54,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Okay, awesome.","index":261,"end_time":762.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":760.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":262,"end_time":763.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":763.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I know we wanted to spend some time here as well.","index":263,"end_time":766.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":764.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":264,"end_time":767.98,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":767.58,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"What I wanted to do.","index":265,"end_time":769.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":767.98,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So I''m slightly confused between tabs.","index":266,"end_time":773.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":769.58,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"What''s the difference between the first guest tab and the second guest tab?","index":267,"end_time":778.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":773.98,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"This is the one.","index":268,"end_time":778.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":778.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Natalie went in and cleaned this up and added in, like, the links to the frameworks and all of that sort of stuff in this.","index":269,"end_time":785.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":778.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And guess two.","index":270,"end_time":786.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":785.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, so then guest two is the one we should be using then.","index":271,"end_time":789.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":786.77,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":272,"end_time":790.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":790.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, so guest one is where I made the updates, unfortunately.","index":273,"end_time":794.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":791.01,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Okay.","index":274,"end_time":794.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":794.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But if you just click to that.","index":275,"end_time":796.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":795.09,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So.","index":276,"end_time":796.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":796.45,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Chris.","index":277,"end_time":799.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":798.61,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I just put them in red so I''d know what I wanted to tell you.","index":278,"end_time":802.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":799.33,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So Chris O'', Boyle, you know, is December 11th.","index":279,"end_time":805.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":802.29,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Abby Fenton is confirmed.","index":280,"end_time":807.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":805.25,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Um, it''s actually going to be January, so date tbd.","index":281,"end_time":812.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":807.8,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"But.","index":282,"end_time":812.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":812.32,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"But January.","index":283,"end_time":813.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":812.56,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Kim Waddy is also confirmed and also haven''t landed the date.","index":284,"end_time":819.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":813.48,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And Mac McGee continues to be a.","index":285,"end_time":823.919,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":819.64,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Wily in the fairy dust.","index":286,"end_time":825.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":823.919,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":287,"end_time":826.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":825.8,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So.","index":288,"end_time":826.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":826.44,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I''m persevering, but I''m.","index":289,"end_time":830.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":828.68,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I''m starting to get frustrated.","index":290,"end_time":831.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":830.12,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So that''s.","index":291,"end_time":832.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":831.88,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"That''s what I got.","index":292,"end_time":833.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":832.64,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Okay, great.","index":293,"end_time":834.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":834.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I continue to think that it''s going to be Chris o'' Boyle in December.","index":294,"end_time":839.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":834.77,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And then these internal.","index":295,"end_time":841.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":839.17,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"We''re going to do the two internal, but we''re going to do one of them.","index":296,"end_time":844.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":841.17,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Rachel and I are going to do one of them.","index":297,"end_time":846.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":845.09,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"December 22nd, we''re going to do the other one.","index":298,"end_time":849.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":846.77,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Sam and I in January.","index":299,"end_time":850.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":849.49,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":300,"end_time":851.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":851.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Day after winter solstice.","index":301,"end_time":853.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":852.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"One thing I want to check, just because I think I said last time Chris is actually my sister was named was Kristen.","index":302,"end_time":861.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":854.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"She went by Chris.","index":303,"end_time":861.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":861.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I want to confirm in the script, should we call her Chris or Kristen?","index":304,"end_time":865.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":861.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I think.","index":305,"end_time":866.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":866.06,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I think the first time I introduce her, I should say Kristen, because that is her, like, proper name.","index":306,"end_time":874.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":867.1,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"But then for the rest of it, I call her Chris.","index":307,"end_time":876.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":874.3,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Okay.","index":308,"end_time":877.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":877.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, we can go through and update that then.","index":309,"end_time":879.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":877.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Great.","index":310,"end_time":881.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":881.1,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":311,"end_time":881.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":881.42,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Thank you for asking that.","index":312,"end_time":882.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":881.82,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, of course.","index":313,"end_time":883.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":882.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":314,"end_time":885.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":884.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Already went through that.","index":315,"end_time":886.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":885.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":316,"end_time":887.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":887.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So for Riverside, unfortunately, they don''t have a method of transferring over, like, admin and.","index":317,"end_time":893.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":887.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And payment especially.","index":318,"end_time":894.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":893.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We are a partner with them, so get you a discounted rate.","index":319,"end_time":897.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":894.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So it would have to be a completely new account if you guys wanted to take over the.","index":320,"end_time":902.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":898.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The management of that.","index":321,"end_time":903.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":902.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, and if we do that, are they able to, like, port content there?","index":322,"end_time":910.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":903.64,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I could.","index":323,"end_time":912.439,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":911.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We could reach out to their support team and see if we can do anything like that.","index":324,"end_time":915.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":912.439,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Natalie, I know you talked to them as well.","index":325,"end_time":916.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":915.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I did look into that.","index":326,"end_time":918.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":917.16,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"You mean, like, transfer the.","index":327,"end_time":920.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":918.56,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Like, the studios to yours?","index":328,"end_time":922.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":920.4,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s not possible, but what we.","index":329,"end_time":924.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":922.49,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Can do is just download them and.","index":330,"end_time":926.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":924.69,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Then you upload them into your studios.","index":331,"end_time":928.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":926.33,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":332,"end_time":930.33,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":929.77,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Okay.","index":333,"end_time":931.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":930.89,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"All right, thank you for letting us know.","index":334,"end_time":933.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":931.85,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"We''ll follow up with you on that.","index":335,"end_time":934.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":933.45,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Great.","index":336,"end_time":935.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":935.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, we''re going through a few other podcasts.","index":337,"end_time":940.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":937.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''ll send over the Chris o'' Boyle after.","index":338,"end_time":942.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":940.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I just.","index":339,"end_time":942.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":942.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''ll make the update on when to use Kristen versus Chris.","index":340,"end_time":945.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":942.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And Rachel, I know you sent over some feedback for the assets just before this, and the same with the quotes and titles.","index":341,"end_time":953.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":946.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":342,"end_time":955.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":955.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Moving efficiently.","index":343,"end_time":956.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":955.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, diving into the AI campaign.","index":344,"end_time":960.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":957.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we had the sequence.","index":345,"end_time":962.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":961.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I know you guys left feedback as well.","index":346,"end_time":964.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":962.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So walking through this.","index":347,"end_time":970.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":969.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So it just seems like some not, like, extreme updates to make.","index":348,"end_time":979.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":974.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we can go ahead and get those done and then sent back over to you.","index":349,"end_time":983.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":980.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Was there anything that you didn''t leave a comment on that you wanted to talk through?","index":350,"end_time":986.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":983.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think in the.","index":351,"end_time":991.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":990.35,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"In the email sequences.","index":352,"end_time":994.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":992.51,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"No, I think it''s all there.","index":353,"end_time":995.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":994.19,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And I think those are more tweaks for the ads.","index":354,"end_time":1002.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":998.11,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"It was a little trickier.","index":355,"end_time":1003.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1002.68,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So.","index":356,"end_time":1007.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1006.76,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":357,"end_time":1012,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1011.56,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So these probably deserve some explaining.","index":358,"end_time":1014.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1012,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So in the case of this first one, the concept of it we like, but we want it to be less simplistic.","index":359,"end_time":1023,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1014.84,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So like a much messier before where it''s a little bit look even more complex looking, but even more importantly in the after, like, just three boxes with arrows is never what a.","index":360,"end_time":1038.119,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1023.8,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Like a, you know, workflow would look like.","index":361,"end_time":1040.839,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1038.439,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So I understand you have, like, limited space, but it just needs to look more robust.","index":362,"end_time":1045.959,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1040.839,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah, no problem.","index":363,"end_time":1048.759,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1046.679,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Our team, Colin, if you open the document, they did take a stab at some of the updates already.","index":364,"end_time":1054.519,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1048.759,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Mm.","index":365,"end_time":1058.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1058.09,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":366,"end_time":1059.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1059.13,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Is that more of what you''re looking for or even more robust?","index":367,"end_time":1065.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1063.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, I think that''s.","index":368,"end_time":1067.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1066.09,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I think that''s much better.","index":369,"end_time":1069.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1068.33,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":370,"end_time":1071.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1071.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Rachel, Julia, what do you think?","index":371,"end_time":1073.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1072.33,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah, I think the only thing that I''m missing but I can be.","index":372,"end_time":1077.45,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1074.33,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"Someone can override me, is on the left.","index":373,"end_time":1083.3,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1080.9,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"It feels like, yes, it''s a squiggle, but in my mind it''s this squiggle of a journey of, you know, going off into all these different Facets and corners rather than playing in the same space.","index":374,"end_time":1096.58,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1083.46,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":375,"end_time":1097.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1097.06,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I do think the right feels much more aligned with the complex challenge of, like, what we''re trying to help solve.","index":376,"end_time":1105.94,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1098.1,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"So that''s my immediate reaction.","index":377,"end_time":1109.84,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1108.08,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":378,"end_time":1111.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1110.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We wanted to go with, like, the scribble because that was in the slide deck that you guys had shared as fodder.","index":379,"end_time":1116.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1111.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"One other thing, I mean, could even be, like, a really poorly drawn, like, map with some X''s and, like, you''re kind of going all these different things and it''s not leading you anywhere.","index":380,"end_time":1125.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1116.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know, that could be another approach.","index":381,"end_time":1127.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1125.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I do think it''s clearer.","index":382,"end_time":1129.68,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1128.16,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"The only thing is I would make the before and after either noetic orange.","index":383,"end_time":1134.56,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1129.68,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Probably noetic orange.","index":384,"end_time":1136.11,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1135.07,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"And then they''ll learn more.","index":385,"end_time":1137.07,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1136.11,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"The green.","index":386,"end_time":1137.71,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1137.07,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Okay.","index":387,"end_time":1138.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1138.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Just so it''s easier for people to read.","index":388,"end_time":1141.07,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1138.83,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":389,"end_time":1142.27,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1141.71,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"And then the learn more.","index":390,"end_time":1144.03,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1142.99,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Maybe a little bit bigger and either both capitalized or both lowercase because it just looks off.","index":391,"end_time":1150.67,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1144.03,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"But I do think it''s clearer.","index":392,"end_time":1152.83,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1151.31,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":393,"end_time":1154.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1154.11,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And I think that.","index":394,"end_time":1155.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1154.47,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I hear you, Julia.","index":395,"end_time":1157.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1156.19,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I. I think we''re fine.","index":396,"end_time":1159.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1157.63,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Because.","index":397,"end_time":1159.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1159.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"AI right now is so inherently messy.","index":398,"end_time":1166.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1162.44,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"If I was just talking about, like, before and after of process, it would be like a process, but it''s not quite working.","index":399,"end_time":1172.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1166.12,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"But I feel like it is a free for all in the AI space.","index":400,"end_time":1177.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1173.24,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So I think the cluster perfect is fine.","index":401,"end_time":1182.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1177.72,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"All right.","index":402,"end_time":1185.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1184.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"At this.","index":403,"end_time":1188.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1187.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I can pull up the last version as well.","index":404,"end_time":1191.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1188.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":405,"end_time":1194.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1193.81,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So this one, just.","index":406,"end_time":1195.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1194.21,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"This one we really liked with.","index":407,"end_time":1196.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1195.09,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"With the Get a handle on the lions just didn''t translate for us.","index":408,"end_time":1201.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1196.65,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Like, I get it.","index":409,"end_time":1201.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1201.21,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"It''s like the unkept looking and then the neat looking one, but it just didn''t seem to translate to what we were trying to say.","index":410,"end_time":1208.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1201.81,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":411,"end_time":1209.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1208.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we did literal handles.","index":412,"end_time":1211.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1209.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":413,"end_time":1213.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1213.6,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":414,"end_time":1216.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1216.48,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And it''s just.","index":415,"end_time":1217.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1216.88,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"It''s very symbolically good because it''s sort of like everybody''s kind of doing their own.","index":416,"end_time":1223.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1217.72,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":417,"end_time":1224.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1224,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":418,"end_time":1225.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1224.8,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And Rachel, we can make the same color changes on this as well.","index":419,"end_time":1228.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1225.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then I''ll show the previous.","index":420,"end_time":1231.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1230.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You''re on mute, Rach.","index":421,"end_time":1232.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1231.84,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Sorry.","index":422,"end_time":1234.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1234.08,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I was switching computers because my work computer needs to be updated for the buttons.","index":423,"end_time":1239.44,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1234.52,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"I think it''s just the same feedback where they should.","index":424,"end_time":1242.15,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1239.83,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"All the text needs to be a little bigger.","index":425,"end_time":1243.95,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1242.15,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Learn and more should both be capital.","index":426,"end_time":1245.51,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1243.95,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"And I think it should be on the green because it''s just a little difficult to read.","index":427,"end_time":1249.03,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1245.59,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"But.","index":428,"end_time":1249.39,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1249.03,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Yep.","index":429,"end_time":1249.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1249.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And the same with the orange.","index":430,"end_time":1251.35,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1250.23,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"But it does look clearer, which is great.","index":431,"end_time":1253.51,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1251.35,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":432,"end_time":1254.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1254.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"To think.","index":433,"end_time":1255.59,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1255.03,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"That was the other version.","index":434,"end_time":1258.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1257.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So here.","index":435,"end_time":1259.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1258.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think we were good with that one.","index":436,"end_time":1264.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1263.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Mm.","index":437,"end_time":1265.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1265.28,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"But we can make the same color and text changes for the CTA in these logos.","index":438,"end_time":1272.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1266.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Great.","index":439,"end_time":1273.6,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1273.2,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"Right.","index":440,"end_time":1276.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1276.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then.","index":441,"end_time":1277.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1276.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Experiments into repeatable momentum.","index":442,"end_time":1281.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1279.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Changing that to workflows.","index":443,"end_time":1284.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1283.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The scattered sticky notes versus true workflow.","index":444,"end_time":1288.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1285.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I like that.","index":445,"end_time":1290,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1289.2,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":446,"end_time":1290.56,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1290.24,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"I think this works a lot.","index":447,"end_time":1291.6,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1290.56,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":448,"end_time":1292.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1291.94,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Stronger.","index":449,"end_time":1292.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1292.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s a lot better.","index":450,"end_time":1294.26,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1293.14,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"I still wouldn''t do the gray as the background because I just think it''s hard.","index":451,"end_time":1298.18,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1294.34,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"But if you want to do, like, a really light gray, then I think it''s okay.","index":452,"end_time":1301.14,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1298.18,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Okay.","index":453,"end_time":1302.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1301.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":454,"end_time":1302.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1302.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I like the idea of gray.","index":455,"end_time":1303.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1302.58,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Agree.","index":456,"end_time":1304.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1303.9,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Lighter.","index":457,"end_time":1304.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1304.18,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Just because it''s so colorful with the.","index":458,"end_time":1306.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1304.9,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yes.","index":459,"end_time":1307.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1306.86,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Of the post, its.","index":460,"end_time":1308.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1307.38,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"But I agree it''s just a little dark for.","index":461,"end_time":1310.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1308.34,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Especially for seeing the sub headers.","index":462,"end_time":1313.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1310.78,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yep.","index":463,"end_time":1314.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1313.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":464,"end_time":1315.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1314.58,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":465,"end_time":1316.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1316.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":466,"end_time":1318.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1317.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then the landing page as well.","index":467,"end_time":1320.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1318.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":468,"end_time":1327.79,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1327.31,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"So Rachel or Julia, do you want to talk about this one?","index":469,"end_time":1330.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1327.79,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":470,"end_time":1332.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1332.11,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Julia, do you want to just both start.","index":471,"end_time":1335.63,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1332.91,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Start with each section.","index":472,"end_time":1336.79,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1335.79,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"We''ll both give our feedback.","index":473,"end_time":1338.11,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1336.79,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Yep.","index":474,"end_time":1338.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1338.19,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Okay.","index":475,"end_time":1340.15,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1339.63,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"So for this one, it''s the same thing where the background''s too dark.","index":476,"end_time":1346.16,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1340.15,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"We have to make sure everything''s accessible.","index":477,"end_time":1348.04,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1346.16,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"And also the images overall, to us just felt very stock and AI generated.","index":478,"end_time":1353.72,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1348.52,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":479,"end_time":1357.6,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1357.24,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"I think there''s, like, this realness that''s missing.","index":480,"end_time":1361.4,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1357.6,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"Whether that''s omitting the person''s face and having more of a zoom in or looking for different imagery options.","index":481,"end_time":1370.21,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1362.52,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"I think that could work a little bit stronger.","index":482,"end_time":1372.37,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1370.21,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":483,"end_time":1373.25,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1372.77,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"And then the next section is making.","index":484,"end_time":1375.85,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1373.81,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Me sign in real quick.","index":485,"end_time":1376.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1375.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No worries.","index":486,"end_time":1377.65,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1376.93,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"I did really new computer, so I''m, like, signed out of everything.","index":487,"end_time":1382.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1378.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Don''t worry.","index":488,"end_time":1383.65,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1383.01,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"Rachel and I have been.","index":489,"end_time":1384.73,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1383.65,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"Have competing teams issues on our end.","index":490,"end_time":1388.69,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1384.73,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":491,"end_time":1389.45,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1389.09,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Teams has not been our friend.","index":492,"end_time":1390.77,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1389.45,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"However, coming into this meeting, I had a breakthrough, so I think I''m on the other side of my issues.","index":493,"end_time":1396.93,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1391.17,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"I''m hoping I am now that I restart.","index":494,"end_time":1399.71,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1397.59,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"We also have Oxford commas that needs.","index":495,"end_time":1401.99,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1399.71,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"To be removed, be omitted.","index":496,"end_time":1403.27,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1401.99,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"I think that the visuals that we made our way into in the Playbooks are more where we want to be.","index":497,"end_time":1411.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1403.51,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"This is.","index":498,"end_time":1412.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1412.31,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"This reminds me of where we kind of started with the Playbooks, and we wanted to make everything, like, a little bit.","index":499,"end_time":1418.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1412.83,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"A little bit lighter, a little bit more human.","index":500,"end_time":1420.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1418.15,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"These people look kind of dark and plastic.","index":501,"end_time":1425.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1422.71,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Like bots.","index":502,"end_time":1427.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1426.4,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":503,"end_time":1428.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1427.84,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And although their skin is perfect, but I think where we, like, ended up, you know, if you look at the.","index":504,"end_time":1436.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1428.56,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"At the Playbooks, that''s.","index":505,"end_time":1439.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1436.72,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"That''s the vibe.","index":506,"end_time":1439.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1439.12,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":507,"end_time":1440.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1440.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I got you a little bit more real representation.","index":508,"end_time":1443.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1440.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":509,"end_time":1444.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1444.16,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"The next section.","index":510,"end_time":1447.6,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1446.08,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Oxford comma in the second bullet.","index":511,"end_time":1454.01,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1451.45,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"And then I''m just gonna make a.","index":512,"end_time":1456.41,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1455.21,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"General comment for Oxford comms.","index":513,"end_time":1458.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1456.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":514,"end_time":1458.89,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1458.41,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":515,"end_time":1459.93,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1459.29,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"And then, Julie, was this the one that we wanted a little bit stronger.","index":516,"end_time":1463.37,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1459.93,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"I don''t think this was the one.","index":517,"end_time":1469.89,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1468.41,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"I thought it was the next one.","index":518,"end_time":1471.13,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1469.89,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"Okay.","index":519,"end_time":1471.61,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1471.13,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":520,"end_time":1472.09,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1471.61,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Oh, ours was gray.","index":521,"end_time":1474.17,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1472.49,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"This looks better with the white.","index":522,"end_time":1475.77,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1474.17,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":523,"end_time":1476.41,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1475.93,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"But I do think the boxes still kind of blend.","index":524,"end_time":1479.94,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1476.9,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"So I think those need to be a slightly different color.","index":525,"end_time":1485.46,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1482.1,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Even if it''s just like the faded out yellow and then the icons are in a different color.","index":526,"end_time":1492.9,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1486.42,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"But.","index":527,"end_time":1493.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1492.9,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"But this does look better than.","index":528,"end_time":1495.34,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1494.1,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"I feel like what we were looking.","index":529,"end_time":1496.42,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1495.34,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"But like let''s make them really pop.","index":530,"end_time":1499.62,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1497.62,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Yep.","index":531,"end_time":1500.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1499.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But it''s great the way that this is broken out.","index":532,"end_time":1503.94,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1501.7,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Also I don''t know if this matters as much because it''s not going to be on NAV right now, but on the rest of our website our buttons were all lowercase.","index":533,"end_time":1514.58,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1505.54,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Nancy, do you think it matters for this?","index":534,"end_time":1516.9,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1515.06,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Our buttons were lower.","index":535,"end_time":1520.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1518.66,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Lowercase.","index":536,"end_time":1520.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1520.02,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":537,"end_time":1521.18,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1520.82,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Let me.","index":538,"end_time":1521.62,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1521.18,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"We might as well.","index":539,"end_time":1522.66,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1521.7,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"We might as well just make it compliant.","index":540,"end_time":1524.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1522.9,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"My bigger comment was like, see how it works?","index":541,"end_time":1528.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1525.22,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Where does that click you?","index":542,"end_time":1529.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1528.82,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah, I was thinking the same thing.","index":543,"end_time":1532.64,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1531.48,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"But this is just a picture, right Colin?","index":544,"end_time":1534.44,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1532.64,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":545,"end_time":1536.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1534.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We haven''t built this.","index":546,"end_time":1537.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1536.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This is just a picture.","index":547,"end_time":1538.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1537.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The.","index":548,"end_time":1540.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1540.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The thing that we had in mind was alluding to a form.","index":549,"end_time":1543.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1540.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Once they click that.","index":550,"end_time":1544.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1543.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":551,"end_time":1546.52,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1545.96,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Could we also do the words discover, design, enable, activate in a color so they pop like whatever the color the icon is, please.","index":552,"end_time":1555.16,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1547.16,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Did you share the 1 sheeters with these guys?","index":553,"end_time":1557.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1555.73,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yes, they have them.","index":554,"end_time":1559.09,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1557.97,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":555,"end_time":1559.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1559.33,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And.","index":556,"end_time":1561.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1561.25,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And Colin, knowing that see how it works is going to go to a form.","index":557,"end_time":1566.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1562.13,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I think maybe it should say learn more or.","index":558,"end_time":1571.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1566.17,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":559,"end_time":1571.609,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1571.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Or even connect with.","index":560,"end_time":1572.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1571.609,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I don''t know.","index":561,"end_time":1572.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1572.41,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Like I just don''t want people to feel bait and switch.","index":562,"end_time":1574.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1572.85,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Like they think they''re going to get some.","index":563,"end_time":1576.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1574.69,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Something.","index":564,"end_time":1576.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1576.45,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Some takeaway.","index":565,"end_time":1577.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1577.01,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":566,"end_time":1578.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1578.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean try to battle that with like the.","index":567,"end_time":1580.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1578.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We guide you through four clear steps.","index":568,"end_time":1582.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1580.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But yeah.","index":569,"end_time":1584.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1582.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Come up with something in between there.","index":570,"end_time":1585.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1584.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Also for our four phase approach to sustainable AI adoption and impact.","index":571,"end_time":1592.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1587.41,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I don''t think we want to be.","index":572,"end_time":1593.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1592.45,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"All.","index":573,"end_time":1594.29,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1593.89,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"Capitals with that.","index":574,"end_time":1597.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1596.21,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Are the other sections.","index":575,"end_time":1600.69,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1599.49,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"I think the other sections are all capitals.","index":576,"end_time":1602.85,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1600.69,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"So we would have to change it for all.","index":577,"end_time":1605.09,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1603.41,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":578,"end_time":1605.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1605.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So sentence case for these.","index":579,"end_time":1607.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1605.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":580,"end_time":1608.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1607.97,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":581,"end_time":1611.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1611.02,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"That''s a peeve of mine.","index":582,"end_time":1612.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1611.26,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I don''t like capitalizing things that.","index":583,"end_time":1614.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1612.78,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"All good.","index":584,"end_time":1616.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1616.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Every brand''s got their.","index":585,"end_time":1617.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1616.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":586,"end_time":1618.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1617.9,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"This is looking great though.","index":587,"end_time":1620.02,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1618.62,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Okay.","index":588,"end_time":1620.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1620.02,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":589,"end_time":1620.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1620.38,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I think it feels very.","index":590,"end_time":1621.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1620.7,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"We should have started by saying like I think it feels very.","index":591,"end_time":1625.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1622.38,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Legit and evolved.","index":592,"end_time":1629.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1627.1,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Well.","index":593,"end_time":1631.34,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1631.02,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"And it.","index":594,"end_time":1631.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1631.34,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":595,"end_time":1632.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1631.78,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And it breaks it out into like bite sized ideas, which is good.","index":596,"end_time":1636.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1632.1,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":597,"end_time":1637.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1636.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And like you can even see a little bit over here, like looking at the whole web Page instead of this zoomed in version.","index":598,"end_time":1641.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1637.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s, it''s nice on the eyes.","index":599,"end_time":1643.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1641.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":600,"end_time":1643.52,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1643.16,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"The bite sized chunks work.","index":601,"end_time":1644.88,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1643.52,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":602,"end_time":1645.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1644.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So people''s brains work now.","index":603,"end_time":1647.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1645.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Attention spans are so low.","index":604,"end_time":1648.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1647.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sure is.","index":605,"end_time":1649.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1649,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I wasn''t paying attention and then Julia.","index":606,"end_time":1654.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1650.84,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"This was the part, right?","index":607,"end_time":1655.04,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1654.24,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":608,"end_time":1655.28,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1655.04,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"This is the section we just felt.","index":609,"end_time":1656.76,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1655.28,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"I think that these check marks overall felt a little.","index":610,"end_time":1661.08,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1656.76,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"Bland, quite frankly.","index":611,"end_time":1666.6,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1664.84,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"Not like they were truly unique to us.","index":612,"end_time":1670.6,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1666.6,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"Like they weren''t hard hitting enough or like they felt a little generic maybe.","index":613,"end_time":1676.12,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1671.56,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":614,"end_time":1679.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1678.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"From a design perspective.","index":615,"end_time":1681.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1679.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Do you guys like how this is laid out or.","index":616,"end_time":1682.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1681.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, yeah, I do.","index":617,"end_time":1684.28,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1682.84,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"I think it works well, especially with the way the content flows before and after.","index":618,"end_time":1690.52,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1684.44,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"Okay, great.","index":619,"end_time":1691.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1691.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, we can rewrite that.","index":620,"end_time":1693.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1692.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Imagine we can''t use this.","index":621,"end_time":1696.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1695.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, it would, it would auto scroll and.","index":622,"end_time":1698.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1696.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, so if it''s auto scrolled, that''s great.","index":623,"end_time":1700.93,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1698.89,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"I was going to say, Nancy, can we use all of these brands?","index":624,"end_time":1704.25,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1700.93,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Well, I mean we''re speaking to AI specifically.","index":625,"end_time":1712.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1707.69,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Or we could do trusted thought partner.","index":626,"end_time":1717.93,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1715.69,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Yeah, like I, I get a little nervous about it.","index":627,"end_time":1723.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1719.13,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Intimating that we''re doing this work for them.","index":628,"end_time":1726.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1723.59,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"All of them.","index":629,"end_time":1727.19,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1726.51,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Could we word it differently?","index":630,"end_time":1732.07,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1730.39,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Like we''re a thought partner to these or we''re a brand builder or something if we want to use them.","index":631,"end_time":1739.03,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1732.15,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"I mean you don''t actually say it but like here we are on the AI services page.","index":632,"end_time":1747.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1741.35,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I don''t know.","index":633,"end_time":1748.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1747.43,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Tricky.","index":634,"end_time":1751.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1750.59,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I don''t know that you can get away with it.","index":635,"end_time":1757.15,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1755.31,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"Candidly I want to, I think this works well, but I don''t know that we can get.","index":636,"end_time":1763.11,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1757.39,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"Yeah, like I love the idea of it but I, but we''re not doing this kind of work for these companies.","index":637,"end_time":1769.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1763.11,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"What if we flipped it and this is like the punctuation at the end of the doc of the page.","index":638,"end_time":1775.87,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1769.71,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"And, and we do keep language somewhat vague like, like it is but saying, you know, Noetic is a trusted thought leader for the following brands.","index":639,"end_time":1786.05,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1776.3,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"So it doesn''t feel like it''s AI content.","index":640,"end_time":1788.77,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1786.05,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"I love that, I love that.","index":641,"end_time":1790.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1788.85,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Because if it''s above the AI content, it just feels like it''s for AI.","index":642,"end_time":1794.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1790.21,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Like it''s for AI.","index":643,"end_time":1795.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1794.77,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":644,"end_time":1796.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1795.97,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And, and.","index":645,"end_time":1797.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1796.33,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Can you do the zoom out?","index":646,"end_time":1801.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1799.25,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I, I, I slightly lost track of where on the page we are.","index":647,"end_time":1807.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1803.18,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":648,"end_time":1807.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1807.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''re towards the bottom.","index":649,"end_time":1808.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1807.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":650,"end_time":1810.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1809.58,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":651,"end_time":1812.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1812.38,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I think that''s Julia.","index":652,"end_time":1814.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1813.18,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I think that''s really good.","index":653,"end_time":1817.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1814.7,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":654,"end_time":1817.66,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1817.34,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"I think it comes after that dark gray bar.","index":655,"end_time":1820.14,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1817.66,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"Okay.","index":656,"end_time":1821.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1820.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yep, that''s a great idea.","index":657,"end_time":1823.26,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1821.9,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"And then I think in the section we haven''t gone through, I''m fairly certain I loved the Last bullet.","index":658,"end_time":1831.97,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1825.42,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":659,"end_time":1832.37,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1832.05,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"I don''t remember what it reads right now, but I wanted to get kind of the group thought on if it should be.","index":660,"end_time":1839.33,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1832.37,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"Do we.","index":661,"end_time":1842.85,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1842.29,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Nancy, Is it correct?","index":662,"end_time":1844.33,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1842.93,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"20 years empowering brands and teams.","index":663,"end_time":1846.81,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1844.33,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Isn''t it more 22?","index":664,"end_time":1848.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1846.81,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I think it''s 23 as of November.","index":665,"end_time":1851.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1849.33,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Or should we do 20?","index":666,"end_time":1852.476,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1851.53,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"20 plus that way it''s evergreen.","index":667,"end_time":1854.85,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1852.544,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Yes.","index":668,"end_time":1855.26,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1855.1,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"Yeah, 20 plus is good.","index":669,"end_time":1856.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1855.26,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I just felt like that la.","index":670,"end_time":1862.22,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1860.38,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"The last bullet feels really strong to me.","index":671,"end_time":1866.7,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1862.46,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"I don''t know if we include that sentiment in maybe the head, you know, the subhead right here, or if it becomes more of a point elsewhere.","index":672,"end_time":1875.66,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1867.18,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"But, like, what we''re trying to achieve with this page and with this campaign is that we have the training and the ability to.","index":673,"end_time":1886.23,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1876.06,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"To engage your team and bring clarity to something that you''re struggling with right now.","index":674,"end_time":1893.26,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1886.38,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":675,"end_time":1893.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1893.42,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And it''s like always humans in the loop.","index":676,"end_time":1896.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1893.9,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":677,"end_time":1896.94,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1896.46,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":678,"end_time":1898.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1897.58,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Well, a couple thoughts.","index":679,"end_time":1903.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1901.42,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Like, you could.","index":680,"end_time":1904.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1903.7,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"You could flip it and make that the top one.","index":681,"end_time":1906.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1904.42,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"You could.","index":682,"end_time":1911.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1910.78,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"You could honestly flip it to like, reverse order where like, human skills, then deep expertise, then women owned, then number of years you could make them.","index":683,"end_time":1921.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1911.3,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I don''t know.","index":684,"end_time":1926.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1925.9,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I think it would get too busy about what I was going to say, so never mind.","index":685,"end_time":1929.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1926.46,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah, why don''t we flip them and.","index":686,"end_time":1931.5,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1929.82,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"And hopefully that kind of satisfies it.","index":687,"end_time":1934.22,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1931.66,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"What is the.","index":688,"end_time":1944.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1943.1,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Mechanically for this?","index":689,"end_time":1948.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1946.67,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Once it.","index":690,"end_time":1949.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1948.75,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Once you make the changes.","index":691,"end_time":1951.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1949.55,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"It''S.","index":692,"end_time":1954.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1953.47,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"It''s a landing page.","index":693,"end_time":1955.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1954.19,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"But like, if I wanted to send a link to the landing page in, like, my outreach, I could do that, right?","index":694,"end_time":1961.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1955.43,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":695,"end_time":1962.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1962.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":696,"end_time":1963.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1963.07,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Okay.","index":697,"end_time":1964.11,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1963.59,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"I don''t know how I feel about the footer part.","index":698,"end_time":1967.15,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1964.35,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"I like the idea of booking a.","index":699,"end_time":1969.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1967.39,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Call, but I feel like it''s so prominent.","index":700,"end_time":1971.79,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1969.67,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Is not like, typical for.","index":701,"end_time":1973.53,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1971.79,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"For Noetic.","index":702,"end_time":1976.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1973.68,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Like, it''s a little bit in your face.","index":703,"end_time":1978.4,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1976.72,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Ready to see the impact?","index":704,"end_time":1981.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1980.08,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I''m good with it.","index":705,"end_time":1984.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1983.2,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I think it''s worth trying.","index":706,"end_time":1985.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1984.28,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Okay.","index":707,"end_time":1986.32,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1985.76,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"It''s not like.","index":708,"end_time":1987.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1986.8,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"You know, it doesn''t force anything, but it gives you a place to be, like.","index":709,"end_time":1993.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1989.52,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah, I want to talk about that.","index":710,"end_time":1994.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1993.52,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":711,"end_time":1995.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1994.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And the other thing, Rachel, is we''re very zoomed into this section right now.","index":712,"end_time":1998.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1995.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know, if someone is reading through the page, absorbing the content, they''re making it all the way down there.","index":713,"end_time":2002.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1998.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They are more likely to actually engage with that CTA and feel like it''s less of a burden.","index":714,"end_time":2007.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2002.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, great.","index":715,"end_time":2008.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2007.5,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I know it would be interesting to see time on page here.","index":716,"end_time":2012.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2008.7,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":717,"end_time":2013.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2012.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":718,"end_time":2013.82,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2013.34,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"I love the format.","index":719,"end_time":2015.58,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2014.38,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"I think it''s really, really cool.","index":720,"end_time":2017.82,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2015.66,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":721,"end_time":2019.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2018.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, well, we will get those updates made.","index":722,"end_time":2021.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2019.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":723,"end_time":2023.18,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2022.46,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":724,"end_time":2023.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2023.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":725,"end_time":2026.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2025.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Diving into November for paid ads.","index":726,"end_time":2030.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2027.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So still hovering up just above the industry benchmark of 0.44.","index":727,"end_time":2034.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2030.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Click through rate 0.47 saw three leads come in at a $541 cost per lead.","index":728,"end_time":2040.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2034.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We do have, we are kind of spread thin on campaigns as far as making the most out of the book.","index":729,"end_time":2046.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2041.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I was very surprised to see six.","index":730,"end_time":2049.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2047.13,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"What are the six?","index":731,"end_time":2050.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2049.21,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So we have the thought leadership, we have.","index":732,"end_time":2055.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2051.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Natalie, you probably have it more on the top of your head right now if you want to jump in.","index":733,"end_time":2060.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2056.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I''m opening it up.","index":734,"end_time":2062.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2061.45,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"But we have, we also have a.","index":735,"end_time":2064.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2062.61,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Couple where we''re doing the document downloads.","index":736,"end_time":2066.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2064.01,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Itself versus taking the playbooks.","index":737,"end_time":2069.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2066.89,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":738,"end_time":2070.45,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2070.05,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"To the Noetic site.","index":739,"end_time":2071.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2070.45,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Let me open it up.","index":740,"end_time":2073.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2071.97,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Well, so what you''re calling campaign, I don''t know if we''re using the term the same way.","index":741,"end_time":2079.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2074.05,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Like, I''m thinking campaign is like new marketing leads is a campaign.","index":742,"end_time":2084.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2079.33,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"You know, the AI stuff we''re doing now is a campaign.","index":743,"end_time":2089.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2085.25,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Attractions was a campaign.","index":744,"end_time":2091.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2089.65,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I don''t, I, I, I''m not trying to.","index":745,"end_time":2096.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2094.01,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Split hairs.","index":746,"end_time":2099.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2098.41,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I''m just trying to get a sense for like when we say campaign, what do we really mean?","index":747,"end_time":2103.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2099.29,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":748,"end_time":2104.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2103.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Bullet.","index":749,"end_time":2106.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2106.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":750,"end_time":2120.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2120.18,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So we have the full, full playbooks for first year CMOs, full playbooks for healthcare, and then the infographics for playbook, CM for the infographics for first year CMO infographics for healthcare, and then we also have the marketing leaders campaign from a couple of months ago, which was a different playbook.","index":751,"end_time":2139.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2120.38,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah, so I think it''s five, not six.","index":752,"end_time":2143.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2142.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, say them again.","index":753,"end_time":2148.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2147.45,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So the full playbook for first year CMOs, full playbook for healthcare, the infographics for first year CMO infographic for healthcare, and then the new marketing leaders.","index":754,"end_time":2164.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2150.01,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Playbook.","index":755,"end_time":2166.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2166.01,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Sorry, say the very last one again.","index":756,"end_time":2177.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2175.62,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"New marketing leaders playbook.","index":757,"end_time":2180.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2178.9,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"How is the new marketing leaders playbook different than the new CMOS playbook?","index":758,"end_time":2195.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2189.14,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"That''s the same thing.","index":759,"end_time":2196.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2195.94,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"That is the, it''s the marketing leadership playbook.","index":760,"end_time":2201.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2198.58,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I think that one was done a couple months ago.","index":761,"end_time":2203.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2201.22,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Oh, that''s, that''s different.","index":762,"end_time":2204.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2203.3,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah, the alignment one.","index":763,"end_time":2206.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2204.58,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And again.","index":764,"end_time":2211.699,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2209.7,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Because I''m trying to figure out if we''re at 5 and we''re spread too thin.","index":765,"end_time":2214.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2211.699,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I gotta understand what all five are so that when we cut things, we know what we''re cutting.","index":766,"end_time":2223.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2218.58,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So when you say infographic around first time CMOs and infographic around health care.","index":767,"end_time":2230.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2223.68,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Are you speaking to.","index":768,"end_time":2234.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2231.84,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"The bite sized versions that we made of the full playbooks?","index":769,"end_time":2240.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2237.12,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Got it.","index":770,"end_time":2241.52,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2240.88,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"Okay.","index":771,"end_time":2242.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2241.52,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Okay, I understand now.","index":772,"end_time":2246,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2244.48,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So essentially what you''re saying is that if we have spend against all of those things, we''re spread too thin.","index":773,"end_time":2255.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2250.15,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So where are we seeing the traction?","index":774,"end_time":2260.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2257.43,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So we''re seeing the traction.","index":775,"end_time":2262.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2261.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And last month it was the infographics for healthcare and the healthcare job titles.","index":776,"end_time":2269.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2262.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What do you mean by healthcare job titles?","index":777,"end_time":2273.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2272.23,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So that''s the document download that we have for the healthcare playbook.","index":778,"end_time":2278.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2274.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So from a campaign perspective, we were seeing traction on the healthcare playbook and the healthcare.","index":779,"end_time":2286.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2280.72,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Like the bite size.","index":780,"end_time":2287.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2286.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, bite size.","index":781,"end_time":2288.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2287.64,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So what''s your, what''s your recommendation of how much to slim and what to keep and whatnot?","index":782,"end_time":2300.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2295.12,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So I think the documents are providing the most fruit.","index":783,"end_time":2305.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2301.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think that the more like brand awareness campaigns towards the job title signals that we were running out of clay for new hires has just become costly and I think there''s just probably a lot of noise that they''re dealing with.","index":784,"end_time":2320.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2306.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s a very highly targeted audience on LinkedIn.","index":785,"end_time":2324.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2321.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So their cost per click tends to be higher versus these document downloads.","index":786,"end_time":2327.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2324.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know, they''re, they''re giving you their contact information, they''re absorbing your content.","index":787,"end_time":2332,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2328.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think there''s more bang for the buck there.","index":788,"end_time":2333.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2332.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, so if we stopped doing the new CMO.","index":789,"end_time":2340.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2335.52,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"That, that outreach and, and I.","index":790,"end_time":2346.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2342.4,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"It feels like the marketing leadership one, that alignment one has been kind of out there for a while.","index":791,"end_time":2353.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2346.56,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah, I think we paused that one as well.","index":792,"end_time":2355.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2353.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Especially since we want to introduce AI.","index":793,"end_time":2356.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2355.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, right.","index":794,"end_time":2358.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2357.47,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Well, and then that.","index":795,"end_time":2360.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2359.15,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So that brings me to my next question is, is if we''re going out with AI, do we need to cut back even more?","index":796,"end_time":2367.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2360.11,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Because I don''t want to go out with a whisper.","index":797,"end_time":2368.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2367.19,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":798,"end_time":2370.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2369.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I think if we have AI, we have.","index":799,"end_time":2374.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2371.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think the bite size infographics, I would keep those versus the full length playbooks because once they download the bite size, then they''re more enticed to just get the playbooks in general anyways.","index":800,"end_time":2388.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2377.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And those are already listed on the website.","index":801,"end_time":2390.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2388.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I would have the infographics and the AI campaign.","index":802,"end_time":2393.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2390.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that''s three right there.","index":803,"end_time":2394.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2393.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I agree.","index":804,"end_time":2395.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2394.97,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yep.","index":805,"end_time":2396.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2395.93,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":806,"end_time":2399.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2398.57,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":807,"end_time":2401.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2400.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, we can make that change as well.","index":808,"end_time":2403.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2401.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And when you say AI campaign, like I''m thinking because it''s campaign.","index":809,"end_time":2407.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2404.09,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So it''s, it''s, it''s the email sequences, it''s the ads we just looked at and getting the page live.","index":810,"end_time":2414.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2407.85,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah, I was talking just specifically right now about the LinkedIn ads.","index":811,"end_time":2418.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2414.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But yes, when we, you know, I''m talking campaign for AI BE emails, LinkedIn outreach and LinkedIn ads.","index":812,"end_time":2423.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2418.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And it might be terminology confusing too, because we set up one campaign in LinkedIn called Mid Noetic and then there''s A bunch of ad sets.","index":813,"end_time":2433.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2424.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s what we''re referring to as campaigns.","index":814,"end_time":2435.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2433.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If it was our own ad platform, we would set them up as campaigns over in yours.","index":815,"end_time":2439.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2435.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So.","index":816,"end_time":2439.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2439.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean, I know that like when we''re talking about expense, that we''re only talking about the.","index":817,"end_time":2447.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2439.54,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"The paid component, but when we''re thinking about just, you know, all of the content that we''re putting out there, you got to think in terms of campaign.","index":818,"end_time":2456.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2447.14,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":819,"end_time":2457.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2456.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Just not saying too many things at once.","index":820,"end_time":2459.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2457.7,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":821,"end_time":2459.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2459.54,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":822,"end_time":2460.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2459.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":823,"end_time":2462.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2461.54,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So add an AI.","index":824,"end_time":2466.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2463.71,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"The infographic on first time cmos infographic on healthcare is what we''re.","index":825,"end_time":2472.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2466.51,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Okay, can you go back to that same slide you were on?","index":826,"end_time":2476.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2472.59,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":827,"end_time":2495.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2495.72,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"It''s such a bummer on the new marketing leaders.","index":828,"end_time":2499.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2495.96,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I just.","index":829,"end_time":2500.28,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2499.72,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"As you said, I think they''re highly sought after.","index":830,"end_time":2502.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2500.28,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"All of these audiences unfortunately are.","index":831,"end_time":2505.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2503.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":832,"end_time":2506.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2506.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":833,"end_time":2510.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2509.64,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Anything else on this one?","index":834,"end_time":2511.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2510.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No.","index":835,"end_time":2512.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2512.28,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I think we''re still in the land of analytics though.","index":836,"end_time":2515.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2512.64,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"On the next.","index":837,"end_time":2515.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2515.32,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":838,"end_time":2517.09,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2516.89,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"Well, we also have.","index":839,"end_time":2517.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2517.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":840,"end_time":2517.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2517.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"With the metrics and Rachel, I know you asked about goals.","index":841,"end_time":2520.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2517.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We did not have a goal that was dedicated to new contacts.","index":842,"end_time":2522.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2520.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It was all about stage zero deals and moving them to stage one.","index":843,"end_time":2526.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2522.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And getting either 16 new opportunities or 200,000 in new hunting opportunities was the goals that we set at the beginning of the year.","index":844,"end_time":2536.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2529.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":845,"end_time":2537.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2537.61,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And then to stage one or later.","index":846,"end_time":2539.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2537.97,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Right.","index":847,"end_time":2539.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2539.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Do you have what we need for the dashboard?","index":848,"end_time":2546.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2542.98,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah, sorry, that was.","index":849,"end_time":2550.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2548.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sorry.","index":850,"end_time":2554.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2554.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"For the dashboard that was getting the leads count fixed or was that something else.","index":851,"end_time":2559.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2554.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"By conflating two things?","index":852,"end_time":2563.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2561.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Are you talking about Nancy, the number that wasn''t popping?","index":853,"end_time":2566.34,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2563.38,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"No, I''m talking about.","index":854,"end_time":2568.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2567.79,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I''m talking about holistically, do.","index":855,"end_time":2570.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2568.71,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Do we have the numbers that we need for the noetic dashboard that rack is asking?","index":856,"end_time":2577.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2570.59,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I think we should because we.","index":857,"end_time":2579.87,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2577.71,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"We were trying to figure out that one error and then the big thing was the different campaigns and the click through rate for each, which is here.","index":858,"end_time":2587.47,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2580.03,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"So I think we should be.","index":859,"end_time":2590.03,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2588.27,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"We should be good.","index":860,"end_time":2591.47,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2590.43,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"I agree.","index":861,"end_time":2592.39,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2591.87,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"I think we got that answered this morning.","index":862,"end_time":2594.19,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2592.39,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"So we haven''t heard back from Raki if she feels that she has everything she needs.","index":863,"end_time":2599.3,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2594.35,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"But based on what we asked, it looks like.","index":864,"end_time":2601.46,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2599.3,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"It looks like you gave us.","index":865,"end_time":2604.26,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2602.82,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"Okay, and then what was with the error?","index":866,"end_time":2607.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2604.34,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Fixed.","index":867,"end_time":2607.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2607.1,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Just so I have it in my brain.","index":868,"end_time":2609.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2607.78,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s.","index":869,"end_time":2610.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2609.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Pipedrive''s API is very limiting.","index":870,"end_time":2612.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2610.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So to get the data to display the way you want, you can''t say year to date, you can''t say this year, you have to say the last 12 months.","index":871,"end_time":2622.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2612.979,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I just adjusted the date range on there to say the last 12 months and it updated.","index":872,"end_time":2626.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2622.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":873,"end_time":2626.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2626.52,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And so then when you.","index":874,"end_time":2627.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2626.88,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So the.","index":875,"end_time":2628.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2627.96,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So the lead number for year to date, aka last 12 months was what, 100 and something, right?","index":876,"end_time":2635.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2628.6,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":877,"end_time":2636.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2636.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I can, Give me one second.","index":878,"end_time":2638.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2636.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I can pull that up.","index":879,"end_time":2639.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2638.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And Colin, this that I''m looking at is in the deck that you sent over for the agenda, correct?","index":880,"end_time":2645,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2639.88,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"The.","index":881,"end_time":2645.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2645.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The spreadsheet.","index":882,"end_time":2646.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2645.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":883,"end_time":2647.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2646.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''ll send this over right now.","index":884,"end_time":2648.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2647.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":885,"end_time":2649.68,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2649.16,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Thank you so much.","index":886,"end_time":2650.68,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2649.68,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"That way I can share with our team.","index":887,"end_time":2653.67,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2650.84,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"All right.","index":888,"end_time":2654.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2654.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This filtered back.","index":889,"end_time":2655.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2654.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So.","index":890,"end_time":2656.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2656.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Previous last.","index":891,"end_time":2660.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2659.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"12.","index":892,"end_time":2662.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2662.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Months include.","index":893,"end_time":2665.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2664.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Got the Jeopardy.","index":894,"end_time":2678.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2677.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Theme song playing in my head.","index":895,"end_time":2679.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2678.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":896,"end_time":2681.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2681.17,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"What I''m trying to resolve is in the pipedrive metrics dashboard.","index":897,"end_time":2687.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2681.37,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Our New north leads year to date is nowhere near that number.","index":898,"end_time":2695.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2688.93,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And I don''t know why.","index":899,"end_time":2699.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2698.53,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"For New north specifically.","index":900,"end_time":2706.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2705.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":901,"end_time":2707.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2707.26,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Can I just show you.","index":902,"end_time":2708.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2707.66,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, sorry, sure.","index":903,"end_time":2710.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2708.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Here.","index":904,"end_time":2719.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2719.1,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So I think that this would be pulling off of what''s tagged.","index":905,"end_time":2736.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2731.03,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":906,"end_time":2738.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2738.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Well, I think what we had originally or when we reset the dashboard because we were trying to give you guys something that you could look at.","index":907,"end_time":2746.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2738.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think it was one of the quarter goals or rocks that you had.","index":908,"end_time":2748.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2746.469,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think we combined that lead number on the dashboard or on data box to be your leads and our leads, we can switch that back to just reflect New North.","index":909,"end_time":2758.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2749.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I see.","index":910,"end_time":2760.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2759.36,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"This is one you guys had an effort to like.","index":911,"end_time":2765.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2763.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We want to use data box as one stop shop that we can go to for our numbers too.","index":912,"end_time":2769.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2765.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":913,"end_time":2770.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2770.24,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":914,"end_time":2774.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2774.4,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I mean.","index":915,"end_time":2775.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2774.8,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"The, the bottom line is it''s all about the stage zeros that we don''t have.","index":916,"end_time":2781.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2777.44,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Right.","index":917,"end_time":2782,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2781.6,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So 100 and whatever leads or 39.","index":918,"end_time":2786.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2782,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"It''s all about conversion at the end of the day.","index":919,"end_time":2790.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2787.69,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So.","index":920,"end_time":2790.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2790.09,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I don''t.","index":921,"end_time":2792.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2792.33,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"As long as we have that in pipe drive, I think it''s fine.","index":922,"end_time":2796.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2793.69,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"That you have it combined.","index":923,"end_time":2798.969,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2797.69,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Okay.","index":924,"end_time":2799.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2799.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And yeah, that, that was what I included in my email as well.","index":925,"end_time":2803.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2800.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I don''t know if there''s any updates with Waymo or Marriott.","index":926,"end_time":2806.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2803.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So what did I tell you last.","index":927,"end_time":2811.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2809.38,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"You were meeting with.","index":928,"end_time":2814.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2813.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I want to say it was Tanya from Marriott.","index":929,"end_time":2817.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2814.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yes.","index":930,"end_time":2818.58,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2818.18,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So I met with Tanya and I have one other.","index":931,"end_time":2820.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2818.58,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I met with Tanya live and.","index":932,"end_time":2822.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2820.5,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And there was nothing imminent, but she is open to introducing me to other people there.","index":933,"end_time":2828.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2822.06,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And so we''re supposed to get together in January.","index":934,"end_time":2830.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2828.38,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I have another woman there who initially engaged through LinkedIn DM.","index":935,"end_time":2836,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2830.58,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I can only communicate with her there unless she emails me, which I tried to get her to do, but she doesn''t.","index":936,"end_time":2841.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2836,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And so she''s gone quiet with Waymo.","index":937,"end_time":2844.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2841.52,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah, I think the last thing you mentioned there was they were expanding.","index":938,"end_time":2848,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2845.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I met with Linda, then I Met with Jackie.","index":939,"end_time":2850.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2848.16,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So Linda was the one who we knew from previous.","index":940,"end_time":2852.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2850.2,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Jackie''s her boss.","index":941,"end_time":2854.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2852.88,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"We had a good conversation, and then they needed to loop back together.","index":942,"end_time":2857.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2854.48,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And now I''m chasing back through Linda because I''m not hearing from Jackie.","index":943,"end_time":2861.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2857.88,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So December''s hard.","index":944,"end_time":2863.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2861.7,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":945,"end_time":2863.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2863.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I don''t think it''s.","index":946,"end_time":2865.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2864.66,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I don''t think it''s a no with them, but I think the biggest challenge with Waymo is, like, they''re moving really quickly, and how do you get aboard the bus?","index":947,"end_time":2873.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2866.42,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"With the right.","index":948,"end_time":2874.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2873.62,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"With the right opportunity.","index":949,"end_time":2875.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2874.58,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So, yeah, that''s as far as we are on both of those.","index":950,"end_time":2880.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2877.54,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":951,"end_time":2881.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2880.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":952,"end_time":2881.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2881.3,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Thank you for the update.","index":953,"end_time":2883.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2882.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yep.","index":954,"end_time":2883.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2883.3,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And then we have the metrics in there as well.","index":955,"end_time":2886.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2884.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We have seen a slight dip in visitors for past 30 days, but that being said, almost the inverse in the average session duration jumping up.","index":956,"end_time":2896.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2886.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So while the amount of visitors has slightly dropped, the average session duration has increased just as much.","index":957,"end_time":2902.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2897.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then the YouTube podcast views have jumped up 32%.","index":958,"end_time":2908.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2904.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that''s great to see.","index":959,"end_time":2909.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2908.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Wow.","index":960,"end_time":2910.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2909.95,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Why do you think who went live just before Mega.","index":961,"end_time":2914.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2910.67,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"It was.","index":962,"end_time":2916.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2916.38,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Let me just double check.","index":963,"end_time":2920.82,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2919.58,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"I don''t want to give you the wrong answer.","index":964,"end_time":2922.62,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2920.82,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"It was.","index":965,"end_time":2925.58,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2925.02,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"It was Mike Linton, which kind of makes sense why it would jump.","index":966,"end_time":2929.02,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2925.74,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s good.","index":967,"end_time":2931.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2930.78,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"It''s good.","index":968,"end_time":2932.34,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2931.82,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"But, yeah, I think that that''s got to be the reason why.","index":969,"end_time":2935.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2932.34,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Can you go to.","index":970,"end_time":2938.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2937.02,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"The website analytics page in.","index":971,"end_time":2943.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2940.31,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"In terms of time on page?","index":972,"end_time":2944.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2943.27,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I. I want to see the breakdown of where.","index":973,"end_time":2948.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2944.63,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":974,"end_time":2949.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2949.35,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I feel like we''re.","index":975,"end_time":2968.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2966.8,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"We''re seeing, like, a good uptick on some of these pages that are, like, still very modest numbers, but like the podcast page.","index":976,"end_time":2983.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2972.56,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Case studies.","index":977,"end_time":2986.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2985.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Case studies.","index":978,"end_time":2987.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2986.64,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Brand strategy.","index":979,"end_time":2991.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2990.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s a pretty significant jump right there.","index":980,"end_time":2993.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2991.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean, 63% out of 31 is not a huge number, but.","index":981,"end_time":2996.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2993.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, but the trending.","index":982,"end_time":3000.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2998.73,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":983,"end_time":3000.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3000.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":984,"end_time":3004.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3004.57,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"The Playbooks.","index":985,"end_time":3006.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3004.97,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"It''s interesting.","index":986,"end_time":3006.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3006.01,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I mean.","index":987,"end_time":3007.45,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3006.93,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"I don''t know what to make of that number.","index":988,"end_time":3012.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3011.37,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"It''s like, a solid number, but down a lot.","index":989,"end_time":3016.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3013.05,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":990,"end_time":3018.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3017.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I believe they were.","index":991,"end_time":3019.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3018.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That was the fresh content that we put up there.","index":992,"end_time":3021.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3019.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we were probably looking at around 150, 160 people, if my math is on going there the 30 days before this measurement.","index":993,"end_time":3033.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3024.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I think that was fresh content on there, too.","index":994,"end_time":3036,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3034.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":995,"end_time":3041.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3040.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And also we have our campaign set on the.","index":996,"end_time":3045.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3041.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The Legion form.","index":997,"end_time":3046.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3045.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''re not sending traffic to the site from those ads.","index":998,"end_time":3049.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3046.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''re trying to just lower the barrier so they convert right on LinkedIn.","index":999,"end_time":3052.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3049.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s true.","index":1000,"end_time":3053.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3052.77,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":1001,"end_time":3058.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3057.65,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And is the.","index":1002,"end_time":3058.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3058.01,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"In the lower left.","index":1003,"end_time":3060.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3059.09,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"That subscriber count is for newsletter, right?","index":1004,"end_time":3066.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3061.89,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yes.","index":1005,"end_time":3067.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3067.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":1006,"end_time":3068.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3068.13,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So.","index":1007,"end_time":3069.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3069.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I have been subscribing people a lot.","index":1008,"end_time":3074.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3071.45,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So.","index":1009,"end_time":3078.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3077.93,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I mean, I would expect that even higher, but that''s like kind of noetic.","index":1010,"end_time":3084.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3080.09,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Generated.","index":1011,"end_time":3084.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3084.29,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"But that''s okay because it gets us on their radar and we care more.","index":1012,"end_time":3089.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3084.69,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I''m now looking at the lower.","index":1013,"end_time":3091.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3089.85,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Right.","index":1014,"end_time":3091.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3091.21,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"