  'Meeting Notes: MiD//Noetic: Weekly Set Meeting  5/8 - Onwards',
  '## **Podcast Compilation and Script Refinement**

The team is finalizing the podcast compilation video with a focus on a strong thematic hook centered on navigating marketing uncertainty in 2025.

- **The compilation intro script will emphasize navigating the complex marketing landscape in 2025**, with Nancy slated to record the opening around December 22nd, aligned with upcoming marketing meetings (12:07)
    - Nancy and Rachel will record the intro together for efficiency during the next episode session on December 22nd.
    - Nancy suggested leading with Mike Linton’s insights on understanding marketing''s role in organizations to better hook senior marketers.
    - Marissa Jarrett’s approval is being sought to retain certain clips that reference her early time at 7:11, ensuring no controversy.
    - Colin will update references from “Kristen” to “Chris” for Chris O’Boyle’s episode, which is planned for a December 11th release.

- **Script feedback focused on tightening segments and improving thematic clarity** (06:00)
    - The team agreed to strengthen the hook around uncertainty and decision-making rather than outdated AI experimentation messages.
    - Minor “nip and tuck” edits included cross-outs and tightening of individual snippets to improve flow.
    - Rachel and Julia confirmed no further major script changes beyond the provided feedback.

## **AI Campaign Creative and Landing Page Updates**

The AI campaign visuals and landing page require improvements to better reflect the campaign’s complexity and brand authenticity.

- **Visuals for email sequences and ads were revised to show a messier, more complex “before” state and a clearer “workflow” after state**, matching AI’s inherently chaotic nature (17:26)
    - The team preferred a scribble or poorly drawn map representing complexity over simplistic three-box diagrams.
    - Color adjustments to “noetic orange” for before and green for learn more CTAs were requested for readability.
    - The “Get a handle on the lions” metaphor was replaced due to poor translation of meaning.
    - Background colors on graphics were adjusted to lighter gray for better contrast with colorful elements.

- **Landing page design feedback stressed making visuals more human and less AI-generated, with clearer calls to action** (22:18)
    - The current images were described as “dark and plastic,” prompting a move toward more realistic, relatable photos.
    - Button text should be lowercase and consistent with other website elements for brand compliance.
    - The call to action “See how it works” may mislead users; alternatives like “Learn more” or “Connect with us” are preferred to avoid bait-and-switch feelings.
    - The four-phase approach text will use sentence case rather than all caps to improve readability and tone.
    - The “trusted thought leader” language will be added above the AI content section to avoid implying direct AI work for listed brands, reducing legal risk.

## **Paid Media Performance and Campaign Prioritization**

Paid ad campaigns delivered modest engagement with a need to consolidate efforts for better focus and cost efficiency.

- **November LinkedIn ads achieved a click-through rate of 0.47%, slightly above the industry benchmark of 0.44%, with three leads at a cost of $541 per lead** (33:43)
    - The team identified five paid campaign components: full playbooks for first-year CMOs and healthcare, infographic versions of those playbooks, and the marketing leadership playbook.
    - Traction was strongest on healthcare infographics and document downloads targeting healthcare job titles.
    - Brand awareness campaigns targeting job titles showed high cost and diminishing returns due to saturated, highly targeted LinkedIn audiences.
    - Colin recommended pausing the new CMO outreach and the marketing leadership campaign to prioritize the AI campaign and the infographic content, reducing overlap and spend.

- **The AI campaign includes LinkedIn ads, email sequences, and outreach, requiring a clear focus to avoid diluted messaging across campaigns** (40:14)
    - The team agreed to maintain the AI campaign alongside healthcare and first-time CMO infographics, totaling three main campaign focuses.
    - Clarification was made regarding campaign terminology differences between LinkedIn ad sets and internal marketing language to ensure alignment on scope and spend.

## **Sales Pipeline Metrics and Dashboard Improvements**

Efforts to refine sales pipeline metrics and dashboard data have improved visibility into lead generation and opportunity progression.

- **Year-to-date leads over the last 12 months stand at approximately 139, with goals targeting 16 new opportunities or $200,000 in new hunting opportunities** (43:46)
    - Colin adjusted the Pipedrive dashboard to use a rolling 12-month date range, resolving previous API limitations.
    - The dashboard currently combines leads from both New North and internal sources, but can be separated if needed for clearer attribution.
    - The focus remains on moving leads from stage zero to stage one and beyond to track conversion effectively.
    - Rachel confirmed that dashboard metrics now include click-through rates by campaign, supporting ongoing performance monitoring.

- **Client engagement updates highlighted ongoing talks with Marriott and Waymo but no imminent deals** (46:49)
    - Meetings with Marriott’s Tanya are planned for January, with openness to internal introductions.
    - Waymo contacts have been challenging to communicate with; the team is pursuing follow-ups but acknowledges the client’s fast-moving environment.
    - December is a difficult month for client engagement due to holiday schedules.

## **Website and Podcast Analytics**

Website visitor patterns and podcast engagement show mixed yet promising trends, signaling opportunities for further content promotion.

- **Website visitors have slightly declined in the past 30 days, but average session duration increased by a similar margin, indicating deeper engagement from fewer visitors** (48:04)
    - Podcast views on YouTube rose by **32%**, largely attributed to the release of the Mike Linton episode.
    - Key pages like case studies and brand strategy saw notable traffic increases, with brand strategy up by **63%**.
    - Playbook page views decreased but remain steady, reflecting the impact of newly published content.
    - The team opted to direct paid ad traffic to LinkedIn lead forms to reduce barriers to conversion rather than sending users to the website.

- **Newsletter subscriber count is growing steadily due to active subscriptions, but listener numbers remain the primary engagement metric** (51:08)
    - Nancy has been actively subscribing contacts to the newsletter to increase visibility.
    - The team recognizes that podcast listening habits often involve non-subscribers, emphasizing quality content over subscription volume.
    - Rachel’s timely promotion of new podcast episodes supports audience growth despite personal challenges faced by guests.

## **Next Steps and Timeline Commitments**

The team established clear timing and responsibilities to advance project completion and maintain campaign momentum.

- **The podcast compilation video is targeted for mid to late December release following script tweaks and recording sessions scheduled for December 11th and 22nd** (54:33)
    - Colin will send the updated Chris O’Boyle episode script with naming corrections within minutes to allow Nancy sufficient time for review.
    - Rachel flagged her absence for the next meeting on December 10th; the team acknowledged and adjusted accordingly.

- **AI campaign creative updates and landing page changes will proceed promptly to enhance visuals, accessibility, and user experience** (21:41)
    - Design and copy edits including color changes, button text compliance, and clearer CTAs will be implemented.
    - The trusted thought leader language positioning will be adjusted to mitigate legal risks tied to brand associations.

- **Paid campaign consolidation will focus on AI and high-performing infographic assets to maximize ROI and reduce ad spend waste** (39:54)
    - Full playbooks and less effective campaigns will be paused to prioritize resources on proven content formats.
    - Ongoing tracking via dashboards and analytics tools will support data-driven decisions moving forward.',
